<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<bible xml:lang="bko" backtTranslaltionDefaultLanguage="en" oxes="2.0">
  <book id="JHN" stage="Rev" version="A">
    <Annotation class="History">
      <Message author="JSW" created="2009-10-02 03:47:28Z" when="2009-10-02 03:47:28Z" stage="Draft">drafted by C. Grimes, with primary reference to HCE, NLT, NRSV, Carson;, Morris, Uma BT; C&amp;B Grimes, advisors; worked with team (June, Mus, Adriana) in Darwin July-Aug 2006, plus read-through pass with Barbara's comments; UNS check in Kupang 21-25 Aug 2006; BT by Chuck; Consultant check by Marge Crofts in Kupang 6-11 Sept 2006; read thru for NT by Chuck, Adriana;</Message>
      <Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2014-02-24 10:48:42Z" when="2014-02-24 10:48:42Z" stage="Consult">Consultant Check: 21-25 August 2006 in Kupang; Consultant: Marge Crofts, approved. Report: KM-John-2Cor-ConsRep.doc</Message>
      <Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2015-01-10 04:11:54Z" when="2015-01-10 04:11:54Z" stage="Rev">Smoothing read through for Kupang mini-Bible with Chuck, Lena, Rina, Oma at UBB. BT cleaned up a bit.</Message>
    </Annotation>
    <p class="Header" usfm="h">Yohanis</p>
    <p class="Title Secondary" usfm="mt2">Tuhan Yesus pung Carita Bae<bt>The Lord Yesus' Good Story</bt></p>
    <p class="Title Secondary" usfm="mt2">iko<bt>according to</bt></p>
    <p class="Title Main" usfm="mt">Yohanis<bt>Yohanis</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yesus tu, sapa?<bt>Who is (this) Yesus?</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="1" />
      <v n="1" />Mula-mula, Tuhan Allah pung Kata-kata su ada.<bt>In the beginning, God's Words/Message already was/existed.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Tuhan pung Kata-kata tu, sama deng satu Orang.<bt>God2's Words/Message were equated with/identical to equal/the same as (but not ‘like’) a Person. [DISCOURSE: this makes the higher level cohesion of the Prologue hang together, and signals the personification in the Gk.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Itu Orang ada sama-sama deng Tuhan Allah.<bt>That Person was together with God.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Deng Dia ju, andia Tuhan Allah.<bt>And He is also God. [EXEG: Message, Source] [NOTE to daughter translations: avoid sense of /sama ke/ meaning ‘is like’.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="can 'orang' be used for 'being'"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:28Z">can 'orang' be used for 'being' in KM</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: In the beginning was the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:28Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: In the beginning was the Word, and the Word was with God, and the Word was God. en arkhéei: v 3 bears out that v 1 echoes Genesis 1:1, which in KM currently is "Mula-mula";<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>lógos: speech, statement, message, gospel, account, event, treatise, reason, argument, Word (of God)--almost always in the broad sense, not the narrow sense of a "word" separated by space on a page. Carson points out that it has enough antecedents in Hebrew /dabar/ that there is no need to look to gnostic, Platonic, or Philonic usage to explain it. God speaks and things happen, and that relation is personified in Wisdom literature Prv 3:19 &amp; 8:30. God expresses himself in creation (Gen 1:3ff, Ps 33:6), revelation (Jer 1:4, Is 9:8, Ezk 33:7, Am 3:1,8), and salvation (Ps 107:20, Is 55:1); John innovates beyond the Old Testament by claiming that God expresses himself in a personality too, the one the disciples experienced. Lógos casts him as a personality but it is not his name; it's an epithet that describes what kind of person he is. Also 1 John 1:1, Rev 19:13<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>theòs éen: definite predicate nouns are often without the article, as "you are [the] King of Israel" in 1:49 is not "a king"; not "divine" or "a god" but specific as "God" (also Jn 8:39, 17:17, Rom 14:17, Gal 4:25, Rev 1:20). Barrett, 'John intends that the whole of his gospel shall be read in the light of this verse'. [Note, this makes the JW translation of this passage 'a god' invalid.]</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="2" />Waktu langit deng bumi balóm jadi,<bt>When the sky and earth had not yet happened/been created/come into being, [EXEG: TH, Deibler; STYLE: ‘sky and earth’ a doublet that represents the whole cosmos.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">itu Orang su ada memang sama-sama deng Tuhan Allah.<bt>that Person already existed beforehand together with God.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: He was in the beginning"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:28Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: He was in the beginning with God.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="3" />Tuhan bekin jadi samua-samua, pake Dia pung Kata-kata tu.<bt>God2 created/made everything come into being, using that Words/Message of His. [EXEG: (Carson): so here: God's Word, understood in the Prologue to be a personal agent, created everything. // Because John is talking about creation, it's better to not force the Person from vs.1, but go back to Word.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Tuhan bekin jadi samua-samua, pake Dia"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:28Z">Tuhan bekin jadi samua-samua, pake Dia pung Kata-kata tu.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Sonde ada satu barang ju yang jadi, kalo itu Orang sonde bekin.<bt>There is not one thing (more on the concrete side of ‘thing’ than the abstract side of ‘thing’) which came into being, if that Person did not make/do it.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: All things were made [came"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:28Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: All things were made [came into being] through him, and without him not one thing was made which was made [came into being].</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="4" />Dia tu, akar dari idop.<bt>He (that one) is the root/source of life.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Jadi orang yang dapa idop yang batúl,<bt>So (consequently), people who get real life,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">dong idop dari Dia.<bt>they live from Him.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Dia ju sama ke Taráng yang bacaya,<bt>He is also like Light which shines,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Itu sama ke dong idop di"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:28Z">Itu sama ke dong idop di taráng,</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ko orang yang idop di itu Taráng,<bt>so that people who live in that Light,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">bisa lia deng mangarti.<bt>can see and understand.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: In him was life, and"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:28Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: In him was life, and the life was the light of men; zooeè: life: true life, eternal life, quality (not just physical, natural life 20:31) controlled by both father and son 5:26. In the rest of the book zooeé is either resurrection life or spiritual life enjoyed now; but here it is self-existing, related not so much to salvation as to creation (CEG: although first phrase here can encompass all these aspects)<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>phóos = light: life, goodness, God's revelation. In the rest of the book, it is revelation which people may receive in active faith and be saved; here it is more like general revelation. But light as a metaphor for either understanding or goodness or salvation fails to resonate with the Pidgin-speaking community, so in every case we have had to handle it as a simile and explain it.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="5" />Itu Taráng tu, basinar tambús maso di galáp;<bt>That Light, shines piercing into the darkness;</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">deng galáp sonde bisa tahan ame itu Taráng.<bt>and (the) darkness is not able to restrain/hold back/impede that Light.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">Te itu Taráng bacaya tarús.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) that Light keeps shining.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And the light shines in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:28Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And the light shines in the dark, and the dark has not [put it out / overcome it / overpower it]. phóos: "a masterpiece of planned ambiguity" not just referring to creation when light shone out of darkness, but moral too, and prevailing. Leads into light/darkness in the rest of the book<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>darkness: death, evil, sin ou katélaben: two readings: darkness did not win over light, darkness never understands light. John may have meant both; he is consciously literary here<span class="Italic">(5)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Naa, ada satu orang laen, nama Yohanis. Tuhan Allah ju utus sang dia,<bt>Naa, [shift] there was another/different person, named Yohanis. God also sent/commissioned him, [DISCOURSE (referent): ‘another/different man’ is necessary to distinguish from the person talked about in v1-5.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: There was a man sent"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:28Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: There was a man sent from God, named John.</Message></Annotation><note reference="1:6" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 3:1, Markus 1:4, Lukas 3:1-2</note><v n="7" />ko jadi saksi yang kasi tau orang so'al itu Taráng. Ko biar samua orang bisa parcaya sang Tuhan, tagal Yohanis pung omong.<bt>to be/become a witness who tells people about that Light. So that everyone can believe in God2, because of what Yohanis had to say.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tóu phootós: Stick to the &quot;light&quot;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:28Z" status="Information">tóu phootós: Stick to the "light" theme as developed in the preceding verses; "God's light" may be overkill. di' autóu: cuz a him, cuz a wat he say<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>LITERALLY: He was sent to be a witness, to testify about the light, that all people might believe through him.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Yohanis ni, bukan itu Taráng. Ma Tuhan utus sang dia ko kasi tau orang so'al itu Taráng.<bt>Now this Yohanis was not that Light. But God2 sent/commissioned him to tell people about that Light.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: He was not that light,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:28Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: He was not that light, but [he was sent] to testify about the light.</Message></Annotation><v n="9" />Te itu Orang yang jadi Taráng batúl, mau datang di ini dunya. Itu Taráng bekin kantara hal-hal yang batúl kasi samua orang.<bt>Cuz (elaboration), that Person who was the real/true Light, was going to come to this world. That Light reveals/makes to become visible true things/matters to everyone.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: He was the true light"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:28Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: He was the true light [coming into the world], which lights every person. éen ... erchómenon: better taken as neuter, agreeing with phóos as subject; note the comma after ánthroopon in Nestle. Not *ho lógos éen tò phóos<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>phootízei: can mean "illuminate inwardly, give knowledge" as Eph 1:18. If it does, there are three possibilities (1) general revelation that shone on every man without exception, including before coming into the world (2) shining in the context of the incarnation, illuminating not 'every man' without exception but 'every man' without distinction (3) Augustine pointed out that in a town with only one teacher, not all the citizens are the teacher's students, but he is the teacher for everyone -- potentially; but that's not what the text says, because it says he gives light to every man. Better to follow the sense of "shed light, make visible, bring to light" not as internal illumination, but the objective revelation, the invasion of light. It shines on every man and divides the race into those who hate the light and those who respond to it. It shines upon every man whether he sees it or not. This fits with aleethinón.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Biar Dia su bekin jadi, samua yang ada di dunya, ma orang di ini dunya sonde kanál ame sang Dia waktu Dia datang tenga di sini.<bt>Even though He had made (caused to come into being) everything that is in the world come into being, nevertheless people in this world did not know/recognise Him when he came to live here.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kósmooi: more restricted than &quot;everything that"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">kósmooi: more restricted than "everything that was made", focussing on the human beings in it in their rebellion against the Word. The evil in the world isn't independent; it's part of the rebellion LITERALLY: He was in the world, and the world was made through him, and the world did not know him.<span class="Italic">(10)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="11" />Biar Dia datang tenga deng Dia pung orang sandiri dong, ma dong sonde mau tarima ame sang Dia.<bt>Even though He came to live with His own people, nevertheless they did not want to accept/receive Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tà ídia: his own property, more"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">tà ídia: his own property, more likely his own home. "his own place" probably best LITERALLY: He came into his own, and his own did not receive him.<span class="Italic">(11)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="12" />Biar bagitu, ma samua orang yang tarima deng parcaya sang Dia, Dia kasi hak sang dong ko jadi Tuhan Allah pung ana-ana.<bt>Even that being the case, nevertheless everyone who accepts/receives and believes in Him, He gives the right to them to be/become God's children. [DISCOURSE: Mar 2011: revised to better reflect Gk referents.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="eis tò ónoma autóu: has the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">eis tò ónoma autóu: has the idea of being in touch with his identity. Not just a fancy way of identifying "him"; it penetrates below the surface to who he really is exousian: right, authority, (power)<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>LITERALLY: But as many as received him, he gave to them the right/authority to become children of God, those who believed in his name.</Message></Annotation><v n="13" />Itu sama ke dong su lahir kambali. Ma dong pung lahir baru tu, bukan sama ke orang barana ana. Deng bukan dari satu laki-laki yang kapingin dapa turunan. Te dong jadi Tuhan pung ana-ana, tagal Tuhan yang kasi dong, itu idop baru.<bt>That's the same as if they had been born again. But that new birth of theirs, is not like a person giving birth to a child. And it is not from one man who wants to get descendants. Cuz (elaboration) they become God2's children, because God2 is the one who makes them live/gives them that new life. [EXEG: Carson, NLT, HCE; NOTE: /turunan/ forces direct biological descent and avoids adoption the /anak/ can carry.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="see Message: These are the God-begotten,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">see Message: These are the God-begotten, not blood-begotten, not flesh-begotten, not sex-begotten;</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="spiritual birth, not physical sarkòs: flesh,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">spiritual birth, not physical sarkòs: flesh, body, not in itself evil the way John uses the word (see v 14), but neutral<span class="Italic">(13) (13) </span>LITERALLY: They were born, not from blood, nor from the will of the flesh [body], nor from the will of a man [male], but from God.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="14" />Ais <span class="Italic">&lt;Tuhan pung Kata-kata&gt;</span> tu,<bt>So then <span class="Italic">&lt;God2's Words/Message&gt;</span> (that I have been referring to),</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ju lahir jadi manusia.<bt>also was born as a human.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Dia idop di kotong pung teng-tenga.<bt>He lived in our-inc midst.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Kotong dapa lia Dia pung hebat.<bt>We could/were able to see His incredibleness/greatness/amazingness. [EXEG: Gk: glory here]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Dia hebat bagitu, tagal Dia tu, Tuhan Allah pung Ana satu biji.<bt>He was incredible like that, because He was/is God's only Child.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Dia suka kasi tunju Dia pung hati bae sang kotong,<bt>He likes to/often shows His goodness/kindness/grace/generosity to us-inc,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">tagal Dia pung sifat memang bagitu.<bt>because His character/characteristic/nature is really like that.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Deng samua yang Dia kasi tau so'al Tuhan Allah, memang batúl.<bt>And everything which He tells about God is really true.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And the Word became flesh"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And the Word became flesh [a human being] and lived among us, and we saw his glory, glory as the one and only Son from the Father, full of grace and truth. kaì .. egéneto: This is the Prologue in a nutshell, and its climax. Everything leads up to this statement. It should not be in a dependent clause. UBS's comment that it is a title is not quite right; there is no status in the world for this to be the title of. It's a description of a unique function, not a title or a nickname<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>sàrx: there is an expression in Pidgin "blood an bone", kind of like "carne y hueso" in Spanish and "flesh and blood" in English, but it probably isn't needed here pleérees kháritos: characterized in everything he does by a kind attitude - this isn't gracious deeds, but a gracious personality. This is part of his being the one who reveals God: kháritos kaì aleetheías are characterictics here of Christ as Lógos.<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>aleetheías: UBS suggests "the truth about God", which makes more sense than truth in the sense of "the truth about biology" or "the truth about Herod" or even "truth in general"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Naa, Yohanis tu, kasi tau so'al ini Orang. Dia batarea bilang, &lt;&lt;Dengar, é! Dia ni, yang beta su carita bilang, &lt;Nanti satu Orang mau datang. Dia tu, lebe hebat dari beta. Te beta balóm lahir, Dia su ada lebe dolo na!&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>Naa [shift], that Yohanis, told about this Person. He shouted saying, “Listen, é! He (this one) is the one I have been telling/narrating saying, ‘Later a Person is going to come. He is greater/more incredible/ more amazing than I. Cuz (elaboration) before I was born, He already existed before that [+confidence/amazement]!’”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Iooánnees: Initial position, taking over the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">Iooánnees: Initial position, taking over the topic; if it were a simple step in a narrative it would be after the verb, but there's no narrative framework until v 19 kékragen: perfect, emphasizing that what he said is still true. The lexical choice suggests two things: addressing a lot of people in a short time, and an urgent feeling about the content. Maybe the quotation should start with &lt;&lt;Eh listen up, you guys!&gt;&gt; to capture that<span class="Italic">(15) (15) </span>próotoòs mou éen: ties back to en arkhéei in v 1 LITERALLY: John testified about him, and yelled out saying, "This is the one of whom I spoke, "After me comes one who was before me, because he was first.<span class="Italic">(15)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Yohanis omong bagitu, tagal itu Orang talalu suka kasi tunju Dia pung hati bae. Deng Dia maen bekin ulang bagitu tarús kasi kotong samua.<bt>Yohanis spoke like that, because that Person really likes to show His goodness/kindness/grace/generosity. And He keeps doing that over and over to all of us-inc. [EXEG: NLT, CEV]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Because from his fullness we"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Because from his fullness we have all received, and grace after grace. hóti: This is generally taken as an explanation by the author of why John the Baptist said what he said, not a continuation of John B's words. It picks up the philosophizing tone of the Prologue, not the urgent preaching of John B<span class="Italic">(16) (16) </span>pleeroómatos: In Paul this is a philosophical technical term for something or someone who fully possesses the divine nature, as over against ordinary people and spiritual beings who are not divine. So it's more than just quantity; it's being the real thing; Col 1:19, 2:9, Eph 1:23, 4:13. In John, however, it's less technical, more like "in everything he does, he exemplifies God's gracious attitude", continuing the theme of v 14 khaàrin antì khàritos: grace upon grace, new graciousness replacing the still considerable grace of the Old Covenant, grace in our lives corresponding to the grace in Christ's life -- all three readings are possible, and though the first is most popular with translators, it's not necessarily the best handling of antí (see Carson)<span class="Italic">(16)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="17" />Dolu-dolu, ba'i Musa yang kasi turun Tuhan pung Atoran sang kotong pung nene-moyang. Ma sakarang itu Orang, andia Yesus Kristus, yang kasi tunju Tuhan pung hati bae sang kotong. Deng samua yang Dia kasi tau so'al Tuhan Allah, memang batúl.<bt>Long ago, grandfather Musa is the one who handed down God2's Regulations/Law to our-inc ancestors. But now that Person (that I have been referring to), who is Yesus Kristus, is the one who shows God2's goodness/kindness/grace/generosity to us-inc. And everything that He tells/explains about God, is really true.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="he khaáris kaì hee aleétheia: because"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">he khaáris kaì hee aleétheia: because it's picking up on a literary theme, the rendering here should match the best rendering of v 14 and 16 LITERALLY: Because the law was given through Moses, but grace and truth came through Jesus Christ.<span class="Italic">(17)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="18" />Sonde parná ada satu orang ju yang lia batúl-batúl sang Tuhan Allah. Ma Dia pung Ana satu biji yang Dia sayang tu, yang su kasi tunju sang kotong Tuhan Allah pung hati. Itu Ana tu, ada di Dia pung Bapa pung sablá. Te Dia ju, andia Tuhan Allah.<bt>There has never been one person who has really seen God. But His only Child whom He loves, is the one who shows us God's liver/character/heart. That Child is at His Father's side. Cuz (elaboration) He is also God. [NOTE: same as last clause in vs.1, except for connector.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: No one has seen God"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: No one has seen God at any time. God, the one and only Son, [the unique and beloved one (himself) God] who is by the Father's side, he has made him known. heoóraken poópote: Abraham, Hagar, Moses, Isaiah saw God in a restricted and partial sense, but they did report seeing him, not just a strange phenomenon. The Jewish idea is that to really see God is beyond what anybody living can handle<span class="Italic">(18) (18) </span>monogeneès theòs: textually strong; "Son" looks like a scribal attempt to simplify an unusual appositive construction with no article "a unique One, himself God" kólpon: used for Lazarus the beggar being right there with Abraham, and John lying where he could talk direct to Jesus in the table arrangement for the Last Supper -- easy access, close association with one person singled out to enjoy it<span class="Italic">(18) (18) </span>exeegeésato: is the aorist a summary of everything Jesus did, or is it the aorist for a general principle -- Jesus stands as the definitive explanation of what God is like, as E. Stanley Jones put it in _The Christ Of The Indian Road_, "People in India understand when you tell them that God is like Jesus."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yohanis tukang sarani kasi tunju sang Tuhan Yesus<bt>Yohanis the Habitual *Baptiser points to the Lord Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 3:1-12; Markus 1:1-8; Lukas 3:1-18)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Satu kali, orang Yahudi pung bos-bos di Yerusalem utus barapa kapala agama, deng barapa orang dari suku Lewi yang biasa layani di Tuhan Allah pung Ruma Sambayang Pusat. Dong pi di kali Yarden pung sablá<bt>One time, the Yahudi people's bosses/leaders in Yerusalem sent/commissioned several *priests (heads of religion), and several people from the Lewi tribe who normally serve/minister in the *Temple (God's Main House of Worship). They went to the other/far side of the Yarden river</bt><note reference="1:19" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Yohanis pung tampa sarani orang, ada ame dari ayat 28.<bt>The place where Yohanis was baptising people is taken from verse 28.</bt></note>ko tanya sang Yohanis tukang sarani bilang, &lt;&lt;Lu ni, Kristus yang Tuhan su janji mau kirim datang, ko?&gt;&gt;<bt>to ask Yohanis the Habitual *Baptiser saying, “Are you Kristus, who God2 promised to send?” [EXEG: on ‘the Jews’: see Carson, &amp; Terry Schram's dissertation “The use of ‘the Jews’ in the fourth gospel”] [DISCOURSE: For background-foreground, location here from verse 28]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="19, 28 Satu kali, Yohanis TS"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">19, 28 Satu kali, Yohanis TS dong (ada) sarani orang di Betania, di kali Yarden pung sablá. Ju orang Yahudi pung bos-bos di Yerusalem kirim/utus barapa kapala agama, deng barapa orang dari suku Lewi yang biasa layani di Ruma Sambayang Pusat. Dong pi (jao) ko tanya sang Yohanis, bilang, &lt;&lt;Lu ni, Kristus, ko?&gt;&gt; [plus add ftn]</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ais dia kasi tau sang dong bilang, dia tu, sapa.<bt>So he told them who he was.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Leuítas: odda guys from da Levi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">Leuítas: odda guys from da Levi ohana dat help dem? LITERALLY: And this is the testimony of John, when the Jews sent priests and Levites to him from Jerusalem to ask him, "Who are you?"<span class="Italic">(19)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="20" />Dia mangaku taráng-taráng bilang, &lt;&lt;Sonde. Beta ni, bukan Kristus.&gt;&gt;<bt>He confessed/acknowledged openly saying, “No. I am not Kristus.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ouk eerneésato: he did not refuse"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">ouk eerneésato: he did not refuse to answer. Nothing about prevarication LITERALLY: And he confessed and did not deny, but confessed, "I am not the Christ."<span class="Italic">(20)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Ju dong tanya lai bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo bagitu, lu ni, sapa? Ba'i Elia, ko?&gt;&gt;<bt>So they asked again/further saying, “If that's the case, who are you? Gf/Ff Elia, right?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Dia manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Sonde ju.&gt;&gt;<bt>He responded saying, “Not (him) either.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Tarús dong tanya lai bilang, &lt;&lt;Jang sampe lu ni, Tuhan pung jubir yang laen tu, ko?&gt;&gt;<bt>So they asked again saying, “Perhaps/Could it be that you are that [+known referent] other *spokesman/prophet of God2's, right?” [EXEG: Carson.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Dia manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Sonde ju.&gt;&gt;<bt>He responded saying, “Not (him) either.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ho propheétees: the specific prophet Moses"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">ho propheétees: the specific prophet Moses wrote about in Deuteronomy 18:15, 18, another eschatological figure in Jewish thought associated with the Messiah LITERALLY: And they asked him, "Who are you, then? Are you Elijah?" He says, "I am not". "Are you the Prophet?" And he said, "No."<span class="Italic">(21)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="1:21" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 18:15, 18, Maleaki 4:5</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Ais itu, ju dong tanya lai bilang, &lt;&lt;Naa, kalo bagitu, lu ni, sapa? Kasi tau dolo! Te botong musti kambali pi lapor sang bos-bos yang utus sang botong. Tolong doo!&gt;&gt;<bt>After that, they asked further saying, “Naa, if that's the case, then who are you? Tell us [+light imperative]! Cuz (elaboration) we-exc must go back and report to the bosses who sent/commissioned us. Help us out here!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then they said to him,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then they said to him, "Who are you? [Tell us] so that we may have an answer to give to those who sent us. What do you say about yourself?"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Ju dia omong iko apa yang ba'i Yesaya parná tulis bilang,<bt>Then he spoke according to what grandfather Yesaya had written saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Beta ni, andia itu orang yang batarea di tampa sunyi bilang,<bt>“I am that person who shouts in the empty place saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">&lt;Samua orang siap-siap bekin bae jalan,<bt>‘All people prepare to make good/fix the way/path,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">ko tarima Tuhan pung datang!<bt>to receive the Lord/God2's coming!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Bekin rata jalan ko sambut sang Dia.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>Make flat/smooth the path to greet Him.’” [NOTE: Same as Mark 1:3, structured as parallelism.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: He said, &quot;I am the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: He said, "I am the voice of one shouting in the desert, 'Prepare the way of the Lord', just as Isaiah the prophet said."</Message></Annotation><note reference="1:23" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 40:3</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Di teng-tenga itu orang yang datang dari Yerusalem dong, ada ju barapa orang dari partei agama Farisi.<bt>Among those people who came from Yerusalem, there were also several people from the Farisi religious party.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ek: There were Pharisees in the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">ek: There were Pharisees in the Sanhedrin, but the Sadducees held the power. The priests were mainly Sadducees, entrenched in the official worship; the Pharisees were reformers, trying to understand the Torah and apply it. In an official delegation, because of the politics of it, there would have had to be one or two Pharisee sympathizers; these are the ones who picked up on the baptism question in the next verse (Carson) LITERALLY: And the ones having been sent [to him] were from the Pharisees.<span class="Italic">(24)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="25" />Ais dong tanya sang Yohanis bilang, &lt;&lt;Bagini. Kalo lu bukan Kristus, bukan ba'i Elia, deng bukan itu Tuhan pung jubir tu, akurang ko lu ada sarani orang? Lu dapa hak dari mana?&gt;&gt;<bt>And they asked Yohanis saying, “It's like this. If you are not Kristus, not grandfather Elia, and not that (known) *spokesperson of God2's, why are you *baptising people? From where do get the right/authority?” [EXEG: Carson]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="2 UNS's tend to use /kanapa/"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">2 UNS's tend to use /kanapa/ more than akurang ko</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tí óun: the implication is not"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">tí óun: the implication is not that Messiah or Elijah or the Prophet were expected to baptize; but that John is acting as if he had a special authority in baptizing other people, and the Pharisees, true to form, want to know where he got that authority from. (According to Carson, proselytes were baptized in some groups, and the Qumran people practiced baptism; but in both cases the candidates baptized themselves. And it's Jewish people, not proselytes, that he is baptizing, which doesn't sit well either.) LITERALLY: And they asked him, "Why do you baptize then, if you are not the Christ, nor Elijah, nor the Prophet?"<span class="Italic">(25)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="26" />Ju Yohanis manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta ni, sarani orang cuma pake aer sa. Ma su ada satu Orang di bosong pung teng-tenga yang bosong sonde kanál.<bt>So Yohanis responded saying, “I baptise people just using water. But there already is a Person in your-pl midst whom you do not know/recognise.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: John answered them, &quot;I baptize"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: John answered them, "I baptize with water. One stands among you that you do not know.</Message></Annotation><v n="27" />Biar beta yang mulai ajar orang lebe dolo, ma Dia lebe hebat dari beta. Biar cuma jadi Dia pung tukang suru-suru sa ju, beta sonde pantas.&gt;&gt;<bt>Even though I began to teach first/before (him), nevertheless He is greater/more amazing/more incredible than I. Even just to be/become His lowly.servant, I am not worthy.” [NOTE to daughter translations: Ftn same as in Mark 1:7, but omitting “stoop to”.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ho opísoo mou erkhómenos: &quot;come afta&quot;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">ho opísoo mou erkhómenos: "come afta" in Pidgin sounds like hostile intent, as when planning a revenge killing. The idea is time sequence LITERALLY: He comes after me, but I am not worthy to loosen his sandal strap.<span class="Italic">(27)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="1:27" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Tulisan bahasa Yunani asli bilang, &lt;&lt;buka dia pung tali sapatu sa ju, beta sonde pantas.&gt;&gt; Dia pung arti bilang, Yohanis cuma orang kici sa. Biar jadi Tuhan Yesus pung tukang suru-suru sa ju, dia sonde pantas.<bt>The original Greek language writing says, &lt;&lt;to undo his shoe strap, it's not fitting/appropriate for me/I am not worthy.&gt;&gt; It's meaning is that Yohanis was just a little person (social status). Even if he just became Lord Yesus' lowly.servant, he wasn't fitting/appropriate/worthy.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Ini hal dong samua jadi di Betania, di kali Yarden pung sablá. Yohanis deng dia pung ana bua dong ada sarani orang di situ.<bt>All these things happened in Betania, on the other side of the Yarden river. Yohanis and his underlings were baptising people there. [EXEG: leave open the option of village or region.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: These things happened in Bethany,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: These things happened in Bethany, on the other side of the Jordan, where John was baptizing. Check how people distinguish the various Waimeas and Konas. Also check if this kind of geographic reference works to wrap up a section -- as if using a footnote about a place signalled the end of an episode. I kind of don't think it works in Pidgin; they may need to have it moved into v 19 in order to make sense out of the whole thing. Maybe part in one place, part here<span class="Italic">(28) (28) </span>Beethaníaai: no known town called Bethany on the east bank, but the region known early as Bashan was called Batanea, it was outside of Herod's bailiwick, and Josephus spells it three different ways so this way isn't out of the question. Carson points out that if it's a region, that allows John to touch base with the entire Land of Israel: Judea, Samaria, Galilee, and now the Transjordanian region</Message></Annotation><note reference="1:28" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">&lt;Betania&gt; ni, laen dari kampong Betania yang deka-deka di kota Yerusalem. Ma dia pung lokasi sonde jalás. Orang yang pintar dong pikir bilang, mangkali ini sama ke da'era Basan, yang ada di dano Galilea pung sablá matahari nae, te Yosefus ju tulis itu tampa pung nama &lt;Batanea&gt;. Yosefus tu, satu orang Yahudi yang tulis Isra'el pung sajara kasi pamarenta Roma.<bt>This &lt;Betania&gt; is different from the village of Betania which is quite close to the city of Yerusalem. But its location isn't clear. Knowledgable people think that it is probably the same as the region of Basan, which is on the east side of lake Galilea, cuz (elaboration, reason) Yosefus also wrote that that place had the name &lt;Batanea&gt;. This Yosefus (that we are referring to) was a Yahudi person who wrote the history of Isra'el for the Roma government.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus tu, sama ke Tuhan Allah pung Domba Ana<bt>The Lord Yesus is like God's *Lamb (sheep offspring)</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="29" />Dia pung beso, Yohanis lia Yesus ada jalan datang di dia. Ju dia omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Lia itu Orang di sana doo! Dia tu, Tuhan Allah pung Domba Ana yang jadi korban ko hapus buang orang di ini dunya pung sala-sala dong.<bt>The next day, Yohanis saw Yesus walking towards him. He said, “Have a look at that Person over there! He is God's *Lamb (sheep offspring) who becomes a *sacrifice to *wipe away the wrongs of the people of this world.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="@@SVC"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">@@SVC</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="epaúrion: probably the day after the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">epaúrion: probably the day after the interview with the delegation íde: highlighting more than suggesting where to look<span class="Italic">(29) (29) </span>amnòs: lamb; not a Messianic symbol, so it's a mind-bender LITERALLY: The next day John saw Jesus coming to him, and said, "Look! The lamb of God who takes away the sin of the world.<span class="Italic">(29)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="30" />Ini Orang ni, yang beta su kasi tau sang bosong kamaren bilang, &lt;Nanti ada satu Orang yang muncul datang. Dia tu, lebe hebat dari beta, tagal Dia su ada lebe dolo dari beta.&gt;<bt>This Person is the one I was telling you-pl about yesterday saying, ‘Later a Person will appear/come. He is greater/more impressive than I, because He already existed before me.’ [EXEG: NOTE to daughter translations: If Gk was /gar/, then it should be KM /te/. But Gk is /hoti/ which is a stronger, asserted reason, so is rendered /tagal/ here.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="émprosthén mou gégonen: all commentators take"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">émprosthén mou gégonen: all commentators take this as rank, not time, even though v 27 is phrased as time LITERALLY: This is the one about whom I said, 'After me comes a man who is greater than me, because he was before me.'<span class="Italic">(30)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="31" />Dolu beta sonde tau, kalo Dia tu, Kristus. Biar bagitu, ma beta su tau beta musti kasi kanál sang Dia di orang Isra'el dong. Tagal itu, beta datang ko sarani orang pake aer.<bt>Previously I did not know that He is/was Kristus. Even that being the case, nevertheless I already knew I must introduce/make Him known to the people of Isra'el. Because of that, I came/have come to baptise people using water. [EXEG: (Carson): “does not mean that John did not know Jesus at all, but only that he did not know him as the Coming One.”]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And I did not know"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And I did not know him, but [I knew that] he should be made known to Israel, therefore I come baptizing with water."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="32-33" />Tuhan Allah utus sang beta ko sarani orang pake aer. Dia ju kasi tau sang beta bilang, &lt;Nanti satu Orang mau datang di lu. Ais Beta pung Roh turun datang tenga di Dia. Itu Orang tu, yang nanti bawa Beta pung Roh Barisi, ko kasi kuasa sang Beta pung orang dong.&gt; Waktu itu Orang datang, beta sonde kanál langsung sang Dia. Ma waktu beta ada lia Tuhan pung Roh turun datang dari langit sama ke burung pompa, ko tenga di Dia, baru beta kanál sang Dia bilang, &lt;Ini Dia, itu Orang tu!&gt;<bt>God sent/commissions me to baptise people using water. He also told me saying, ‘Later a Person is going to come to you-sg. Then My Spirit will descend coming staying on/in Him. That Person is the one who will bring/bear/carry/deliver My *Holy/Clean/Pure Spirit, to give power/authority to My people.’ When that Person came, I didn't recognise Him immediately. But when I saw God2's Spirit descend coming from the sky like a dove, to stay on/in Him, only then did I recognise Him saying, ‘This is Him, that Person (who has been being referred to)!’ [DISCOURSE: Quote margin in the Greek violates local discourse structure. In other books we've also had to get rid of similar quote margins. Quote margins imply a change of speaker here.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And John gave this testimony:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And John gave this testimony: "I saw the Spirit come down from heaven like a dove and stay on him. And I [still] did not know him, but the one who sent me to baptize with water had said to me, "The one on whom you see the Spirit descend and stay on him, he is the one who baptizes with the Holy Spirit."</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ais itu ju, Yohanis carita tamba"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">Ais itu ju, Yohanis carita tamba so'al dia pung pangalaman, bilang, &lt;&lt;</Message></Annotation><v n="34" />Beta lia itu hal dong deng beta pung mata biji sandiri. Ais beta kasi tau sang bosong bilang, &lt;Itu Orang yang ada datang tu, andia Tuhan Allah pung Ana!&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>I saw that matter with my very own eyes. [DISCOURSE: High level evidential statement.] So I am telling you-pl, ‘That Person who is coming there, that is God's Child!’”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And I have seen and"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And I have seen and have testified that he is the Son of God."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus pili Dia pung ana bua partama dong<bt>The Lord Yesus chooses His first *disciples</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="35" />Dia pung beso, Yohanis ada badiri deng dia pung ana bua, dua orang.<bt>The following day, Yohanis was standing with two of his *disciples.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Again, the next day after,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Again, the next day after, John stood, and two of his disciples,</Message></Annotation><v n="36" />Waktu Yohanis lia Yesus ada jalan lewat di situ, dia kasi tau bilang, &lt;&lt;Lia dolo! Te Dia tu, Tuhan Allah pung Domba Ana yang nanti jadi korban!&gt;&gt;<bt>When Yohanis saw Yesus walking by there, he told/explained saying, “Look [+light imperative]! Cuz (elaboration) He (there, definite, specific) is God's Lamb who will become a *sacrifice!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And looking at Jesus as"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And looking at Jesus as he walked, he said, "Look! The Lamb of God!"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="Cook\CNT\cn01660b.tif" rtfFormat="width:6.5cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:right" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="37" />Ais ju Yohanis pung ana bua dua orang yang dengar dia pung omong tu, kasi tenga sang dia, ko jalan iko sang Yesus.<bt>Then Yohanis' two disciples who heard what he was saying, left him to go following Yesus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And the two disciples heard"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And the two disciples heard him speak, and they followed Jesus.</Message></Annotation><v n="38" />Ju Yesus bale, ais lia dong ada iko sang Dia. Tarús Dia tanya sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Karmana? Ada parlú, ko?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus turned, and saw that they were following Him. So He asked them saying, “How about it? Do you need something?” (=idiomatic way of saying “What do you want?”)</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Dong tanya bale sang Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;<span class="Italic">Rabi</span> tenga di mana?&gt;&gt; (Di dong pung bahasa Aram, &lt;<span class="Italic">Rabi</span>&gt; pung arti bilang, &lt;Bapa Guru&gt;.)<bt>They asked Him in return saying, “Where does <span class="Italic">Rabi</span>  (=you) live/stay?” (In their Aram language, <span class="Italic">Rabi</span> means, ‘Father Teacher’.)</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then Jesus turned, and saw"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then Jesus turned, and saw them following, and said to them, "What do you want?" They said to him, "Rabbi, (which is to say, being interpreted, 'Master') where do you live?"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="39" />Ais Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Mari ko lia sandiri sa.&gt;&gt; Ju dong iko deng Dia, ais lia Dia pung tampa tenga. Waktu dong sampe, su kira-kira jam ampa sore. Ais dong tenga deng Dia sampe matahari tanggalám.<bt>Then Yesus responded saying, “Just come and see for yourselves.” So they accompanied Him, and saw the place where He stayed/lived. When they arrived, it was around 4 o'clock in the afternoon. So/then they stayed with Him until the sun went down. [EXEG: although Morris says “and probably means that they spent the night with him.” which makes good sense the way the verse is constructed and situationally, unfortunately there is not strong additional support, and is by inference. So we take the safer interpretation of just being together through the remaining daylight hours.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: He said to them, &quot;Come"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: He said to them, "Come and see." They came and saw where he lived, and stayed with him that day, because it was about the tenth hour.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Itu waktu, su kira-kira jam ampa"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">Itu waktu, su kira-kira jam ampa sore. Jadi, itu malam dong tenga deng Dia.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="40" />Naa, dari itu dua orang yang dengar Yohanis pung omong, ais iko sang Yesus tu, ada satu nama Anderias. Dia tu, Simon Petrus pung adi.<bt>Naa [shift], from those two people who heard what Yohanis said, and then followed Yesus, there was one named Anderias. He was Simon Petrus' younger brother.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: One of the two who"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: One of the two who heard John speak and followed him was Andrew, Simon Peter's brother.</Message></Annotation><v n="41" />Pulang deng pulang ju Anderias pi cari dia pung kaka Simon, ais bilang, &lt;&lt;We, bu! Botong su bakatumu deng <span class="Italic">Mesias</span>!&gt;&gt; (Di dong pung bahasa, &lt;<span class="Italic">Mesias</span>&gt; pung arti bilang, &lt;Kristus, andia Orang yang Tuhan su janji memang dari dolu ko mau kirim datang.&gt;)<bt>Upon returning home, Anderias (first thing) went to look for his older brother Simon, then said, “We, older brother! We-exc have met with the <span class="Italic">Mesias</span>!” (In their language, ‘<span class="Italic">Mesias</span>’ means, ‘Kristus, that is the Person whom God2 has promised beforehand from long ago to send coming.’)</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="UNS = pas dia pulang @@"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">UNS = pas dia pulang @@ pulang deng pulang ju / datang deng datang ju / sampe deng sampe ju/ masak deng masak ju / mandi deng mandi ju / dudu deng dudu ju / carita deng carita ju / makan deng makan ju / tulis deng tulis ju "immediately after (activity) / first thing after..."<span class="Italic">(41)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: He first found his own"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: He first found his own brother Simon, and said to him, "We have found the Messiah, which is, being interpreted, the Christ."</Message></Annotation><v n="42" />Ais dia antar dia pung kaka pi Yesus.<bt>Then he brought/escorted his older brother to Yesus.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ju Yesus lia sang Simon, ais Dia kasi tau bilang, &lt;&lt;Lu ni, Simon. Lu pung bapa tu, Yohanis. Mulai sakarang orang pange sang lu, &lt;<span class="Italic">Kefas</span>&gt;&gt;&gt; (Dia pung arti sama deng &lt;Petrus&gt;, andia &lt;batu&gt;.)<bt>And Yesus looked at him, and told saying, “You are Simon. Your father is Yohanis. Beginning now people will call you, ‘<span class="Italic">Kefas</span>’” (That means the same as ‘Petrus’, which is ‘rock’.)</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And he brought him to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And he brought him to Jesus. And when Jesus saw him, he said, "You are Simon, son of John. You will be called Cephas, which is translated, 'Rock'."</Message></Annotation><note reference="1:42" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Nama <span class="Italic">Kefas</span> tu, dari bahasa Aram <span class="Italic">kefa</span>. Dia pung arti &lt;batu&gt;. Nama <span class="Italic">Petrus</span> tu, dari bahasa Yunani <span class="Italic">petra</span>. Dia pung arti ju &lt;batu&gt;.<bt>The name <span class="Italic">Kefas</span> is from the Aram language <span class="Italic">kefa</span>. It means ‘rock’. The name <span class="Italic">Petrus</span> is from the Yunani language <span class="Italic">petra</span>. It also means ‘rock’.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus pange sang Filipus deng Natanel<bt>The Lord Yesus calls/summons Filipus and Natanel</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="43-44" />Di situ ju ada satu orang laen, nama Filipus. Dia pung kampong asal, andia Betsaida. Petrus deng Anderias asal dari situ ju.<bt>There, there was also another person, name Filipus. His village of origin was Betsaida. Petrus and Anderias also originated from there.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Naa, dia pung beso, Yesus putus mau pi propinsi Galilea. Ju Dia pi katumu sang Filipus, ais Dia ajak bilang, &lt;&lt;Mari iko sang Beta ko jadi Beta pung orang!&gt;&gt;<bt>Naa, the next day, Yesus decided to go to the province of Galilea. And He went to meet Filipus, and invited him saying, “Come on, follow Me and be/become My person!” [EXEG: NLT, CONNOT, Carson] [DISCOURSE: reordered for RL foreground-background.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: The next day Jesus decided"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: The next day Jesus decided to go to Galilee, and he found Philip, and said to him, "Follow me." LITERALLY: Now Philip was from Bethsaida, the city of Andrew and Peter.<span class="Italic">(43)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Dia pung beso, Yesus putus mau"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">Dia pung beso, Yesus putus mau pi propinsi Galilea. Ju Dia pi katumu sang Filipus/Filipus, ais Dia ajak, bilang, &lt;&lt;Mari, iko sang Beta ko jadi Beta pung orang!&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="45" />Ais Filipus pi cari sang Natanel, ju kasi tau bilang, &lt;&lt;Bu, é! Botong su katumu itu Orang yang ba'i Musa su tulis dalam Tuhan pung Atoran. Tuhan pung jubir dolu-dolu dong ju tulis so'al ini Orang. Dia pung nama Yesus, dari kampong Nasaret. Dia pung bapa, nama Yusuf.&gt;&gt;<bt>So/then Filipus went to look for Natanel, and told him saying, “Older brother, é! We have met that Person who grandfather Musa has written about in God2's Regulations/Law. God2's spokespeople from long ago also wrote about this Person. His name is Yesus, from the village of Nasaret. His father is named Yusuf.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Philip found Nathanael, and said"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Philip found Nathanael, and said to him, "We have found him whom Moses in the book of the law, and the prophets wrote about, Jesus from Nazareth, the son of Joseph."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="46" />Ma Natanel manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Orang Nasaret!? Awe'! Sonde ada satu hal bae yang kaluar dari situ, ó!&gt;&gt;<bt>But Natanel responded saying, “A Nasaret person!? Awe'! [=annoyance, or contrary to what was expected] There is not anything good that comes out of there, ó!”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ju Filipus bilang, &lt;&lt;Weh! Jang bagitu. Mari ko lia sandiri sa!&gt;&gt;<bt>And Filipus said, “We! Don't be like that. Come on and see for yourself!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And Nathanael said to him,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And Nathanael said to him, "Can anything good come out of Nazareth?" Philip said to him, "Come and see."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="47" />Waktu Natanel ada jalan datang, Yesus su lia sang dia memang, ju bilang, &lt;&lt;Dia ni, orang jujur! Te di dia pung hati, sonde ada putar-balek. Dia ni, orang Isra'el tulen!&gt;&gt;<bt>When Natanel was walking toward [Him], Yesus saw him straight away/beforehand, and said, “This guy is an honest person! Cuz (elaboration) in his liver there is no deceit. This guy is a true/genuine/authentic Isra'el person!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="&lt;&lt;Itu orang sana tu, satu orang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">&lt;&lt;Itu orang sana tu, satu orang Isra'el tulen! Sonde ada (pung) putar-balek di dia pung hati. Te dia cuma tau omong yang batúl.&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tukang tipu = tuti (KM slang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">tukang tipu = tuti (KM slang abbreviation)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Jesus saw Nathanael coming to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Jesus saw Nathanael coming to him, and said about him, "Look! An Israelite indeed, in whom there is nothing false."</Message></Annotation><note reference="1:47" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Yesus ada maen kata di sini. Te waktu Tuhan balóm kasi nama &lt;Isra'el&gt; sang ba'i Yakob, nama Yakob pung arti &lt;tukang tipu&gt;. (Lia <span class="Italic">Carita Mula-mula</span> 27:1-40, 32:22-32.) Yesus pung maksud sini bilang, Natanel ni, orang Isra'el yang model laen dari ba'i Yakob. Te Natanel ni, orang hati lurus.<bt>Yesus is making a word play here. Cuz (elaboration) when God2 had not yet given the name ‘Isra'el’ to grandfather Yakob, the name Yakob meant ‘habitual deceiver’. (Look at <span class="Italic">Story of Beginnings</span> 27:1-40, 32:22-32.) Yesus' meaning here is that this Natanel is an Isra'el person of a different model/type/kind than grandfather Yakob. Cuz (elaboration) this Natanel is a straight/righteous/honest person.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="48" />Natanel tanya bilang, &lt;&lt;Karmana sampe Bos kanál sang beta?&gt;&gt;<bt>Natanel asked saying, “How is it that Bos knows/recognises me?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Bagini. Beta su dapa lia sang lu waktu lu ada di bawa itu pohon.<bt>Yesus responded saying, “It's like this. I already saw you when you were under that tree.</bt><note reference="1:48" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Bahasa Indonesia pake kata &lt;pohon ara&gt; dari istila Yunani συκῆ <span class="Italic">(sukē).</span> Ma Alkitab kasi tunju satu pohon di sana yang orang biasa makan dia pung bua. Di Indonesia sablá timur, orang sonde makan &lt;pohon ara&gt; pung bua. Jadi &lt;pohon ara&gt; di Alkitab bahasa Indonesia, sonde sama ke kotong pung pohon ara di sini.<bt>Bahasa Indonesia uses the word ‘pohon ara’ for the Yunani term συκῆ <span class="Italic">(sukē).</span> But the Bible designates a tree from there which people usually eat its fruit. In Indonesia eastern side, people do not eat ‘ara tree's’ fruit. So (consequently) ‘ara tree’ in the Indonesian Bible, is not the same as our-inc ara tree here.</bt></note>Itu waktu, Filipus balóm pi pange ame sang lu.&gt;&gt;<bt>At that time, Filipus had not yet called/summoned you.” [NOTE to daughter translations: footnote is same as in Mark 11:13.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Nathanael said to him, &quot;How"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Nathanael said to him, "How do you know me?" Jesus answered, "Before Philip called you, when you were under the fig tree, I saw you."</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Yesus manyao, bilang, &lt;&lt;Bagini. Waktu Filipus"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">Yesus manyao, bilang, &lt;&lt;Bagini. Waktu Filipus balóm pi pange ame sang lu, ais lu ada di bawa itu pohon, Beta su dapa lia sang lu.&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="49" />Ais Natanel mangaku bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa Guru ni, pasti Tuhan Allah pung Ana! Deng Bapa ju, tantu kotong orang Isra'el pung Raja!&gt;&gt;<bt>So/then Natanel acknowledged/confessed saying, “Father Teacher, surely (you) are God's Child! And You are also surely the King of the people of Isra'el!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Nathanael said to him, &quot;Teacher,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Nathanael said to him, "Teacher, you are the Son of God, you are the King of Israel."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="50" />Yesus tanya sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Kira-kira lu ni, parcaya sang Beta tagal tadi Beta bilang, &lt;Beta su dapa lia sang lu waktu lu ada di bawa itu pohon,&gt; ko? Inga, te nanti lu bisa dapa lia hal-hal yang lebe hebat lai!<bt>Yesus asked him saying, “Perhaps you believe in Me, because I just said, ‘I already saw you when you were under that tree,’ right? Remember, later you will be able to see matters that are even greater/more amazing/more incredible!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Jesus said to him, &quot;Because"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Jesus said to him, "Because I said to you, 'I saw you under the fig tree' you believe? You will see greater things than these."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="51" />Batúl! Beta kasi tau memang. Nanti bosong lia langit tabuka. Ju Tuhan pung ana bua di sorga dong ada turun-nae di Beta pung sablá. Deng Beta ni, Manusia Tulen.&gt;&gt;<bt>That's right! I'm telling you this directly/beforehand. Later you-pl will see the sky opened. And God2's *angels (underlings in/from heaven) descending-ascending at My side. And I here, am the *Son of Man (Authentic/Ideal Human).” [EXEG: Carson] [DISCOURSE: Quote margin in the Greek violates local discourse structure. In other books we've also had to get rid of similar quote margins. Quote margins imply a change of speaker here.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And he told him, &quot;That's"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And he told him, "That's right! And I say this too: After this you will see heaven open, and the angels of God going up and coming down by the Son of Man."</Message></Annotation><note reference="1:51" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Di <span class="Italic">Carita Mula-mula</span> 28:10-17, Yakob ada mimpi di Betel. Dalam dia pung mimpi, dia lia Tuhan pung ana bua dong turun-nae di satu tangga yang Yakob subu bilang, &lt;&lt;pintu pi sorga&gt;&gt;.<bt>In <span class="Italic">Story of Beginnings</span> 28:10-17, Yakob has a dream at Betel. In his dream, he sees god2's *angels descending-ascending on a ladder that Yakob refers to as “the door/gate to heaven”.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Pesta kawin di kampong Kana<bt>Wedding feast/festival in the village of Kana</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="2" />
      <v n="1" />Dia pung lusa, ada pesta kawin di kampong Kana, di propinsi Galilea. Deng Yesus pung mama ada iko.<bt>The day after next [today = 1, tomorrow = 2, day after = 3], there was a wedding feast/festival/celebration in the village of Kana in the province of Galilea. And Yesus' mama went to participate. [EXEG: ‘third day’ see discussion in Carson. NLT ‘next day’ and CEV ‘three days later’ are both incorrect.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="@! CEV &amp; NLT both wrong"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">@! CEV &amp; NLT both wrong here;</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And the third day [two"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And the third day [two days later] there was a wedding in Cana of Galilee. And Jesus mother was there.</Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Yesus deng Dia pung ana bua dong ju dapa undang. Ais dong ju pi.<bt>Yesus and his *disciples (underlings/followers) also got invited. So they also went.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And both Jesus and his"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And both Jesus and his disciples were invited to the wedding.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Ma lama-lama, te anggor di tampa pesta mulai abis. Ais Yesus pung mama kasi tau sang Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Tolong doo! Te dong pung anggor su abis ni.&gt;&gt;<bt>But eventually the wine (assimilated loan) at the wedding place began to run out. So/then Yesus' mama told Him saying, “Help out! Cuz (reason) their wine is already running out here/now.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And when they lacked wine,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And when they lacked wine, Jesus' mother said to him, "They have no wine."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Ma Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Mama. Akurang ko mama mau Beta yang ator? Te Beta pung waktu balóm pas ni.&gt;&gt;<bt>But Yesus responded saying, “Mama. Why do you want me to handle it/arrange/ manage/fix/put in order? Cuz (elaboration) My time is not yet just.right.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tis: not my kuleana / job"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">tis: not my kuleana / job / worry LITERALLY: Jesus said to her, "Mother [Woman], why do you want me to get involved? My time has not yet come."<span class="Italic">(4)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Ma Dia pung mama kasi tau sang orang karjá di situ dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Dengar, é! Dia suru bosong bekin apa, na, bekin iko sa.&gt;&gt;<bt>But His mama told the workers there saying, “Listen, é! Whatever He orders you-pl to do, na, just go along with it/do accordingly.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: His mother said to the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: His mother said to the servants, "Whatever he says to you, do it."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="Cook\CNT\cn01667b.tif" rtfFormat="width:6.5cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:right" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Di situ ada anam kumbang, yang orang bekin ame dari batu. Satu kumbang tu, tampung aer kira-kira 75-115 liter. Orang Yahudi biasa pake aer dari kumbang macam bagitu ko bekin barisi diri iko dong pung atoran agama.<bt>There, there were six clay/stone jars/jugs/basins, which people made from stone. One of those jugs could liquid.hold about 75-115 liters. Yahudi people normally used water from jugs of that sort to clean/purify themselves according to their religious regulations. [EXEG: (quantity) NLT note.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="for prayer/worship? tampung = hold, contain"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">for prayer/worship? tampung = hold, contain</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Like huge water coolers, but open"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">Like huge water coolers, but open only at the top. Made out of chipped stone. LITERALLY: And there were six waterjugs made of stone sitting there, for the purification of the Jews, each holding from 20 to 30 gallons.<span class="Italic">(6)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="7" />Ais Yesus kasi tau sang itu orang karjá dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Pi ame aer ko isi ini kumbang dong.&gt;&gt; Ju dong isi sampe ponu rata.<bt>So/then Yesus told those workers saying, “Go fetch water to fill these jugs.” Then they filled them until full flat (=to the brim).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ponu rata = to the brim"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">ponu rata = to the brim</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Jesus said to them, &quot;Fill"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Jesus said to them, "Fill the waterjugs with water." And they filled them up to the brim.</Message></Annotation><v n="8" />Ais Dia kasi tau sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Naa. Timba ame sadiki, ko bawa kasi sang tuan pesta.&gt;&gt; Ju dong bekin iko.<bt>So/Then He told them saying, “Naa. Dip/scoop out a little, to take to the master of the feast.” And/then they did accordingly.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And he said to them,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And he said to them, "Take some out now, and take it to the head of the feast." And they took it. architriklinos: lit. 'ruler of the table'; superintendant of the wedding, chief steward, head waiter, in charge of catering, master of the banquet<span class="Italic">(8)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="9" />Sampe di sana, itu tuan pesta rasa coba itu aer. Ma tau-tau itu aer su jadi anggor! Dia bingung, te dia sonde tau dong dapa itu anggor dari mana. (Ma itu orang karjá dong tau.)<bt>Arriving there, the master of the feast tasted testing that water. But contrary to expectation that water had become wine! He was confused, cuz (reason) he didn't know where they had gotten that wine from. (But those workers knew.)</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ais dia pange ame sang baroit laki-laki.<bt>So/then he called/summoned the bridegroom.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: When the head of the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: When the head of the feast had tasted the water that was made into wine, but didn't know where it came from, (but the servants who took out the water knew,) he called the bridegroom.</Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Ju dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Bagini. Kotong pung biasa, tuan ruma bagi kasi anggor yang paling bae lebe dolo. Kalo orang dong su minum banya, baru dia kasi kaluar anggor kalás dua. Ma lu bekin tabale. Lu kasi kaluar anggor kalás dua lebe dolo, ais baru anggor yang paling bae dari balakang!&gt;&gt;<bt>And he said, “It's like this. Our-inc custom is the master of the house distributes out the best wine first. If/when people have already drunk alot, only then does he bring out the second class wine. But you-sg have done it the other way around. You brought out the second class wine first, and only later on the best wine!” [NOTE to daughter translations: /kalás dua/ can be rendered as /anggor yang sonde bae/ or /anggor asam/.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: He said to him, &quot;Everybody"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: He said to him, "Everybody puts out the best wine at the beginning, and when people have drunk a lot, then that which is cheaper. But you have kept the best wine until now." methyskw: does not refer to consuming too much liquid, but to inebriation, but there is 'no ground here for conclusions regarding the degree of intoxication of the guests at this wedding'. On the other hand, wine in the ancient world was diluted with water to between one-third and one-tenth of its fermented strength, i.e. something less strong than American beer. Undiluted wine, about the strength of wine today, was viewed as 'strong drink', and earned much more disapprobation. (Carson)<span class="Italic">(10)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Itu hal jadi di kampong Kana, di propinsi Galilea. Itu partama kali Yesus bekin tanda heran yang orang dapa lia. Dia kasi tunju Dia pung hebat bagitu, ju Dia pung ana bua dong parcaya sang Dia.<bt>That event/thing/issue happened in the village of Kana, in the province of Galilea. It was the first time Yesus did an *amazing sign which people could see. He showed his incredibleness/greatness/amazingness like that, and His *disciples believed in/trusted Him. [EXEG: Gk: glory here] [DISCOURSE: Framed as high-level evidential, validating the event as historical.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: This beginning of signs [miracles]"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: This beginning of signs [miracles] Jesus did in Cana of Galilee, and showed his glory. And his disciples believed in him.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Ais itu, ju Yesus, Dia pung mama, Dia pung adi dong, deng Dia pung ana bua dong turun pi kota Kapernaum. Ma dong cuma tenga di situ barapa hari sa.<bt>After that, then Yesus, His mama, His younger siblings, and His *disciples descended to the city of Kapernaum. But they only stayed there for several/a few days.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: After that he went down"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: After that he went down to Capernaum, he, and his mother, and his brothers, and his disciples. And they stayed there a few days.</Message></Annotation><note reference="2:12" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 4:13</note></p>
    <Annotation class="History">
      <Message author="JSW" created="2009-10-02 03:47:29Z" when="2009-10-02 03:47:29Z" stage="Draft">DONE ch. 2: HCE, NRSV, NLT, Message, Source, Carson</Message>
    </Annotation>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus usir buang orang dari Tuhan Allah pung Ruma Sambayang Pusat<bt>The Lord Yesus evicts people from *God's *Temple (Main House of Worship/Prayer)</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 21:12-13; Markus 11:15-17; Lukas 19:45-46)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Waktu orang Yahudi dong pung hari bae Paska su deka-deka datang, Yesus nae pi kota Yerusalem.<bt>When the Yahudi people's feast day/holiday Paska was very near, Yesus went up to the city of Yerusalem.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: The Jewish Passover was almost"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: The Jewish Passover was almost there, and Jesus went up to Jerusalem.</Message></Annotation><note reference="2:13" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 12:1-27</note><v n="14" />Di Ruma Sambayang Pusat pung kintal, Yesus lia orang dong ada bajual sapi, domba, deng burung pompa yang orang béli ko pake jadi korban. Di situ, ju ada orang yang dudu di meja ko tukar doi yang orang pake kasi sang Tuhan Allah di Ruma Sambayang Pusat tu.<bt>In the *Temple yard, Yesus saw people were selling cows, sheep, and doves/pidgeons which people bought to use as *sacrifices (assimilated loan). There, there were also people who sat at tables to exchange money that people used to give to God at that Temple.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Doves or pigeons? LITERALLY: And found"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">Doves or pigeons? LITERALLY: And found in the Temple those who sold oxen and sheep and doves, and the moneychangers sitting.<span class="Italic">(14)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Ju Dia ame tali barapa urat ko bekin jadi cambuk. Ais Dia usir kasi kaluar sang dong samua dari itu kintal. Dia ju foo buang itu sapi deng domba dong. Dia kasi tabanting itu meja dong, deng po'a kasi tasiram buang itu doi dong.<bt>Then He took several strands of rope to make a whip. And He evicted all of them from that yard. He also herded/shooed away the cows and sheep. He overturned the tables, and poured spilling out the money.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="foo = one UNS not know"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">foo = one UNS not know</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: He made a whip out"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: He made a whip out of cords, and drove them all out of the temple yard, the sheep and the oxen, poured out the changers' money, and overturned the tables.</Message></Annotation><v n="16" />Ju Dia suru orang yang jual burung pompa dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bawa kaluar ini barang dari sini! Ini tampa ni, bukan pasar! Jang bekin Beta pung Bapa pung Ruma jadi tampa badagang!&gt;&gt;<bt>And He ordered the people who sold the doves saying, “Take these things away from here! This place here is not a market! Don't make My Father's House become a place of commerce!” [EXEG: things = birds and their cages. Ex.Helps, TRT]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: He said to those who"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: He said to those who sold doves, "Take these things away! Do not make my Father's house into a house of trade [/market]!</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Ju Dia pung ana bua dong inga Tuhan pung Tulisan Barisi yang tulis bilang,<bt>And His disciples remembered the *Scriptures (God2's Holy/Clean Writings which wrote/were written saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Beta sayang mati sang Tuhan pung Ruma.<bt>“I dearly/ deeply/ intensely love God2's House.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Andia ko beta pung hati samangat ko jaga dia pung nama bae.&gt;&gt;<bt>That is why my liver is enthusiastic/energetic/zestful to guard its good name/reputation.” [EXEG: zeal for the house; make sure it is not phrased as God's reputation.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And his disciples remembered that"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And his disciples remembered that it was written, "The zeal for your house burns in me like a fire."</Message></Annotation><note reference="2:17" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 69:9</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Ais orang Yahudi pung bos-bos suru sang Yesus bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo lu memang ada pung hak usir orang bagitu, na, kasi tunju satu tanda heran sang botong ko jadi bukti!&gt;&gt;<bt>Then the bosses/leaders of the Yahudi people ordered Yesus saying, “If you-sg really have the right to evict people like that, na, show us-exc an *amazing sign as proof/evidence!” [EXEG: on ‘the Jews’: see Carson, &amp; Terry Schram's dissertation “The use of ‘the Jews’ in the fourth gospel”]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then the Jews said to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then the Jews said to him, "Since you are doing these things, what sign [miracle] do you show us?"</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ais orang Yahudi pung bos-bos tanya"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">Ais orang Yahudi pung bos-bos tanya sang Dia/Yesus, bilang, &lt;&lt;Lu kasi tunju tanda heran karmana sang botong, ko kasi tunju lu pung hak usir orang bagitu?&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo bosong bekin ancor ini tampa barisi ni, nanti dia pung lusa, Beta kasi bangun kambali.&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus responded saying, “If you-pl destroy/ruin/fall apart this clean/holy/pure place here, later the day after next, I will raise it again/rebuild it.” [EXEG: discussion in CONNOT for 2:1 &amp; 2:19 for ‘on the third day’. See Carson on /naos/, not the normal word for ‘temple’ here. TH for command vs. conditional--command doesn't fit in these target lgs.] [NOTE to daughter translations: word for ‘destroy’ needs to collocate both with buildings and with bodies.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Jesus told them, &quot;Destroy this"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Jesus told them, "Destroy this temple, and in three days [two days later] I will raise it up."</Message></Annotation><note reference="2:19" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 26:61, 27:40, Markus 14:58, 15:29</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Ma dong protes bilang, &lt;&lt;Dapa di mana? Te orang dong kasi bangun ini Ruma Sambayang Pusat sampe ampa pulu anam taon. Akurang ko Lu kira kata, Lu cuma parlú tiga hari sa ko kasi bangun kambali?!&gt;&gt;<bt>But they protested saying, “(Idiom) Where do you get that (=unbelievable)? Cuz (elaboration) people took 46 years to build this Temple. Why do You think that You only need just three days to rebuild it?!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Dapa di mana? = it's unbelievable"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">Dapa di mana? = it's unbelievable</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then the Jews said, &quot;It"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then the Jews said, "It took forty six years to build this temple, and you are going to rebuild it in three days?"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Ma dong sonde mangarti, kalo Yesus ada omong so'al Dia pung badan, yang sama ke satu tampa barisi.<bt>But they didn't understand that3 Yesus was talking about His body, which is like a clean/holy/pure place.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But he spoke of the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But he spoke of the temple of his body.</Message></Annotation><v n="22" />Jadi di balakang hari, waktu Yesus su mati, ais idop kambali, Dia pung ana bua dong baru inga apa yang Dia su kasi tau memang sang dong. Ju dong parcaya apa yang Tuhan pung Tulisan Barisi ada tulis dari dolu-dolu, deng apa yang Yesus su kasi tau memang sang dong.<bt>So (consequently), later on, when Yesus had died, and then lived again, His disciples only then remembered what He had told beforehand to them. And they believed what the Scriptures wrote from long ago, and what Yesus had told them beforehand.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Therefore, when he had risen"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Therefore, when he had risen from the dead, his disciples remembered that he had said this to them, and they believed the Scripture, and the word that Jesus had spoken.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus tau samua orang pung dalam hati<bt>The Lord Yesus knows everyone's inner heart</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Yesus tenga tahan di kota Yerusalem ko iko hari bae Paska di situ. Ju banya orang dapa lia tanda-tanda heran yang Dia bekin, ais ju dong parcaya sang Dia.<bt>Yesus stayed temporarily in the city of Yerusalem to participate in the Paska holiday/festival there. And many people were able to see the various amazing signs that He did, and so they believed in Him. [EXEG: believed in his name = 1) believed in Him, 2) believed in his rank (as Messiah) [NLT]; rank is one common sense of Gk ‘name’.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Now when he was in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Now when he was in Jerusalem at the Passover, on the feast day, many believed in him when they saw the signs [miracles] which he did.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ju banya orang parcaya sang Dia,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">Ju banya orang parcaya sang Dia, tagal dong dapa lia tanda heran [pl?] yang Dia [bekin//kasi tunju sang dong].</Message></Annotation><v n="24-25" />Ma Yesus sonde parcaya deng dong, tagal Dia su tau samua orang pung dalam hati. Dia sonde parlú orang ko kasi tau sang Dia, tagal Dia sandiri su tau memang manusia pung dudu-badiri.<bt>But Yesus did not trust them [slightly different grammatical frame from ‘believe’, although same lexeme], because He already knew everyone's inner heart (liver). He did not need people to tell/explain to Him, because He himself already knew beforehand/directly what people are like/the human condition/situation (idiom) [EXEG: pantas: 1) all (of them), 2) all (of humanity) here is generic ‘humanity’ (Morris, TRT, NLT, The Source, NRSV, CEV, TB); little support for #1 here.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="parcaya sang = believe in ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">parcaya sang = believe in ; parcaya deng = trust them ; baca orang??</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But Jesus did not entrust"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But Jesus did not entrust himself to them, because he knew all people, LITERALLY: He did not need anyone to tell him what people are like, because he knew what was inside people.<span class="Italic">(24) (24) </span>anthropos: here is generic 'humanity' (NLT, The Source)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus ba'omong deng Nikodemus<bt>The Lord Yesus talks with Nikodemus</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="3" />
      <v n="1" />Ada satu orang dari partei agama Farisi, dia pung nama Nikodemus. Dia tu, orang Yahudi dong pung guru bésar satu.<bt>There was a person from the Farisi religious party, named Nikodemus. He was an important teacher of the Yahudi people. [EXEG: See Carson]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: There was a man of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: There was a man of the Pharisees, Nicodemus his name, a leader of the Jews.</Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Satu kali, dia datang malam-malam katumu sang Yesus. Ju dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa Guru! Botong tau bilang, Tuhan yang utus sang Bapa ko ajar sang botong. Te tanda-tanda heran yang Bapa bekin dong tu, kasi tunju bukti bilang, Tuhan yang kasi itu kuasa sang Bapa. Kalo sonde bagitu, na, pasti itu tanda heran sonde bisa jadi.&gt;&gt;<bt>One time, he came at night (reduplication implies quietly/secretly) to meet Yesus. And he said, “Father Teacher! We-exc know that God2 has sent/commissioned You to teach us-exc. Cuz (elaboration) the various amazing signs that You do show proof/evidence that God2 is the one who has given You power/authority. If that were not the case, na, surely those amazing signs wouldn't happen/work.” [EXEG: NLT]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: He came to Jesus at"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: He came to Jesus at night and said to him, "Teacher, we know that you are a teacher who came from God, because no one can do the signs [miracles] which you are doing, if God were not with him."</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kalo bukan Tuhan yang kasi kuasa"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">kalo bukan Tuhan yang kasi kuasa ko bekin tanda-tanda heran, sonde ada satu orang ju yang bisa bekin tanda sama ke Lu.&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="Cook\CNT\cn01670b.tif" rtfFormat="width:6.5cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:right" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Batúl! Deng Beta ju mau kasi tau bagini: kalo orang sonde lahir kambali, na, dia sonde bisa jadi Tuhan pung orang.&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus responded saying, “That's true! And I also want to tell you this: if a person is not born again, na, he cannot be/become God2's person.” [EXEG: while the Greek word is polysemous (1. again, 2. from above), and Jesus seems to be using it with double meaning, Nicodemus clearly understood the ‘again’ sense of the word (In vs.4 he reflects it back with “second time”). So the rendering in this verse has to set up the dialogue in the next verses.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="anwthen: 1) again, 2) from above"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">anwthen: 1) again, 2) from above LITERALLY: Jesus answered him, "That's true! I tell you, if anyone is not born again [from above], he cannot see [/experience] the kingdom of God.<span class="Italic">(3)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Ais Nikodemus tanya bilang, &lt;&lt;Ma karmana orang bisa lahir bagitu, kalo dia su bésar datang!? Dia sonde bisa maso kambali pi dalam dia pung mama pung tampa ana kali kadua, ais dia pung mama barana ulang sang dia. Sonde mungkin, to!?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Nikodemus asked saying, “But how can a person be born like that if s/he is already grown!? S/he cannot enter again into his mama's womb a second time, and then his mama gives birth again to him. That's not likely, right!?”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="gerwn: old, grown, adult LITERALLY: Nicodemus"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">gerwn: old, grown, adult LITERALLY: Nicodemus said to him, "How can a person be born when he is old? He cannot go into his mother's womb a second time and be born!<span class="Italic">(4)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Batúl! Ma Beta kasi tau bagini: orang musti lahir deng aer ko jadi barisi, deng lahir deng roh ko jadi orang baru. Deng bagitu, baru dia bisa maso jadi Tuhan Allah pung orang.<bt>Yesus responded saying, “True! But I'll tell you this: a person must be born with water to be/become clean/pure/holy, and be born with spirit to be/become a new person. In that way, only then can s/he enter becoming God's person. [EXEG: see Carson for extensive discussion of various interpretations of “born of water and spirit”, and concludes “a new birth that cleanses and renews”; NET Bible has a more concise note, summarizing the issue. Note: it is “spirit”, not “the Spirit” (no article). See Message.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="See John 3:3. LITERALLY: Jesus answered"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">See John 3:3. LITERALLY: Jesus answered him, "That's right! I tell you, whoever is not born of water and spirit, cannot enter into the kingdom of God.<span class="Italic">(5)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="6" />Te manusia lahir dari manusia, ma orang pung roh lahir baru dari Tuhan pung Roh.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) humans are born from humans, but a person's spirit is reborn/ born anew/ new birth from God2's Spirit. [EXEG: NLT, Carson]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: That which is born of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: That which is born of the flesh is flesh, and that which is born of the spirit is spirit.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Te manusia jadi dari manusia, ma"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">Te manusia jadi dari manusia, ma orang pung roh jadi dari Tuhan pung Roh.</Message></Annotation><v n="7" />Jang heran kalo Beta kasi tau bilang, &lt;Bosong musti lahir baru, ko dapa idop baru.&gt;<bt>Don't be surprised if I tell you saying, ‘You-pl must be born anew, to get new life.’</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="humas: 2p LITERALLY: Do not be"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">humas: 2p LITERALLY: Do not be surprised that I tell you, 'You must be born again.'<span class="Italic">(7)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="8" />Kotong banding deng angin. Te angin fuu iko dia pung mau. Kotong bisa dengar dia pung bunyi, ma sonde tau dia datang dari mana, deng mau pi mana. Samua orang yang lahir baru dari Tuhan pung Roh ju bagitu. Te kotong bisa lia Tuhan pung Roh su bekin orang jadi baru, biar kotong sonde mangarti karmana itu hal bisa jadi.&gt;&gt;<bt>Let's compare [it] with wind. Cuz (elaboration) wind blows following/according to its will/wishes. We-inc hear its sound, but don't know it comes from where, and is going to where. Everyone who is born anew from God2's Spirit is also like that. Cuz (elaboration) we-inc can see God2's Spirit has made a person become new, even though we don't understand how that can happen.” [EXEG: Carson, CONNOT, TRT (Carlton).]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: The wind blows where it"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: The wind blows where it wishes, and you hear its sound, but you do not know where it is coming from or where it is going. Thus it is with everyone who is born from the Spirit.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Kotong banding deng angin. Te angin"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">Kotong banding deng angin. Te angin fuu sini-sana // kiri-kanan (*iko dia pung mau). Kotong bisa dengar dia pung bunyi, ma sonde mangarti batúl angin datang/asal dari mana, ko mau pi mana. (Samua orang yang lahir (kambali) dari/deng Tuhan pung Roh ju bagitu. // Kotong ju dapa lia dia pung bukti/dampak/tanda/ujung dari samua orang yang lahir (kambali/batúl) dari/deng Tuhan pung Roh. // Kotong bisa lia Tuhan pung Roh su bekin orang jadi baru, biar kotong sonde mangarti karmana itu hal jadi.&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Ais Nikodemus tanya bilang, &lt;&lt;Karmana ko bisa jadi bagitu?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Nikodemus asked saying, “How can that happen/come to be/work?”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Nicodemus answered him, &quot;How can"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Nicodemus answered him, "How can these things be?"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;We, bu. Bu su jadi orang Isra'el pung guru bésar. Akurang ko bu sonde mangarti ini hal dong?<bt>Yesus responded saying, “We [+disbelief], older brother [+intimate respect]. You are the people of Isra'el's important teacher. How is it that you don't understand these things?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ho: the implication is that Nicodemus"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">ho: the implication is that Nicodemus was the main teacher of the nation, not just one among many; (Carson: You are the Reverend Professor Doctor...) LITERALLY: Jesus said to him, "You are the teacher of Israel, and you do not know these things?"<span class="Italic">(10)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="11" />Beta kasi tau yang batúl. Naa, botong mangarti ini hal dong. Te botong jadi saksi so'al hal-hal yang botong su lia sandiri. Ma bosong sonde tarima bae botong pung omong.<bt>I am telling what is true. Naa, we-exc understand these things. Cuz (elaboration) we are a witness/testifying of various things we have seen ourselves. But you-pl don't accept what we say. [EXEG: Q: who is we? TRT: “It is not clear who 'we (exclus.)' refers to here and there is much disagreement about this, so it is probably best translate 'we' literally. Many Bible scholars think it refers to Jesus and His disciples or followers (as in Jn 9.4). Some others think this is the editorial 'we' that means 'I' (Jesus). Some others think it refers to Christians who were alive at the time that John wrote this book. However, some others think it refers to Jesus and God's prophets, especially John the Baptizer, and a few think it refers to Jesus and His Father and/or the Holy Spirit (see Jn 8.18). It is very likely that Jesus is echoing/repeating Nicodemus' use of 'we' in verse 2.” See also Carson, TH, CONNOT, Ex.Helps. Our protocol is to preserve the ambiguity of the Gk where all the options are acceptable.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="we know/understand, we speak, we have"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">we know/understand, we speak, we have seen, we testify; you-pl LITERALLY: I am telling you the truth. We know what we speak of, and we have seen what we testify about, and you do not receive our testimony.<span class="Italic">(11) (11) </span>UBS wants to keep "we", as reflecting not only Jesus' testimony but that of John and the Christian community, but it jams up the Pidgin to say "we" without intervention, and it violates the integrity of the story in Greek.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Beta mangarti ini hal dong deng"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">Beta mangarti ini hal dong deng Beta kasi tau yang batúl. Te Beta jadi saksi so'al hal-hal yang Beta su lia sandiri. Ma bosong sonde tarima bae Beta pung omong.</Message></Annotation><v n="12" />Bosong sonde mau parcaya waktu Beta kasi tau so'al hal-hal yang jadi di bumi. Apalai kalo Beta kasi tau so'al hal-hal yang jadi di langit. Pasti bosong lebe sonde parcaya lai!<bt>You-pl don't want to believe when I tell/explain about things which happen on earth. Let alone/even less if I tell/explain about things which happen in the sky/heaven. Surely you-pl would believe even less (Lit: even more not believe)!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: If I speak to you"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: If I speak to you about earthly things and you do not believe, how will you believe if I speak to you about heavenly things?</Message></Annotation><v n="13" />Sonde ada satu orang ju yang nae pi mangada sang Tuhan di langit. Cuma Beta sa, andia Manusia Tulen ni, yang turun datang dari Dia.<bt>There is not one person who has ascended and faced God2 in heaven. Only Me, that is *Son of Man (Ideal/Authentic Human), who descended here coming from Him. [EXEG: heaven = Jewish circumlocution for God]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Nobody has gone into heaven"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Nobody has gone into heaven except the Son of Man, who came down from heaven.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Dolu-dolu di tampa sunyi, ba'i Musa kasi tagantong satu ular tambaga di atas kayu, ko samua orang dapa lia sang dia, ais ju dong dapa salamat. Hal bagitu ju musti jadi kasi Beta, Manusia Tulen ni. Nanti dong mau kasi tagantong sang Beta di atas kayu,<bt>Long ago in the lonely place (=wilderness), grandfather (=historical figure) Musa hung a copper/bronze snake on a wood/tree/pole, so everyone could see it and they could be/get *saved/delivered/ rescued (from bad consequences). A thing/event like that must also happen to Me, the Ideal Human. They (non-referential) are going to hang Me on a wood/tree/pole, [EXEG: HCE, CONNOT points out inappropriate to mention cross here.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Just as Moses lifted up"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Just as Moses lifted up the snake in the wilderness, thus it is necessary that the Son of Man be lifted up,</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:14" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Daftar Sensus 21:4-9</note><v n="15" />ko samua orang yang parcaya sang Beta dapa idop yang batúl yang sonde tau putus-putus.<bt>so that everyone who believes in Me will get *true/real life that never ends.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: so that everyone who believes"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: so that everyone who believes in him may have eternal life.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Te Tuhan Allah talalu sayang sang samua orang di ini dunya. Andia ko Dia utus sang Beta, Dia pung Ana satu biji ni, ko biar samua orang yang parcaya sang Beta sonde tapisa buang dari Tuhan. Deng bagitu, dong dapa idop yang batúl yang sonde tau putus-putus.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) God really loves everyone in this world. That is why He sent/commissioned Me, His only Child, so that everyone who believes in Me will not be separated off/cut off (completely) from God2. In that way, they can get *true/real life that never ends. [EXEG: Gk word is not “die”, but more sense of “die spiritually”. Problem: neither believers nor non-believers are “completely destroyed” but get eternal life or eternal punishment. Carlton (TRT) notes, “The translation of ‘perish’ should not mean ‘be completely destroyed/annihilated’. You could say ‘be lost (spiritually)’”; HCE “cut off from God”; NRSV, NLT “perish” (church language--zero meaning), CEV “never really die” (unsatisfactory on several counts), TB binasa “be destroyed, annihilated”.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="CHECK: talalu sayang vs. sayang talalu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">CHECK: talalu sayang vs. sayang talalu (over the top); CEV</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Pidgin doesn't let you switch from"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">Pidgin doesn't let you switch from "I" to "him" in the middle of a section when you're really talking about the same person. apoletai: perish, come to destruction, fail to obtain, be lost (in religious sense, economic, sheep gone astray) [not the normal Gk word for 'die']<span class="Italic">(16) (16) </span>hina ... mee apoleetai ... ekheei: aorist subjunctive and present subjunctive. This is carried by the two senses of "get" forced by the two different grammatical environments: get + state ... get + NP. The first is "come to be in one of two polar states with no middle ground"; the second is "possess something". LITERALLY: For thus God loved the world, so that he gave his only Son, in order that everyone who believes in him should not die but have eternal life.<span class="Italic">(16)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="17" />Naa! Tuhan sonde utus sang Beta, Dia pung Ana, datang di ini dunya ko putus orang pung hukuman. Ma Dia utus sang Beta ko kasi salamat sang orang dari dong pung sala-sala.<bt>Naa! [Discourse shift] God2 did not send/commission Me, His Child, to come to this world to decide people's punishment. But He sent/commissioned Me to *save people from their wrongs.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="krinei: judge, evaluate, condemn, decide LITERALLY:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">krinei: judge, evaluate, condemn, decide LITERALLY: For God did not send his Son into the world in order to condemn the world, but so the world might be saved through him.<span class="Italic">(17)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="18" />Tuhan Allah sonde hukum orang yang parcaya sang Beta. Ma Dia su putus memang hukuman kasi orang yang sonde parcaya sang Beta, <span class="Italic">tagal </span>itu orang sonde parcaya sang Beta, andia Tuhan Allah pung Ana satu biji ni.<bt>God does not punish people who believe in Me. But He has already decided beforehand the punishment for people who don't believe in Me, <span class="Italic">because </span>that person doesn't believe in Me, that is, in God's only Child. [NOTE: heavy, but reflects the meaning bits and style of Gk]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: He who believes in him"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: He who believes in him is not condemned, but he who does not believe has already been condemned, because he has not believed in the name of the only Son of God.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Kalo orang parcaya sang Beta, Tuhan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">Kalo orang parcaya sang Beta, Tuhan Allah sonde (kasi) hukum sang dia/dong. Ma orang yang sonde parcaya sang Beta, Tuhan su putus dia pung hukuman, tagal dia/dong sonde parcaya sang Beta, andia Tuhan Allah pung Ana satu biji.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Macam ke bagini: Tuhan su kirim datang taráng ko bacaya di ini dunya. Ma orang lebe suka idop di galáp. Dong sonde mau idop di taráng, tagal dong pung bekin, tar bae. Andia ko Tuhan mau hukum sang dong.<bt>It's like this (Idiom: think of it like this): God2 has sent light to shine in this world. But people preferred to live in the dark. They did/do not want to live in the light, because their deeds/what they do is not good. That is why God is going to punish them.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Dia pung gambar, bagini. = Macam"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">Dia pung gambar, bagini. = Macam ke bagini</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="See John 1:5. LITERALLY: But this"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">See John 1:5. LITERALLY: But this is the judgement, that the light has come into the world, and people loved the darkness rather than the light, because their deeds were evil.<span class="Italic">(19)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Dia pung gambar, bagini:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">Dia pung gambar, bagini:</Message></Annotation><v n="20" />Te samua orang yang bekin tar bae dong, binci deng itu taráng. Dong sonde suka itu taráng bacaya di dong, ko biar itu taráng jang buka kasi talanjang dong pung jahat.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) everyone who does what is not good, hates that light. They don't like that light shining on them, so that the light doesn't expose naked/totally their evil.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="elengchthei): the verb suggests not only"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">elengchthei): the verb suggests not only exposure but shame and conviction (Carson) phaula: mean, morally base, bad (LN); thoughtless, trivial, petty, careless acts (Source); worthless, bad, evil, base (BADG)<span class="Italic">(20) (20) </span>LITERALLY: For everyone who does evil hates the light, and does not come to the light, lest their deeds should be exposed.</Message></Annotation><v n="21" />Ma orang yang bekin iko yang batúl, dong datang ko biar itu taráng bacaya di dong. Te itu taráng kasi tunju bilang, dong ada bekin iko Tuhan pung mau.&gt;&gt;<bt>But people who do according to what is right/true, they come so that the light shine on them. Cuz (elaboration) that light shows that they are doing according to God2's will.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="to do the truth: a Semitic"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">to do the truth: a Semitic expression which means 'to act faithfully', 'to act honourably' LITERALLY: But the one who does the truth comes to the light, in order to show his deeds, that they are done through God.<span class="Italic">(21)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <Annotation class="History">
      <Message author="JSW" created="2009-10-02 03:47:29Z" when="2009-10-02 03:47:29Z" stage="Draft">DONE ch. 3: HCE, NRSV, NLT, Message, Source, Carson</Message>
    </Annotation>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus deng Yohanis tukang sarani<bt>The Lord Yesus and Yohanis the *Habitual Baptiser</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Ais itu, Yesus deng Dia pung ana bua dong kaluar dari kota Yerusalem, ma dong tenga tahan di da'era Yudea. Di situ dong sarani orang.<bt>After that, Yesus and His disciples left the city of Yerusalem, but they stayed temporarily in the region of Yudea. There they *baptised (method neutral) people. [EXEG: Jn. 4:2 says Jesus himself did not baptise, thus 3p subject here. Jerusalem from high-level context + NLT]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: After these things, Jesus and"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: After these things, Jesus and his disciples went into the land of Judea, and he stayed with them there and baptized.</Message></Annotation><v n="23-24" />Itu waktu, Herodes dong balóm lempar maso sang Yohanis tukang sarani pi dalam bui. Ais Yohanis ju ada sarani orang di kampong Ainon, deka di kampong Salim, tagal ada banya aer di situ. Ju orang maen datang di Yohanis ko dia sarani sang dong.<bt>At that time, Herodes (collective) had not yet thrown Yohanis the Habitual Baptiser into prison. And Yohanis was also baptising people in the village of Ainon, near the village of Salim, because there was a lot of water there. And people kept coming to Yohanis so he would *baptise them. [EXEG: not volume of water, but number of springs, streams. See Carson.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Referent of 1st dong??"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">Referent of 1st dong??</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: John was also baptizing in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: John was also baptizing in Aenon near Salim, because there was plenty of water there. The people were going and were being baptized. LITERALLY: For John was not yet thrown in prison.<span class="Italic">(23)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="3:24" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 14:3, Markus 6:17, Lukas 3:19-20</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Naa, agama Yahudi ada satu adat ko bekin barisi diri, baru dong bole sambayang. Di situ ada satu orang Yahudi yang baparkara deng Yohanis pung ana bua dong so'al itu hal.<bt>Naa, the Yahudi religion had a ritual to cleanse/purify oneself, before they could pray. There, there was a Yahudi person who was disputing with Yohanis' disciples/underlings about that matter/issue. [EXEG: fungsi dari sarani orang--Message.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: There was an argument between"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: There was an argument between some of John's disciples and a Jew about ritual purification.</Message></Annotation><v n="26" />Ais dong datang di Yohanis ko kasi tau bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa Guru! Inga ko sonde, itu Orang yang cari bapa di kali Yarden pung sablá tu, yang bapa bilang, Dia tu, andia Kristus? Dia ju ada sarani orang! Sonde ada yang datang di botong lai! Te samua orang maen pi di Dia sa!&gt;&gt;<bt>So/then they came to Yohanis to tell/report saying, “Father Teacher! Do you remember or not, that Person who was looking for you on the other side of the Yarden river, who you said that He was Kristus? He is also baptising people! Nobody's coming to us anymore! Cuz (elaboration) everyone just keeps going to Him!” [EXEG: NLT “instead of coming here to us.” Convey speaker attitude.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sonde tau hal, te = there"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">sonde tau hal, te = there is no reason for it</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ide: look, listen, pay attention LITERALLY:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">ide: look, listen, pay attention LITERALLY: And they came to John and said to him, "Teacher, the one who was with you on the other side of the Jordan [River], whom you testified about, look, he is baptizing and everybody is going to him."<span class="Italic">(26)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />Yohanis manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Bagini! Orang sonde bisa bekin apa-apa, kalo Tuhan Allah di sorga sonde buka jalan kasi sang dia.<bt>Yohanis responded saying, “It's like this! A person cannot do anything, if God in heaven does not open the way for him. [EXEG: Carson, NLT, CEV]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: John answered them, &quot;No man"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: John answered them, "No man can receive anything unless it has been given him from heaven.</Message></Annotation><v n="28" />Bosong sandiri su dengar beta kasi tau taráng-taráng bilang, &lt;Beta ni, bukan itu Kristus yang kotong ada batunggu-tunggu. Ma Tuhan su utus sang beta lebe dolo, ko buka jalan kasi sang Kristus. Bagitu sa!&gt;<bt>You-pl yourselves have heard me explaining clearly/forthrightly saying, ‘I here, am not that Kristus whom we have been eagerly awaiting. But God2 has sent/commissioned me ahead of time/prior, to open the way for Kristus. That's (how it is/what I've said)!’</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: You yourselves are my witnesses,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: You yourselves are my witnesses, that I said, 'I am not the Christ, but I was sent ahead of him.'</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:28" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yohanis 1:20</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="29" />Umpama, baroit laki-laki ada dia pung baroit parampuan. Ma dia pung saksi, yang badiri deng dia, pung hati sanáng kalo dengar baroit laki-laki ba'omong. Yesus tu, sama ke satu baroit laki-laki. Deng beta ni, sama ke Dia pung saksi. Andia ko sakarang beta pung hati talalu sanáng.<bt>As an example, a bridegroom has his bride. But his witness (Indonesian/Kupang technical term for an official companion of the wedding party.), who stands with him, is happy if/when he hears the bridegroom talking. The Yesus is like a/the bridegroom. And me here, am like His witness. That is why now my liver is really happy. [EXEG: ‘complete, fulfilled’ carried by ‘now’.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: The one who has the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: The one who has the bride is the bridegroom. But the friend of the bridegroom, who stands and hears him, is glad because of the voice of the bridegroom. Therefore my joy has been made complete.</Message></Annotation><v n="30" />Yang pantíng tu, Dia musti batamba tarús jadi orang bésar, ais biar ko beta bakurang tarús jadi orang kici.&gt;&gt;<bt>The important thing is, He must keep increasing in importance/significance/greatness (big person), and it's fine if I keep decreasing becoming insignificant (small person).”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: He must increase while I"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: He must increase while I must decrease."</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Yang pantíng tu, Dia musti batamba"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">Yang pantíng tu, Dia musti batamba tarús jadi orang bésar, te beta cuma orang kici sa. Biar beta tamba kurang, ju bae.&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Orang yang turun datang dari sorga<bt>The person who descends coming (=comes down) from heaven</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="31" />Yohanis omong sambung lai bilang, &lt;&lt;Dia turun datang dari Tuhan Allah di langit, andia ko Dia lebe bésar dari samua. Ma beta cuma datang dari ini dunya, andia ko beta sama ke samua orang di ini dunya. Beta omong so'al hal yang jadi hari-hari di ini dunya. Ma yang turun datang dari Tuhan di langit tu, pasti Dia lebe hebat dari samua.<bt>Yohanis continued speaking saying, “He came down from God in heaven, so that is why he is greater than everything/everyone. But I have only come from this world, so that is why I am like everyone in this world. I speak about everyday matters in this world. But the one who comes down from God2 in heaven is more amazing/ incredible/ greater than all/everything/ everyone. [EXEG: NLT. /dunya/ here is not about sinfulness but about limitations (Carson).] [STYLE: use /besar/ and /hebat/ to highlight two aspects of the implied status.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: He who comes from above"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: He who comes from above is above all. He who is from the earth belongs to the earth and speaks about earthly matters, but he who comes from heaven is above all.</Message></Annotation><v n="32" />Dia kasi tau so'al apa yang Dia sandiri su lia deng su dengar. Ma orang sonde tarima bae apa yang Dia su kasi tau.<bt>He tells about what He himself has already seen and already heard. But people don't accept what He has said.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: He testifies to what he"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: He testifies to what he has seen and heard, and nobody receives his testimony.</Message></Annotation><v n="33" />Kalo orang tarima apa yang itu Orang dari atas su kasi tau tu, itu ju kasi tunju bukti bilang, dia parcaya Tuhan pung omong tu, batúl.<bt>If people accepted what that Person from above has already said/told/explained, it would also show evidence/proof that he believes what God2 says is true.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="esphragisen: certify, validate, put a seal"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">esphragisen: certify, validate, put a seal on, give in a secure/definitive manner, make known, mark LITERALLY: The one who receives his testimony has certified that God is truthful.<span class="Italic">(33)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="34" />Itu Orang yang Tuhan kirim datang tu, kasi tau Tuhan Allah pung pasán. Te Tuhan su kasi Dia pung Roh sang Dia deng sonde ada pung batas.<bt>That Person whom God2 sent, tells God's message. Cuz (elaboration) God2 has given His Spirit to Him without limit.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: The one whom God sent"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: The one whom God sent speaks God's words, because God does not limit the Spirit he gives him.</Message></Annotation><v n="35" />Te Bapa di sorga sayang mati sang Dia pung Ana. Deng Dia sarakan samua-samua di itu Ana pung tangan.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) Father in heaven really loves His Child. And He has turned over/entrusted everything into that Child's hand [STYLE: They insist this is natural, not a Hebraism--I've heard a number of these expressions in other non-translation contexts. With /tangan/ implies also giving responsibility/authority for dealing with it according to the giver's wishes.] [EXEG: leave broad ‘everything’ vs. specific ‘power/authority’]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sarakan samua-samua di itu Ana pung"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">sarakan samua-samua di itu Ana pung tangan. = with tangan implies also giving responsibility/authority for dealing with it according to the giver's wishes</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: The Father loves the Son"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: The Father loves the Son and has given all things into his hand.</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:35" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 11:27, Lukas 10:22</note><v n="36" />Ais orang yang parcaya sang itu Ana tu, dong dapa idop yang batúl yang sonde tau putus-putus. Ma orang yang sonde parcaya sang Dia, deng sonde bekin iko Dia pung pasán, dong sonde dapa itu idop, te Tuhan Allah tatáp kasi tunju Dia pung mara ko hukum sang dong.&gt;&gt;<bt>So then people who believe in that Child, they will get real life that never ends. But people who don't believe in Him, and don't do according to His message, they don't get that life, cuz (elaboration) God's steadfastly shows His anger to punish them.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Since there is substantial doubt that"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">Since there is substantial doubt that these are the words of Jesus, but more likely an editorial comment by John the writer (see Carson), third person is fine here, though it isn't in Verse 16. LITERALLY: The one who believes in the Son has eternal life. But the one who disobeys the Son will not see life, but the wrath of God stays on him.<span class="Italic">(36)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus ba'omong deng satu parampuan di Samaria<bt>The Lord Yesus talks with a woman in Samaria</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="4" />
      <v n="1-2" />Kalo banding Yohanis deng Yesus, na, Yesus pung ana bua dong mulai sarani lebe banya orang yang iko sang Dia. Yesus sandiri sonde sarani orang, cuma Dia pung ana bua dong sa yang sarani orang. Ais waktu Yesus dapa tau bilang, orang dari partei agama Farisi su dengar dong ada sarani lebe banya orang,<bt>When comparing Yohanis with Yesus, na, Yesus' disciples began to baptise more people who were following Him. Yesus himself did not baptise people, only His disciples baptised people. So then when Yesus found out that people of the Farisi religious party had heard they were baptising more people, [DISCOURSE: restructured for background - foreground.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="oun: so (loose, resumptive, transitional), therefore"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">oun: so (loose, resumptive, transitional), therefore LITERALLY: Therefore when Jesus knew that the Pharisees had heard that Jesus was gaining and baptizing more disciples than John,<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>LITERALLY: (But Jesus himself did not baptize, but his disciples.)</Message></Annotation><v n="3" />ju Dia deng Dia pung ana bua dong jalan kasi tenga da'era Yudea, ko pulang kambali pi propinsi Galilea.<bt>He and His disciples left the region of Yudea, to return again to the province of Galilea.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="SVC"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">SVC</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: He left Judea, and went"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: He left Judea, and went again into Galilee.</Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Ma dong musti jalan lewat propinsi Samaria ko tambús pi Galilea.<bt>But they had to go through/by way of the province of Samaria to come out in Galilea.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But he had to go"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But he had to go through Samaria.</Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Dong jalan, ju dong sampe di satu kota di Samaria, nama Sikar, deka-deka di tana yang ba'i Yakob kasi sang dia pung ana Yusuf.<bt>They went/ travelled, and they arrived at a city in Samaria, named Sikar, very near to the land which grandfather Yakob had given to his child Yusuf.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then he came to a"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then he came to a city in Samaria, named Sychar, near the property that Jacob gave to his son Joseph.</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:5" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 33:19, Yosua 24:32</note><v n="6-8" />Di situ ada satu parigi, nama &lt;parigi Yakob&gt;. Tenga hari, ju Yesus dong sampe di situ. Dia rasa cape dari dong pung jalan, ais Dia dudu barenti cape di itu parigi. Ju Dia pung ana bua dong kasi tenga Dia sandiri di situ, ko dong maso pi béli makan di kota.<bt>There, there was a well, named ‘Yakob's well’. In the middle of the day, Yesus (collective) arrived there. He felt tired from their trip, so He sat to rest at that well. And His disciples left Hims alone there, to go into the city to buy food.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ais satu parampuan dari itu kota datang ko ame aer di itu parigi. Yesus minta sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Susi. Beta bisa minta aer minum sadiki, ko?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then a woman from that city came to get water at that well. Yesus requested of her saying, “Older sister. Can I ask for a drink? (idiomatic)”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: 6 Now Jacob's well was"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: 6 Now Jacob's well was there. So Jesus, being tired from the trip, sat down on the well/spring/fountain. It was about the sixth hour. LITERALLY: 7 A Samaritan woman came to get water. Jesus said to her, "Give me a drink." 8 (For his disciples had gone into the city to buy food.)<span class="Italic">(6)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="Cook\CNT\cn01674b.tif" rtfFormat="width:6.5cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:right" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Ma itu parampuan takuju, tagal orang Yahudi biasa sonde mau bacampor deng orang Samaria. Ais dia tanya bale sang Yesus bilang, &lt;&lt;Weh! Om orang Yahudi. Beta ni, orang Samaria. Sonde sala ni, ko? Om minta minum di beta?&gt;&gt;<bt>But that woman was surprised, because Yahudi people normally don't want to mix/interact with Samaria people. So she asked Yesus in return saying, “Weh! [+mild objection] Uncle (MB) is a Yahudi person. I'm a Samaria person. Isn't it wrong for you to ask me for a drink? (Or: don't you have a problem with this, asking me for a drink?)”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sunchrwntai: associate, share things in common,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">sunchrwntai: associate, share things in common, use dishes with LITERALLY: Then the Samaritan woman said to him, "How come that you, being a Jew, ask for a drink from me, a Samaritan woman? For the Jews have nothing to do with the Samaritans."<span class="Italic">(9)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ma itu parampuan tanya (bale) sang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">Ma itu parampuan tanya (bale) sang Dia, bilang, &lt;&lt;Weh! Bapa/Om orang Yahudi. Beta orang Samaria. Jadi, akurang ko Bapa/Om minta minum sang/dari beta // beta yang kasi minum!? Te bosong orang Yahudi biasa enteng/noju/sonde mau bacampor deng botong orang Samaria na!&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:9" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Esra 4:1-5, Nehemia 4:1-2</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Yesus kasi tau bilang, &lt;&lt;Bagini. Kalo susi tau apa yang Tuhan Allah mau kasi samua orang, deng tau Beta yang minta minum ni, Sapa, tantu susi minta bale aer dari Beta. Ais Beta kasi aer yang bawa idop.&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus explained saying, “It's like this. If you knew what it was that God wants to give everyone, and knew Who I am who is asking for a drink, surely you would ask me for water in return/instead. And I would give water that brings life.” [EXEG: “God's gift” 1) that He wants to give you (NLT, CEV), 2) that He wants to give everyone (Jews and Samaritans alike) (HCE, context), 3) “gift of God” = Torah (Odeburg, in Carson), 4) eternal life (Carson).]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Jesus told her, &quot;If you"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Jesus told her, "If you knew God's gift, and who asked you for a drink, you would have asked him instead, and he would have given you living water."</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ju Beta kasi sang lu (satu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">ju Beta kasi sang lu (satu macam) aer yang bawa idop yang batúl yang sonde putus-putus.</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:10" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yeremia 2:13, Sakaria 14:8; Yeheskial 47:9</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Itu parampuan bilang, &lt;&lt;Om pung ember timba sonde ada. Deng ini parigi ni, ju dalam. Dari mana Om mau dapa itu aer yang bawa idop tu? Ko itu aer ada di mana lai?<bt>The woman said, “Uncle has no dipping bucket. And this well is also deep. Where are you going to get that water that brings life? Where could that water be?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: The woman said to him,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: The woman said to him, "Sir, you have nothing [no bucket] to draw water with, and the well is deep. So where do you keep this living water?</Message></Annotation><v n="12" />Mana mungkin Om lebe hebat dari kotong pung ba'i Yakob! Dia yang kasi tenga ini parigi sang botong. Deng dia sandiri ju minum dari ini parigi. Dia pung ana-ana, deng dia pung binatang dong ju bagitu.&gt;&gt;<bt>It is surely not possible that you are greater than our-inc grandfather Yakob! He is the one who left this well for us-exc. And he himself also drank from this well. His children, and his animals also did that.” [EXEG: cattle = flocks; NRSV, NLT, CEV]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Are you greater than our"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Are you greater than our father Jacob, who gave us the well, and drank from it himself, and his children and his cattle?"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Inga, é! Orang yang biasa minum dari ini parigi ni, nanti aus ulang lai.<bt>Yesus responded saying, “Remember, é! A person who normally/habitually drinks from this well, will later get thirsty again.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Jesus said, &quot;Whoever drinks [habitually]"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Jesus said, "Whoever drinks [habitually] this water will get thirsty again.</Message></Annotation><v n="14" />Ma orang yang minum itu aer yang Beta kasi, nanti sonde aus ulang lai. Te aer yang Beta kasi tu, sama ke satu mata aer yang maspurak kaluar. Itu aer tu, bawa idop yang batúl yang sonde tau putus-putus.&gt;&gt;<bt>But the person who drinks that water that I give, will later not get thirsty again. Cuz (elaboration) the water that I give, is like a spring which bursts out (under pressure)/artesians out. That water brings real life which never ends.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But whoever drinks [once] of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But whoever drinks [once] of the water that I will give him will never thirst again, but the water that I will give him will become in him a well of water springing up into eternal life."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Itu parampuan bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo bagitu, na, Om kasi beta itu aer su, ko biar beta sonde usa aus lai! Deng bagitu, beta sonde usa datang ulang-ulang ko timba aer di sini lai.&gt;&gt;<bt>The woman said, “If that's the case, na, Uncle give me that water [+imperative], so that I don't have to get thirsty again! In that way, I won't have to keep coming here to fetch water anymore.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: The woman said to him,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: The woman said to him, "Sir, give me this water, that I will not thirst nor [have to] keep coming here to draw water."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Ais Yesus suru bilang, &lt;&lt;Bagini. Susi pulang dolo. Pange susi pung laki, ais bale datang di sini.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus commanded saying, “[Do] like this. Older sister go home now, Summon your man/husband, then come back here.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: He said, &quot;Go, call your"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: He said, "Go, call your husband, and come here."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17-18" />Dia manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Ma beta sonde ada laki.&gt;&gt;<bt>She responded saying, “But I don't have a husband.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ju Yesus bilang, &lt;&lt;Batúl. Lu omong jujur. Te lu parná ada lima laki. Deng yang ada sakarang ni, bukan lu pung laki.&gt;&gt;<bt>And Yesus said, “True. You speak honestly. Cuz (elaboration) you have had five men/husbands. And the one now, is not your husband.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: The woman said to him,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: The woman said to him, "I do not have a husband." Jesus said to her, "You have said well that you do not have a husband. LITERALLY: Because you have had five husbands, and now the one you have is not your husband. You have told the truth."</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lima yang beda-beda."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">lima yang beda-beda.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Ju itu parampuan bilang, &lt;&lt;Awii! Sakarang beta su tau, Om ni, Tuhan pung jubir satu.<bt>Then the woman said, “Awii! [+amazement] Now I know that Uncle here, is one of God2's *spokespeople.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: The woman said to him,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: The woman said to him, "Sir, I see that you are a prophet.</Message></Annotation><v n="20" />Naa, beta mau tanya. Botong orang Samaria pung nene-moyang dong sémba sang Tuhan Allah di ini gunung Gerisim.<bt>Naa, [shift] I want to ask. We-exc Samaria people's ancestors worshipped God on this Gerisim mountain.</bt><note reference="4:20" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Gunung Gerisim tu, deka deng kampong Sikem di propinsi Samaria. Di tulisan bahasa Yunani, cuma tulis bilang, &lt;&lt;di ini gunung&gt;&gt;. Ma orang yang pintar dong samua bilang, itu gunung pung nama, andia &lt;&lt;Gerisim&gt;&gt;.<bt>That Gerisim mountain was near the village of Sikem in the province of Samaria. In the Yunani language writings, it only says, “at this mountain”. But all the knowledgeable people say the name of that mountain is “Gerisim”.</bt></note>Ma bosong orang Yahudi bilang, kalo mau sémba sang Tuhan Allah, samua orang musti pi Yerusalem. Iko Om, yang batúl tu, karmana?&gt;&gt;<bt>But you-pl Yahudi people say, if (you/people) want to worship God, everyone must go to Yerusalem. According to you, the truth is what?” [EXEG: NLT]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Our fathers worshipped on this"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Our fathers worshipped on this mountain, but you say that in Jerusalem is the place where it is necessary to worship."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Susi parcaya dolo deng Beta pung omong ni, te ini batúl. Mau sémba sang Tuhan di ini gunung ko, di Yerusalem ko, nanti dia pung waktu datang, dua-dua sonde ada pung guna lai.<bt>Yesus responded saying, “Older sister should believe what I am telling you, cuz it is true. Whether one wants to worship God2 on this mountain or, in Yerusalem or [open disjunction], the time will come when both/neither will be of anymore use. [EXEG: NLT, Carson “Believe me (pisteuw plus the dative; cf. notes on 2:22), are not an invitation to trust Jesus with saving faith, but a simple asseverative” = conversational device.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Jesus said to her, &quot;Woman,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Jesus said to her, "Woman, believe me, the hour is coming when you will not worship the Father on this mountain, nor at Jerusalem.</Message></Annotation><v n="22" />Bosong orang Samaria sonde tau banya, so'al bosong sémba sang sapa. Ma botong orang Yahudi tau banya, so'al Tuhan Allah yang botong sémba. Te Dia mau pake botong ko buka jalan, ko biar orang bisa dapa salamat dari dong pung sala-sala.<bt>You-pl Samaria people don't understand a lot about who you worship. But we-exc Yahudi people know a lot about God whom we worship. Cuz (elaboration) He wants to use us-exc to open the way so that people can be saved from their sins. [EXEG: NLT, CEV]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="HCE last sentence problematic here."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">HCE last sentence problematic here.</Message><Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2015-11-20 00:26:41Z">EXEG:</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: You do not know whom"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: You do not know whom you worship. We know whom we worship, because salvation is from the Jews.</Message></Annotation><v n="23" />Nanti dia pung waktu datang, andia su mulai sakarang ni, orang yang ada sémba batúl sang kotong pung Bapa di sorga, na, dong sémba sang Dia iko Dia pung Roh, deng iko apa yang batúl. Te Bapa di sorga suka deng orang macam bagitu yang sémba sang Dia.<bt>The time is going to come, and has already begun now, when people who truly worship out-inc Father in heaven, na, they worship Him according to His Spirit, and according to what is true. Cuz (elaboration) Father in heaven likes people of that sort who worship Him. [EXEG: 23-24 based on plays on multiple senses of spirit; if want to preserve parallels in these well known verses, must go with Spirit, rather than spirit.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="and truth -- from really knowing"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">and truth -- from really knowing about the God they worship? NOTE Message: "Your worship must engage your spirit in the pursuit of truth...."</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="proskunew: bow down before, worship LITERALLY:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">proskunew: bow down before, worship LITERALLY: But the hour is coming and is already here, when the true worshippers will worship the Father in spirit/Spirit and truth; for the Father looks for that kind of people to worship him.<span class="Italic">(23)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Nanti dia pung waktu datang, padahal"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">Nanti dia pung waktu datang, padahal dia pung waktu su ada sakarang, yang, orang yang sémba batúl sang Bapa, dong sémba iko Dia pung Roh, deng iko yang batúl. orang yang sémba batúl sang Bapa di sorga, dong sémba sang Dia dari dong pung dalam hati, tagal dong kanál batúl sang Dia. Padahal, Bapa di sorga cari/suka orang macam bagitu yang/ko sémba sang Dia.<span class="Italic">(23)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="24" />Te Tuhan tu, roh. Ais orang yang sémba sang Dia musti sémba iko Dia pung Roh, deng iko apa yang batúl.&gt;&gt;<bt>Cuz (elaboration) God2 is spirit. So then people who worship Him must worship according to His Spirit, and according to what is true.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="R besar = rakus"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">R besar = rakus</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: God is spirit/Spirit, and those"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: God is spirit/Spirit, and those who worship him must worship him in spirit/Spirit and truth.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Itu parampuan kasi tau bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta su tau itu Mesias mau datang, andia yang orang subu bilang, &lt;Kristus&gt;, yang Tuhan Allah su janji memang mau kirim datang. Nanti kalo Dia su datang, na, pasti Dia kasi tau samua-samua sang kotong.&gt;&gt;<bt>The woman said/told/explained saying, “I know that the *Mesias (loan) is going to come, that is the one who people refer to saying ‘Kristus’, who God has promised beforehand to send coming. Later when He has come, na, surely He will explain everything to us-inc.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: The woman said to him,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: The woman said to him, "I know that Messiah is coming, the one who is called 'Christ'. When he comes, he will tell us everything."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="26" />Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Andia Beta su, yang ada ba'omong sakarang ni.&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus responded saying, “That is Me [+emphatic], who is speaking to you now.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Jesus said to her, &quot;I"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Jesus said to her, "I am he, the one who is speaking to you."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />Pas itu waktu, Dia pung ana bua dong datang kambali dari kota. Dong heran, tagal dong lia Dia ada ba'omong deng parampuan Samaria satu. Ma sonde ada yang tanya sang itu parampuan bilang, &lt;&lt;Lu mau apa?&gt;&gt; Deng sonde ada yang tanya sang Yesus bilang, &lt;&lt;Akurang ko Bos ba'omong deng ini parampuan?&gt;&gt;<bt>Just at that time, His disciples came back from the city. They were surprised/ amazed, because He was speaking with a Samaria woman. But there was no one who asked the woman saying, “What do you want?” And there was no one who asked Yesus saying, “Why is Bos speaking to this woman?” [EXEG: Carson]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="@@GRAMMAR parampuan Samaria satu ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">@@GRAMMAR parampuan Samaria satu ;</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: At that moment his disciples"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: At that moment his disciples came, and they were amazed that he spoke to the woman. But no one said, "What do you want?" or, "Why are you talking to her?"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Ais, itu parampuan jalan kasi tenga dia pung kumbang di situ, ko pulang pi dalam kota. Ju dia carita kasi orang di situ dong bilang,<bt>So/then, that woman left her jug behind there, to/and returned into the city. And she told/narrated to the people there saying,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Therefore the woman left her"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Therefore the woman left her waterpot and went back into the town, and said to the people,</Message></Annotation><v n="29" />&lt;&lt;Mari ko lia coba ini Orang dolo! Te Dia kasi tabuka abis samua-samua yang beta su parná bekin. Jang-jangan Dia ni, Kristus, yang Tuhan su janji mau kirim datang!&gt;&gt;<bt>“Come have a look at this person [+light imperative]! Cuz (elaboration) He has completely revealed everything I've ever done. What if/could it be/perhaps He is Kristus, who God2 promised to send!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="@@ PHONOLOGY jang-jangan = [jaɲ-jaŋan] parallels"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">@@ PHONOLOGY jang-jangan = [jaɲ-jaŋan] parallels [bam-baɲa]</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: &quot;Come, see a man who"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: "Come, see a man who told me everything I ever did. Is this not the Christ?"</Message></Annotation><v n="30" />Ais orang dong kaluar dari itu kota, ju pi lia sang Yesus.<bt>So/then, the people went out from that city, and went to see Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then they left the town,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then they left the town, and came to him.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="31" />Waktu itu parampuan baru pulang pi kota, Yesus pung ana bua dong buju-buju sang Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa Guru! Mari makan doo!&gt;&gt;<bt>When that woman had just gone home to the city, Yesus' disciples begged/coaxed Him saying, “Father Teacher! Come eat [+light imperative]!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: In the meantime his disciples"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: In the meantime his disciples begged him, "Teacher, eat".</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="32" />Ma Dia manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta su ada pung makanan yang bosong sonde tau.&gt;&gt;<bt>But He responded saying, “I already have food that you-pl don't know (about).”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But he said to them,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But he said to them, "I have food to eat that you do not know."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="33" />Dia pung ana bua dong batanya satu deng satu bilang, &lt;&lt;Karmana ni? Sapa yang su datang ko kasi Dia makanan?&gt;&gt;<bt>His disciples asked each other saying, “How is this? Who is it who has come to give Him food?”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Therefore his disciples said to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Therefore his disciples said to each other, "Could anyone have brought him something to eat?"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="34" />Ma Yesus kasi tau bilang, &lt;&lt;Bagini. Tuhan Allah utus sang Beta ko bekin iko Dia pung mau, deng kasi jalan Dia pung karjá sampe abis. Itu, sama ke makanan buat Beta.<bt>But Yesus explained saying, “It's like this. God sent/commissioned Me to do according to His will, and carry out His work until it is done/completed. That is like food to/for Me.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Jesus said to them, &quot;My"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Jesus said to them, "My food is to do the will of the one who sent me, and to finish his work."</Message></Annotation><v n="35" />Naa. Bosong biasa lia-lia di ladang, ais takser bilang, &lt;Masi ampa bulan lai, baru bisa koru.&gt; Dengar, é! Beta kasi tau. Kalo bosong lia bae-bae, ladang dong sakarang su siap koru. Ladang dong, sama ke itu orang banya di sana yang ada datang di kotong. Te dong tu, su siap parcaya sang Beta.<bt>Naa. [+Discourse shift] You-pl normally have a good look at a field/the fields, then guess/estimate saying, &lt;Still four more months before [we] can pick/harvest (grain).&gt; Listen, é! I'm telling you (how it really is). If you look carefully, the fields are now already ready to pick/harvest. Those fields are like those people there who are coming to us-inc. Cuz (elaboration) they are ready to believe in Me. [EXEG: In consultant check UNS's had difficulty figuring out field = ??; So from Kankanay, Western Bukidnon, Yakan, Tagbanwa BT's, we put in last 2 sentences.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="takser Western Bukidnon BT “Because look"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">takser Western Bukidnon BT “Because look at these many people.” Kankanay BT “Look (strong command) at the people who are coming. They are the ones I am comparing to ripe rice in the field, because they ought to be harvested.” Yakan BT “Look at the people who are coming here. If compared to rice, they are ripe already and ready to be harvested. It means they will soon believe in me. ... And the people they gather are given life forever.” Tagbanwa BT “For look at those crowds of people coming towards us. As for them, what they're like are plants ready for harvest.”<span class="Italic">(35)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Do you not say, 'There"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Do you not say, 'There are still four months, and than the harvest comes?' Look, I say to you, Lift up your eyes and look at the fields, for they are ripe for the harvest.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Naa. Bosong biasa lia-lia di ladang,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">Naa. Bosong biasa lia-lia di ladang, ais takser, bilang, &lt;Masi ampa bulan lai, baru bisa koru.&gt; Dengar é! Beta kasi tau. Kalo bosong lia bae-bae, ladang dong sakarang su siap koru.</Message></Annotation><v n="36" />Bukan cuma bagitu sa, te tukang koru dong yang ada kumpul dong pung hasil dalam gudang, su mulai tarima ame dong pung upa. Dong tu, sama ke orang yang kasi tunju jalan ko orang parcaya sang Tuhan Allah, ais dapa idop yang batúl yang sonde tau putus-putus. Deng bagitu, orang yang tanam bibit, deng orang yang koru hasil dong, bisa sanáng sama-sama.<bt>Not only that, cuz/but the pickers/ harvesters who are gathering/ collecting their yield/ produce in the storehouses/ bodegas, have already begun to receive their wages/ payment/ reward. Those one are like people who show the way for people to believe in God, and get real life which never ends. In that way, people who plant seeds, and people who pick/ harvest the produce/ result, can be happy together. [EXEG: NLT, Carson.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="does /panen, koru/ imply both cutting"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">does /panen, koru/ imply both cutting and gathering? Yes.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And the one who harvests"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And the one who harvests is being paid and gathers the crops for eternal life, that both he who plants and he who harvests may be glad together.</Message></Annotation><v n="37" />Orang bilang, &lt;Satu orang tanam bibit; orang laen yang kumpul dia pung hasil.&gt; Itu batúl tu.<bt>People say, ‘One person plants seed; other/another is the one who gathers the crop/result/harvest.’ That's true.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: In this the saying is"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: In this the saying is true: One is the planter and another the harvester.</Message></Annotation><v n="38" />Beta su utus sang bosong ko pi kumpul hasil dari orang laen pung karjá. Memang bukan bosong yang karjá, ma bosong yang dapa ontong dari dong pung cape.&gt;&gt;<bt>I have sent/ commissioned you-pl to go gather/ collect produce/ harvest from the work of other people. It's really not you who did the work, but you are the ones who get/gain the benefit from their efforts/tiredness.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: I sent you to harvest"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: I sent you to harvest that which you did not work for. Others worked, and you got the benefits of their work.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="39" />Itu waktu, ada banya orang Samaria di itu kota yang parcaya sang Yesus, tagal itu parampuan pung omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Dia kasi tabuka abis samua-samua yang beta su parná bekin.&gt;&gt;<bt>At that time, there were many Samaria people in that city who believed in Yesus, because of what that woman said saying, “He completely revealed/exposed everything I have ever done.” [NOTE: same as vs.29] [DISCOURSE: “At that time” needed to signal shift in topic.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And many of the Samaritans"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And many of the Samaritans of that town believed in Jesus because of what the woman had testified, "He told me all that I ever did."</Message></Annotation><v n="40" />Ais waktu dong datang di Yesus, dong minta-minta sang Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa tenga deng botong di sini sa!&gt;&gt; Ju Dia tenga tahan dua hari di situ.<bt>Then when they came to Yesus, they begged Him saying, “Father just stay/live with us here!” And He stayed temporarily two days there.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: So when the Samaritans had"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: So when the Samaritans had come to him, they begged him to stay with them, and he stayed there two days.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="41" />Deng banya orang laen ju parcaya sang Dia, tagal Dia pung omong.<bt>And many other people also believed in Him, because of what He said.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And many more believed because"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And many more believed because of his own word.</Message></Annotation><v n="42" />Ju dong kasi tau sang itu parampuan bilang, &lt;&lt;Kamaren tu, botong cuma dengar lu pung omong sa. Ma sakarang botong parcaya sang Dia, tagal botong dengar langsung dari Dia. Botong tau batúl bilang, ini Orang ni, yang bisa kasi salamat sang kotong samua di ini dunya dari kotong pung sala-sala dong.&gt;&gt;<bt>And they told the woman saying, “Yesterday, we-exc only heard what you-sg had to say. But now we-exc believe in Him, because we listened to Him directly. We really know that this Person is the one who can save all of us-inc in this world from our wrongs.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kamaren"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">kamaren</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And said to the woman,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And said to the woman, "Now we believe, not because of what you said, but because we have heard ourselves, and know that this is really the Savior of the world."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <Annotation class="History">
      <Message author="JSW" created="2009-10-02 03:47:29Z" when="2009-10-02 03:47:29Z" stage="Draft">DONE ch. 4: HCE, NRSV, NLT, Message, Source, Carson</Message>
    </Annotation>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus bekin bae satu pagawe pung ana<bt>The Lord Yesus heals an official's child</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="43" />Yesus dong tenga dua hari di situ, ais ju dong jalan tarús pi propinsi Galilea.<bt>After Yesus (collective) had stayed there two days, then they continued going/travelling to the province of Galilea.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: After two days he went"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: After two days he went from there into Galilee.</Message></Annotation><v n="44" />(Satu kali Yesus parná omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Orang sonde suka kasi hormat sang Tuhan Allah pung jubir di dia pung kampong sandiri.&gt;&gt;)<bt>(One time Yesus had spoken saying, “People don't like to give respect to God's spokesperson in his own village.”)</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For Jesus himself testified that"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For Jesus himself testified that a prophet is not respected in his own country.</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:44" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 13:57, Markus 6:4, Lukas 4:24</note><v n="45" />Dolu waktu balóm pesta Paska, banya orang Galilea dong su pi kota Yerusalem ko bekin hari bae di sana. Ju dong sampat lia samua yang Yesus bekin di Yerusalem. Andia ko waktu Dia pulang pi Galilea, dong tarima bae sang Dia.<bt>Previously when it was not.yet Paska feast, many Galilea people had gone to the city of Yerusalem to make/do the festival there. And they had opportunity/were able to see everything that Yesus did in Yerusalem. That is why when He returned (home) to Galilea, they accepted/received Him. [CONNECTORS: Carson, Message.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then when he came into"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then when he came into Galilee, the Galileans welcomed him, because they had seen all the things he had done in Jerusalem at the feast, because they too had gone to the feast.</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:45" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yohanis 2:23</note><v n="46" />Ais Yesus dong jalan tarús pi ulang lai di kampong Kana di propinsi Galilea. Dia parná bekin aer jadi anggor di situ.<bt>So/then Yesus (coll.) continue going and went again to the village of Kana in the province of Galilea. He had (once/ever) made water become wine there.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Itu waktu tu, ada satu pagawe di kota Kapernaum. Dia pung ana laki-laki ada saki.<bt>At that time, there was an official in the city of Kapenaum. His son was sick.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ein: 'there was' (presentational clause, AGNT,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">ein: 'there was' (presentational clause, AGNT, NRSV, NLT, CEV), not 'was there' LITERALLY: So Jesus came again into Cana of Galilee, where he had made the water wine. And there was a certain nobleman, whose son was sick at Capernaum.<span class="Italic">(46)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="4:46" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yohanis 2:1-11</note><v n="47" />Waktu itu pagawe dapa dengar bilang, Yesus su pulang datang di Galilea dari propinsi Yudea, ju dia jalan nae pi Kana ko cari sang Yesus. Katumu, ju dia noki-noki ko Yesus turun datang bekin bae sang dia pung ana. Te itu ana su mau mati.<bt>When that official heard that Yesus had already come back/home to Galilea from the province of Yudea, he went up (topographical) to Kana to look for Yesus. When he met [Him], he begged2 for Yesus to come down and heal his child. Cuz (elaboration) that child was about to die.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: When he heard that Jesus"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: When he heard that Jesus had come from Judea into Galilee, he went to him, and begged him to come down and heal his son, because he was about to die.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="48" />Yesus kasi tau sang itu pagawe bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo bosong sonde dapa lia Beta bekin tanda heran macam-macam, na, bosong sonde mau parcaya sang Beta!&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus told that official saying, “If you-pl don't see Me doing various amazing signs, na, you don't want to believe in Me!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then Jesus said to him,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then Jesus said to him, "Unless you see signs and wonders, you will not believe."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="49" />Itu pagawe manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Bos, tolong datang doo. Te kalo sonde, na, beta pung ana su mati ni.&gt;&gt;<bt>That official responded saying, “Bos, please come (now/first). Cuz (elaboration) if not, na, my child is dead (sense of “will surely die”).”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: The official said to him,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: The official said to him, "Sir, come down or my child will die."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="50" />Ais Yesus kasi tau sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Pulang su. Te lu pung ana tu, idop.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus told him saying, “Go on home. Cuz your-sg child is alive/lives/will live.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ju dia bale ko pulang memang, tagal dia parcaya deng Yesus pung omong tu.<bt>So he turned and returned (home) immediately, because he believed/trusted what Yesus had said.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Jesus said to him, &quot;Go"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Jesus said to him, "Go on your way. Your son is alive." The man believed what Jesus had told him, and went on his way.</Message></Annotation><v n="51" />Waktu dia pulang, dia pung orang karjá dong datang katumu sang dia di jalan bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa jang susa lai, te bapa pung ana ada idop.&gt;&gt;<bt>When/while he was returning (home), his workers came and met him on the road saying, “Father/you don't need to be troubled anymore, cuz (reason) your child is alive.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: While he was going, his"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: While he was going, his servants met him, and told him, "Your son is alive."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="52" />Ais dia tanya sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Dia mulai bae dari jam barapa?&gt;&gt;<bt>So he asked them saying, “He began to get better/well from what time?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Dong manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Mulai tenga hari kamaren jam satu, dia pung panas turun memang.&gt;&gt;<bt>They responded saying, “Beginning from mid-day yesterday at one o'clock, his fever went down straight away.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then he asked them the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then he asked them the time when he got better. And they told him, "Yesterday at one o'clock the fever left him."</Message></Annotation><v n="53" />Ais, itu pagawe inga memang bilang, dia pung ana su jadi bae, mulai dari waktu Yesus kasi tau bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa pung ana tu, idop.&gt;&gt; Ju dia, deng dia pung isi ruma samua parcaya sang Yesus.<bt>So then that official remembered/knew right away that his child had become well, beginning from when/the time Yesus said, “Your child is alive.” Then he, and all his householf (=family + servants) believed in Yesus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="oikia: 1) house, 2) family, household"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">oikia: 1) house, 2) family, household 3) property; 'family' in broad sense of "those related by blood and marriage, as well as slaves and servants, living in the same house or homestead" (LN) LITERALLY: So the father knew that was the hour when Jesus told him, "Your son lives," and he believed, and his whole household.<span class="Italic">(53)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="54" />Jadi ini ni, tanda heran nomer dua yang Yesus bekin waktu Dia kaluar dari Yudea, ko pi Galilea.<bt>So this here was the second amazing sign which Yesus did when he came out from Yudea, to go to Galilea.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: This was again the second"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: This was again the second miracle Jesus did when he had come out of Judea into Galilee.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus bekin bae satu orang lumpu di kolam Batesda<bt>The Lord Yesus heals a paralysed person in/at the pool/pond Batesda</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="5" />
      <v n="1" />Ais itu, ada satu hari bae agama Yahudi. Andia ko Yesus dong jalan pi kota Yerusalem.<bt>After that, there was a Yahudi religious feast/festival/holiday. That is why Yesus (coll.) went to the city of Yerusalem.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: After this there was a"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: After this there was a feast of the Jews, and Jesus went up to Jerusalem.</Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Di situ, ada satu kolam yang ada pung lima teras deka-deka di satu pintu, yang dia pung nama, Pintu Domba. Dalam dong pung bahasa Aram, itu kolam pung nama <span class="Italic">&lt;Batesda&gt;.</span><bt>There, there was a pool which had five porches/ pavilions/ terraces/ awnings quite near a door/gate named Sheep Door/Gate. In their Aram language, that pool's name was &lt;<span class="Italic">Batesda</span>&gt;. [Greek TEXT: TH says Bethzatha reading is “least problematic”, following GNT (but with a doubtful D reading), and this is followed by NRSV, CEV, Source; Carson and Morris favour Bethesda, followed by NIV, NLT, TB, Message; Bethsaida is weakest reading.] [NOTE to daughter translations: MTTs ask re: the meaning of ‘Betesda’. Carson says ‘House of Outpouring’, giving the Hebrew form on which the Gk is derived. TRT &amp; Morris say ‘House of Mercy’. TH ‘House of (divine) Mercy’. None of these are easily translatable to add to the footnote.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="@@ NOTE: all change in other"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">@@ NOTE: all change in other books Betesda &gt; Batesda.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Now there is at Jerusalem"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Now there is at Jerusalem by the Sheep Gate a pool, which is called 'Bethzatha' in the [Hebrew / Aramaic] language, which has five porches.</Message></Annotation><note reference="5:2" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Ada tulisan bahasa Yunani saparu tulis &lt;Betesda&gt;, saparu tulis &lt;Betsata&gt;, deng saparu lai tulis &lt;Betsaida&gt;. Pintu Domba ju ada di <span class="Italic">Nehemia</span> 3:1,32; 12:39. Kota Yerusalem ada pung banya pintu maso pi kota. Pintu laen-laen ada pung fungsi laen-laen. Dolu-dolu, dong biasa pake ini Pintu Domba ni, ko domba dong maso lewat di situ.<bt>Some Yunani language writings write ‘Betesda’, some write ‘Betsata’, and some others write ‘Betsaida’. The Sheep Gate is also in <span class="Italic">Nehemia</span> 3:1,32; 12:39. The city of Yerusalem has many doors/gates going into the city. Diffeent gates had different functions. Long ago, they normally/often used this Sheep Gate for sheep to enter via there.</bt></note><v n="3" />Ada banya orang saki yang biasa batunggu di itu teras dong. Conto ke: orang buta, orang lumpu, deng orang yang sonde bisa bagarák. [Dong ada tunggu-tunggu kapan itu aer mulai bagarák.<bt>There were many sick people who normally waited (durative) at/on those terraces. For example: blind people, paralysed people, and people who couldn't move. [They were (eagerly) waiting for when that water would begin to move.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: In these lay a big"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: In these lay a big crowd of sick people, blind, lame, paralyzed, [waiting for the moving of the water.</Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Te satu-satu kali, Tuhan pung ana bua dari sorga maso pi dalam itu aer, ko bekin aer bagarák. Ais itu, sapa yang maso lebe dolo pi dalam itu aer, na, dia yang jadi bae dari dia pung panyaki.]<bt>Cuz (elaboration) once in awhile, God2's angel/underling from heaven would enter into that water, to make the water move. After that, whoever entered the water first, na, s/he is the one who would become healed from his/her sickness.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For every now and then"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For every now and then an angel went down into the pool, and stirred up the water. Then whoever stepped in first, after the stirring up of the water, was made well from whatever disease he had.]</Message></Annotation><note reference="5:4" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Kata-kata dalam kurung ni, sonde ada dalam tulisan bahasa Yunani yang paling bae deng yang paling tua dong.<bt>The words in these parantheses do not exist in the Yunani language writings which are the best and the oldest.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Naa, di situ ada satu orang yang su saki 38 taon.<bt>Naa, [+shift from background to foreground] there, there was a person who had been sick for 38 years.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: A man was there who"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: A man was there who had been sick thirty-eight years.</Message></Annotation><v n="6" />Ju Yesus lia itu orang ada tidor di situ. Dia tau itu orang su saki dari lama, ais Dia tanya bilang, &lt;&lt;Bu, é! Mau jadi bae, ko?&gt;&gt;<bt>And Yesus saw that person laying there. He knew that person had been sick for a long time, so He asked saying, “Older brother, é! Do (you) want to be healed/become well?”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: When Jesus saw him lying"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: When Jesus saw him lying there, and knew that he had been sick a long time already, he said to him, "Do you want to get well?"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Dia manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Mau sa, Bos. Ma dia pung masala, andia: kalo aer su mulai bagarák, sonde ada orang yang koko kasi maso beta dalam aer. Kalo beta coba sandiri, na, su ada orang laen yang maso lebe dolo dari beta.&gt;&gt;<bt>He responded saying, “I sure do, Bos. But the problem is, like this: if/when the water has begun to move, there is nobody to carry (as child in arms) to put me into the water. If I try myself, na, there is already someone else who gets in ahead of me.” [EXEG: Carson points out that this Gk vocative of /kyrie/ is simply a socially appropriate greeting, and spiritual overtones should not be forced into it.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: The sick man answered, &quot;Sir,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: The sick man answered, "Sir, I don't have anyone here to put me in the pool when the water is stirred up. While I am trying to get in, somebody else gets there first."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Ju Yesus suru sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Badiri su! Gulung ame lu pung tikar, ko pulang su.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus commanded him saying, “Stand up! Roll up your mat, and go on home.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Jesus said to him, &quot;Get"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Jesus said to him, "Get up, pick up your mat, and walk."</Message></Annotation><v n="9" />Yesus omong abis bagitu, ju itu orang jadi bae memang. Ais dia bangun, angka dia pung tikar, ju mulai jalan pulang.<bt>When Yesus had finished speaking like that, that person became well immediately. So he got up, picked up his mat, and began to wolk/go home.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Itu hal pas kaná deng orang Yahudi pung hari sambayang.<bt>That matter happened on the Yahudi people's day of worship. [DISCOURSE: WHEN it happened is background, but is needed here to introduce basis for following dispute.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Immediately the man was made"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Immediately the man was made well, and picked up his mat, and walked. And that day was the sabbath.</Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Ais orang Yahudi dong pung bos-bos kasi tau sang itu orang yang baru bae bilang, &lt;&lt;Weh! Lu tau, ko sonde? Ini hari ni, hari barenti karjá. Iko kotong pung atoran agama, sonde bole ada orang angka bawa tikar, te itu dia pung nama, karjá!&gt;&gt;<bt>So/then the bosses of the Yahudi people told that person who had just been healed saying, “Weh! [+rebuke] You should really know this. (Lit: do you know, or not?) Today is the day of rest (stopping work). According to our religious regulations, nobody is allowed to carry their mat, cuz that would be categorised as work!” [NOTE: Productive RL grammatical construction: cuz that, its name, XX = this would be categorised/ named/ classified as XX] [DISCOURSE: Lu tau, ko sonde? for carrying speaker attitude.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="te itu dia pung nama, XX!"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">te itu dia pung nama, XX! karjá, disko, KKN, ini digolongkan sebagai XX, masuk dalam klasifikasi XX, this would be categorised as XX</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: So the Jewish leaders said"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: So the Jewish leaders said to the man that had been healed, "It is the Sabbath. It is not lawful for you to carry your mat."</Message></Annotation><note reference="5:10" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Nehemia 13:19, Yeremia 17:21</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Dia manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Aduu, bapa dong, é! Bapa dong jang mara. Te Orang yang bekin bae sang beta tu, yang parenta sang beta bilang, &lt;Guling lu pung tikar, ko pulang su.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>He responded saying, “Adu, fathers, é! You shouldn't be angry. Cuz (elaboration) the Person who healed me is the one who commanded me saying, ‘Roll2 up your mat, and go one home.’”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: He answered them, &quot;The man"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: He answered them, "The man who made me well told me, 'Pick up your mat and walk.'"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Ais dong tanya sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Heh! Yang suru lu angka tikar tu, sapa?&gt;&gt;<bt>So.then they asked him saying, “Hee! The one who ordered you to pick up your mat, is who?”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then they asked him, &quot;Who"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then they asked him, "Who was the man that told you, 'Pick up your mat and walk?'"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Ma itu orang yang baru bae tu, sonde kanál Yesus tu, sapa. Te Yesus su kaluar diam-diam, tagal ada banya orang di situ.<bt>But that person who had just been healed did not know who Yesus was. Cuz (elaboration) Yesus had gone out quietly/unnoticed, because there were many people there.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But the man that had"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But the man that had been healed did not know who he was; and Jesus had slipped out, there being a crowd in that place.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Sonde lama, ju Yesus nae katumu itu orang di Ruma Sambayang Pusat pung kintal. Ais Yesus kasi tau bilang, &lt;&lt;Dengar, é! Sakarang lu su bae. Jang bekin sala lai, ko biar lu jang dapa kaná hal yang lebe tar bae.&gt;&gt;<bt>Soon after that, Yesus happened to meet that person in the *Temple's yard. Then Yesus told (him) saying, “Listen, é! Now you are well. Don't do wrong/sin anymore, so that you do not (adversely) experience/get anything that is even worse.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="nae katumu = (accidentally), happened to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">nae katumu = (accidentally), happened to meet, tidak direncanakan</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Afterward Jesus found him in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Afterward Jesus found him in the temple and said to him, "Listen! You are well. Do not sin any more, so that a worse thing will not happen to you."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Ais, itu orang pi cari orang Yahudi dong pung bos-bos, ju kasi tau bilang, &lt;&lt;Yang bekin bae sang beta tu, Dia pung nama, Yesus.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then that person went to look for the Yahudi people's bosses, and told them saying, “The one who healed me, His name is Yesus.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: The man went away and"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: The man went away and told the Jewish leaders that it was Jesus who had made him well.</Message></Annotation><v n="16" />Andia ko dong mulai bekin sangsara sang Yesus, tagal Dia bekin bae orang, pas kaná di hari sambayang.<bt>That is why they began to cause trouble/suffering/torment Yesus, because He healed a person on the day of worship.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(Message -really set them off)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">(Message -really set them off)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For that reason they began"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For that reason they began to persecute Jesus, because he had done this healing on the Sabbath.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Ma Yesus kasi tau sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bagini. Beta pung Bapa sonde tau barenti karjá. Jadi Beta ju karjá jalan tarús.&gt;&gt;<bt>But Yesus told them saying, “It's like this. My Father never (=doesn't know how to) stop working. So (consequently) I also keep on working.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="GRAMMAR karjá/makan/nonton jalan tarús = keep"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">GRAMMAR karjá/makan/nonton jalan tarús = keep on XX</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But Jesus answered them, &quot;My"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But Jesus answered them, "My Father works until now, and I work."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <Annotation class="History">
      <Message author="JSW" created="2009-10-02 03:47:29Z" when="2009-10-02 03:47:29Z" stage="Draft">DONE ch. 5: HCE, NRSV, NLT, Message, Source, Carson, Morris</Message>
    </Annotation>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus mangaku diri bilang, Dia tu, Tuhan Allah pung Ana<bt>The Lord Yesus acknowledges/confesses Himself saying, He is God's Child</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Tagal orang Yahudi dong pung bos-bos su cap bilang, Yesus ada langgar dong pung atoran hari barenti karjá, andia ko dong cari jalan lebe karás ko mau bunu bekin mati sang Dia. Lebe-lebe lai, Dia ju bilang, Tuhan Allah tu, Dia pung Bapa. Deng omong bagitu, Dia angka Dia pung diri sama ke Tuhan.<bt>Because the Yahudi people's bosses had already branded/assessed/categorised/judged saying, Yesus was violating/transgressing their regulation/s of the day of rest, so that is why they were looking even harder for a way to kill Him. Even more than that, He had said that God was His Father. By speaking like that, He elevated/lifted Himself to be the same as/equal (status) with God2.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="cap = nilei"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">cap = nilei</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Therefore the Jews tried harder"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Therefore the Jews tried harder to kill him, because he not only had broken the sabbath, but he said God was his own Father, thus making himself equal to God.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Tagal bagitu, orang Yahudi dong pung"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">Tagal bagitu, orang Yahudi dong pung bos-bos cari jalan lebe karás ko mau bunu bekin mati sang Yesus. Te Dia su langgar dong pung atoran hari barenti karjá. Lebe-lebe lai, Dia ju bilang, Tuhan Allah tu, Dia pung Bapa. Deng omong bagitu, Dia angka Dia pung Diri sama ke Tuhan.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Ais Yesus kasi tau sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Batúl! Beta kasi tau memang bilang, Beta sonde bisa bekin apa-apa dari Beta pung diri sandiri. Te Beta ni, Tuhan Allah pung Ana. Andia ko Beta cuma bisa bekin iko apa yang Beta lia Bapa ada bekin. Beta lia Beta pung Bapa bekin apa, na, Beta ju bekin iko bagitu.<bt>So.then Yesus told them saying, “True! I'm telling you directly/straight out that I cannot do anything from my own self. Cuz (elaboration) I (here) am God's Child. That is why I can only do according to what I have seen Father do./I see Father doing. (Whatever) I see My Father doing, na, I also do accordingly.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: So Jesus answered them, &quot;That's"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: So Jesus answered them, "That's right! I tell you, The Son cannot do anything by himself, but only what he sees the Father doing. For whatever the Father does, these the Son does likewise.</Message></Annotation><v n="20" />Beta pung Bapa di sorga sayang mati sang Beta, andia Dia pung Ana. Dia ju kasi tunju sang Beta samua-samua yang Dia ada bekin. Nanti Dia mau kasi tunju sang Beta hal-hal yang lebe hebat lai, ko biar bosong lia, ais taheran-heran!<bt>My Father in heaven dearly loves Me, that is His Child. He also shows Me everything that He does/is doing. Later He is going to show Me things that are even more incredible, so that you-pl will see and be amazed/awed! [NOTE: added ellipted proposition “see and” from consultant input of Amarasi check. May 2014.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For the Father loves the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For the Father loves the Son, and shows him all things that he himself is doing. And he will show him greater things than these, that you may be amazed.</Message></Annotation><v n="21" />Beta pung Bapa kasi idop kambali orang mati. Bagitu ju, nanti Beta kasi idop yang batúl sang sapa sa, iko Beta pung mau.<bt>My Father brings dead people back to life. Like that also, I will give real life to whoever follows My will/desires. [EXEG: Carson, Morris.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="HCE rethink last clause; should be"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">HCE rethink last clause; should be "live for real kind" ?</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For as the Father raises"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For as the Father raises the dead and makes them alive, even so the Son makes alive those he wants to.</Message></Annotation><v n="22" />Yang batúl, bagini: Bapa sandiri sonde putus hukuman kasi sang orang. Ma Dia su sarakan samua kasi sang Beta, te Beta ni, Dia pung Ana. Ais Beta yang putus bilang, orang ada bekin yang batúl, ko sonde.<bt>The truth is like this: (My) Father himself doesn't decide/judge punishment for people. But He has turned over everything to Me, cuz (elaboration) I am His Child. So then I am the one who decides that/whether (a) person has done what is right, or not.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For the Father judges no"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For the Father judges no one, but has turned all judgment over to the Son.</Message></Annotation><v n="23" />Beta pung Bapa suka ko samua orang taro hormat sang Beta, sama ke dong ju taro hormat sang Dia. Te orang yang sonde taro hormat sang Beta, andia Dia pung Ana ni, na, dia ju sonde taro hormat sang Bapa yang su utus sang Beta.<bt>My Father likes for everyone to show respect for Me, just as they also show respect for Him. Cuz (elaboration) a person who doesn't show respect for Me, that is His Child, na, he also doesn't show respect for (My) Father who sent/commissioned Me.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: That everyone might honor the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: That everyone might honor the Son, just as they honor the Father. He who does not honor the Son, does not honor the Father who sent him.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Batúl! Beta kasi tau memang. Orang yang dengar Beta pung omong, deng parcaya sang Tuhan Allah yang utus sang Beta, na, dia su dapa idop yang batúl yang sonde tau putus-putus. Tuhan sonde hukum sang dia lai. Te itu orang sonde kaná hukuman mati lai, ma dia su maso jadi orang yang idop tarús deng Tuhan.<bt>That's right! I'm telling (you) straight. (A) person who hears what I have to say/My message, and believes in God who sent/commissioned Me, na, he has gotten real life which never ends. God2 doesn't/won't punish him any more/is no longer going to punish him. Cuz (elaboration) that person no longer experiences the death penalty/punishment of death, but s/he has already entered (into the category/affiliation) of people who live continually with God2.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="@@Te itu orang su kaluar dari"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">@@Te itu orang su kaluar dari orang yang kaná hukum tarús, ko maso jadi orang yang idop tarús deng Tuhan. // Batúl! Beta kasi tau memang. Orang yang dengar Beta pung omong, deng parcaya sang Tuhan Allah yang utus sang Beta, su dapa idop yang batúl yang sonde tau putus-putus. Tuhan sonde hukum sang dia lai. Dia ju sonde mati tatáp/tarús lai, te sakarang dia idop tarús. [Dia ju kaluar dari orang yang kaná hukum tarús/tapisa dari Tuhan, ko maso di orang yang idop tarús deng Dia.]<span class="Italic">(24)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Su kaluar dari dia pung hukuman"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">Su kaluar dari dia pung hukuman ??</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="metabebeiken: has been transferred, to change"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">metabebeiken: has been transferred, to change from one state to another, transferred from one status to another LITERALLY: "That's right! I tell you, Whoever hears my word, and believes in him who sent me, has eternal life, and will not be condemned, but has passed from death to life.<span class="Italic">(24)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="25" />Batúl! Beta kasi tau memang. Dia pung waktu su deka-deka datang, andia su mulai sakarang ni, ko orang mati dengar suara dari Beta, andia Tuhan pung Ana. Te orang yang dengar deng tarima bae Beta pung omong, nanti dia dapa idop yang batúl.<bt>That's right! I'm telling (you) straight. The time is very near, in fact it has already begun now, for dead people to hear the voice from Me, that is God2's Child. Cuz (elaboration) a/the person who hears/listens and accepts what I have to say/My message, will get/obtain real life.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: That's right! I tell you:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: That's right! I tell you: The hour is coming and has come, when the dead will hear the voice of the Son of God, and they who hear it shall live.</Message></Annotation><v n="26" />Samua idop ba'akar di Beta pung Bapa. Dia ju kasi sang Beta idop yang batúl. Te Beta ni, Dia pung Ana na.<bt>All life is rooted/sourced in My Father. He has also given Me real life. Cuz (elaboration) I am His Child [+obvious (speaker attitude)]. [EXEG: Context: from 5:18ff. “making himself equal with God”, followed by additional qualities that the Son shares with the Father; NRSV, NIV, NLT, Carson, Morris, TB all go to “life-in-himself” (setting the stage for the resurrection, cf. vs.25, 28-29). TEV, CEV, Uma, Yakan, TH go to “power to give life” which is harder to support immediately from the Gk text, both lexically and grammatically (In Gk Jesus is the recipient of “give”), although it resonates with vs.24. From the claims in the Prologue, and John's penchant for using multiple senses of words simultaneously, it is difficult to limit the first clause to just “real/true life” only.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="!@ CEV (see above)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">!@ CEV (see above)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Just as the Father has"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Just as the Father has life in himself, he has given to the Son to have life in himself.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="1. Beta pung Bapa ada kuasa"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">1. Beta pung Bapa ada kuasa ko kasi idop yang batúl sang orang. Itu kuasa ju ada di Beta, te Beta jadi Dia pung Ana, deng Dia su kasi itu kuasa sang Beta (ko kasi idop yang batúl sang orang). 2. Idop ada di Beta pung Bapa pung diri. Itu idop ju ada di Beta pung diri. Te Beta ni, Dia pung Ana na.<span class="Italic">(26)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="27" />Beta pung Bapa ju kasi hak deng kuasa sang Beta ko putus samua orang pung hukuman, tagal Beta ni, andia Manusia Tulen.<bt>My Father has also given/gives the right and power/authority to Me to decide/judge everyone's punishment, because I am the *Son of Man (Authentic/Ideal Human).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And has given him authority"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And has given him authority to carry out judgment also, because he is the Son of Man.</Message></Annotation><v n="28" />Bosong jang heran, te sadiki lai samua orang mati nanti dengar Beta pung suara.<bt>You-pl should not be surprised, cuz (elaboration) soon all the dead people will hear My voice.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Do not be surprised at"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Do not be surprised at this, because the time is coming when those that are in the tombs will hear his voice,</Message></Annotation><v n="29" />Ais dong nanti idop kambali. Ju dong kaluar dari kuburan. Orang yang dolu bekin yang bae, dapa idop yang batúl yang sonde tau putus-putus. Ma orang yang dolu bekin yang jahat, kaná hukum tarús.&gt;&gt;<bt>So/then, they will come back to life/live again. And they will come out from the graves. People who formerly did good, will get/obtain real life which never ends. But people who formerly did evil, will experience continual punishment.” [EXEG: “eternal life” Carson, Morris, NLT, TB]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: and will come forth, those"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: and will come forth, those who have done good to the resurrection of life, and/but those who have done evil to the resurrection of condemnation.</Message></Annotation><note reference="5:29" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Daniel 12:2</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Ada banya saksi yang kasi tau so'al Tuhan Yesus<bt>There are many witnesses that tell about the Lord Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="30" />Yesus omong tamba bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta sonde bisa bekin apa-apa, kalo Beta balóm dengar dari Beta pung Bapa. Kalo Beta su dengar abis, baru Beta putus orang pung parkara. Tagal itu, apa yang Beta putus tu, batúl. Te Beta sonde coba iko Beta pung mau sandiri sa, ma iko Beta pung Bapa pung mau. Ko Dia yang utus sang Beta na!<bt>Yesus continued speaking saying, “I cannot do anything, if I have not yet heard from My Father. If/when I have already heard/finished listening/heard everything, only then will I decide a person's case. Because of that, what I decide is true/correct. Cuz (elaboration) I do not try to follow My own will/desire, but follow My Father's will/desire. Cuz He is the one who sent/commissioned Me [+emphatic]! [EXEG: NLT]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: I can do nothing by"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: I can do nothing by myself. As I hear, I judge, and my judgment is just/right, because I do not try to do my own will, but the will of my Father who sent me.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Yesus omong tamba, bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta sandiri"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">Yesus omong tamba, bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta sandiri sonde bisa bekin apa-apa. Ais, kalo Beta putus orang pung parkara, bilang, dong yang bekin bae, ko (dong yang bekin) jahat, itu tagal Beta ada (ba'omong/konsultasi? NLT) dengar Beta pung Bapa pung omong (kasi sang Beta). Andia ko Beta putus yang/deng batúl/adil. Te Beta sonde coba iko Beta pung mau sa, ma iko Beta pung Bapa pung mau. Ko Dia yang utus sang Beta na!</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="31" />Kalo cuma Beta sandiri yang kasi tau so'al Beta pung diri sa, na, Beta pung omong tu, sonde sah.<bt>If only I myself am the one to tell/explain about My self, na, what I have to say/My message is not valid/legal.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: If I testify about myself,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: If I testify about myself, my testimony is not valid.</Message></Annotation><v n="32" />Ma ada orang laen yang jadi saksi so'al Beta. Deng Beta tau dong omong yang batúl so'al Beta.<bt>But there is another person who is a witness about Me. And I know they speak the truth about Me. [EXEG: OT principle--2-3 witnesses; vs.31 I about myself, vs.32 more than just me; vs.33 John TS; vs. 36a God the Father; vs.36b the works that I do; vs.38 God's Word; so even though the Gk is singular in vs. 32, it sets up a series of witnesses “in addition to Yesus”]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: There is another who testifies"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: There is another who testifies about me, and I know that [his testimony/what is testified] about me is true.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Deng Beta tau dia pung omong"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">Deng Beta tau dia pung omong tu, batúl.</Message></Annotation><v n="33" />Bosong parná utus orang ko pi tanya sang Yohanis tukang sarani. Ju dia omong yang batúl so'al Beta.<bt>You-pl have sent/commissioned people to go ask Yohanis the Habitual Baptiser. And he spoke what is true about Me.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="memartureiken: speak well of, testified, witnessed"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">memartureiken: speak well of, testified, witnessed LITERALLY: You sent [messengers] to John, and he has testified the truth.<span class="Italic">(33)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="5:33" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yohanis 1:19-27, 3:27-30</note><v n="34" />Padahal Beta sonde parlú manusia pung rekomendasi. Ma Beta kasi inga ini hal dong, ko bosong bisa dapa salamat dari bosong pung sala-sala.<bt>In fact, I don't need a recommendation from humans [alludes to a formal/legal affirmation]. But I remind (you) of these things, so that you can be/obtain saved from your *wrongs/sins. [NOTE to daughter translations: if /rekomendasi/ is problematic, try /omong yg bae so'al Beta/.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: I do not need testimony"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: I do not need testimony from people, but I say these things that you may be saved.</Message></Annotation><v n="35" />Yohanis pung omong tu, sama ke satu lampu yang manyala taráng. Waktu dia pung taráng masi manyala, bosong pung hati sanáng.<bt>Yohanis' message was like a like that shines brightly. When his light was still burning/shining, your livers were happy.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: He [John] was a burning"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: He [John] was a burning and shining light. You were willing for a while to enjoy his light.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="36" />Padahal ada Orang yang lebe hebat dari Yohanis yang omong yang batúl so'al Beta. Andia Beta pung Bapa di sorga yang su sarakan banya tugas sang Beta, ko Beta kasi jalan sampe abis. Ini tugas dong ni yang kasi tunju bukti bilang, Bapa yang ada utus sang Beta.<bt>But in fact there is a Person who is greater/more incredible that Yohanis who speaks the truth about Me. That is, My Father in heaven who has turned over much work/handed over many responsibilities to Me, so that I will carry them out until completed. These tasks/responsibilities (that I carry out) are what show proof/evidence that Father is the one who sent/commissioned Me. [EXEG: Carson (totality of Christ's work), NLT “my teachings &amp; my miracles”.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="erga: works, deeds (plural, not singular"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">erga: works, deeds (plural, not singular as in NIV) LITERALLY: But I have a greater witness than John. For the deeds which the Father gave me to finish, those things that I do, they testify about me, that the Father has sent me.<span class="Italic">(36)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="37" />Deng Dia yang utus sang Beta, omong yang batúl so'al Beta ju. Naa, bosong sandiri balóm parná dengar langsung Dia pung suara, ko, lia langsung Dia pung rupa.<bt>And He who sent/commissioned Me, also speaks the truth about Me. Naa, you-pl yourselves have never heard His voice directly, or directly seen His form/shape/face. [NOTE: a different word is ‘face’ only, this one is broader]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And the Father himself who"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And the Father himself who sent me has testified about me. You have never heard his voice, or seen his form.</Message></Annotation><note reference="5:37" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 3:17, Markus 1:11, Lukas 3:22</note><v n="38" />Tuhan pung Kata-kata sonde idop di bosong pung hati, tagal bosong sonde parcaya sang Beta, yang Dia utus.<bt>God2's Words/Message does not live in your livers, because you don't believe in Me, whom He sent/commissioned.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And you do not have"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And you do not have his word staying in you, because you do not believe the one he sent.</Message></Annotation><v n="39" />Bosong suka pareksa sampe alus-alus Tuhan pung Tulisan Barisi, tagal bosong pikir di situ nanti bosong katumu jalan ko dapa idop yang batúl yang sonde tau putus-putus. Padahal itu Tulisan dong tu, ada kasi tau so'al Beta.<bt>You like to carefully examine in detail the *Scriptures (God2's Clean/Holy/Pure Writings, because you think that there you will find/encounter/meet the way to get/obtain real life which does not end. In fact, those Writings tell about Me.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: You search the Scriptures, because"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: You search the Scriptures, because you think you have eternal life in them, and they are the ones that testify about me.</Message></Annotation><v n="40" />Ma bosong sonde mau datang di Beta, ais maso jadi Beta pung orang, ko biar bosong bisa dapa itu idop yang batúl yang sonde tau putus-putus.<bt>But you don't want to come to Me, and so enter to become My person, so that you can get/obtain that real life that never ends.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But you will not come"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But you will not come to me that you can have life.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="41" />Beta sonde parlú ko orang angka-angka sang Beta.<bt>I don't need for people to elevate/honour Me. [EXEG: Gk: glory here]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: I do not accept glory/praise/honor/approval"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: I do not accept glory/praise/honor/approval from people.</Message></Annotation><v n="42" />Ma Beta tau parsís bosong pung dalam hati. Andia ko Beta tau bilang, bosong sonde ada pung kasi-sayang sang Tuhan Allah.<bt>But I precisely/exactly know your inner hearts/livers. That is why I know that you have no love for God (at all--fairly strong).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But I know you, that"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But I know you, that you do not have the love of God in you/among you.</Message></Annotation><v n="43" />Beta datang di ini dunya, tagal Beta pung Bapa yang pegang kuasa ada utus sang Beta datang. Ma bosong sonde tarima sang Beta. Padahal kalo ada orang laen yang datang pake dia pung kuasa sandiri, bosong tarima bae sang dia.<bt>I came to this world, because My Father who holds power/authority was sending/commissioning Me to come. But you did not accept Me. Whereas, if there was another person who came useing his own authority, you would accept/receive him well/nicely.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: I have come in my"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: I have come in my Father's name [authority], and you do not receive me. If another comes in his own name [by his own authority], you will receive him.</Message></Annotation><v n="44" />Bosong satu deng satu suka makan puji. Ma bosong sonde toe kalo Tuhan Allah ada puji sang bosong, ko sonde. Padahal Dia tu, Tuhan! Sonde ada yang laen lai. Jadi, kalo bosong sonde toe sang Dia, karmana ko bosong bisa parcaya sang Dia?<bt>You like to eat each other's praise. But you don't care if God is praising you, or not. In fact/keep in mind, He is God2! There is no other. So (consequently), if you don't care about Him, how could you believe in Him? [EXEG: Gk: glory here 2x]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="@@NLT &quot;from God alone&quot; incorrect here;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">@@NLT "from God alone" incorrect here; should be "from the only God"</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: How can you believe, who"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: How can you believe, who receive glory/honor/praise/approval from each other, but do not seek the honor that comes from the only God?</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="45" />Jang pikir bilang, Beta yang lempar sala sang bosong di Beta pung Bapa pung muka. Sonde. Yang lempar sala sang bosong tu, andia ba'i Musa. Padahal bosong ada baharap sang dia, tagal dia yang kasi bosong Tuhan pung Atoran.<bt>Don't think that I am the one blaming/accusing you in front of My Father. No. The one who is accusing you, is grandfather Musa. Whereas in fact, you-pl are hoping in him, because he is the one who gave (you) God2's Regulations/Law.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Do not think that I"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Do not think that I will accuse you to the Father. The one who accuses you is Moses, in whom you have hoped.</Message></Annotation><v n="46" />Naa, kalo bosong parcaya batúl sang Musa, tantu bosong ju parcaya sang Beta. Te dia ada tulis so'al Beta.<bt>Naa, if you really/truly believed in Musa, surely you would also believe in Me. Cuz (elaboration) he wrote about Me.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For if you believed Moses,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For if you believed Moses, you would have believed me, because he wrote about me.</Message></Annotation><v n="47" />Ma tagal bosong sonde parcaya batúl sang apa yang dia tulis, karmana ko bosong mau parcaya apa yang Beta omong? Sonde mungkin, to!&gt;&gt;<bt>But because you don't really/truly believe in what he wrote, how could you/are you going to believe what I say/My message? That's not likely, right?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But since you do not"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But since you do not believe what he wrote, how will you believe what I say?</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus kasi makan lima ribu orang lebe<bt>The Lord Yesus feeds more that five thousand people</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 14:13-21; Markus 6:30-44; Lukas 9:10-17)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="6" />
      <v n="1-4" />Ais itu, orang Yahudi pung hari bae &lt;Paska&gt; su deka-deka. Ju Yesus dong pi dano Galilea pung sablá. (Itu dano pung nama laen, andia, &lt;dano Tiberias&gt;.) Banya orang iko sang Dia pi sana, tagal dong lia tanda-tanda heran yang Dia su bekin waktu Dia bekin bae orang saki dong. Sampe di dano pung sablá, ju Yesus deng Dia pung ana bua dong nae pi satu gunung kici. Ais dong dudu di situ.<bt>After that, the Yahudi people's festival/feast/holiday ‘Paska’ was nearing. And Yesus (coll.) went to the other side of lake Galilea. (That lake's other name, is ‘lake Tiberias’.) Manay people followed Him there, because they saw the various amazing signs which He had done when He healed sick people. Arriving at the other side of the lake, Yesus and His disciples went up a small mountain. Then they sat there. [DISCOURSE: Time frame moved forward for RL background-foreground patterns.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Restructure loses &quot;after these things&quot; ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">Restructure loses "after these things" ;</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="vague time reference LITERALLY: After these"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">vague time reference LITERALLY: After these things, Jesus went over Lake Galilee, which is Tiberias.<span class="Italic">(1) </span>LITERALLY: A large crowd followed him, because they saw the miracles/signs which he did for those who were sick. LITERALLY: Jesus went up on a hill, and there he sat with his disciples. And the Passover, a feast of the Jews, was near.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Waktu Yesus lia ada banya orang datang bakumpul, ju Dia tanya sang Dia pung ana bua satu, nama Filipus bilang, &lt;&lt;Kotong bisa béli makan di mana, ko kasi makan ini orang dong?&gt;&gt;<bt>When Yesus saw there were many people coming gathering (together), He asked one of His disciples, named Filipus saying, “Where can we-inc buy food to feed these people?”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: When Jesus looked up, and"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: When Jesus looked up, and saw that a large crowd had come, he said to Philip, "Where can we buy bread/food that these people may eat?"</Message></Annotation><v n="6" />Memang Yesus su tau Dia mau bekin karmana. Ma Dia omong bagitu ko mau tes sang Filipus.<bt>Yesus really already knew what He was going to do. But He spoke like that to test Filipus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tes = tes barang di toko"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">tes = tes barang di toko ko mau lia dia bae, ko sonde ; coba = Mus feels has negative overtones ; uji = can be for positive purposes</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: He said this to test"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: He said this to test Philip, because he himself knew what he would do.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ko coba lia Filipus mau bekin"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">ko coba lia Filipus mau bekin karmana.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Ju Filipus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Awe'! Biar satu tukang ada karjá dua ratus hari ju, ma dia pung gaji masi sonde cukup ko béli roti kasi sang dong samua! Biar tiap orang dapa roti sadiki ana ju, itu sonde akan cukup!&gt;&gt;<bt>And Filipus responded saying, “Awe'! [+dismay, annoyance] Even if a craftsman whorked for 200 days, nevertheless his wages/payment would still not be enough to buy bread for all those people! Even for each person to get a little bit of bread, it would not be enough!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="!@ CEV says &quot;take almost a"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">!@ CEV says "take almost a year's wages just to buy only a little bread for each of these people" which is different from "not enough to buy even a little"</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Philip answered him, &quot;Two hundred"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Philip answered him, "Two hundred denarii/days' wages worth of bread would not be enough for each one to have a little."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Ais Yesus pung ana bua satu lai, nama Anderias, andia Simon Petrus pung adi, kasi tau sang Yesus bilang,<bt>Then another one of Yesus' disciples, named Anderias, that is Simon Petrus' younger brother, told Yesus saying,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: One of the disciples, Andrew,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: One of the disciples, Andrew, Simon Peter's brother, said to him,</Message></Annotation><v n="9" />&lt;&lt;Bapa! Ada satu ana di sini yang bawa roti lima bua, deng ikan dua ekor. Ma sonde mungkin itu cukup ko kasi makan orang bagini banya!&gt;&gt;<bt>“Father! There is one child/underling here who brought five loaves (lit: fruit), and two fish. But it's likely/probably not enough to feed this many people!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: &quot;There is a boy here"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: "There is a boy here who has five small loaves of barley bread and two small fish. But what is that among so many?"</Message></Annotation><note reference="6:9" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Tulisan bahasa Yunani asli tulis bilang, dong bekin ini roti dari <span class="Italic">krithinos</span>. Alkitab bahasa Indonesia tulis bilang, &lt;jelai&gt;. Dia pung biji amper sama deng jagong rote.<bt>The original Yunani language writings write saying, they made this bread from <span class="Italic">krithinos</span>. The Indonesian language Bible writes it is &lt;jelai&gt;. It's seeds are very similar to ‘Rote corn’ (a barley/sorghum type of grain).</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Di situ ada banya rumput. Ais Yesus suru Dia pung ana bua dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Ator ko dong samua dudu.&gt;&gt; Ju dong dudu. Itu waktu, orang pung banya lai! Yang laki-laki sa, kira-kira ada lima ribu orang.<bt>There, there was a lot of grass. So Yesus ordered His disciples saying, “Arrange for them to all sit down.” And they sat. At that time, there were a lot of people! [idiomatic = huge number] Just the men numbered around five thousand.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Jesus said, &quot;Make the people"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Jesus said, "Make the people sit down." Now, there was a lot of grass there. So the men sat down, numbered about five thousand.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Ais Yesus ame itu roti dong, ju Dia minta tarima kasi sang Tuhan. Tarús Dia bagi kasi Dia pung ana bua dong. Ju dong pi babagi kasi itu orang banya. Dia bekin yang sama deng itu ikan ju. Samua makan sampe kinyang.<bt>Then Yesus took that bread (pl), and He gave thanks to God. Then He divided it out to His disciples. Then they went and divided it out to the crowds. He did the same with those fish. Everyone ate until full. [EXEG: Gk is “he divided...”, but in 10 and 12 he has the disciples doing the work. So we have it indirect.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Jesus took the loaves, and"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Jesus took the loaves, and when he had given thanks, he gave them to the disciples, and the disciples gave them to the ones sitting down. Likewise the fish. And they had as much as they wanted.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Waktu samua su makan sampe kinyang, ju Yesus suru Dia pung ana bua dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Kumpul ame itu makanan sisa dong, ko jang ada yang tabuang parcuma.&gt;&gt;<bt>When everyone had eaten until full, Yesus ordered His disciples saying, “Gather up the leftover food, so there is nothing wasted needlessly.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: When they were full, he"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: When they were full, he said to his disciples, "Gather up what is left, so that nothing be wasted."</Message></Annotation><v n="13" />Ais dong kumpul ame itu makanan sisa dong dari itu roti lima bua, sampe isi ponu di 12 bakul.<bt>So they gathered up the leftover food from those five loaves of bread, to the point that they filled full 12 baskets.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: So they gathered up the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: So they gathered up the remains, and filled twelve baskets with the pieces of the barley loaves that were left.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Waktu orang banya dong su lia tanda heran yang Yesus bekin tu, dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Awii! Dia ni, pasti itu Jubir yang Tuhan su janji mau kirim datang.&gt;&gt;<bt>When the crowds saw the amazing sign that Yesus had done, they said, “Awii! [+amazement] He here, is surely that *Spokesperson that God2 promised to send coming/here.” [DISCOURSE: “into the world” made implicit.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then those people, seeing the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then those people, seeing the miracle/sign that Jesus did, said, "This is truly the Prophet that is coming into the world."</Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Yesus tau bilang, itu orang banya dong mau paksa sang Dia ko jadi raja. Ais Dia bangun jalan, ju Dia nae lebe jao lai di satu gunung kici, ko biar Dia bisa sandiri di situ.<bt>Yesus knew that the crowds wanted to force Him to become king. So/then He got up and left, and went further up on a small mountain, so that He could be alone there.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: When Jesus knew that they"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: When Jesus knew that they were coming to take him by force to make him king, he left and went up to a hill again, by himself.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus jalan di atas aer<bt>The Lord Yesus walks on water</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 14:22-33; Markus 6:45-52)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Waktu matahari baru tanggalám, Yesus pung ana bua dong jalan turun pi dano.<bt>When the sun had just set/drowned, Yesus' disciples walked/went down to the lake.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="opsia: evening; after sunset, before dark"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">opsia: evening; after sunset, before dark LITERALLY: When evening came, his disciples went down to the lake.<span class="Italic">(16)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="17" />Yesus balóm datang bagabung deng dong. Ju dong nae pi satu parahu, ais mulai badayong pi kota Kapernaum, di dano pung sablá. Waktu dong mulai badayong tu, hari su galáp.<bt>Yesus had not yet come to join with them. Then they got into a boat, and began to paddle to/toward the city of Kapernaum, on the other side of the lake. When they began to paddle/go, it was already dark. [DISCOURSE (foreground-background): OV last clause moved to beginning of verse at consultant's suggestion. Amarasi check: May 2014.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: They got into a boat,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: They got into a boat, and started across the lake to Capernaum. By then it was already dark, and Jesus had not yet joined them.</Message></Annotation><v n="18" />Ju aer dano mulai bagalombang pi-datang, tagal angin ribut ada fuu barmaen.<bt>Then the water of the lake began be wavy in all directions, because a strong wind kept blowing (erratically).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: The lake was being stirred"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: The lake was being stirred up, because a strong wind was blowing.</Message></Annotation><v n="19" />Waktu Yesus pung ana bua dong su badayong kira-kira lima kilo, ju dong dapa lia Dia ada jalan di atas aer. Dia datang deka-deka di dong pung parahu, ju dong taku mau mati.<bt>When Yesus' disciples had paddled/gone about five kilometers, they saw/happened to see Him walking on the water. He came very close to their boat, and they were terrified/very afraid.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: So when they had rowed"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: So when they had rowed 25 or 30 furlongs ([3 or 4 miles; 4.6-5.5km), they saw Jesus walking on the lake, and coming near the boat, and they were afraid.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Ma Yesus kasi tau bilang, &lt;&lt;We! Jang taku! Te ini Beta ni.&gt;&gt;<bt>But Yesus told (them) saying, “We! Don't be afraid! It's Me here.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But he said to them,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But he said to them, "It is I. Do not be afraid".</Message></Annotation><v n="21" />Tagal itu, dong su sonde taku lai. Ju dong mau-mau ko Dia nae parahu sama-sama deng dong. Sonde sangka-sangka, te itu parahu su sampe di dong pung tujuan.<bt>Because of that, they weren't afraid anymore. And they intensely wanted him to get into the boat with them. Without being aware of it/Unnoticed, the boat had arrived at their destination.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Paksa pung paksa = keep insisting"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">Paksa pung paksa = keep insisting</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="oun: therefore, consequently, so then LITERALLY:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">oun: therefore, consequently, so then LITERALLY: Therefore/then they willingly let him into the boat, and immediately the boat arrived at the place they were headed.<span class="Italic">(21)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Orang dong ada cari-cari sang Tuhan Yesus<bt>People kept looking for the Lord Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22-24" />Dia pung beso, itu orang banya dong masi ada di dano pung sablá. Dong ada deka-deka deng itu tampa yang Yesus minta tarima kasi sang Tuhan Allah, ais kasi makan sang dong. Ju dong dapa tau bilang, kamaren cuma ada satu parahu di situ sa. Ma Yesus pung ana bua dong su pake itu parahu ko jalan kasi tenga itu tampa. Deng Yesus sandiri sonde nae itu parahu ko pi sama-sama deng Dia pung ana bua dong.<bt>The next day, the crowds were still on the other side of the lake. They were near the place where Yesus had given thanks to God, and then fed them. They found out/came to realise that yesterday/the previous day there had only been one boat at that place. But Yesus' disciples had already used that boat to leave that place. And Yesus himself had not gotten into that boat to go together with His disciples.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: The next day, when the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: The next day, when the people who stood on the other side of the lake realized that there was no other boat there except the one his disciples had been in, and that Jesus had not gone with his disciples in the boat, but that his disciples had gone away alone, LITERALLY: Although other boats from Tiberias had come near the place where they had eaten the bread, after the Lord had given thanks,<span class="Italic">(22)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ma ada barapa parahu laen dari kota Tiberias yang pi-datang di itu tampa. Ais waktu itu orang banya dapa tau bilang, Yesus deng Dia pung ana bua su sonde ada di situ lai, ju dong nae itu parahu laen dong, ko pi cari sang Yesus di Kapernaum, di itu dano pung sablá.<bt>But there were several other boats from the city of Tiberias who often came to that place. So then when the crowds found out/came to understand that Yesus and His disciples were no longer there, they got into those other boats, to go look for Yesus in Kapernaum, on the other side of the lake.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: When the people therefore saw"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: When the people therefore saw that Jesus was not there, nor his disciples, they also got in the boats, and came to Capernaum, looking for Jesus.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus sama ke Roti yang bawa idop<bt>The Lord Yesus is like Bread which brings life</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Ais dong katumu sang Yesus di dano pung sablá. Ju dong tanya sang Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa Guru! Bapa sampe di sini, dari kapan?&gt;&gt;<bt>So/then they found/met Yesus on the other side of the lake. And they asked Him saying, “Father Teacher! When did you arrive here?”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: When they found him on"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: When they found him on the other side of the lake, they asked him, "Teacher, when did you come here?"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="26" />Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Yang batúl, bagini: bosong sonde cari sang Beta tagal bosong su lia tanda-tanda heran. Ma bosong cari sang Beta, tagal Beta kasi makan sang bosong, sampe bosong kinyang.<bt>Yesus responded saying, “In truth, it's like this: you-pl are not looking for Me because you have seen various amazing signs. But you look for Me, because I fed you, to the point that you got full.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Jesus told them, &quot;I tell"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Jesus told them, "I tell you the truth. You are looking for me, not because you saw miracles/signs, but because you ate the bread and got filled up.</Message></Annotation><v n="27" />Dengar bae-bae! Jang cuma karjá ko dapa makanan yang nanti jadi busuk buang. Ada lebe bae bosong karjá ko dapa makanan yang batahan tarús, yang bawa idop yang batúl yang sonde tau putus-putus. Te Beta ni, andia Manusia Tulen. Beta yang bisa kasi itu idop sang bosong. Te Bapa di sorga su sarakan itu hak sang Beta na.&gt;&gt;<bt>Listen carefully! Don't just work to get food which will rot away. It would be better to work to get food which keeps/perseveres on, which brings real life that doesn't stop. Cuz (elaboration) I am the *Son of Man. I am the one who can give you that life. Cuz (elaboration) Father in heaven has given/turned over that right to Me.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Do not work for food"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Do not work for food that spoils, but for food that lasts for eternal life; which the Son of Man will give you. Because he is the one on whom God the Father has put his seal of approval."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Ju dong tanya bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo bagitu, na, botong musti bekin karmana, ko biar botong bisa kasi jalan Tuhan pung karjá?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then they asked saying, “If that's the case, na, what must we-exc do so that we can carry out God's work?”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then they said to him,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then they said to him, "What shall we do, that we might do the work of God?"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="29" />Yesus kasi tau bilang, &lt;&lt;Tuhan pung karjá tu, bagini: bosong musti parcaya sang Beta. Te Tuhan Allah tu, yang utus sang Beta.&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus told them saying, “God2's work is like this: you must believe in Me. Cuz (elaboration) God is the one who sent/commissioned Me.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Jesus said to them, &quot;This"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Jesus said to them, "This is the work of God, that you believe on him whom he has sent."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="30" />Ais dong tanya lai bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa mau kasi tunju tanda heran karmana, ko botong bisa lia deng parcaya sang Bapa? Tarús Bapa mau bekin apa kasi botong lai?<bt>Then they asked again saying, “What amazing sign are You going to show, so we can see it, and believe in You? And/Furthermore, what else are You going to do for us? [EXEG: NLT]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Therefore they said to him,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Therefore they said to him, "What sign do you show us that we may see and believe you? What will you do?</Message></Annotation><v n="31" />Conto ke, kotong pung nene-moyang dong makan roti <span class="Italic">manna</span> di tampa sunyi. Itu jadi sama ke ada tatulis di Tuhan pung Tulisan Barisi bilang, &lt;Dia kasi sang dong roti yang turun dari langit, ko dong makan.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>For example, our-inc ancestors ate the <span class="Italic">manna</span> bread in the empty place. That is like what is written in the *Scriptures saying, ‘He gave them bread which came down from the sky/heaven, for them to eat.’”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Our fathers ate manna in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Our fathers ate manna in the desert. As it is written, 'He gave them bread from heaven to eat.'"</Message></Annotation><note reference="6:31" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 16:4, 15, Lagu Puji dong 78:24</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="32" />Yesus bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta kasi tau yang batúl, bagini: dolu, bukan ba'i Musa yang kasi turun itu roti dari langit sang bosong pung nene-moyang dong. Te yang kasi turun tu, Beta pung Bapa di sorga. Sakarang Dia ju ada sadia kasi sang bosong roti dari langit. Ma ini roti ni, Roti yang batúl yang batahan tarús.<bt>Yesus said, “I tell (you) what is true, like this: formerly/long ago, it was not grandfather Musa who sent down that bread from the sky to your ancestors. Cuz (elaboration) the one who sent it down, was My Father in heaven. Now He is also prepared to give you-pl bread from the sky/heaven. But this bread (that I'm talking about), is the true/real Bread that keeps/perseveres on. [EXEG: NLT, Carson; NOTE to daughter translations: “true bread” should somehow link to vs. 27 “food that lasts for eternal life”.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then Jesus said to them,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then Jesus said to them, "I tell you the truth, Moses did not give you the bread from heaven, but my Father gives you the real bread from heaven.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Sakarang Dia ju ada sadia kasi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">Sakarang Dia ju ada sadia kasi sang bosong roti yang batúl yang batahan tarús. Itu roti tu, turun dari langit ju.</Message></Annotation><v n="33" />Te ini Roti dari Tuhan ni, andia, Yang turun dari sorga deng bawa idop kasi orang di ini dunya.&gt;&gt;<bt>Cuz (elaboration) this Bread from God2 is the One who descends/comes down from heaven and brings life to people in this world.” [NOTE to daughter translations: if the “yang” construction is difficult in other lgs, try “Dia yang”.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For the bread of God"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For the bread of God is the one who comes down from heaven and gives life to the world."</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Te itu Roti yang dari Tuhan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">Te itu Roti yang dari Tuhan tu, andia Beta, yang turun dari sorga. Beta ni, yang bawa idop kasi orang di ini dunya.&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="34" />Ais dong minta bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa! Na, kasi itu roti tarús sang botong doo!&gt;&gt;<bt>So/then they requested saying, “Bapa! Na, keep giving that bread to us!” [+mild imperative]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: They asked him, &quot;Sir, give"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: They asked him, "Sir, give us this bread from now on."</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ais dong minta, bilang, &lt;&lt;Bos! Na,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">Ais dong minta, bilang, &lt;&lt;Bos! Na, kasi itu roti tarús sang botong do!&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="35" />Ju Yesus kasi tau sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta ni, andia itu Roti. Te Beta yang bawa idop yang batúl. Jadi orang yang maso jadi Beta pung orang, sonde akan lapar lai! Deng orang yang parcaya sang Beta, sonde akan aus lai!<bt>Then Yesus told/explained to them saying, “I am that Bread. Cuz (elaboration) I am the one who brings real life. So (consequently) people who enter (affiliation) becoming My people, will not be hungry again! And people who believe in Me, will not be thirsty again!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Jesus said to them, &quot;I"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Jesus said to them, "I am the bread of life. He who comes to me will never get hungry, and he who believes in me will never get thirsty.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="36" />Ma Beta parná kasi tau sang bosong bilang, biar bosong su lia sang Beta, ma bosong masi sonde parcaya sang Beta ju.<bt>But I have told you that even though you have seen Me, nevertheless you still don't believe in Me (either).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But I told you that"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But I told you that you have seen me, and not believed.</Message></Annotation><v n="37" />Padahal samua orang yang Beta pung Bapa su pili ko jadi Beta pung orang dong, nanti dong datang di Beta. Deng kalo ada orang datang di Beta, sonde mungkin Beta mau usir buang sang dia!<bt>Whereas, everyone whom My Father has chosen to be/become My people, they will come to Me. And if/when a person comes to Me, it is not likely/probably that I will evict/kick him out! [+understatement]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: All that the Father gives"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: All that the Father gives me shall come to me, and he who comes to me I will never throw out.</Message></Annotation><v n="38" />Te Beta turun datang dari langit. Beta datang ko bekin iko Beta pung Bapa pung mau, te Dia yang utus sang Beta na. Beta sonde mau cuma bekin iko Beta pung mau sandiri sa.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) I came down from the sky/heaven. I came to do according to My Father's will/desires, cuz (elaboration) He is the one who sent/commissioned Me. [+obvious] I don't just want to do My own will.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For I came down from"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For I came down from heaven, not to do my own will, but the will of the one who sent me.</Message></Annotation><v n="39" />Deng Dia pung mau, bagini: dari samua orang yang Dia su pili ko jadi Beta pung orang dong, Dia mau ko Beta kumpul ame sang dong samua. Beta sonde bole kasi biar satu ju yang ilang. Ma nanti di hari kiamat, Beta musti kasi dong idop kambali.<bt>And His will is like this: from all the people whom He has chosen to become My people, He wants Me to gather/ collect all of them. I am not allowed/ permitted to let one of them disappear/be lost. But later at the end of the world, I must make them live again/ come back to life. [EXEG: NLT, Carson, Morris; NOTE: the vague Gk. phrase “raise up at the last day” occurs in vs. 39, 40, 44, 54. So there needs to be cohesion. MEANING: NRSV “raise up”, NLT “raise from dead”, CEV “raise to life”, HCE “bring back to life”; Carlton (TRT) “raise from the dead”; Carson “This preservation of each individual in the collective of the elect includes resurrection at the last day. ... in clear references to the final resurrection (vv. 39, 40, 44, 54), ... All of this explanation is part of the bread of life discourse. These verses not only contribute to the explanation as to why some believe and some do not, but, culminating in the promise of eternal, resurrection life,...” Morris “a future resurrection.... It is unthinkable that death should blot out forever the life that Christ gives. Because he is what he is, he will assuredly raise up those to whom he gives life.” Compare with similar phrasing “resurrection at the last day” in 11:24. LEX: it doesn't seem the Gk word can support the sense of “take up to heaven”--which is a possible reading of the English. (In Gk the object changes position or state, but not location). Theological PROBLEM: what about those who are not dead, i.e. 1 Thess. 4:14-17? But should views on theology be driving the translation? Or should the text? The translation principles we subscribe to say we have to be guided by the text. Apparently John is not addressing that issue here.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="anasteisw: will raise up, cause to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">anasteisw: will raise up, cause to stand up, raise to life, raise to adulthood, erect a building, rise up against (rebel) LITERALLY: And this is the Father's will, who sent me, that of all those whom he has given me, I should lose none of them, but raise them up at the last day.<span class="Italic">(39)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="40" />Sama ke Beta bilang tadi, Beta pung Bapa mau ko samua orang yang kanál deng parcaya sang Beta, andia Dia pung Ana ni, na, dong bisa dapa idop yang batúl yang sonde tau putus-putus. Ais nanti di hari kiamat, Beta kasi idop kambali sang dong.&gt;&gt;<bt>It's like I said earlier, My Father wants for everyone who knows and believes in Me, that is His Child (here), na, they can get/obtain real life that never ends. Then later at the end of the world, I will bring them back to life/make them live again.” [EXEG: “who sent me” made implicit as in NLT to reduce heavy information load. It's in vs.38.; on “raise up at the last day” see note at 6:39.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And this is the will"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And this is the will of him that sent me, that everyone who sees the Son, and believes in him, may have eternal life, and I will raise him up at the last day."</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="samua orang yang kanál sang Beta,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">samua orang yang kanál sang Beta, andia Dia pung Ana tu, deng parcaya sang Beta, na, dong bisa dapa idop yang batúl yang sonde tau putus-putus. Sama ke Beta bilang tadi, Beta pung Bapa, andia yang utus sang Beta tu, Dia pung mau, bagini: samua orang yang kanál deng parcaya sang Beta, andia Dia pung Ana ni, na, dong bisa dapa idop yang batúl yang sonde tau putus-putus. Ais nanti di hari kiamat, Beta kasi dong idop kambali.&gt;&gt;<span class="Italic">(40)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="41" />Naa, orang Yahudi pung bos-bos mulai mangomel sang Dia, tagal Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Itu Roti dari Tuhan tu, andia Beta, yang turun dari sorga.&gt;&gt;<bt>Naa, [shift] the Yahudi people's bosses began to grumble/complain to Him, because He said, “That Bread from God2 is Me, who came down from heaven.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Therefore the Jews started to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Therefore the Jews started to grumble at him, because he said, "I am the bread which came down from heaven."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="42" />Dong ba'omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Su karmana ni? Ini Orang ni, andia Yesus, bapa Yusuf pung ana, to? Botong kanál Dia pung mama-bapa dong. Jadi karmana ko sakarang Dia bilang, &lt;Beta turun datang dari sorga&gt;? Dapa dari mana?&gt;&gt;<bt>They talked (reciprocally) saying, “How is this? This Person here, is Yesus, father Yusuf's child, right? We-exc know His mother-father (coll.). So (consequently) how is it that now He says, ‘I came down from heaven’? Where does He get that?”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: They said, &quot;Isn't this Jesus,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: They said, "Isn't this Jesus, the son of Joseph, whose father and mother we know? How is it that he now says, 'I came down from heaven'?"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="43" />Yesus suru sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Weh! Barenti mangomel di situ, é!<bt>Yesus ordered them saying, “Weh! Stop that grumbling there, é!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: So Jesus said to them,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: So Jesus said to them, "Stop grumbling among yourselves!</Message></Annotation><v n="44" />Beta pung Bapa di sorga yang utus sang Beta datang di sini. Sonde ada orang yang bisa datang di Beta, kalo Beta pung Bapa sonde antar bawa sang dia. Ais nanti di hari kiamat, Beta kasi idop kambali sang dong.<bt>My Father in heaven is the one who sent/ commissioned Me to come here. Nobody can come to Me, if My Father does not bring/ escort him. So later at the end of the world, I will bring them back to life. [EXEG: NLT; on “raise up at the last day” see note at 6:39.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="anasteisw: will raise up, cause to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">anasteisw: will raise up, cause to stand up, raise to life, raise to adulthood, erect a building, rise up against (rebel) LITERALLY: Nobody can come to me unless the Father who sent me draws him to me. And I will raise him up at the last day.<span class="Italic">(44)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="45" />Tuhan pung jubir dolu-dolu dong parná tulis bilang, &lt;Tuhan Allah mau ajar sang samua orang.&gt; Naa, samua orang yang dengar sang Bapa di sorga, deng balajar dari Dia, dong datang di Beta ko jadi Beta pung orang.<bt>God2's spokespeople long ago once wrote saying, ‘God want to teach everyone.’ Naa, everyone who listens to/obeys Father in heaven, and learns from Him, they come to Me to become My people.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: It is written in the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: It is written in the Prophets, 'They will all be taught by God.' Everyone who has listened and learned from the Father, comes to me.</Message></Annotation><note reference="6:45" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 54:13</note><v n="46" />Beta ni, yang turun datang dari Tuhan Allah. Jadi cuma Beta sa yang parná lia sang Dia. Sonde ada satu orang laen ju yang parná lia langsung sang Bapa di sorga.<bt>I here and the one who came down from God. So (consequently), I am the only one who has ever seen Him. There is not a single other person who has ever seen Father in heaven directly.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Nobody has seen the Father"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Nobody has seen the Father except the one who is from God. He has seen the Father.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Cuma Beta sandiri sa, yang turun"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">Cuma Beta sandiri sa, yang turun datang dari Tuhan Allah, yang parná lia sang Dia.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="47" />Batúl! Beta ju kasi tau memang sang bosong! Orang yang parcaya sang Beta, nanti dapa idop yang batúl yang sonde tau putus-putus.<bt>That's right! I'm telling you straight! The person/whoever believes in Me, will get real life that never ends.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: That's right! And I tell"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: That's right! And I tell you: The one who believes has eternal life.</Message></Annotation><v n="48" />Te Beta ni, andia Roti yang bawa itu idop tu.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) I am the Bread that brings that life (that I've been talking about).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: I am the bread of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: I am the bread of life.</Message></Annotation><v n="49" />Dolu bosong pung nene-moyang dong makan roti <span class="Italic">manna</span> waktu bajalan kuliling di tampa sunyi. Biar dong makan itu roti, ma lama-lama dong mati ju.<bt>Formerly/long ago, your ancestors ate <span class="Italic">manna</span> bread while the walked around in the empty place. Even though they ate that bread, nevertheless eventually they also died.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kuliling ~ kaliling"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">kuliling ~ kaliling</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Your fathers ate manna in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Your fathers ate manna in the wilderness, and they died.</Message></Annotation><v n="50" />Ma Roti yang turun dari sorga sakarang ni, laen. Te samua orang bole makan. Dia pung arti bilang, samua orang yang parcaya sang Beta tu, dong sonde tapisa buang dari Tuhan Allah lai.<bt>But the Bread which comes down from heaven now is different. Cuz (elaboration) everyone is allowed to eat it. That means that everyone who believes in Me, they will not be separated off/cut off from God anymore. [EXEG: HCE]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="UNS rasa ancor"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">UNS rasa ancor</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: This is the bread that"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: This is the bread that comes down from heaven, which anyone can eat, and not die.</Message></Annotation><v n="51" />Te Beta ni, andia Roti yang bawa idop, yang turun datang dari sorga. Ais nanti kalo Beta mati, Beta sarakan Beta pung badan ko samua orang di ini dunya bisa idop. Ju orang yang makan dari itu Roti, dong tu dapa idop yang batúl yang sonde tau putus-putus.&gt;&gt;<bt>Cuz (elaboration) I am the Bread that brings life, that comes down from heaven. So then later when I die, I turn over/surrender My body so that everyone in this world can live. And people who eats from that Bread, they are the ones who will get/obtain real life that never ends.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: I am the living bread"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: I am the living bread that came down from heaven. If anyone eats this bread, he will live forever. The bread which I will give is my flesh/body, which I will give for the life of the world.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Te Beta ni, sama ke roti"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">Te Beta ni, sama ke roti yang batúl. Beta yang turun (datang) dari sorga. Deng Beta yang bisa kasi orang idop yang batúl yang sonde putus-putus. Nanti kalo Beta mati, Beta sarakan Beta pung badan ko jadi (sama ke/itu) roti. Beta sarakan Beta pung diri bagitu, ko samua orang di ini dunya bisa idop. Ju orang yang makan dari itu roti/Beta, kasi orang idop yang batúl yang sonde putus-putus.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="52" />Dengar bagitu, ju orang Yahudi pung bos-bos mulai bakanjar satu deng satu bilang, &lt;&lt;Awe'! Dia omong apa tu? Karmana ko ini Orang bisa kasi Dia pung badan ko kotong makan?&gt;&gt;<bt>Hearing that, the Yahudi people's bosses began to argue with each other saying, “Awe'! [+dismay, annoyance, frustration] What's He saying/talking about? How can this Person give His body for us-inc to eat?”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then the Jews began to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then the Jews began to argue sharply among themselves. They said, "How can this man give us his body to eat?"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="53" />Ju Yesus kasi tau sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta omong yang batúl. Deng Beta kasi tau bagini: Beta ni, Manusia Tulen. Orang yang mau idop yang batúl, musti ta'ika deng Beta. Jadi, kalo bosong sonde makan Beta pung badan, deng sonde minum Beta pung dara, na, sonde ada idop yang batúl di bosong.<bt>And Yesus told/explained to them saying, “I'm telling the truth. And I tell (you) this: I am the *Son of Man (Authentic/Ideal Human). The person who wants real life must be bound/linked to Me. So (consequently) if you-pl do not eat My body, and do not drink My blood, na, there is no real life in you. [EXEG for ftn: Carson notes that there are significant problems with interpreting this as primarily a reference to the Eucharist, and favours vs.53-54 as a metaphorical repetition of vs. 40, where it is “see and believe”; Morris agrees it is not primarily about the Eucharist but about belief and relationship. “Eating and drinking Christ’s flesh and blood thus appears to be a very graphic way of saying that people must take Christ into their innermost being. ... a challenge to enter the closest and most intimate relation with him.”]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="!@ CEV seems to be undertranslated/weak"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">!@ CEV seems to be undertranslated/weak here ;</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Jesus said to them, &quot;That's"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Jesus said to them, "That's right! And I tell you this: Unless you eat the flesh of the Son of Man, and drink his blood, you do not have any life in you.</Message></Annotation><note reference="6:53-54" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Waktu Yesus omong so'al makan Dia pung badan, deng minum Dia pung dara, na, Dia pung maksud bilang, orang musti parcaya sang Dia, deng idop ta'ika deng Dia tarús. Banding deng <span class="Italic">Yohanis</span> 6:40.<bt>When Yesus spoke about eating His body, and drinking His blood, na, He meant that people must believe in Him and live bound/linked with Him continually. Compare with <span class="Italic">Yohanis</span> 6:40.</bt></note><v n="54" />Te orang yang makan Beta pung badan, deng minum Beta pung dara, su dapa idop yang batúl yang sonde tau putus-putus. Ais nanti di hari kiamat, ju Beta kasi idop kambali sang dia.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) the person who eats My body, and drinks My blood, has already gotten/obtained real life that never ends. So later at the end of the world, I will bring him back to life. [EXEG: on “raise up at the last day” see note at 6:39.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Whoever eats my body and"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Whoever eats my body and drinks my blood has eternal life, and I will raise him up at the last day.</Message></Annotation><v n="55" />Te makanan yang batúl, andia Beta pung badan. Deng minuman yang batúl, andia Beta pung dara.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) the real food is My body. and the real drink is My blood.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For my body is real"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For my body is real food, and my blood is real drink.</Message></Annotation><v n="56" />Jadi orang yang makan Beta pung badan, deng minum Beta pung dara tu, ada idop ta'ika deng Beta. Deng Beta ju ta'ika deng dia.<bt>So (consequently) the person who eats My body, and drinks My blood, is living bound/linked to Me, And I am also bound/linked with him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: The one who eats my"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: The one who eats my body and drinks my blood stays/remains in me and I in him.</Message></Annotation><v n="57" />Bapa di sorga yang utus sang Beta tu, Dia idop batúl-batúl. Deng Beta ju dapa idop yang batúl dari Dia. Andia ko orang yang makan Beta pung badan, dia ju nanti dapa idop yang batúl dari Beta.<bt>Father in heaven who sent/commissioned Me, He really lives/is alive. And I also get/obtain real life from Him. That's why the person who eats My body, he will also later get real life from Me.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: As the living Father has"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: As the living Father has sent me, and I live because of the Father, so he that eats me, he will live because of me.</Message></Annotation><v n="58" />Naa, dolu bosong pung nene-moyang makan itu roti <span class="Italic">manna</span> yang turun dari langit. Biar dong makan itu roti, ma lama-lama dong mati ju. Ma Roti yang turun dari sorga sakarang ni, laen. Te orang yang makan ini Roti ni, nanti dapa idop yang batúl.&gt;&gt;<bt>Naa, formerly/long ago, your ancestors ate that <span class="Italic">manna</span> bread which came down from heaven. Even though they ate that bread, nevertheless eventually they also died. But the Bread that comes down from heaven now, is different. Cuz (elaboration) the person who eats this Bread will get real life.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: This is the bread that"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: This is the bread that came down from heaven, not as your fathers ate manna, and died. The one who eats of this bread will live."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="59" />Yesus ajar ini hal dong dalam orang Yahudi pung ruma sambayang satu di kota Kapernaum.<bt>Yesus taught this issue/matter in a Yahudi people's house of worship in the city of Kapernaum.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: He said these things in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: He said these things in the synagogue, as he taught in Capernaum.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Banya orang ondor diri dari Tuhan Yesus<bt>Many people retreat/withdraw from the Lord Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="60" />Naa, ada banya orang yang iko sang Yesus. Ma waktu dong dengar Dia ajar bagitu, ju ada yang omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Dia pung ajaran tu, barát, é! Sapa yang bisa tarima itu ajaran?&gt;&gt;<bt>Naa, [discourse shift] there were many people who followed Yesus. But when they heard Him teach like that, there were those that spoke saying, “That teaching of His is heavy, é! Who can accept that teaching?” [EXEG: (Carson, Morris, Carlton) not hard to understand, but hard to accept, offended their sensibilities [also NRSV, NLT, NIV] See also context of vs.61-66.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Therefore, many of his disciples,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Therefore, many of his disciples, when they heard that, they said, "This is a hard teaching. Who can understand it?"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="61" />Ma Yesus dapa tau dong ada bamangomel bagitu, ju Dia tanya bilang, &lt;&lt;Ini ajaran bekin bosong susa, ko?<bt>But Yesus found out/came to know they were grumbling (among themselves) like that, so He asked saying, “Does this teaching cause difficulty for you-pl?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Jesus was aware that his"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Jesus was aware that his disciples were grumbling at this, and he said, "Does this offend you?</Message></Annotation><v n="62" />Karmana lai kalo nanti bosong lia Beta, Manusia Tulen ni, nae kambali pi sana, di Beta pung tampa dolu?<bt>How about if/when you see Me, the Son of Man, ascend back up there, in My former place?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: What if you see the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: What if you see the Son of Man ascend up where he was before?</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="63" />Tuhan pung Roh yang bawa idop yang batúl. Bukan orang pung badan yang bisa bawa itu idop yang batúl. Ma Beta pung Kata-kata dong ba'akar dari Tuhan pung Roh. Jadi itu Kata-kata ju ada bawa idop yang batúl kasi orang dong.<bt>God2's Spirit is the one that brings real life. It is not a person's body that can bring life. But My Words/Message are rooted in God's Spirit. So (consequently) those Words/Message also bring real life to people.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: &quot;It is the Spirit that"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: "It is the Spirit that gives life. The body does not profit at all. The words that I speak to you, they are Spirit and they are life.</Message></Annotation><v n="64" />Ma ada bosong saparu yang sonde parcaya sang Beta.&gt;&gt;<bt>But there are some of you who don't believe in Me.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Yesus omong bagitu, tagal Dia su tau dari mula-mula sapa yang sonde parcaya, deng sapa yang nanti jual buang sang Dia.<bt>Yesus spoke like that, because He already knew from the beginning who it was that didn't believe, and who it was that would later sell Him off (=betray Him).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But there are some of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But there are some of you that do not believe." Because Jesus knew from the beginning who the ones were that did not believe, and who would betray him.</Message></Annotation><v n="65" />Ju Dia omong tamba bilang, &lt;&lt;Andia ko Beta su kasi tau sang bosong bilang, Beta pung Bapa di sorga musti buka jalan kasi orang dolo, baru itu orang bisa maso jadi Beta pung orang.&gt;&gt;<bt>And He spoke further saying, “That is why I have told you that, My Father in heaven must open the way for people first, only then can that person enter becoming My person.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And he said, &quot;This is"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And he said, "This is why I said to you that no one can come to me unless the Father enables him."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="66" />Mulai itu waktu, ju ada banya dari Dia pung ana bua dong ondor diri dari Dia, te dong sonde mau iko sang Dia lai.<bt>Beginning from that time, there were many of His disciples who pulled back/retreated from Him, cuz (elaboration) they didn't want to follow Him anymore.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: From that time on many"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: From that time on many of his disciples went back, and did not follow him any more.</Message></Annotation><v n="67" />Ais Yesus tanya sang Dia pung ana bua dua blas orang tu bilang, &lt;&lt;Ais bosong karmana? Mau ondor diri dari Beta ju, ko?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus asked his twelve disciples saying, “How about you-pl? Do you also want to retreat from Me?”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then Jesus said to the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then Jesus said to the twelve, "Will you also go away?"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="68" />Ma Simon Petrus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Bos! Botong mau pi di sapa lai? Sonde ada orang laen lai yang bisa kasi tau sang botong, karmana ko botong bisa dapa itu idop yang batúl yang sonde tau putus-putus. Cuma Bos sandiri sa!<bt>But Simon Petrus responded saying, “Bos! Who else would we go to? There is nobody else who can tell/explain to us-exc, how we can get/obtain that real life that never ends. Only You!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then Simon Peter answered him,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then Simon Peter answered him, "Lord, to whom will we go? You have the words/message of eternal life.</Message></Annotation><v n="69" />Deng botong parcaya sang Bos. Te botong su tau bilang, Bos ni, andia Tuhan Allah pung Orang Barisi tu.&gt;&gt;<bt>And we believe in You. Cuz (elaboration) we know that You here are God's Holy/Clean/Pure Person [+known information].”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And we believe and know"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And we believe and know that you are the Holy One from God."</Message></Annotation><note reference="6:68-69" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 16:16, Markus 8:29, Lukas 9:20</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="70" />Yesus kasi tau sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta su pili ame bosong dua blas orang. Ma inga, é! Ada satu dari bosong yang ke setan!&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus told them saying, “I have chosen the twelve of you. But remember, é! There is one of you who is like an evil spirit!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Jesus answered them, &quot;Haven't I"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Jesus answered them, "Haven't I chosen you twelve? Yet one of you is a devil!"</Message></Annotation><v n="71" />Yang Dia maksud tu, Yudas, andia Simon Iskariot pung ana. Yudas tu, satu dari Dia pung ana bua dua blas orang. Dia tu, yang nanti jual buang sang Yesus.<bt>The one He was meaning was Yudas, that is Simon Iskariot's child. That Yudas was one of His twelve disciples. He is the one who would later sell of Yesus (=betray).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: He spoke about Judas, the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: He spoke about Judas, the son of Simon Iscariot, one of the twelve, because it was he who would later betray him.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus deng Dia pung adi-adi dong<bt>The Lord Yesus and His younger siblings</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="7" />
      <v n="1" />Ais itu, ju Yesus dong jalan kuliling di propinsi Galilea. Dia sonde mau pi jalan kuliling di propinsi Yudea, tagal ada orang Yahudi pung bos-bos di sana yang mau bunu bekin mati sang Dia.<bt>After that, Yesus (coll.) walked/went around the province of Galilea. He didn't want to go around in the province of Yudea, because there were bosses of the Yahudi people there who wanted to kill Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: After that, Jesus went around"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: After that, Jesus went around in Galilee. He did not want to go around in Judea, because the Jewish leaders wanted to kill him.</Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Itu waktu, orang Yahudi pung pesta panen yang dong subu bilang, &lt;&lt;Pesta Teng&gt;&gt;, su deka-deka.<bt>At that time, the Yahudi people's harvest festival that they referred to saying, “Canopy Festival” was very near.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="@@Marge suggests info about feasts should"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">@@Marge suggests info about feasts should eventually go into glossary. Otherwise they consume huge amounts of space and need to be repeated in various places. People aren't necessarily going to read the first occurrence (although this is the only occurrence in the NT)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="in Genesis, sukot = &quot;shade places&quot;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">in Genesis, sukot = "shade places" LITERALLY: The Jewish feast of [Tabernacles / Shelters] was near.<span class="Italic">(2)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dalam bahasa Yunani, andia |iskeinopeigia|r. Bahasa"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">dalam bahasa Yunani, andia <span class="Italic">skeinopeigia</span>. Bahasa Ibrani bilang, <span class="Italic">sukot</span>. Dua-dua</Message></Annotation><note reference="7:2" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">&lt;Pesta Teng&gt; tu, jalan sampe 8 hari. Itu pesta paling rame. Waktu itu pesta panen masi jalan, orang Isra'el tenga tahan di bawa teng yang dong bangun di dong pung ruma. Itu teng kasi inga sang dong bilang, dolu dong pung nene-moyang ju ada tenga di bawa teng, waktu dong ada jalan kuliling di tampa sunyi. Itu teng ju sama ke teng yang orang kasi badiri dalam kabón waktu musim panen. Baca di <span class="Italic">Kaluar dari Masir</span> 23:16; <span class="Italic">Kapala Agama dong pung Atoran</span> 23:33-36, 39-43; <span class="Italic">Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop</span> 16:13-15; <span class="Italic">Sakaria</span> 14:16-19.<bt>[Adapted from Carlton TRT] The &lt;Canopy Festival’ ran for 8 days. That festival was very festive. While that harvest festival was going, the people of Israél lived temporarily under canopies which they erected at their houses. Those canopies reminded them that long ago their ancestors had also lived under canopies when they were going around in the empty place. That canopy was also like the canopies people erected in their fields during the harvest season. Read about it in <span class="Italic">Going out from Egypt</span> 23:16; <span class="Italic">Regulations of the Priests</span> 23:33-36, 39-43; <span class="Italic">Retelling about the Life Way</span> 16:13-15; <span class="Italic">Sakaria</span> 14:16-19.</bt></note><v n="3" />Ais Yesus pung adi-adi suru sang Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Lebe bae, Bu angka kaki dari sini, ko jalan pi Yudea. Ko biar orang yang iko sang Bu di sana ju bisa dapa lia hal-hal yang Bu ada bekin.<bt>Then Yesus' younger siblings ordered/told Him saying, “It would be better if Older Brother gets out of here, to go to Yudea. So that the people who follow You there can also be able to see the various things that You are doing.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then his brothers told him,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then his brothers told him, "Leave here and go into Judea, so your disciples can see the deeds you are doing.</Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Te kalo satu orang mau ko banya orang lia dia pung hebat, na, dia jang bekin deng sambunyi-sambunyi. Tagal Bu ada bekin tanda heran macam-macam, ada lebe bae lai, kalo samua orang bisa dapa lia apa yang Bu ada bekin!&gt;&gt;<bt>Cuz (elaboration) if a person wants many people to see his greatness, na, he shouldn't do it in secret. Because You are doing various sorts of amazing signs, it would be even better, if everyone could be able to see those things You are doing!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Because nobody does things in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Because nobody does things in secret if he wants to be known openly. Since you are doing these things, show yourself to the world."</Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Dia pung adi-adi dong omong bagitu, tagal dong sandiri sonde talalu parcaya deng Dia.<bt>His younger siblings spoke like that, because they themselves didn't have much confidence/trust in Him. [EXEG: episteuon: here ‘trust, reliance, have confidence in’; (LN, Carson) they did not understand the significance of what they saw, nor his real identity, so they didn't trust/have confidence in him to do what made sense on their terms.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="episteuon: here 'trust, reliance, have confidence"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">episteuon: here 'trust, reliance, have confidence in'; (LN, Carson) they did not understand the significance of what they saw, nor his real identity, so they didn't trust/have confidence in him to do what made sense on their terms LITERALLY: Because not even his brothers believed in him.<span class="Italic">(5)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Ju Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Bagini. Sakarang Beta pung waktu balóm sampe. Ma kalo bosong mau pi, na, kapan-kapan ju bisa.<bt>And Yesus responded saying, “It's like this. At this time, My time has not yet arrived. But if you-pl want to go, na, you can go whenever.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Jesus said to them, &quot;It"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Jesus said to them, "It is not time for me to go yet. You can go any time.</Message></Annotation><v n="7" />Orang di ini dunya dong sonde binci sang bosong. Ma dong binci mati sang Beta, tagal Beta buka ko kasi tunju abis dong pung bekin-bekin tu. Te dong pung hati jahat.<bt>People in this world don't hate you. But they really hate Me, because I expose and show all the things that they are doing (reduplication implies not everything is above board). Cuz (elaboration) their livers are evil.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: The world cannot hate you,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: The world cannot hate you, but it hates me, because I testify about the things they do, that they are evil.</Message></Annotation><v n="8" />Kotong pung hari bae agama tu, su deka-deka datang. Biar bosong sa yang nae pi Yerusalem dolo. Beta balóm mau pi, te dia pung waktu balóm pas.&gt;&gt;<bt>Our-inc religious holiday is very near. Just let it be you-pl who go up to Yerusalem now. I don't want to go yet, cuz (elaboration) the time is not yet right.” [TEXT: see Carson for discussion of variants in Gk text between ‘not’ and ‘not yet’.] [NOTE to daughter translations: The translation of this verse needs to be faithful, but also not clash horribly with vs.10, where he “changes” his mind and goes anyway.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: You go up to the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: You go up to the feast. I am not going [yet] to this feast, because it is not the right time yet."</Message></Annotation><v n="9" />Dia omong abis bagitu, ju Dia tenga di propinsi Galilea sa.<bt>When He finished speaking, He just stayed on in the province of Galilea.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: After he said these things,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: After he said these things, he stayed in Galilee.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus iko hari bae agama Yahudi<bt>The Lord Yesus participates in a/the Yahudi religious festival</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Ma waktu Dia pung adi-adi dong su barangkat ko pi iko orang Yahudi pung hari bae di Yerusalem, Yesus ju iko pi. Ma Dia pi sambunyi-sambunyi, ko biar orang sonde tau.<bt>But when His younger siblings had left to go participate in the Yahudi people's holiday/festival in Yerusalem, Yesus also followed (later). But he went secretly, so that people wouldn't know.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But after his brothers went"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But after his brothers went to the feast, then he also went, not openly, but in secret.</Message></Annotation><v n="11" />Di Yerusalem, waktu hari bae, orang Yahudi pung bos-bos ada cari-cari sang Dia. Dong batanya bilang, &lt;&lt;Itu Orang ada di mana, é?&gt;&gt;<bt>In Yeruslaem, during the festival, the Yahudi people's bosses kept looking for Him. They were asking each other saying, “Where is that Person, é?”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then the Jews looked for"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then the Jews looked for him at the feast. They said, "Where is that one?"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Banya orang ada bakusu-kusu so'al Dia. Saparu bilang, &lt;&lt;Dia tu, orang bae.&gt;&gt;<bt>Many people were whispering (to each other) about Him. Some said, “He is a good person.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Saparu lai bilang, &lt;&lt;Sonde! Dia tu, tukang putar-balek yang suka tipu orang banya dong.&gt;&gt;<bt>Some others said, “No! He is a habitual liar who likes to/often deceives many people/the crowd.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: There was a lot of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: There was a lot of whispering about him in the crowd. Some said, "He is a good man." Others said, "No, he deceives the crowd."</Message></Annotation><v n="13" />Ma sonde ada yang barani omong taráng-taráng so'al Yesus, tagal dong taku deng itu bos-bos dong.<bt>But there was nobody who dared talk openly/clearly/plainly about Yesus, because they were afraid of those bosses.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But no one talked openly"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But no one talked openly about him, because they were afraid of the Jewish leaders.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Pas di teng-tenga itu hari bae, ju Yesus maso pi dalam Ruma Sambayang Pusat. Ais Dia mulai mangajar di situ.<bt>Right in the middle of that festival (time), Yesus went into the Temple. And He began to teach there.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: The feast was already half"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: The feast was already half way through when Jesus went up to the Temple to teach.</Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Ju orang Yahudi dong pung bos-bos heran bilang, &lt;&lt;Ini Orang sonde parná balajar banya sama ke kotong. Ma akurang ko Dia tau banya hal bagini?&gt;&gt;<bt>The Yahudi people's bosses were surprised/amazed saying, “This Person has never studied/learned much like we-inc have. But how is it that He knows so many things like this?” [EXEG: LN, Carson, NLT]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: The Jewish leaders were amazed,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: The Jewish leaders were amazed, and they said, "How does this man know so much when he has never been trained?"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Ju Yesus kasi tau sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Dengar, é. Hal-hal yang Beta ajar dong, bukan dari Beta sandiri, ma dari Dia yang utus sang Beta.<bt>Yesus told them saying, “Listen, é! The things/matters that I teach, are not from Me myself, but from Him who sent/commissioned Me.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Jesus answered them, &quot;My teaching"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Jesus answered them, "My teaching is not my own, but is from him who sent me.</Message></Annotation><v n="17" />Orang yang batúl-batúl mau bekin iko Tuhan Allah pung mau, dia nanti dapa tau, Beta pung ajaran dong tu, batúl-batúl datang dari Tuhan, ko, cuma datang dari Beta sandiri sa.<bt>A person who really wants to do according to God's will/desires, he will be able to know/come to know, (if) My teaching really comes from God2, or only comes from Me myself.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="thelei: purpose to, resolve, (earnestly) desires"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">thelei: purpose to, resolve, (earnestly) desires LITERALLY: If anyone wants to do what God wants, he will know about the teaching, whether it is from God, or if I speak on my own authority.<span class="Italic">(17)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="18" />Te orang yang cuma omong pake dia pung kuasa sandiri, dia cuma mau cari nama sa. Ma orang yang mau angka nama bae dari orang yang utus sang dia tu, pasti omong jujur. Deng dia sonde ada pung putar-balek.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) a person who only speaks using his own power/authority, s/he is only just trying to make a name for himself. But a person who wants to elevate/promote the good name/reputation of the person who sent/commissioned him, is surely speaking the truth. And he has no deceit/distortion. [EXEG: Gk: glory here]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: The one who speaks on"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: The one who speaks on his own authority is trying to get glory for himself. But the one who tries to get glory for the one who sent him, that one is true/honest, and there is nothing false in him.</Message></Annotation><v n="19" />Ba'i Musa su kasi Tuhan pung Atoran dong sang bosong. Ma bosong sonde bekin iko. Jadi akurang ko bosong ada cari-cari jalan ko mau bunu bekin mati sang Beta?&gt;&gt;<bt>Gf/Ff Musa already gave God2's Regulations/Law to you-pl. But you don't do accordingly/obey. So (consequently) why is it that you keep trying to find a way to kill Me?”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Moses gave you the law,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Moses gave you the law, but none of you do what it says. So why are you trying to kill me?"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Ais orang banya dong tanya bilang, &lt;&lt;Lu omong apa, ni? Mangkali lu ada takaná setan, ko? Sapa yang ada cari jalan ko mau bunu sang lu?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then many people asked saying, “What are you-sg talking about here? It seems/probably you have been possessed/affected by an *evil spirit, right? Who is loking for a way to kill you?”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: The crowd said, &quot;You have"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: The crowd said, "You have a demon! Who is trying to kill you?"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Ju Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Bagini. Beta baru bekin satu tanda heran di hari sambayang sa, ma bosong samua su kakodok.<bt>And Yesus responded saying, “It's like this. I just did one *amazing sign on a day of worship, but [contrary to expectation] you are all annoyed/upset (lit: constricted). [EXEG: NLT, CEV-note; higher-level context; NRSV “astonished”, CEV “amazed”, NLT “offended”, both LN &amp; BAGD say of Gk word “whether the reaction is favorable or unfavorable depends on the context”; Carson “astonishment-not the astonishment that leads to praise”; Carlton (TRT) “negative connotations ... surprised/ shocked/ upset”.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Jesus answered them, &quot;I did"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Jesus answered them, "I did one miracle, and you were all amazed.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ma bosong samua su taheran-heran."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">ma bosong samua su taheran-heran.</Message></Annotation><v n="22" />Ma satu-satu kali, bosong ju karjá di hari sambayang, ke bagini: ba'i Musa su kasi turun sunat pung atoran bilang, kalo orang barana ame ana laki-laki, na, dia pung dalapan hari, bosong musti sunat sang itu ana. Biar lai itu hari tu, pas kaná deng hari sambayang, bosong musti sunat sang dia. (Ma iko yang batúl, itu atoran lebe tua dari ba'i Musa. Te Tuhan Allah su kasi itu atoran lebe dolo kasi sang ba'i Abraham.)<bt>But every once in awhile you-pl also work on the day of worship in this way: Gf/Ff Musa has handed down the *regulation of *circumcision saying, if a person gives birth to a son, na, on his day eight, you must circumcise that child. Even if that day falls on a day of worship, you must circumcise him. (But in actual fact/truth, that regulation is older than Gf/Ff Musa. Cuz (elaboration) God had already given that regulation before that to Gf/Ff Abraham.) [EXEG: NLT]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Because Moses gave you circumcision--even"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Because Moses gave you circumcision--even though it was not Moses, but your ancestors--you circumcise your sons on the Sabbath.</Message></Annotation><note reference="7:22" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 17:10, Kapala Agama dong pung Atoran 12:3</note><v n="23" />Jadi, kalo sunat satu ana pas di hari sambayang sa sonde langgar Musa pung atoran, na, akurang ko bosong mara sang Beta tagal Beta bekin bae orang lumpu pas di hari sambayang? Sonde maso akal, to!?<bt>So (consequently) if circumcising a child on the day of worship itself does not violate/transgress Musa's regulation, na, why is it that you-pl are angry with Me because I healed a paralysed person on the day of worship? It doesn't make sense, right!?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: If circumcision can be received"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: If circumcision can be received by a person on the Sabbath, so that the law of Moses may not be broken, are you angry at me because I have made a man well on the Sabbath?</Message></Annotation><note reference="7:23" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yohanis 5:9</note><v n="24" />Jang nilei orang gara-gara hal-hal yang bosong cuma bisa lia deng bosong pung mata sa. Pikir panjang ko timbang samua-samua deng bae-bae dolo, ais baru bosong putus yang batúl.&gt;&gt;<bt>Don't evaluate/judge people on account of things/matters/issues that you-pl can only see with your eyes. Thing long (idiom=think through the implications &amp; issues) to weigh/evaluate everything carefully first, and only then decide what is right.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="!@ NLT undertranslated here"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">!@ NLT undertranslated here</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Do not judge by external"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Do not judge by external standards, but judge by true standards."</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Jang lempar sala gara-gara hal-hal yang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">Jang lempar sala gara-gara hal-hal yang bosong cuma bisa lia deng bosong pung mata sa. Kalo mau jadi ke hakim yang putus deng batúl, na, pikir panjang ko timbang samua-samua deng batúl.&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus tu, andia Kristus, ko?<bt>Is the Lord Yesus, the Kristus?</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Ais itu, ada barapa orang dari kota Yerusalem batanya bilang, &lt;&lt;Ini Orang ni, yang dong ada cari-cari ko mau bunu, ko?<bt>After that, there were several people from the city of Yerusalem who were asking (each other) saying, “This Person here, isn't He the one they keep looking for to kill?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then some people from Jerusalem"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then some people from Jerusalem said, "Isn't this the one they are trying to kill?</Message></Annotation><v n="26" />We, hebat, ó! Te Dia ada omong taráng-taráng di orang banya pung muka. Ma sonde ada yang suru ko Dia paróp Dia pung mulu. Iko bosong, karmana? Kira-kira yang pegang kuasa dong su tau, ko sonde, bilang, ini Orang ni, andia Kristus yang Tuhan su janji memang ko mau kirim datang, ko?<bt>We, that's amazing, ó! Cuz (elaboration) He is speaking openly in front of lots of people. But nobody is ordering Him to shut His mouth. According to you-pl, how is it? Do you think perhaps that those in authority already know, or not, that this Person is Kristus, whom God promised to send, or (what)? [EXEG: Are they praising or criticising him here? Morris clearly falls on side of praise; HCE]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But look! He talks openly,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But look! He talks openly, and nobody says anything to him. Do the rulers really know that this is the Christ?</Message></Annotation><v n="27" />Ma dia pung masala, bagini: nanti, kalo Tuhan kirim datang sang Kristus, sonde ada orang yang tau Dia dari mana. Ma botong su tau ini Orang dari mana.&gt;&gt;<bt>But there's a problem, like this: later, if/when God2 sends Kristus coming, nobody knows where He is from. But we-exc already know where this Person is from.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But we know where this"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But we know where this one came from. When Christ comes, nobody will know where he is from.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Itu waktu, Yesus masi ajar orang di Ruma Sambayang Pusat pung kintal. Waktu dengar itu orang dong omong bagitu, ju Dia tanya sang dong pake suara karás bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong pikir kata, bosong kanál sang Beta, deng tau parsís Beta datang dari mana, ko? Beta ni, sonde datang di sini iko Beta pung mau sandiri. Te yang utus sang Beta tu, batúl-batúl ada. Deng bosong sonde kanál sang Dia.<bt>At that time, Yesus was still teaching people in the Temple's yard. When [He] heard people talking like that, He asked them using a loud voice saying, “You-pl think that you know Me, and you know exactly where I come from, right? I did not come here according to My own desires/will. Cuz (elaboration) that one who sent Me, really is/exists. And you don't know/recognise Him. [EXEG: ‘real’ (Carson) he really is the one who sent Jesus; the Jews would not doubt that God is real; =the one who sent me really exists. EXEG: although “the one who sent me” is a common way that John uses to refer to God, translating that as “God” here would destroy the coherence of the veiled reference in this passage.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Jang mara, ma... carries speaker attitude,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">Jang mara, ma... carries speaker attitude, picking up on suara karás.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then Jesus said in a"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then Jesus said in a loud voice in the temple, where he was teaching, "Do you know me, and you know where I come from? I did not come on my own authority. The One who sent me is real/true/sincere, and you do not know him.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Padahal, Beta sonde datang di sini"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">Padahal, Beta sonde datang di sini</Message></Annotation><v n="29" />Ma Beta kanál sang Dia, te Beta datang dari Dia, deng Dia yang utus sang Beta.&gt;&gt;<bt>But I know Him, cuz (elaboration) I came from Him, and He is the one who sent/commissioned Me.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: I know him, because I"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: I know him, because I come from him, and he sent me."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="30" />Ais ju dong coba tangkap sang Dia. Ma sonde ada yang bisa pegang ame sang Dia, te Dia pung waktu balóm pas.<bt>Then they tried to catch/arrest Him. But there was nobody who was able to grab Him (successfully), cuz (elaboration) His time was not yet right.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then they tried to seize"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then they tried to seize him. But no one laid a hand on him, because his time had not come yet.</Message></Annotation><v n="31" />Dari itu orang banya di situ dong, ada banya ju yang parcaya sang Dia. Dong ba'omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Ini Orang su bekin banya tanda heran. Ais nanti, kalo Kristus datang, sonde mungkin Dia bekin lebe dari ini Orang, to?&gt;&gt;<bt>From/Among those many people there, there were also many who believed in Him. They spoke with each other saying, “This Person has done/made many amazing signs. So later, if/when Kristus comes, it's not likely/probably that He will do more than this Person, right?”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: From the crowd, many believed"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: From the crowd, many believed in him. They said, "Whenever the Christ comes, will he do more signs than this one does?"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Dong suru orang pi tangkap sang Tuhan Yesus<bt>They (non-referential) order people to go catch/arrest the Lord Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="32" />Di itu orang banya pung teng-tenga, ada barapa orang dari partei agama Farisi ju. Dong dapa dengar orang banya ada bakusu-kusu itu hal dong so'al Yesus. Ais dong, deng kapala agama Yahudi pung bos-bos kirim Ruma Sambayang Pusat pung tukang jaga barapa orang, ko pi tangkap ame sang Yesus.<bt>Among those many people, there were several people from the Farisi religious party also. They had heard the many people/crowds whispering those things about Yesus. So/then they, and the *chief priests (Yahudi priests' bosses) sent several Temple guards to go catch/arrest Yesus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: The Pharisees heard the crowd"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: The Pharisees heard the crowd whispering those things about him, and the chief priests and Pharisees sent some guards to arrest him.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="Cook\CNT\cn01737b.tif" rtfFormat="width:6.5cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:right" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="33" />Ju Yesus kasi tau bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta pung waktu ko ada sama-sama deng bosong, tenga sadiki sa. Te sonde lama lai, Beta pulang kambali pi Dia yang utus sang Beta.<bt>Then Yesus told (people) saying, “My time to be together with you-pl, just remains a little longer. Cuz (elaboration) soon/in near future, I am going back (home) to Him who sent/commissioned Me. [NOTE to daughter translations: if you use ‘God’ here, then the confusion of the next verses doesn't work. It is a deliberately veiled reference.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then Jesus said, &quot;A little"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then Jesus said, "A little while longer I will be with you, and then I will go back to the one who sent me.</Message></Annotation><v n="34" />Ais nanti bosong mau cari sang Beta, ma bosong sonde katumu. Te Beta mau pi satu tampa yang bosong sonde bisa iko.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then later, you-pl will look for Me, but you won't find [Me]. Cuz (elaboration) I am going to a place that you cannot go/follow.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: You will look for me,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: You will look for me, but you will not find me, because where I am going to be, you cannot go."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="35" />Ais ju orang Yahudi pung bos-bos dong batanya satu deng satu bilang, &lt;&lt;Kira-kira ini Orang ada mau pi mana? Dia pi tampa mana, yang botong sonde bisa katumu sang Dia? Dia mau pi sambunyi di orang Yahudi yang idop tasiar di luar negrí, ko? Dia mau pi ajar orang yang pake bahasa Yunani di sana, ko? Ko, karmana?<bt>Then the bosses of the Yahudi people asked each other saying, “Probably/I wonder where this Person is going to go? He is going to what place that we-exc can't find Him? Is He going to go hide among the Yahudi people who live scattered abroad (outside the country), or (what)? Is He going to go teach the people who speak the Yunani language there (remote), or (what)? Or something else? [EXEG: Carson points out that ‘diaspora’ in the genitive relating to the first group best refers to (Greek-speaking) Jews. And the second most likely to Greek-speaking proselytes. The evidence for putting the focus on “gentiles” over “Greek-speakers” in this context is not strong in ways it often is elsewhere. See also NLT and CEV.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then the Jews said to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then the Jews said to each other, "Where does he intend to go, that we cannot find him? Will he go to the ones scattered among the Greeks, and teach the Greeks?"</Message></Annotation><v n="36" />Dia pung maksud apa, ko Dia omong bilang, &lt;Bosong mau cari sang Beta, ma bosong sonde katumu.&gt; Deng, &lt;Beta mau pi satu tampa yang bosong sonde bisa iko&gt;?&gt;&gt;<bt>What does He mean when He says, ‘You will look for Me, but you won't find (Me).’ And, ‘I am going to a place that you cannot follow’?”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: What is he talking about"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: What is he talking about when he says, 'You will look for me, but you will not find me', and, 'where I am going to be, you cannot go'?"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Aer yang bawa idop<bt>Water that brings life</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="37" />Pas di pesta pung hari tarahir, yang jadi hari paling bésar tu, ju Yesus badiri, ko batarea bilang, &lt;&lt;Dengar, ó! Sapa yang aus, na, biar dia datang di Beta ko minum!<bt>On the (very) last day of the feast, which was the most important day, Yesus stood and shouted saying, “Listen, ó! Whoever is thirsty, na, let him come to Me to/for a drink!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: On the last day, the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: On the last day, the biggest day of the feast, Jesus stood and shouted, "Whoever is thirsty, let him come to me and drink.</Message></Annotation><note reference="7:37" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kapala Agama dong pung Atoran 23:36</note><v n="38" />Te kalo ada yang parcaya sang Beta, na, datang minum sa! Te Tuhan pung Tulisan Barisi su tulis bilang, &lt;Aer yang bawa idop nanti maspurak kaluar dari orang parcaya dong pung dalam hati.&gt; Ais dong dapa idop yang batúl. Deng bagitu, dong ju tolong orang laen ko dapa itu idop yang batúl.&gt;&gt;<bt>Cuz (elaboration) if there is (someone) who believes in Me, na, just come and drink! Cuz (elaboration) the Scriptures have written saying, ‘Water that brings like will flow/burst out (under pressure) from the innermost heart/liver of the believer.’ So then they will get real/true life. In that way, they will also help other people to get that real life.” [EXEG: NLT, HCE--water doesn't just flow out and go down the drain, but it does some good.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Whoever believes in me, as"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Whoever believes in me, as the Scripture says, rivers of life-giving water will flow out from inside him."</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Te sapa yang parcaya sang Beta,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">Te sapa yang parcaya sang Beta, nanti dapa idop yang batúl. Dong ju tolong orang ko dapa itu idop yang batúl, sama ke satu kali yang bawa idop maspurak kaluar dari dong pung hati. Itu sama ke Tuhan pung Tulisan Barisi tulis tu.</Message></Annotation><note reference="7:38" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yeskial 47:1-12, Sakaria 14:8, Nehemia 9:15,19-20</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="39" />Naa, Yesus ada omong so'al Tuhan pung Roh, tagal samua orang yang parcaya sang Yesus nanti tarima itu Roh. Ma waktu Yesus omong bagitu, dong balóm tarima itu Roh, tagal Tuhan balóm kasi. Tuhan memang balóm kasi, tagal Dia balóm angka nae tinggi-tinggi sang Yesus.<bt>Naa, [shift/introduce conclusion] Yesus was speaking about God2's Spirit, because everyone who believes in Yesus will/would receive that Spirit. But when Yesus was speaking like that, they had not yet received that Spirit, because God2 had not yet given [it]. God2 really had not yet given [it], because He had not yet *glorified (elevated/promoted very high/exalted Yesus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: (He said this about the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: (He said this about the Spirit, which those who believed in him were going to receive. At that time the Spirit had not yet been given, because Jesus had not been raised to glory.)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Orang dong mulai tabagi-bagi tagal Tuhan Yesus<bt>People began to be divided/split because of the Lord Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="40" />Banya orang di situ dengar Yesus omong bagitu. Ju ada yang ba'omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Pasti ini Orang ni, Tuhan Allah pung Jubir yang Dia su janji memang dari dolu!&gt;&gt;<bt>Many people there heard Yesus talk like that. And there were those who said (to each other), “Surely this Person is God's Spokesperson, whom He had promised beforehand from long ago!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Many of the people in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Many of the people in the crowd heard him say that, and said, "This man is really the Prophet!"</Message></Annotation><note reference="7:40" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 18:18-19</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="41" />Ada saparu lai, yang bilang, &lt;&lt;Sonde! Dia ni, andia Kristus, yang Tuhan su tunju memang dari dolu!&gt;&gt;<bt>There were some others, who said, “No! This guy, is Kristus, whom God2 designated from long ago!”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ma ada saparu lai, yang protes bilang, &lt;&lt;Sonde bisa! Te Kristus tu, bukan orang Galilea. Batúl, to?<bt>But there were still others who protested, syaing, “That cannot be! Cuz (elaboration) that Kristus, is not a Galilea person, right?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Others said, &quot;This is the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Others said, "This is the Christ." But others said, "The Christ will not come from Galilee, will he?"</Message></Annotation><v n="42" />Te Tuhan pung Tulisan Barisi ada tulis bilang, Kristus tu, raja Daud pung turunan. Di tampa laen ju ada tatulis bilang, Dia tu, orang Betlehem, andia raja Daud pung kampong. Bagitu, to?&gt;&gt;<bt>Cuz (elaboration) the *Scriptures write that the Kristus is king David's descendant. In another place if is also written saying, the He is a person from Betlehem, that is king David's village. That's how it is, right? [NOTE to daughter translations: Cross ref. Indonesian TB gives Bethlehem info in Micah 5:1 (as do BHS and LXX). Most English sources put it in 5:2 as in our cross ref. below, and don't even seem to be aware there is a discrepency. NRSV has a footnote noting there is different versification in the Hebrew. TH has some discussion. I haven't chased down why the English translations put it in 5:2. The reference is memorised for catechism and Sunday school. So don't be surprised if someone makes an issue. It's not as simple as just saying “TB got the versification wrong.” I'm trying to get a copy of the TNIV, which apparently is the only recent resource dealing with the mismatch in versification.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Doesn't the Bible say that"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Doesn't the Bible say that the Christ will be a descendant of David, and come from Bethlehem, the town of David?</Message></Annotation><note reference="7:42" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">2 Samuel 7:12, Mika 5:2</note><v n="43" />Jadi orang dong mulai tabagi-bagi tagal Yesus.<bt>So (consequently) the people began to become divided/split/factioned because of Yesus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Therefore there was a division"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Therefore there was a division in the crowd because of him.</Message></Annotation><v n="44" />Ada ju barapa orang yang mau tangkap ame sang Dia. Ma sonde ada yang pegang ame sang Dia.<bt>There were several people who wanted to catch/arrest Him. But nobody was able to grab/hold (successfully) Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Some wanted to arrest him,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Some wanted to arrest him, but nobody laid a hand on him.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Orang Yahudi pung bos-bos sonde parcaya sang Tuhan Yesus<bt>The bosses of the Yahudi people don't believe in the Lord Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="45" />Ais itu, ju itu Ruma Sambayang Pusat pung tukang jaga dong yang datang ko mau tangkap sang Yesus, kambali datang di kapala agama Yahudi pung bos-bos deng orang Farisi dong. Ais, itu orang bésar dong tanya bilang, &lt;&lt;Weh! Kanapa bosong sonde bawa datang sang Dia?&gt;&gt;<bt>After that, the Temple guards who had come to catch/arrest Yesus, returned back to the *chief priests and the Farisi people. So/then those important people asked saying, “Weh! Why didn't you-pl bring Him here?”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: The temple guards went back"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: The temple guards went back to the chief priests and Pharisees, who asked them, "Why didn't you bring him in?"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="46" />Dong manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Awii! Sonde parná ada orang yang omong sama ke Dia!&gt;&gt;<bt>They responded saying, “Awii! [+amazement] There has never been a person who spoke like Him!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: The guards answered, &quot;Nobody ever"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: The guards answered, "Nobody ever spoke like this man!"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="47" />Itu orang Farisi dong tanya bilang, &lt;&lt;Heh! Bosong ju su kaná tipu, ko?<bt>The Farisi people asked saying, “Heh! Have you also been deceived/tricked?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then the Pharisees asked them,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then the Pharisees asked them, "Are you also deceived?</Message></Annotation><v n="48" />Inga, é! Te sonde ada dari botong orang Farisi, ko, dari bos-bos yang parcaya sang Dia. Ia, to? Kalo itu orang bésar sonde parcaya, na, akurang ko bosong mau parcaya sang Dia?<bt>Think about this, é! Cuz (elaboration) there is nobody from our Farisi people, or, from the bosses/leaders who believe in Him. That's right, right? If those big/important people don't believe, na, why do you-pl want to believe in Him? [NOTE: Last sentence added, because at consultant check, UNS's couldn't get the ellipsed proposition, i.e. why they were saying this vs.48.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Have any of the leaders"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Have any of the leaders or the Pharisees believed in him?</Message></Annotation><v n="49" />Ma ini orang banya dong yang mau parcaya sang Dia, sonde tau Tuhan pung Atoran. Nanti Tuhan hukum barát sang dong!&gt;&gt;<bt>But these many people/crowds who are wanting to believe in Him, don't know God2's Regulations/Law. God2 is going to punish them heavily/severely!” [NOTE: connector ‘but’ added to reflect the contrast between those who don't believe and those who do.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But this crowd/mob, who do"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But this crowd/mob, who do not know da Law, they are under God's curse!"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="50" />Ma di situ ju ada orang Farisi satu, nama Nikodemus. Dia tu, yang parná datang malam-malam ko ba'omong deng Yesus. Ais dia tanya sang dong bilang,<bt>But there, there was also a Farisi person, named Nikodemus. He was the one who once came (secretly) at night to speak with Yesus. So/then he asked them saying,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Nicodemus said to them, (the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Nicodemus said to them, (the one who came to Jesus at night. He was a Pharisee)</Message></Annotation><note reference="7:50" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yohanis 3:1-2</note><v n="51" />&lt;&lt;Karmana? Iko kotong pung atoran agama, kotong putus memang orang pung parkara dolo? Ko, kotong musti dengar sang dia dolo ko cari tau dia ada bekin apa, baru bisa putus dia pung parkara?&gt;&gt;<bt>“How is it? According to our-inc religious regulations, do we-inc first decide beforehand a person's case? Or, must we listen to him first, to find out what he has done, (and) only then can we decide his case?”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Does our Law judge a"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Does our Law judge a man before it hears him, and knows what he is doing?</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="52" />Ju dong masparak sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Weh! Lu ni, orang Galilea sama ke Dia, ko? Coba pareksa sampe alus-alus Tuhan pung Tulisan Barisi doo! Baca bae-bae ko lu tau bilang, sonde ada Tuhan pung jubir satu yang datang dari Galilea!&gt;&gt;<bt>And they spoke angrily at him saying, “Weh! Are you-sg here a Galilea person like Him, or (what)? Make a careful examination of the Scriptures! Read it carefully so you know that there is not a single *spokesperson of God2's who comes from Galilea!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: They asked him, &quot;Are you"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: They asked him, "Are you also from Galilee? Study and see that no prophet comes from Galilee."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Satu parampuan yang maen serong<bt>A woman who committed adultery/illicit sex</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="53" />[Ju dong bubar, ko samua pulang.<bt>[Then they dispersed, and everyone went home.</bt><note reference="7:53-8:11" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Alkitab bahasa Yunani yang paling tua deng yang paling bae dong, sonde mua ini carita. Abad ka-10, baru ini carita mulai muncul di tulisan bahasa Yunani.<bt>The oldest and best Yunani language Bibles don't carry this story. It was the 10-th century before this story began to appear in the Yunani language writings.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="8" />
      <v n="1" />Ma Yesus pi gunung Saitun.<bt>But Yesus went to Saitun (Olives-loan) mountain.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then everyone went home. But"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then everyone went home. But Jesus went to the Mount of Olives.</Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Dia pung beso papagi, ju Dia maso pi Ruma Sambayang Pusat pung kintal. Banya orang datang bakumpul di Dia. Ais Dia dudu ko mulai ajar sang dong.<bt>Early the next morning, He entered into the Temple yard. Many people came to gather (around) Him. Then He sat and began to teach them.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Early the next morning he"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Early the next morning he went to the Temple. The whole crowd gathered around him, and he sat down and began to teach them.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Itu waktu, ada satu parampuan yang kaná tangkap basa waktu dia ada maen serong. Ju barapa guru agama deng barapa orang Farisi hela bawa sang dia pi sang Yesus. Ais dong paksa sang itu parampuan ko badiri di dong samua pung muka.<bt>At that time, there was a woman who had been caught wet (Idiom = caught red-handed/ in the act) (while she was committing adultery/illicit sex. And several religious teachers and several Farisi people brought her (implies force/compelled) to Yesus. And they forced that woman to stand in front of all of them.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kaná tangkap basa ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">kaná tangkap basa =</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="agousin: lead, bring, escort; often involves"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">agousin: lead, bring, escort; often involves force LITERALLY: The teachers of the Law and the Pharisees brought a woman who had been caught committing adultery to him, and made her stand in front of all of them.<span class="Italic">(3)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Ju dong kasi tau sang Yesus bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa Guru. Ini parampuan kaná tangkap basa waktu dia ada maen serong.<bt>Then they told Yesus saying, “Father Teacher. This woman was caught wet while she was committing adultery/illicit sex.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: They said to Jesus, &quot;Teacher,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: They said to Jesus, "Teacher, this woman was caught committing adultery.</Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Naa, iko ba'i Musa pung Atoran dong, ada parenta yang bilang, &lt;Orang yang maen serong musti kaná hukum lempar sampe mati.&gt; Iko Bos, karmana?&gt;&gt;<bt>Naa [here's the point], according to grandfather Musa's Regulations/Law, there is a command that says, ‘A person who commits adultery/illicit sex must be punished by throwing (stones) until dead.’ According to You, how is it/should it be?”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Now, Moses commanded in the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Now, Moses commanded in the Law that such people should be stoned. But what do you say?"</Message></Annotation><note reference="8:5" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kapala Agama dong pung Atoran 20:10, Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 22:22-24</note><v n="6" />Dong mau coba hiki sang Dia, ko dong bisa lempar sala ko mau kasi jato sang Dia.<bt>They wanted to ensnare/trap Him, so they could accuse/blame [Him] to bring Him down.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lempar sala = 1) blame, accuse,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">lempar sala = 1) blame, accuse, 2) shift the blame (if problem, try "kasi jato")</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Yesus sonde manyao langsung, ma Dia jongko ko tulis di tana, pake Dia pung ujung jari.<bt>Yesus did not respond directly, but He squatted to write on the ground, using the end/tip of his finger.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: They said this to test/trap"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: They said this to test/trap him, so they could accuse him. But Jesus stooped over and wrote with his finger in the dirt.</Message></Annotation><v n="7" />Dong tanya-tanya sang Dia tarús. Ais Dia badiri, ju kasi tau sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bagini. Kalo ada dari bosong yang sonde parná bekin sala, na, dia tu yang bisa lempar batu yang partama ko hukum sang ini parampuan.&gt;&gt;<bt>They kept asking Him. Then He stood, and told them saying, “Like this. If there is among you-pl someone who has never done wrong/sinned, na, he is the one who can throw the first stone to punish this woman.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: So when they continued asking"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: So when they continued asking him, he straightened up, and said to them, "Whichever one of you has not committed a sin, may throw the first stone at her."</Message></Annotation><v n="8" />Ais Dia jongko ulang lai, ju tulis tamba di tana.<bt>Then He squatted again, and wrote more on the ground.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then he stooped down again,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then he stooped down again, and wrote on the ground.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Waktu dong dengar Dia pung omong tu, dong jadi malu. Te dalam dong pung hati, dong tau bilang, dong ju ada parná bekin sala. Ais dong bubar satu-satu, mulai dari yang tua sampe yang muda. Lama-lama ju, tenga Yesus deng itu parampuan sandiri di situ.<bt>When they heard what He said, they became ashamed. Cuz (elaboration) in their livers they knew that they had also done wrong. So/then they dispersed one by one, beginning from the oldest to the youngest. Eventually, there remained just Yesus and that woman there by themselves.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="@@ dengar pung dengar = over"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">@@ dengar pung dengar = over a period of time ; dengar deng dengar ju = immediately upon.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: When they heard that, they"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: When they heard that, they were convicted by their own consciences, and went away one by one, from the oldest to the youngest. Jesus was left standing alone, and the woman still standing there.</Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Ais Yesus badiri lai, ju tanya bilang, &lt;&lt;Hee? Ko dong ada di mana? Sonde ada orang laen di sini yang mau kasi sala ko hukum sang lu, ko?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus stood up again, and asked saying, “Hee? Where are they? Isn't there anyone else here who is going to blame/accuse2 and punish you?”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then he straightened up again."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then he straightened up again. He said to the woman, "Where are they? Is there no one left to condemn you?"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Ju dia manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Sonde ada, Bapa.&gt;&gt;<bt>She responded saying, “There's nobody, Father.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ais Yesus kasi tau sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta ju sonde mau hukum sang lu. Pulang su. Ma inga. Jang bekin sala lai!&gt;&gt;]<bt>So/then Yesus told her saying, “I also am not going to punish you. Go on home. But remember. Don't do wrong/sin again/anymore!”]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: She said, &quot;Nobody, sir.&quot; Jesus"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: She said, "Nobody, sir." Jesus said to her, "I do not condemn you either. Go, but do not sin any more."]</Message></Annotation><note reference="7:53-8:11" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Alkitab bahasa Yunani yang paling tua deng yang paling bae dong, sonde mua ini carita. Abad ka-10, baru ini carita mulai muncul di tulisan bahasa Yunani.<bt>The oldest and best Yunani language Bibles don't carry this story. It was the 10-th century before this story began to appear in the Yunani language writings.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus sama ke taráng kasi orang di ini dunya<bt>The Lord Yesus is like light for the people of this world</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Ais Yesus omong ulang lai deng orang banya dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta ni, sama ke taráng kasi orang di ini dunya. Orang yang iko sang Beta sonde idop di galáp, ma dia tenga di taráng yang bawa idop yang batúl.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus spoke again with the many people saying, “I am like light for the people of this world. A/the person who follows Me does not live in darkness, but s/he lives in the light that brings real life.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then again Jesus spoke to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then again Jesus spoke to them and said, "I am the light of the world. He who follows me will not live in the dark, but shall have the light of life.</Message></Annotation><note reference="8:12" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 5:14, Yohanis 9:5</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Ada barapa orang Farisi yang protes bilang, &lt;&lt;Weh! Lu mau jadi saksi so'al Lu pung diri sandiri, ko? Sonde bisa! Te iko kotong pung atoran, musti orang laen yang jadi saksi kasi satu orang, bukan itu orang sandiri. Jadi botong sonde mau tarima, deng sonde mau parcaya.&gt;&gt;<bt>There were several Farisi people who protested saying, “Weh! You-sg want to be a witness about Your own self, right? That can't be! Cuz (elaboration) according to our-inc regulations, it must be someone else who is a witness for a person, not that person themself. So (consequently), we-exc are not going to accept [it], and are not going to believe.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: The Pharisees said to him,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: The Pharisees said to him, "Now you are testifying fo yourself, so your testimony is not trustworthy."</Message></Annotation><note reference="8:13" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yohanis 5:31</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Bagini. Biar Beta jadi saksi kasi Beta pung diri sandiri, ma Beta pung omong tu, batúl. Te Beta sandiri yang tau parsís Beta asal dari mana, deng mau pi mana. Bosong sonde tau Beta dari mana, deng ju sonde tau Beta nanti mau pi mana.<bt>Yesus responded saying, “It's like this. Even if I am a witness for Myself, nevertheless what I have to say is true. Cuz (elaboration) I myself am the one who knows precisely where I originated from, and where I am going. You-pl don't know where I am from, and also don't know where I'm going to go.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Jesus told them, &quot;Even though"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Jesus told them, "Even though I testify for myself, my testimony is true. Because I know where I came from and where I am going. You do not know where I came from or where I am going.</Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Bosong nilei orang pake manusia pung ukuran. Ma Beta sonde pake manusia pung ukuran ko nilei satu orang ju.<bt>You assess/evaluate people using human standards/measurements. But I don't use human standards/measurements to assess/evaluate people. [EXEG: Carson points out that to ‘pass judicial sentence’ here would directly contradict Jesus' other sayings in John. He favours ‘assess’ from the lexicon and context.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: You assess/judge from human standards."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: You assess/judge from human standards. I assess/judge no one.</Message></Annotation><v n="16" />Kalo Beta nilei orang, Beta pung ukuran tu, batúl. Te Beta sonde nilei sandiri, ma Beta bekin samua-samua sama-sama deng Beta pung Bapa yang utus sang Beta.<bt>If I assess/evaluate a person, My measurement is correct. Cuz (elaboration) I don't assess alone/by myself, but I do everything together with My Father who sent/commissioned Me.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But if I judge, my"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But if I judge, my judgment is true, because I am not alone, but I do everything with the Father who sent me.</Message></Annotation><v n="17" />Jang lupa, te ada tatulis di bosong pung Atoran agama bilang, &lt;Kalo ada dua orang saksi yang omong hal yang sama, na, itu sah.&gt;<bt>Don't forget. Cuz (elaboration) it is written in you-pl religious Regulations/Law saying, ‘If there are two witnesses who say the same thing, na, it is valid/legal.’</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: It is written in your"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: It is written in your Law that the testimony of two men is true.</Message></Annotation><v n="18" />Jadi bukan cuma Beta sandiri sa yang jadi saksi so'al Beta pung diri. Te Beta pung Bapa yang utus sang Beta ju ada jadi saksi yang omong so'al Beta.&gt;&gt;<bt>So (consequently), I am not the only one who is a witness about Myself. Cuz (elaboration) My Father who sent/commissioned Me is also a witness who speaks about Me.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: I am one that testifies"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: I am one that testifies about myself, and the Father who sent me also testifies about me.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Dong tanya bilang, &lt;&lt;Ko Lu pung Bapa tu, ada di mana?&gt;&gt;<bt>They asked saying, “So this Father of Yours, where is He?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ju Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong sonde kanál batúl sang Beta. Bosong ju sonde kanál sang Beta pung Bapa. Te kalo bosong kanál batúl sang Beta, tantu bosong kanál sang Dia ju.&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus responded saying, “You-pl don't really know Me. You also don't know My Father. Cuz (elaboration) if you really knew Me, you would certainly also know Him.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: They asked him, &quot;Where is"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: They asked him, "Where is your father?" Jesus answered, "You do not know me or my Father. If you knew me, you would know my Father too."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Ini samua ni, Yesus kasi tau waktu Dia mangajar di Ruma Sambayang Pusat, deka-deka di tampa yang dong pake ko kumpul doi kolekte. Sonde ada yang tangkap sang Dia, tagal dia pung waktu balóm pas.<bt>All this/these things, Yesus explained/told when He was teaching in the Temple, near the place which they used to gather the collection money. There was nobody who caught/arrested Him, because the time was not yet right.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Jesus said all this as"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Jesus said all this as he taught in the temple, by the Temple treasury. And nobody touched him, because it was not time yet for that.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">&lt;&lt;Nanti Beta pi satu tampa yang bosong sonde bisa iko&gt;&gt;<bt>“I will go to a place where you-pl can't go/follow”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Yesus omong tamba sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Nanti Beta kasi tenga sang bosong, ko pi tampa laen. Bosong nanti cari-cari sang Beta, ma sonde dapa, te bosong sonde ada pung hak pi itu tampa. Ais nanti kalo bosong mati, bosong masi pikol bosong pung sala.&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus continued speaking to them saying, “Later I will leave you-pl behind, to go to another/different place. You will keep looking for Me, but [you] will not find/get [Me], cuz (elaboration) you have no right/authority to go to that place. Then later when you die, you will still be bearing/shoulder carrying your wrong/sin.” [EXEG: ‘sin, wrong’ here is singular in the Gk. Carson and Morris both say it refers to the sin of rejecting Jesus as Messiah, and not believing in Him.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="cari doak sang beta"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">cari doak sang beta</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: He said again to them,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: He said again to them, "I am going away, and you will look for me, but you will die in your sin. Where I am going, you cannot come."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Ais orang Yahudi pung bos-bos batanya satu deng satu bilang, &lt;&lt;Dia ada omong apa ni? Dia mau bunu diri, ko? Te Dia bilang, &lt;Bosong sonde bisa pi itu tampa.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>Then the bosses of the Yahudi people asked each other saying, “What's He talking about here? is He going to kill himself? Cuz He said, ‘You cannot go to that place.’”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: So the Jewish leaders said,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: So the Jewish leaders said, "Will he kill himself, because he said, 'Where I am going you cannot come'?"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Ju Yesus kasi tau sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong dari bumi di bawa. Ma Beta dari langit di atas. Bosong orang dari ini dunya. Ma Beta bukan orang dari ini dunya.<bt>Then Yesus told them saying, “You-pl are from the earth below. But I am from the sky above. You-pl are people from this world. But I am not a person from this world.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And he said to them,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And he said to them, "You are from below, I am from above. You are from this world, I am not from this world.</Message></Annotation><v n="24" />Andia ko Beta kasi tau tadi bilang, nanti kalo bosong mati, bosong masi pikol bosong pung sala-sala dong. Te kalo bosong sonde parcaya bilang, Beta ni, andia Kristus, yang Tuhan su kirim datang, nanti kalo bosong mati, pasti bosong masi pikol bosong pung sala-sala dong.&gt;&gt;<bt>That is why I said just now that, later when you die, you will still be carrying your sins. Cuz (elaboration) if you do not believe, that I am the Kristus, whom God2 has sent here, later when you die, surely you will still be carrying your sins.” [EXEG: ‘sins’ here is pl.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Therefore I said to you"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Therefore I said to you that you will die in your sins. Because if you do not believe that I am he, you will die in your sins."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Ais dong tanya bilang, &lt;&lt;Weh! Ko Lu ni, sapa?&gt;&gt;<bt>So they asked saying, “Weh! So who are You-sg?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta su kasi tau memang dari mula-mula.<bt>Yesus responded saying, “I have already told you beforehand from the beginning.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Therefore they said to him,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Therefore they said to him, "Who are you?" Jesus said to them, "What I told you at the start/beginning.</Message></Annotation><note reference="8:25" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Bahasa Yunani di sini bisa ada dua arti. Yang satu, andia: &lt;Beta su kasi tau memang dari mula-mula.&gt; Yang satu lai, andia: &lt;Akurang ko Beta mau omong sang bosong?&gt;<bt>The Yunani language here can have two meanings. The one is: ‘I have already told you beforehand from the beginning.’ The other one is: ‘Why do I bother to speak to you?’</bt></note><v n="26" />Ada banya hal yang Beta bisa kasi tau so'al bosong. Bosong pung sala ju banya. Ma Beta sonde kasi tunju itu hal dong. Naa, Yang utus sang Beta datang di sini tu, kalo Dia omong, Dia cuma tau omong yang batúl sa. Deng Beta cuma kasi tau sang orang di ini dunya, hal-hal yang Beta su dengar dari Dia.&gt;&gt;<bt>There are many things/matters that I can say/tell/explain about you-pl. Your wrongs/sins are also many. But I am not going to show those things. Naa, the One who sent/commissioned Me to come here, if/when He speaks, He only knows how to tell the truth. And I only tell people in this world things which I have heard from Him.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: I have many things to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: I have many things to say and judge about you. But the one who sent me is true/real/genuine/reliable, and I speak to the world the things that I have heard from him.</Message></Annotation><v n="27" />(Dia pung maksud, Dia pung Bapa di sorga. Ma dong sonde tangkap ame Dia pung maksud.)<bt>(He meant His Father in heaven. But they didn't (fully/really) catch His meaning.)</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: They did not know that"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: They did not know that he spoke to them of the Father.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Ju Yesus omong tamba bilang, &lt;&lt;Nanti kalo bosong su gantong sang Beta, Manusia Tulen ni, di atas kayu palang, baru bosong mangarti bilang, Beta ni, andia Kristus. Deng Beta sonde bekin apa-apa dari Beta sandiri, ma Beta cuma ajar hal-hal yang Bapa di sorga su ajar sang Beta.<bt>Then Yesus spoke further saying, “Later when you-pl have already hung Me, the *Son of Man (Authentic/Ideal Human) on a *cross, only then will you understand that I am the Kristus. And I don't do anything from Myself, but I only teach (the) things which Father in heaven has taught Me. [EXEG: NLT. Note Gk here is ‘lifted up’ with no mention of the cross. Carson &amp; others observe that ‘lifted up’ evokes both 1) hanging on a tree, and 2) ascension. KM /ta'angkat/ evokes glorification, but not death and clashes in this context. What we have here is a compromise, even though it is probably too early to make crucifixion explicit. Dhao has an ‘angkat’ word that works for both senses, so your lg might too. Avoid /paku/ here.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then Jesus said to them,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then Jesus said to them, "When you have lifted up the Son of Man, you will know that I am he, and I do not do anything by myself, but just as the Father has taught me, those things I teach.</Message></Annotation><v n="29" />Yang utus sang Beta ju ada sama-sama deng Beta tarús. Dia sonde parná kasi biar Beta sandiri, tagal Beta salalu bekin iko Dia pung mau.&gt;&gt;<bt>The one who sent/commissioned Me is continually with Me. He has never left Me alone, because I always do according to His will/desire.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And the one who sent"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And the one who sent me is with me. He has not left me alone, because I always do the things that please him."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="30" />Waktu Yesus kasi tau ini hal dong, ju ada banya orang yang parcaya sang Dia.<bt>When Yesus explained/told these things, there were many people who believed in Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: When he had said these"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: When he had said these things, many believed in him.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">&lt;&lt;Bosong ni, andia ba'i Abraham pung turunan dong&gt;&gt;<bt>“You-pl are grandfather Abraham's descendants”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="&lt;&lt;Bosong ni, andia ba'i Abraham pung"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">&lt;&lt;Bosong ni, andia ba'i Abraham pung turunan&gt;&gt; &lt;&lt;Hal-hal yang batúl, yang kasi bebas sang bosong&gt;&gt;<span class="Italic">(30) (30) </span>&lt;&lt;Bebas dari sala pung kuasa&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="&lt;&lt;Nanti bosong dapa tau apa yang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">&lt;&lt;Nanti bosong dapa tau apa yang batúl&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="31" />Ais ju Yesus kasi tau sang itu orang Yahudi dong yang parcaya sang Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo bosong idop ta'ika deng Beta pung Kata-kata dong, deng bosong balajar tarús dari Beta, na, bosong jadi Beta pung ana bua yang batúl.<bt>Then Yesus told those Yahudi people who believed in Him saying, “If you-pl live bound/linked to My Words, and you continue to learn from Me, na, you are/become my true/real *disciples. [EXEG: HCE, and unpacking meaning of Gk /matetheis/ as ‘learner, being instructed, getting training’.] [EXEG: Gk in next 2 passages is wordplay on ‘father’ and children: 1) biological, 2) genealogical, 3) character. In Timor region, sense #1 works, but not #2 and #3.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="BI hidup semati"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">BI hidup semati</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then Jesus said to the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then Jesus said to the Jews who had believed in him, "If you remain in my word/message, you are really my disciples.</Message></Annotation><v n="32" />Ais bosong bisa dapa tau hal-hal yang batúl. Deng itu hal-hal yang batúl, yang kasi bebas sang bosong, ko bosong sonde usa jadi budak lai.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then you can (come to) know things that are true. And those things that are true, are what will free/release you, so you no longer need to be slaves anymore.” [EXEG: larger context of dialogue.] [NOTE to daughter translations: Don't flesh out meaning of “slave” here as in vs.36, because reaction in verse 33 shows they are taking Jesus literally.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: You will know the truth,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: You will know the truth, and the truth will make you free."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="33" />Ais dong protes bilang, &lt;&lt;Heh! Botong ni, bukan orang pung budak! Te botong ni, ba'i Abraham pung turunan! Jadi akurang ko Lu omong bilang, nanti botong jadi bebas?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then they protested saying, “Hee! We-exc here are not a person's slaves! Cuz (elaboration) we are grandfather Abraham's descendants! So (consequently) why is it that You-sg say that we will become free?”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: They answered him, &quot;We are"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: They answered him, "We are the descendants of Abraham, and we have never been slaves. Why do you say that we will become free?"</Message></Annotation><note reference="8:33" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 3:9, Lukas 3:8</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="34" />Ju Yesus kasi tau sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Yang Beta omong tu, batúl. Te samua orang yang idop bekin sala dong, su jadi sama ke satu budak yang cuma iko-iko sala pung mau sa.<bt>Then Yesus told/explained to them saying, “What I said is true. Cuz (elaboration) everyone who lives doing wrong, has become like a slave who only follows/goes along with the desires/will of wrong/sin.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Jesus answered them, That's right!"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Jesus answered them, That's right! I tell you that everyone who practices sin is a slave of sin.</Message></Annotation><v n="35" />Ma dia pung biasa, bagini: budak dong sonde biasa tenga tarús di satu ruma. Te cuma bos pung ana sa yang tenga tarús di situ.<bt>But the norm is like this: slaves don't normally live continually in a house. Cuz (elaboration) it's only the boss's children who keep living there. [ALT + NOTE to daughter translations: May be too vague and nonsensical for UNSs to grasp anything from. Worldview clash: slaves CAN be permanent members of households here, so the literal is nonsensical and not a true statement. But slaves don't have inheritance rights, so consider ALT below, which fits the higher level context and communicates the intent of the verse. EXEG: See Morris about ‘rights’ here, and discussion of related problems in TH. ALT: /budak dong sonde biasa dapa bagian dari dia pung tuan pung ruma. Te cuma itu tuan pung ana sandiri yang dapa bagian di situ./ “slaves don't normally get/obtain a portion/share/inheritance from the house of his master/owner. Cuz (elaboration) it's only the master/owner's children who get/obtain a portion/share/inheritance there.”]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: The slave does not stay"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: The slave does not stay in the household forever, but the son stays forever.</Message></Annotation><v n="36" />Jadi, kalo Beta, andia Tuhan pung Ana, hapus buang bosong pung sala-sala dong, na, bosong su bebas, deng su sonde jadi sala pung budak lai. Deng bagitu, bosong bebas batúl, deng sonde usa iko sala pung mau lai!<bt>So (consequently) if I, that is God2's Child, wipe away your wrongs/sins, na, you are already free, and are no longer a slave to sin. In that way, you are truly free, and no longer need to follow the will/desires of wrong/sin. [DISCOURSE: EXEG: HCE, unpack higher level context.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Therefore, if the Son will"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Therefore, if the Son will make you free, you will really be free.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="37" />Beta su tau bosong ni, andia ba'i Abraham pung turunan. Biar bagitu, ma bosong maen cari-cari jalan ko mau bunu bekin mati sang Beta, tagal bosong sonde mau tarima Beta pung ajaran. Te di bosong pung hati, su sonde ada tampa lai ko simpan Beta pung Kata-kata.<bt>I already know that you-pl here, are grandfather Abraham's descendants. Even that being the case, nevertheless you keep looking for ways to kill Me, because you don't want to accept My teaching. Cuz (elaboration) in your hearts (livers), there is no longer any place for you to keep/store/put away My Words/Message.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: I know that you are"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: I know that you are Abraham's descendants, but you are trying to kill me, because you [have no room for / can't bear / can't accept] my word.</Message></Annotation><v n="38" />Beta kasi tau hal-hal yang Beta su lia, yang Beta pung Bapa su kasi tunju sang Beta. Deng bosong bekin iko hal-hal yang bosong su dengar dari bosong pung bapa dong.&gt;&gt;<bt>I tell the things which I have seen, which My Father has shown Me. And you-pl do according to the things which you have heard from your fathers.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: I tell what I have"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: I tell what I have seen from my Father, and you do what you have heard from your father."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">&lt;&lt;Bosong pung bapa tu, andia setan pung bos&gt;&gt;<bt>“Your-pl father is the boss of the evil spirits”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="39" />Dong manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Botong ni, ba'i Abraham pung turunan!&gt;&gt;<bt>They responded saying, “We are grandfather Abraham's descendants!” [EXEG: Gk is wordplay on ‘father’ 1) biological, 2) genealogical, 3) character. In Timor region, sense #1 works, but not #2 and #3.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Yesus kasi tau bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo bosong jadi ba'i Abraham pung turunan yang batúl, bosong musti conto ame sang dia.<bt>Yesus told (them) saying, “If you were grandfather Abraham's real descendants, you-pl must follow his example.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: They answered him, &quot;Our father"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: They answered him, "Our father is Abraham." Jesus said to them, "If you were Abraham's children, you would do Abraham's works."</Message></Annotation><v n="40" />Ma ba'i Abraham sonde parná bekin jahat sama ke yang bosong bekin tu! Te bosong maen cari-cari jalan ko mau bunu bekin mati sang Beta. Padahal Beta ni, yang kasi tau sang bosong hal-hal yang batúl, yang Beta dengar dari Tuhan.<bt>But grandfather Abraham never did evil like (what) you-pl are doing! Cuz (elaboration) you keep looking for a way to kill Me. When in fact, I am the one who tells you things that are true, which I heard from God2.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But now you try to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But now you try to kill me, a man who has told you the truth which I have heard from God! Abraham did not do that.</Message></Annotation><v n="41" />Bosong pung bekin, memang sonde lari jao dari bosong pung bapa.&gt;&gt;<bt>What you do, really is not running far from (idiom (understatement = exactly the same as)) your father (generic, unmarked for number).”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Idiom (above)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">Idiom (above)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ma dong protes bilang, &lt;&lt;Heh! Botong ni, ana sah! Jang bilang, botong ni, ana haram! Te botong pung Bapa, cuma satu sa, andia Tuhan Allah!&gt;&gt;<bt>But they protested saying, “Heh! We are legitimate children! Don't say that we here are illigitimate children (=product of illicit sex)! Cuz (elaboration) we-exc have only one father, and that is God!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ana haram = hasil maen serong"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">ana haram = hasil maen serong ; ana galáp = 1) ana dari hasil perbuatan gelap, 2) orang bekin jahat</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: You do the deeds of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: You do the deeds of your father." They said to him, "We were not born illegitimately! We have one father, God!"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="42" />Ju Yesus kasi tau sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Ma kalo Tuhan Allah batúl-batúl jadi bosong pung Bapa, pasti bosong sayang sang Beta. Te Beta datang dari Dia, deng Beta ada di sini. Beta sonde datang iko Beta pung mau sandiri. Ma Beta datang, tagal Dia yang utus sang Beta.<bt>Yesus told them saying, “But if God were really your Father, surely you-pl would love Me. Cuz (elaboration) I come from Him, and I am here. I didn't come following My own will. But I came, because He is the one who sent/commissioned Me.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Jesus said to them, &quot;If"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Jesus said to them, "If God were your father, you would love me, for I came from God, and I am here. I did not come on my own, but he sent me.</Message></Annotation><v n="43" />Akurang ko bosong sonde mangarti Beta pung omong? Mangkali tagal bosong sonde mau dengar, na!<bt>Why is it that you can't understand what I am saying? Perhaps/Probably it is because you don't want to hear [+obvious]!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Why do you not understand"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Why do you not understand what I say? Because you cannot hear my word.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="44" />Bosong ni, satu model ke setan dong pung bos. Te bosong suka bekin iko dia pung mau! Dari mula-mula, dia tukang bunu orang. Dia lawan hal yang batúl, te dia su tola buang samua yang batúl. Kalo dia putar-balek, itu memang dia pung biasa. Te dia tu, tukang putar-balek, deng tukang omong kosong pung ba'i!<bt>You here are the same model/type/kind as the boss of the evil spirits. Cuz (elaboration) you like to do according to his will/desires! From the beginning, he was (characterised as) a murderer. He opposes things that are true, cuz (elaboration) he has rejected everything that is true. When he deceives, that really is his norm. Cuz he is a (habitual) liar, and the grandfather of b.s. (idiom)!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: You are from your father,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: You are from your father, the Devil, and the things your father desires, that is what you do. He was a murderer from the beginning. He has not stood for the truth, and does not have the truth in him. When he tells a lie, he tells what is natural to him, because he is a liar and the father of lies.</Message></Annotation><v n="45" />Beta ni, yang kasi tau hal yang batúl. Ma bosong sonde parcaya sang Beta.<bt>I (on the other hand) am the one who tells what is true. But you-pl don't believe (in) Me.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: I say what is true,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: I say what is true, and you do not believe me.</Message></Annotation><v n="46" />Coba! Sapa dari bosong yang bisa kasi tunju bukti bilang, Beta su bekin sala? Heran, é! Kalo Beta omong yang batúl, akurang ko bosong sonde mau parcaya sang Beta?<bt>Try (=have a think about this0! Who among you can show proof/evidence that I have done wrong/sin? That's surprising, é! If I say what is true, why is it that you don't want to believe (in) Me?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Which one of you can"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Which one of you can prove that I have sinned? If I tell the truth, why don't you believe me?</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="47" />Naa, orang yang ba'asal dari Tuhan Allah dengar sang Dia pung Kata-kata. Ma bosong ni, sonde ba'asal dari Tuhan, andia ko bosong sonde suka dengar sang Beta.&gt;&gt;<bt>Naa [shift/introduce conclusion], a/the person who originate from God listens to/obeys His Words/Message. But you here do not originate from God2, so that is why you don't like to listen to Me.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: The one who comes from"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: The one who comes from God listens to God's word. That is why you do not listen to me, because you are not from God.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">&lt;&lt;Ba'i Abraham balóm ada, ma Beta su ada lebe dolo&gt;&gt;<bt>“Gf/Ff Abraham did not yet exist, but I already existed before that”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="48" />Orang Yahudi pung bos-bos manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Weh! Botong su omong batúl tu. Te botong su bilang, Lu ni, bukan orang Yahudi isi-isi, ma Lu orang Samaria. Lu ju su takaná setan!&gt;&gt;<bt>The Yahudi people's bosses responded saying, “Weh! We-exc have told the truth. Cuz (elaboration) said that You are not a real/genuine Yahudi, but you are a Samaria person. And You have also been possessed by/adversely affected by an evil spirit!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: The Jews answered him, &quot;Aren't"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: The Jews answered him, "Aren't we right when we say that you are a Samaritan, and you have an evil spirit inside you?"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="49" />Ju Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta sonde takaná setan. Beta taro hormat sang Beta pung Bapa di sorga, ma bosong sonde taro hormat sang Beta.<bt>Yesus responded saying, “I have not be possessed by an evil spirit. I show respect/honour to My Father in heaven, but you do not show respect to Me.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Jesus answered them, &quot;I do"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Jesus answered them, "I do not have an evil spirit, but I honor my father, and you dishonor me.</Message></Annotation><v n="50" />Beta sonde angka-angka diri ko kasi tunju Beta pung hebat sandiri. Ma ada Satu yang mau kasi tunju Beta pung hebat. Biar Dia yang putus kalo Beta pung omong batúl, ko sonde.<bt>I don't elevate/promote myself to show how great I am. But there is One who wants to/is going to show my greatness/incredibleness/amazingness. Let Him be the one to decide if what I say is true, or not. [EXEG: Gk: glory here] [EXEG: NLT, Uma, Deibler. context.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: I do not look for"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: I do not look for my own glory. There is one who is seeking it and who is the judge.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="51" />Beta pung Kata-kata, memang batúl! Ais orang yang dengar deng bekin iko Beta pung Kata-kata dong, sonde akan mati.&gt;&gt;<bt>My Words/Message really is true! So then the person who hears and does according to My Words/Message is not going to die [+certain].</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: That's right! And I tell"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: That's right! And I tell you, whoever obeys my word/message will never see death.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="52" />Dengar bagitu, ju orang Yahudi pung bos-bos kasi tau sang Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Sakarang botong su tau Lu omong gila, tagal Lu su takaná setan. Te ba'i Abraham sandiri, mati. Tuhan pung jubir dolu-dolu dong, ju mati. Ma Lu bilang, &lt;orang yang dengar deng bekin iko Beta pung Kata-kata dong, sonde akan mati.&gt; Memang Lu su gila!<bt>Hearing that, the bosses of the Yahudi people told Him saying, “Now we-exc know that You are talking crazy, because You have been possessed by an evil spirit. Cuz (elaboration) grandfather Abraham himself died. God2's *spokespeople long ago also died. But You say, ‘the person who hears and does according to My Words/Message is not going to die.’ You really are must be crazy!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then the Jews said to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then the Jews said to him, "Now we know that you have an evil spirit. Abraham died, and the prophets, and you say, 'Whoever obeys my word, he will never see death."</Message></Annotation><v n="53" />Ko Lu pikir, Lu lebe hebat dari Abraham yang su mati? Ko, Lu lebe hebat dari Tuhan pung jubir yang su mati dong? Lu pikir, Lu ni, sapa?&gt;&gt;<bt>Do You think You are greater that Abraham who died? Or, are You greater than God2's spokespeople who died? Who do you think you are?”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Are you greater than our"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Are you greater than our father Abraham, who died? And the prophets died. Who do you think you are?" [Or "Who are you making yourself out to be?" (Carson, Bruce)]</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="54" />Ju Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo Beta yang angka-angka diri, orang sonde mau tarima. Padahal bukan Beta yang angka-angka diri, ma Beta pung Bapa yang angka tinggi-tinggi sang Beta. Dia tu, yang bosong mangaku bilang, Dia jadi bosong pung Tuhan Allah.<bt>Yesus responded saying, “If I elevate/promote Myself, people will not accept it/me. Whereas in fact, it is not Me who is elevating Myself, but My Father who is *glorifying (elevating way up high) Me. He is the one you-pl acknowledge, saying He is your God. [EXEG: Gk: glory here]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mangaku-mangaku = keep saying (sense of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">mangaku-mangaku = keep saying (sense of ridicule)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Jesus answered, &quot;If I glorify"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Jesus answered, "If I glorify myself, my glory is nothing/not valid. It is my Father who glorifies me, whom you say is your God.</Message></Annotation><v n="55" />Ma bosong sonde kanál sang Dia. Beta yang kanál bae. Kalo Beta bilang Beta sonde kanál sang Dia, Beta tukang omong kosong, sama ke bosong. Ma Beta kanál bae sang Dia, deng Beta ju bekin iko Dia pung Kata-kata.<bt>But you don't know Him. I know Him well. If I said I didn't know Him, I would be a liar, just like you. But I know Him well, and I also do according to His Words/Message.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: You have not known him."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: You have not known him. I know him. If I say that I do not know him, I would be a liar, like you. But I know him and I keep/obey his word/message.</Message></Annotation><v n="56" />Bosong pung ba'i Abraham pung hati paling sanáng, waktu dia ada tunggu-tunggu mau lia Beta pung datang. Dia memang su dapa lia, ais dia puas.&gt;&gt;<bt>Your grandfather Abraham was really happy, when he was eagerly awaiting to see My coming. He really has already been able to see (it), and so he is satisfied.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="@! CEV grossly undertranslated here"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">@! CEV grossly undertranslated here</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(Alternate) Dia dapa lia abis, ju"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">(Alternate) Dia dapa lia abis, ju dia puas memang</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="xairw: glad, happy agalliaw: rejoice, exult"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">xairw: glad, happy agalliaw: rejoice, exult [strong word, see John 5:35]<span class="Italic">(56) (56) </span>LITERALLY: Your father Abraham rejoiced to see my day. He saw it and was glad."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="57" />Orang Yahudi pung bos-bos kasi tau bilang, &lt;&lt;Lu pung umur balóm sampe 50 taon ju! Ma Lu bilang Lu su dapa lia sang ba'i Abraham. Batúl, ko?&gt;&gt;<bt>The Yahudi people's bosses said, “You are not yet 50 years old! But You say You have already seen grandfather Abraham. Is that right?”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: The Jews said to him,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: The Jews said to him, "You are not fifty years old yet. Have you seen Abraham?"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="58" />Ju Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Batúl! Te ba'i Abraham balóm ada, ma Beta su ada lebe dolo.&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus responded, “That's right! Cuz (elaboration) grandfather Abraham did not yet exist, but I already existed before that.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="??How do we get &quot;I am&quot;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">??How do we get "I am" into this??</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Jesus said to them, &quot;That's"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Jesus said to them, "That's right! I tell you, before Abraham was, I was."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="59" />Ais, itu orang dong angka batu ko mau lempar sang Dia, tagal Dia angka diri sama ke Tuhan. Ma Dia jalan sambunyi-sambunyi ko kaluar dari Ruma Sambayang Pusat pung kintal.<bt>So/then those people picked up stones to throw at Him, because He elevated/lifted Himself to be the same as/equal (status) with God2. [NOTE: same wording as in Jn. 5:18; added because UNS's at consultant check couldn't make the link with vs. 58 as to why they wanted to stone him.] But He went secretly/hidden (from view) to go out from the Temple yard.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then they picked up stones"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then they picked up stones to throw at him. But Jesus hid himself, and went out of the temple.</Message></Annotation><note reference="8:59" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yohanis 5:18</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus bekin bae satu orang buta<bt>The Lord Yesus heals a blind person</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="9" />
      <v n="1" />Ais itu, Yesus dong ada jalan. Ju Dia lia satu orang buta, yang su buta memang dari lahir.<bt>After that, Yesus (coll.) were walking. And He saw a blind person who had been blind from birth.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And as he went along,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And as he went along, he saw a man who was blind from birth.</Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Ais Yesus pung ana bua dong tanya bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa Guru! Sapa yang bekin sala, sampe ini orang jadi buta bagini? Gara-gara dia sandiri ko, tagal dia pung mama-bapa?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus' disciples asked saying, “Father Teacher! Who is it that did wrong/sin, to the point that this person became blind like this? Is it on account of he himself or, because of his mother-father?”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: His disciples asked him, “Teacher,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: His disciples asked him, “Teacher, who sinned, this one or his parents, so that he was born blind?”</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Ini orang buta sonde bekin sala. Deng dia pung mama-bapa ju sonde bekin sala ko dia jadi buta. Dia lahir bagitu, ko biar samua orang bisa dapa lia Tuhan pung bekin bae di dia.<bt>Yesus responded saying, “This blind person did not do wrong. And his mother-father also did not do wrong so that he became blind. He was born like that, so that everyone would be able to see God's goodness done to him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Jesus answered, “Neither this man"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Jesus answered, “Neither this man or his parents sinned. But [this happened] so that the working of God can be seen in him.</Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Tuhan Allah yang utus sang Beta. Jadi kotong musti usaha ko kasi jalan Dia pung karjá waktu taráng masi ada. Te nanti galáp su datang, orang sonde bisa karjá lai.<bt>God is the one who sent/commissioned Me. So (consequently) we-inc must make the effort to carry out His work while there is still light/the light still exists. Cuz (elaboration) later when the darkness has come, people won't be able to work anymore.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: We must do the work"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: We must do the work of him who sent me while it is day. The night comes, when nobody can work.</Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Waktu Beta masi ada di ini dunya, Beta sama ke taráng yang bacaya kasi samua orang.&gt;&gt;<bt>While I am still in this world, I am like light which shines on/for everyone.” [EXEG: NRSV, NLT, Carson; STYLE: having ‘world’ twice is heavy in KM.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: While I am in the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: While I am in the world, I am the light of the world.”</Message></Annotation><note reference="9:5" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 5:14, Yohanis 8:12</note></p>
    <fig path="Cook\CNT\cn01739b.tif" rtfFormat="width:6.5cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:right" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Yesus omong abis bagitu, ju Dia sumbur luda di tana. Ais Dia jongko, ko edok bekin lompor. Ju dia samér itu lompor di itu orang buta pung mata.<bt>After Yesus finished speaking like that, He spat spittle on the ground. Then He squatted, to mix it into mud. Then He smeared it on that blind person's eyes.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lompor = mud ; samér ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">lompor = mud ; samér = smear ; sumbur luda = spit (w/force) can be directed, can imply spray, buang luda = dropping spit ; jongko by itself (short duration) ; dudu jongko = (for awhile, on-going)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="epechrisen: annoint, rub on, smear LITERALLY:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">epechrisen: annoint, rub on, smear LITERALLY: After he said that, he spat on the ground, and made mud from the saliva, and put it on the man's eyes.<span class="Italic">(6)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="7" />Ais Dia pasán bilang, &lt;&lt;Pi di kolam Siloam, ko cuci lu pung muka di situ.&gt;&gt; (Dalam bahasa Ibrani, <span class="Italic">Siloam</span> pung arti bilang, &lt;kirim datang&gt;.) Ais, itu orang buta pi sana, ju dia cuci dia pung muka. Waktu dia bale datang, dia su bisa dapa lia!<bt>The He instructed saying, “Go to the Siloam pool, to wash your face there.” (In the Ibrani language, <span class="Italic">Siloam</span> means ‘send coming’.) Then that blind person went there, and he washed his face. When he came back he was already able to see! [EXEG: not sure of basis for NIV ‘went home’; ‘came back’ seems to have stronger lexical and contextual support, NRSV, NLT (note CEV loses it altogether); “Hebrew” from Carson. NOTE to daughter translations: Siloam = bilingual word play between Hebrew "water sent" and Greek Jesus sent"= MC (channeling of water, sent through conduit), CEV (One who is Sent); TB (yg diutus); LN (send someone, apostelw), Carson (“received its water through a channel which carried (or 'sent') it from the spring of Gihon in the Kidron valley.” also “The suitability of drawing attention to Siloam may have depended simply on its name. As it was called 'Sent', so Jesus was supremely the sent one (cf. notes on 20:21). Moreover, in Isaiah 8:6 the Jews reject the waters of Shiloah; here they reject Jesus.”); Morris (“Originally the name will have had to do with the fact that this water was “sent” into the pool by a channel; the Hebrew is active and in the first place will have referred to this channel, the “sender.” But the pool was given the name quite early (Neh. 3:15; Isa. 8:6). For John such a name has obvious spiritual significance and is not to be overlooked. So he draws attention to the meaning. In this Gospel the thought of being sent is very prominent. Again and again John refers to Jesus as having been “sent” by the Father.”) In KM, “bawa” works for water, but not for Christ. “Utus” works for Christ and reflects the Greek, but doesn't work for water, and doesn't reflect the Hebrew, which is what we're saying here. “Kirim datang” works for both, and beautifully resonates with phrasing that we have been using in many books about the coming of the Messiah.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="@! CEV missing 'came back' ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">@! CEV missing 'came back' ; cuci muka = ; @@ bawa datang aer @@?? Siloam = bilingual word play between Hebrew "water sent" and Greek Jesus sent"= MC (channeling of water, sent through conduit), CEV (One who is Sent); TB (yg diutus); LN (send someone, apostelw), Carson (“received its water through a channel which carried (or 'sent') it from the spring of Gihon in the Kidron valley.” also “The suitability of drawing attention to Siloam may have depended simply on its name. As it was called 'Sent', so Jesus was supremely the sent one (cf. notes on 20:21). Moreover, in Isaiah 8:6 the Jews reject the waters of Shiloah; here they reject Jesus.”); Morris (“Originally the name will have had to do with the fact that this water was “sent” into the pool by a channel; the Hebrew is active and in the first place will have referred to this channel, the “sender.” But the pool was given the name quite early (Neh. 3:15; Isa. 8:6). For John such a name has obvious spiritual significance and is not to be overlooked. So he draws attention to the meaning. In this Gospel the thought of being sent is very prominent. Again and again John refers to Jesus as having been “sent” by the Father.”)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="nipsai: wash (a part of the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">nipsai: wash (a part of the body) LITERALLY: And said to him, "Go, wash in the pool of Siloam (which means, Sent). So he went and washed, and came back seeing.<span class="Italic">(7)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="9:7" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 49:10; 2 Raja-raja dong 20:20; Yesaya 8:6</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Ais itu, ju itu orang pung tatangga dong, deng yang parná lia dia jadi tukang minta-minta, mulai batanya bilang, &lt;&lt;We! Ini ni, orang buta yang dolu maen dudu minta-minta, to?&gt;&gt;<bt>After that, that person's neighbours, and those who had seen him as a beggar, began to ask each other saying, “We! This one here, is the blind person who used to sit around begging, right?”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Therefore his neighbors, and those"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Therefore his neighbors, and those who had seen him begging before, said, "Isn't this the one that used to sit and beg?"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Orang saparu bilang, &lt;&lt;Hoo! Andia dia su!&gt;&gt;<bt>Some people said, “Hoo! [=affirmation] That him alright!”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Orang saparu laen bilang, &lt;&lt;Sonde! Dia tu, cuma mirip-mirip ke itu satu sa!&gt;&gt;<bt>Some other people said, “No! He only just resembles that one!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="= amper sama, muka ba'iko ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">= amper sama, muka ba'iko = resemble (parents with children, cousins)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ma itu orang sandiri kasi tau sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Sonde! Ini beta su! Yang dolu buta tu!&gt;&gt;<bt>But that person himself told them saying, “No! It's me! That one who used to be blind!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Some said, &quot;This is the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Some said, "This is the one!" Others said, "No, he just looks like him." But he said, "I am the one!"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Ais dong tanya sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Karmana sampe lu su bisa dapa lia ni?&gt;&gt;<bt>So they asked him saying, “How is it that you are able to see now?”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: So they said to him,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: So they said to him, "So how were your eyes opened?"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Ju dia manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Bagini! Itu Orang yang nama Yesus tu, bekin lompor, ais Dia taro di beta pung mata. Ju Dia suru sang beta bilang, &lt;Pi di kolam Siloam, ko cuci lu pung muka di situ.&gt; Ais beta bekin iko. Andia ko sakarang beta su bisa dapa lia!&gt;&gt;<bt>He responded saying, “It's like this! That Person named Yesus, made mud, then He put it in my eyes. And He ordered me saying, ‘Go to the Siloam pool, to wash your face there.’ So I did accordingly. That is why now I am able to see!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: He answered, &quot;The man called"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: He answered, "The man called Jesus made mud and put it on my eyes, and told me, 'Go to the pool of Siloam and wash.' And I went and washed, and received sight."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Ais dong tanya sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Ko itu Orang ada di mana?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then they asked him saying, “So where is that Person?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Dia manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Tau lai ni!&gt;&gt;<bt>He responded saying, “Who knows? (idiomatic=I don't know)”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: They said to him, &quot;Where"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: They said to him, "Where is he?" He said, "I don't know."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Orang Farisi dong pareksa orang yang parná buta tu<bt>Farisi people examine/interrogate the person who had once been blind</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13-14" />Naa, itu hari, waktu Yesus bekin lompor, ju bekin orang buta bisa dapa lia tu, jato kaná di orang Yahudi pung hari barenti karjá. Ju dong antar bawa itu orang yang parná buta tu, ko pi mangada di partei agama Farisi pung orang dong.<bt>Naa, [shift] that day, when Yesus made the mud, and made the blind person be able to see, fell on the Yahudi people's day of rest/stopping work. And they (non-referential) took/led that person who had once been blind, to front up (come before an authority figure) to people from the Farisi religious party.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: They brought the one who"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: They brought the one who was blind to the Pharisees. LITERALLY: The day when Jesus made the mud and opened his eyes was the Sabbath.<span class="Italic">(13)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Ais, itu orang Farisi dong tanya sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Coba lu kasi tau doo! Akurang ko lu sakarang su bisa dapa lia?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then those Farisi people asked him saying, “Try and explain this (to us)! Why is it that you-sg now are able to see?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Dia manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Bagini. Itu Orang taro lompor di beta pung mata. Ais beta pi cuci beta pung muka. Sakarang beta su bisa dapa lia.&gt;&gt;<bt>He responded saying, “It's like this. That Person put mud on my eyes. Then I went and washed my face. Now I am able to see.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: So the Pharisees also asked"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: So the Pharisees also asked him how he could see. He told them, "He put mud on my eyes, and I washed, and I see."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Ada orang Farisi saparu bilang, &lt;&lt;Itu Orang yang bekin bae sang lu tu, bukan dari Tuhan Allah. Botong tau, tagal Dia su langgar atoran so'al hari barenti karjá.&gt;&gt;<bt>There were some of the Farisi people who said, “That Person who healed you, is not from God. We-exc know, because He has violated/transgressed the regulation/s about the day of rest.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ada saparu lai yang bilang, &lt;&lt;Karmana sampe orang yang bekin sala bisa bekin tanda-tanda heran bagitu?&gt;&gt; Ais dong deng dong bakanjar sampe tapica-pica.<bt>There were some others who said, “How could it be that a person who does wrong/sin could do various amazing signs like that?” So they argued among themselves to the point that they were divided/factioned.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="schisma: division, split into groups LITERALLY:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">schisma: division, split into groups LITERALLY: Then some of the Pharisees said, "This man is not from God, because he does not keep the Sabbath." But others said, "How can a sinful man do such signs?" And there was a division among them.<span class="Italic">(16)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Jadi dong tanya ulang sang itu orang yang dolu buta bilang, &lt;&lt;Iko lu, itu Orang yang buka ame lu pung mata tu, orang model ke karmana?&gt;&gt;<bt>So (consequently), they again asked the person who had been blind saying, “According to you, that Person who opened your eyes, is what model/type/kind of person?”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="orang macam apa // orang model"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">orang macam apa // orang model ke karmana --&gt; sifat (bae ko sonde)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Dia manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Iko beta, na, Dia tu, Tuhan pung jubir satu.&gt;&gt;<bt>He responded saying, “According to me, na, He is one of God2's *spokespeople.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then they said to the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then they said to the blind man again, "What do you say about him, that he opened your eyes? And he said, "He is a prophet."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Ma orang Yahudi pung bos-bos dong sonde parcaya bilang, itu orang tu, parná buta, ais sakarang su bisa dapa lia. Ju dong suru pi pange dia pung mama-bapa ko datang mangada.<bt>But the bosses of the Yahudi people did not believe that this person had ever been blind, and now was able to see. So they ordered to summon his mother-father to come front up.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But the Jews did not"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But the Jews did not believe that he had been blind and received his sight, until they sent for the parents of the man who had received his sight.</Message></Annotation><v n="19" />Waktu dong su datang, itu bos-bos tanya bilang, &lt;&lt;Ini satu ni, bosong pung ana, ko? Batúl, ko sonde, dia su buta memang dari lahir? Ais karmana ko sakarang dia su bisa dapa lia?&gt;&gt;<bt>When they had come, those bosses asked saying, “This one here, is your child, right? Is it true or not, that he was blind from birth? And how is it that now he is able to see?”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Is this too polite? It needs"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">Is this too polite? It needs to be demanding and condescending.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: They asked them, &quot;Is this"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: They asked them, "Is this your son, who you say was born blind? How does he now see?"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Itu orang pung mama-bapa manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Dia ni, memang botong pung ana. Deng dia su buta memang dari lahir.<bt>That person's mother-father responded saying, “He here really is our-exc child/offspring. And he has been blind from birth.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: His parents answered them, &quot;We"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: His parents answered them, "We know that this is our son, and that he was born blind.</Message></Annotation><v n="21" />Ma botong sonde tau, dia pake apa ko sakarang su bisa dapa lia. Sapa yang buka dia pung mata, botong ju sonde tau. Dia tu, su bésar. Tanya langsung sa, te dia bisa carita sandiri!&gt;&gt;<bt>But we don't know what he used so that now he is able to see. Who it was that opened his eyes, we also don't know. He is big/grown. Jast ask him directly, cuz (elaboration) he is able to tell/narrate (for) himself!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But by what means he"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But by what means he sees now, we don't know. Or who opened his eyes, we don't know. He is of age, ask him. He will speak for himself."</Message></Annotation><v n="22" />Dong omong bagitu, tagal dong taku sang orang Yahudi pung bos-bos dong. Tagal dong tau bilang, itu bos-bos su basakongkol bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo ada orang mangaku bilang, Yesus tu, andia Kristus, na, botong musti usir buang itu orang yang mangaku bagitu dari kotong orang Yahudi pung ruma sambayang.&gt;&gt;<bt>They spoke like that, because they were afraid of the Yahudi people's bosses. Because they knew that those bosses had already conspired/plotted among themselves saying, “If there is a person who acknowledges/confesses that Yesus is Kristus, na, we-exc must evict that person who confesses that from out-inc Yahudi houses of worship.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: His parents said that, because"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: His parents said that, because they feared the Jews, for the Jews had agreed already that if anyone confessed that he was the Christ, he would be put out of the synagogue.</Message></Annotation><v n="23" />Andia ko itu orang pung mama-bapa manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Dia su bésar. Tanya langsung sang dia sa.&gt;&gt;<bt>That is why that person's mother-father responded saying, “He is already grown. Just ask him directly.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Because of that his parents"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Because of that his parents said, "He is of age; ask him."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Ais dong pange ulang sang itu orang yang dolu buta tu. Ju dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bagini! Lu musti omong jujur di Tuhan Allah pung muka ko jaga Dia pung nama bae. Te botong tau parsís, Yesus tu, orang jahat.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then they summoned back that person who had been blind. And they said, “It's like this! You-sg must speak honestly before God to guard His good name/reputation. Cuz (elaboration) we-exc know for sure, that Yesus (known referent) is an evil person.” [EXEG: Gk: give glory to God, here]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dos doksan tooi theooi: = swear"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">dos doksan tooi theooi: = swear that you will tell the truth, not Praise God! More like "don't louse up God's reputation" LITERALLY: So a second time they called the man who had been blind to them and said to him, "Give God the glory [and tell the truth]. We know for sure that this man is a sinner."<span class="Italic">(24)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Orang yang parná buta manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa dong jang mara, é! Te beta sonde tau kalo Dia tu, orang jahat, ko sonde. Yang beta tau parsís, andia, dolu beta buta; ma sakarang beta su bisa dapa lia.&gt;&gt;<bt>The person who had been blind responded saying, “I apologise if I'm out of line here (Lit: Fathers (coll.) don't be angry, é!) Cuz (elaboration) I don't know if He is an evil person, or not. What I know for sure is that, I used to be blind; but now I am able to see.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: So he answered, &quot;Whether he"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: So he answered, "Whether he is a sinner or not, I don't know. I know one thing, that I was blind, now I see."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="26" />Dong tanya sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Ko Dia bekin apa sang lu? Dia buka lu pung mata karmana?&gt;&gt;<bt>They asked him saying, “So what did He do to you? How did He open your eyes?”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: They said to him, &quot;What"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: They said to him, "What did he do to you? How did he open your eyes?"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />Ju dia manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Hee! Ko tadi beta su carita, ma bosong sonde mau dengar. Akurang ko bosong mau beta carita ulang lai? Mangkali bapa dong ju mau jadi Dia pung ana bua, ko?&gt;&gt;<bt>And he responded saying, “Hee! I already told you-pl just now, but you didn't/don't want to listen. Why is it that you want me to tell it again? Perhaps you (fathers) also want to become His disciples, or (what)?”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: He answered them, &quot;I told"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: He answered them, "I told you already and you did not listen. Why do you want to hear it again? You don't want to become his disciples too, do you?"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Ais dong maki-maki sang dia, ju dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Biar ko lu sa yang jadi Dia pung ana bua! Te botong ni, ba'i Musa pung ana bua dong.<bt>So/then they cursed/swore at/verbally abused him, and they said, “Leave it at just you being His disciple! Cuz (elaboration) we-exc here, are grandfather Musa's disciples.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="eloidoreisan: insult, revile, slander, NLT curse"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">eloidoreisan: insult, revile, slander, NLT curse LITERALLY: Then they insulted him and said, "You are his disciple! We are Moses' disciples.<span class="Italic">(28)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="29" />Botong tau Tuhan Allah ba'omong deng Musa. Ma botong sonde tau itu Orang tu, datang dari lobang mana.&gt;&gt;<bt>We know that God spoke with Musa. But we don't know what hole that Person came from/out of [+derogatory].”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="with contempt"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">with contempt</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: We know that God spoke"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: We know that God spoke to Moses. But we do not know where this one came from.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="30" />Orang yang dolu buta manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Heran, é! Bosong sonde tau Dia datang dari mana. Padahal Dia yang buka beta pung mata ko sakarang beta su bisa dapa lia.<bt>The person who had been blind responded saying, “That's amazing, é! You-pl don't know where He came from. Whereas in fact, He is the one who opened my eyes so now I am able to see.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: The man answered them, &quot;This"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: The man answered them, "This is amazing, that you do not know where he came from, and yet he opened my eyes.</Message></Annotation><v n="31" />Kotong samua tau bilang, Tuhan Allah sonde dengar sang orang jahat, to? Ma Tuhan dengar sang orang hati lurus, yang idop bekin iko Dia pung mau.<bt>All of us-inc know that God doesn't listen to evil people, right? But God2 listens to people with straight/honest/righteous livers, who live according to His will/desires.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: We know that God does"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: We know that God does not listen to sinners, but if anyone is godly and does his will, he hears him.</Message></Annotation><note reference="9:31" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 66:18,19</note><v n="32" />Mulai dari Tuhan Allah bekin langit deng bumi sampe sakarang ni, balóm parná ada satu carita ju, so'al orang yang bekin bae orang yang su buta dari lahir, ko dia bisa dapa lia.<bt>Beginning from God making the sky and earth (STYLE: doublet associated with the whole of creation) up until now, there has not yet been a story about a person who healed a person who had been blind from birth so that he was able to see.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: From the beginning of the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: From the beginning of the world, it has never been heard of that anyone has opened the eyes of a man born blind.</Message></Annotation><v n="33" />Jadi, kalo Yesus bukan datang dari Tuhan Allah, pasti Dia sonde bisa bekin apa-apa, to?&gt;&gt;<bt>So (consequently), if Yesus did not come from God, surely He wouldn't be able to do anything, right?”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: If this one were not"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: If this one were not from God, he couldn't do anything."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="34" />Ju dong manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Weh! Lu ni, orang jahat dari lu pung mama barana ame sang lu! Karmana sampe lu pikir lu bisa ajar bale sang botong?&gt;&gt; Ais ju dong usir buang sang dia dari dong pung ruma sambayang.<bt>And they responded saying, “Weh! You here are an evil person from (the time) your mother gave birth to you! How is it that you think you are able to teach us-exc?” So/then they evicted him from their houses of worship. [EXEG: Carson, Morris, NLT, CEV]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: They said to him, &quot;You"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: They said to him, "You were born entirely in sin! Are you teaching us?" And they threw him out.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Orang yang hati buta<bt>People who are blind in their livers/hearts</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="35" />Waktu Yesus dapa dengar dong su usir buang itu orang yang parná buta dari ruma sambayang, ju Dia pi cari sang itu orang, sampe dapa. Ju Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Karmana! Lu parcaya sang Manusia Tulen, ko?&gt;&gt;<bt>When Yesus (happened to) hear that they had evicted that person who had been blind from their houses of worship, He went to look for that person, until (He) found (him). And He said, “How about it! Do you beleive in the Son of Man (Authentic/Ideal Human)?”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Jesus heard that they had"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Jesus heard that they had thrown him out, and he found him and said, "Do you believe in the Son of Man?"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="36" />Dia tanya bale bilang, &lt;&lt;Ko Dia tu, sapa, Bos? Tolong kasi tau dolo, ko biar beta bisa parcaya sang Dia.&gt;&gt;<bt>He asked back saying, “So who is He, Bos? Please tell me first/now, so that I can believe in Him.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: He answered him, &quot;Who is"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: He answered him, "Who is he, Lord/Sir, so that I can believe in him?"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="37" />Ju Yesus kasi tau bilang, &lt;&lt;Lu su katumu sang Dia. Dia tu, andia Beta ni, yang sakarang ada ba'omong deng lu.&gt;&gt;<bt>And Yesus told (him) saying, “You have already met Him. He is Me, who is now speaking with you.” [NOTE to daughter trans: ‘see’ resonates nicely with ‘blind’; but it may be more natural in the context to say ‘met’.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hewrakas: see, visit, experience, understand LITERALLY:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">hewrakas: see, visit, experience, understand LITERALLY: Jesus said to him, "You have already seen him, and he is the one who is talking to you."<span class="Italic">(37)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="38" />Ais, itu orang bilang, &lt;&lt;Bos, beta parcaya!&gt;&gt; Ju dia tikam lutut ko sémba sang Yesus.<bt>So/then that person said, “Bos, I believe!” And he bowed to worship Yesus. [EXEG: Carson notes that the physical sense of ‘bow before’ is unambiguous, but observes that the Evangelist probably used it at two levels to include the sense of ‘worship’; Implication: translating ‘worship’ as primary is missing the action, whereas translating ‘bow down’ is safe. both is OK, but may be heavy/overtranslation.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="prosekuneisen: worship, prostrate, bow down, do"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">prosekuneisen: worship, prostrate, bow down, do obeisance to, bow to worship LITERALLY: He said, "Lord, I believe!" And he bowed down before him."<span class="Italic">(38)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="39" />Ais Yesus kasi tau sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta datang di ini dunya ko kasi tunju orang pung sala-sala dong, ko biar orang buta bisa dapa lia, deng orang yang bisa lia jadi buta.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus told him saying, “I came to this world to show people's wrongs/sins, so that blind people can see, and people who can see become blind.” [NOTE: If you spiritualise too much in this verse, the reactions in the next verse don't make sense.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Jesus said to him, &quot;For"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Jesus said to him, "For judgment I came into the world, so that those who do not see may see, and those who see may be made blind."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="40" />Di situ ada barapa orang Farisi yang dengar Dia pung omong tu. Ju dong tanya bilang, &lt;&lt;Karmana, ni? Su jalás-jalás, botong sonde buta, to?&gt;&gt;<bt>There, there were several Farisi people who heard what He was saying. So they asked saying, “How is this? It's quite clear that we-exc are not blind, right?” [NOTE: Set up question so expected answer is confirmation of their assumption.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Some from the Pharisees heard"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Some from the Pharisees heard that, and said to him, "We're not blind, are we?"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="41" />Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Bagini. Kalo bosong memang buta, na, sonde ada yang kasi sala sang bosong. Ma bosong bilang, bosong tu, orang yang bisa lia. Andia ko bosong masi pikol bosong pung sala.&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus responded saying, “It's like this. If you were really blind, na, nobody would fault/blame/accuse you. But you say that you are people who are able to see. That is why you still carry your wrong/sin.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Jesus said to them, &quot;If"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Jesus said to them, "If you were blind, you would not have sin. But now you say that you see, so you remain in your sin."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Umpama so'al gambala deng dia pung domba<bt>*Illustration/parable about a shepherd and his sheep</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="10" />
      <v n="1" />Yesus omong pake satu umpama bilang, &lt;&lt;Yang Beta kasi tau sang bosong ni, batúl. Domba ada pung kandang. Kalo ada orang yang sonde maso lewat pintu, ma nae ko maso lewat pagar, na, su jalás, dia tu, pancuri.<bt>Yesus spoke using an illustration/parable saying, “What I am telling you-pl her/now is true. Sheep have their pens/corrals. If there is a person who doesn't enter by/via the door/gate, but climbs up to get in by/via the fence, na, it's clear that he is a thief. [DISCOURSE (information load): Trying to force “thief and robber” is too heavy in KM. One is seen as reinforcing the other, not adding info.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: &quot;This is true, what I"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: "This is true, what I am telling you: He who doesn't go into the sheep pen by the door, but climbs in another way, is a thief and a robber.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="HK-LB\LB00014c.tif" rtfFormat="width:6.5cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:right" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="2" />Ma yang maso iko pintu tu, andia domba pung gambala yang piara sang dong.<bt>But the one who enters through the door/gate, is the *sheep's *shepherd who cares for/raises them.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But he who goes in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But he who goes in by the gate is the shepherd of the sheep.</Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Tukang jaga pintu kanál itu gambala, ais buka pintu kasi sang dia. Domba dong ju kanál itu gambala pung suara. Ais, kalo dia pange dong pung nama satu-satu, dong iko sang dia pi luar.<bt>The guard/watchman at the door/gate knows/recognises that shepherd, and so opens the door/gate for him. The sheep also know/recognise that shepherd's voice. So then, if/when he calls each of their names, they follow him going outside.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: The gatekeeper opens the gate"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: The gatekeeper opens the gate for him. The sheep hear his voice, and he calls his own sheep by name, and leads them out.</Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Waktu dia antar sang dong kaluar, dia jalan di muka. Domba dong iko dari balakang, tagal dong kanál dia pung suara.<bt>When he leads them outside, he walks in front. The sheep follow from behind, because they know/recognise his voice.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: When he takes his own"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: When he takes his own sheep out, he goes in front of them, and the sheep follow him, because they know his voice.</Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Kalo ada orang yang domba dong sonde kanál, na, dong sonde iko sang dia. Ma dong lari fuik, tagal dong sonde kanál orang asing pung suara.&gt;&gt;<bt>If there is a person who the sheep don't know/recognise, na, they don't follow him. But they run off, because they don't know/recognise the stranger's voice.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: They will not follow a"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: They will not follow a stranger, but will run away from him, because they do not know the voice of strangers."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Biar Yesus carita itu umpama kasi sang dong, ma dong sonde mangarti Dia pung maksud ju.<bt>Even though Yesus told that illustration to them, nevertheless they didn't understand His meaning.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Jesus told them this parable,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Jesus told them this parable, but they did not understand what he was telling them.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus sama ke gambala yang bae [\s2]<bt>The Lord Yesus is like a good shepherd [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Ais Yesus kasi tau tamba sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Yang Beta kasi tau sang bosong ni, batúl. Beta sama ke pintu di domba pung kandang.<bt>Then Yesus explained further to them saying, “What I am telling you is true. I am like the door/gate in the sheep's pen/corral.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then Jesus said to them"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then Jesus said to them again, "This is true what I am telling you, that I am the door of the sheep.</Message></Annotation><v n="8" />Samua orang yang datang lebe dolo dari Beta, dong sama ke pancuri. Biar dong pange-pange, ma domba dong sonde dengar sang dong.<bt>Everyone who came before Me are like thieves. Even if they kept caling on and on, nevertheless the sheep don't listen to those people.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: All that ever came before"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: All that ever came before me are thieves and robbers, but the sheep did not hear them.</Message></Annotation><v n="9" />Ais Beta sama ke itu pintu. Kalo ada yang mau maso lewat Beta, Tuhan Allah mau kasi salamat sang dia dari dia pung sala-sala dong. Itu sama ke dia maso pi Tuhan pung tampa, lewat Beta yang jadi dia pung pintu. Deng orang yang maso lewat Beta, dia jalan bebas pi mana sa, deng dapa makan-minum yang batúl.<bt>So then I am like that door/gate. If there is (someone) who wants to enter by/via Me, God is going to save him from his wrongs/sins. That is the same as if He enters into God2's place, by/via Me who is its door/gate. And the person who enters by/via Me, he is free to go wherever, and get/obtain real/true food-drink. [EXEG: (Morris) “We should not attempt to find some esoteric meaning for ‘come in and go out.’ It is simply an expression to indicate free and secure movement (cf. Knox, ‘he will come and go at will’).”; NLT = wherever they go.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="one UNS took last sentence of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">one UNS took last sentence of /makan-minum yang bae/ to prosperity</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: I am the door. If"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: I am the door. If anyone will go in through me, he will be saved, and will go in and out and find pasture.</Message></Annotation><note reference="10:9" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 118:20</note><v n="10" />Pancuri dong cuma bekin kaco sa, te dong datang ko curi, bunu bekin mati, deng kasi ancor buang orang pung idop. Ma Beta bawa idop yang paling bae, te Beta datang ko biar orang bisa idop tanáng, deng idop yang batúl.<bt>Thieves only bring chaos/disorder/disruption, cuz (elaboration) they come to steal, kill/murder, and ruin/destroy a person's life. But I bring the best life, cuz (elaboration) I come so that a person can live calmly/safe, and have real/true life. [EXEG: Carson]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: The thief only comes to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: The thief only comes to steal, kill, and destroy. I have come that they might have life, and have it more abundantly.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Pancuri dong cuma datang ko curi,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">Pancuri dong cuma datang ko curi, bunu bekin mati, deng kasi ancor buang (satu tampa). Ma Beta datang ko biar orang dong bisa idop di dong pung hati, deng dapa idop yang batúl.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Beta ju sama ke satu gambala yang bae. Te gambala yang bae su sadia sarakan dia pung diri sampe mati, ko biar dia pung domba dong bisa idop.<bt>I am also like a good shepherd. Cuz (elaboration) a good shepherd is ready/prepared to turn over/surrender/give up himself to the point of death, so that his sheep can live. [EXEG: (Carson): means no more than that he is prepared to do so. He is willing to risk his life for the sheep.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: I am the good shepherd."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: I am the good shepherd. The good shepherd gives his life for his sheep.</Message></Annotation><v n="12" />Ma orang karjá yang bukan itu domba dong pung tuan, kalo dia lia ada satu anjing utan datang, ju dia lari fuik, ko kasi tenga itu domba dong di situ. Ais, anjing utan tangkap ame sang domba, ju domba yang laen dong lari batasiram.<bt>But a worker who is not the master/owner of those sheep, if he sees a wild dong come, he runs off, and abandons the sheep there. Then the wild dog catches the sheep, and the other sheep run away scattering (in all directions).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lari talamburan = lari tasiram"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">lari talamburan = lari tasiram</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But he who is a"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But he who is a hired man, and not the shepherd, who doesn't own the sheep, sees the wolf coming, and leaves the sheep, and runs away, and the wolf catches them, and scatters the sheep.</Message></Annotation><v n="13" />Itu orang karjá lari, tagal dia cuma karjá cari doi sa. Dia sonde toe ko mau jaga bae-bae sang itu domba dong.<bt>That worker runs, because he is only working for money. He doesn't care to guard the sheep carefully.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: The hired man runs away"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: The hired man runs away because he is a hired man, and does not care about the sheep.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Batúl! Beta sama ke gambala yang bae. Beta kanál deng Beta pung domba dong. Deng dong ju kanál sang Beta.<bt>That's true! I'm like a good shepherd. I know/recognise My sheep. And they also know/recognise Me.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: &quot;I am the good shepherd,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: "I am the good shepherd, and I know my sheep, and they know me.</Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Itu sama ke Bapa di sorga kanál sang Beta, deng Beta ju kanál sang Dia. Beta ju su sadia sarakan Beta pung diri sampe mati, ko biar Beta pung domba bisa idop.<bt>It's like Father in heaven knows/recognises Me, and I also know/recognise Him. I am also ready/prepared to turn over/give up Myself to the point of death, so that My sheep can live.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: As the Father knows me,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: As the Father knows me, even so I know the Father, and I lay down my life for the sheep.</Message></Annotation><note reference="10:15" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 11:27, Lukas 10:22</note><v n="16" />Ada Beta pung domba laen, yang balóm bagabung deng Beta pung domba di sini dong. Beta musti pi kumpul ame sang dong ju. Nanti kalo dong su dengar Beta pung suara, dong kanál memang. Ais ju dong datang bagabung ko jadi satu kumpul yang ada pung satu gambala.<bt>I have other sheep, who have not yet joined with My sheep here. I must go gather them together. Later when they have heard My voice, they will know/recognise (Me) immediately. So then they will come and join into one gathering/flock that has one shepherd. [EXEG: building on higher level context with 10:3-5]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: I have other sheep which"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: I have other sheep which are not from this flock. I must bring them too. They will hear my voice, and they will become one flock and there will be one shepherd.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Tagal itu, Beta pung Bapa di sorga sayang sang Beta. Te Beta su sadia sarakan Beta pung diri sampe mati, ko Beta bisa idop kambali.<bt>Because of that, My Father in heaven loves Me. Cuz (elaboration) I am ready/prepared to give up Myself to the point of death, so I can live again/come back to life. [EXEG: Carson, HCE]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: &quot;Because of this the Father"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: "Because of this the Father loves me, because I give up my life, that I may receive it again.</Message></Annotation><v n="18" />Sonde ada orang yang paksa Beta ko mati, ma Beta sandiri yang sadia sarakan Beta pung diri sampe mati. Beta ada pung hak ko sarakan Beta pung diri. Beta ju ada pung hak ko ame kambali. Ini parenta ni, Beta su tarima dari Beta pung Bapa di sorga.&gt;&gt;<bt>There is nobody who forces Me to die, but I myself am the one who is prepared to give up Myself to the point of death. I have the right to give up Myself. I also have the right to take it back. This command here, I have received from My father in heaven.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Nobody takes it from me,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Nobody takes it from me, but I lay it down by myself. I have power to lay it down and I have power to take it back again. This commandment I have received from my Father."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Tagal dong dengar Yesus pung omong bagitu, ju orang Yahudi dong bakanjar ulang lai.<bt>Because they heard Yesus talking like that, the Yahudi people were arguing again.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: There was a division again"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: There was a division again among the Jews because of these words.</Message></Annotation><v n="20" />Ada banya dari dong yang bilang, &lt;&lt;Weh! Ini orang ni, gila! Deng Dia ju takaná setan! Akurang ko bosong mau dengar ame sang Dia?&gt;&gt;<bt>There were many of the who said, “Weh! This person here is crazy! And He has also been possessed by an evil spirit. Why is it that you want to listen to Him?”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Many of them said, &quot;He"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Many of them said, "He has an evil spirit, and is crazy! Why do you listen to him?"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Ma ada saparu lai yang bilang, &lt;&lt;Ini bukan orang gila pung omong, to? Kata-kata bagitu tu, sonde parná kaluar dari setan pung mulu! Deng setan dong ju sonde bekin orang buta bisa dapa lia, to?&gt;&gt;<bt>But there were some others who said, “This is not the talk of a crazy person, right? Words like that have never come out of an evil spirit's mouth! And evil spirits also don't make blind people able to see, right?”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Others said, &quot;These are not"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Others said, "These are not the words of someone who has an evil spirit! Can an evil spirit open the eyes of the blind?"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Orang Yahudi pung bos-bos sonde mau tarima sang Tuhan Yesus<bt>The bosses of the Yahudi people don't want to accept the Lord Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Itu waktu, orang Yahudi ada mau bekin dong pung agama pung hari bae satu. Itu hari bae tu, jato kaná di musim dingin. Di itu pesta, orang Yahudi dong inga waktu orang laen su bekin kamomos sang Tuhan pung Ruma Sambayang Pusat di kota Yerusalem, ais dong bekin barisi ko tabis kambali.<bt>At that time, the Yahudi people were about to make one of their religious festivals/holidays. That holiday fell on/during the cold season. At that feast, the Yahudi people remembered when other people/ foreigners had defiled/made dirty God2's Temple in the city of Yerusalem, and then they had made it clean/purified it to consecrate/ordain it again.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Marge suggests eventually moving this info"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">Marge suggests eventually moving this info to Glossary.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Chanukah, after Antiochus Epiphanes had defiled"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">Chanukah, after Antiochus Epiphanes had defiled it LITERALLY: It was time for the Festival of Dedication in Jerusalem, and it was winter.<span class="Italic">(22)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="10:22" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Sakarang ni, orang Yahudi dong subu itu hari bae bilang, <span class="Italic">Hanuka,</span> yang jato deka-deka di hari Natal. Dia pung carita bagini: waktu taon 167 SM, ada satu jendral orang Siria, nama Antiokus Epifanes, yang bekin ancor kota Yerusalem. Dia ju bekin kamomos Ruma Sambayang Pusat, tagal dia bongkar buang meja korban di situ, ais dia kasi badiri dia pung barang songgo di situ. Tagal itu, orang Yahudi dong marontak. Ais tanggal 25, bulan <span class="Italic">Kislef,</span> taon 164 SM, dong bekin barisi kambali Ruma Sambayang Pusat, ju dong bekin satu acara ko tabis ulang.<bt>These days the Yahudi people refer to that holiday/festival saying, <span class="Italic">Hanuka</span>, which falls quite near to Natal (Christmas). It's story is like this: in the year 167 BC, there was a Sirian general, named Antiokus Epifanes, who destroyed the city of Yerusalem. He also defiled/made dirty the Temple, because he broke up/destroyed the *altar (sacrifice table) there, and he erected/set up his objects of traditional worship there. Because of that, the Yahudi people rebelled. Then on the 25th day of <span class="Italic">Kislef</span> in the year 164 BC, they made clean/purified the Temple again, and they made a ceremony to consecrate/ordain it again.</bt></note><v n="23" />Yesus ada jalan kuliling dalam Ruma Sambayang Pusat pung kintal, di tampa yang dong subu bilang, &lt;Ruma Loos Raja Soleman&gt;.<bt>Yesus was walking around inside the Temple yard, in the place they refer to as ‘King Soleman's Pavilion’ (=large, open-sided).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Soleman = Kupang ; Salomo ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">Soleman = Kupang ; Salomo = Indonesian</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Jesus was walking in the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Jesus was walking in the temple, in Solomon's Porch/Colonnade.</Message></Annotation><v n="24" />Ju orang Yahudi pung bos-bos datang makarubu sang Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Weh! Botong musti tunggu tarús sampe kapan, baru botong bisa dapa tau? Kalo Bos ni, andia Kristus, na, tolong kasi tau taráng-taráng doo.&gt;&gt;<bt>And the bosses of the Yahudi people came and crowded around Him saying, “Weh! How long will we-exc have to keep waiting, before we can find out? If Bos (=You) here are Kristus, na, please tell us plainly/openly.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="badiri kapúng = keliling, encircle"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">badiri kapúng = keliling, encircle</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: The Jews came around him"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: The Jews came around him and said to him, "How long will you keep us in suspense? If you are the Christ, tell us plainly."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta su kasi tau memang, ma bosong sonde mau parcaya. Padahal hal-hal yang Beta bekin, samua iko Beta pung Bapa pung parenta sa. Itu hal dong yang kasi tunju bilang, Beta ni, sapa.<bt>Yesus responded saying, “I have already told you (before this), but you don't want to believe. Whereas in fact, the things that I do, are just following My Father's commands. Those are the things which show who I am.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Jesus answered them, &quot;I told"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Jesus answered them, "I told you already, but you do not believe. The things that I do in my Father's name speak for me.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Yesus manyao, bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta su kasi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">Yesus manyao, bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta su kasi tau memang, ma bosong sonde mau parcaya. Jadi, biar itu hal-hal yang Beta bekin tagal Beta pung Bapa suru sang Beta bagitu, yang kasi tunju, bilang, Beta ni, sapa.</Message></Annotation><v n="26" />Ma bosong sonde parcaya sang Beta, tagal bosong bukan Beta pung domba.<bt>But you don't believe in Me, because you are not My sheep.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But you do not believe,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But you do not believe, because you are not my sheep.</Message></Annotation><v n="27" />Te Beta pung domba yang batúl tu, kanál Beta pung suara. Dong ju iko sang Beta. Beta ju kanál sang dong.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) My real/true sheep know/recognise My voice. They also follow/obey Me. I also know/recognise them.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="akouousin: hear, able to hear, receive"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">akouousin: hear, able to hear, receive news, pay attention to, obey, understand LITERALLY: My sheep hear my voice, and I know them, and they follow me.<span class="Italic">(27)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="28" />Beta kasi sang dong idop yang batúl yang sonde tau putus-putus, deng dong ju sonde tapisa buang dari Tuhan. Sonde ada satu orang ju yang bisa rampas ame sang dong dari Beta.<bt>I give them real life that never ends, and they also are not separated off/cut off from God2. There is not one person who can snatch them (successfully) from Me. [EXEG: on “perish” see note at 3:16.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: I give them eternal life,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: I give them eternal life, and they will never perish/be destroyed, and no one can snatch them out of my hand.</Message></Annotation><v n="29" />Beta pung Bapa di sorga yang sarakan sang dong kasi Beta. Dia lebe hebat dari samua-samua. Andia ko sonde ada satu ju yang bisa rampas ame sang dong dari Dia pung tangan.<bt>My Father in heaven is the one who handed them over/entrusted them to Me. He is greater/more amazing than everything. That is why there is nobody who can snatch them from His hand.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: My Father, who has given"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: My Father, who has given them to me, is greater than all, and no one can snatch them out of my Father's hand.</Message></Annotation><v n="30" />Te Beta pung Bapa deng Beta tu, satu.&gt;&gt;<bt>Cuz (elaboration) My Father and I are one/united.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: My Father and I are"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: My Father and I are one.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="31" />Dengar bagitu, ju orang Yahudi pung bos-bos angka batu satu kali lai, ko mau lempar bekin mati sang Yesus.<bt>Hearing that, the bosses of the Yahudi people picked up stones once again, to throw killing Yesus. [EXEG: Carson, NLT, CEV.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Again the Jews picked up"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Again the Jews picked up stones to stone him.</Message></Annotation><v n="32" />Ju Yesus kasi tau sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Heh! Beta su kasi tunju banya hal yang bae dari Beta pung Bapa. Bosong ada pake hal bae yang mana, ko mau lempar bekin mati sang Beta?&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus told them saying, “Hee! [+annoyance] I have shown (you) many good thing from My Father. Which of these good things are you-pl using to stone Me to death?”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Jesus responded to them, &quot;I"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Jesus responded to them, "I showed you many good deeds from my Father. For which of those deeds do you stone me?"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="33" />Dong manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Botong sonde lempar sang lu tagal lu bekin hal bae. Ma botong kasi hukum lempar sang lu tagal lu su hojat barát! Te lu cuma manusia, ma lu angka diri sama ke Tuhan Allah! Su talalu lai!&gt;&gt;<bt>They responded saying, “We-exc are not stoning you, because you do good things. But we are punishing you by stoning, because you have *blasphemed/slandered/ insulted (God) in a serious/heavy way! Cuz (elaboration) you are only human, but you elevate yourself to be the same as God. That's way beyond (what's acceptable)!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: The Jews answered him, &quot;We"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: The Jews answered him, "We are not stoning you for good deeds, but for blasphemy, and because you are a man, but you make yourself God!"</Message></Annotation><note reference="10:33" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kapala Agama dong pung Atoran 24:16</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="34" />Ju Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Karmana? Di itu Atoran Agama yang bosong pegang tu, ada tulis bilang, &lt;Beta kasi tau memang bilang, bosong bos-bos ni, tuhan&gt;.<bt>Then Yesus responded saying, “How's that? In those Religious Regulations that you hold, it is written saying, ‘I have told (you) saying, you-pl leaders/bosses here, are god/s’. [EXEG: Carson, Morris, TRT, favour interpretation that this is about leaders, not about all of God's people. NOTE to daughter translations: We tried ‘dewa’ here instead of ‘tuhan’, but it broke the logic of Jesus' argument thru vs. 36.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Jesus answered them, &quot;Isn't it"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Jesus answered them, "Isn't it written in your Law, "I said, 'You are gods'?</Message></Annotation><note reference="10:34" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 82:1,2,6</note><v n="35" />Naa. Kotong su tau bilang, samua yang ada tatulis dalam Tuhan pung Tulisan Barisi tu, batúl, deng sonde bisa tahapus buang. Tuhan sandiri subu sang itu orang dong bilang, dong tu, &lt;tuhan&gt;.<bt>Naa. [shift, setting up a conclusion] We-inc already know that everything that is written in the Scriptures is true, and cannot be erased/wiped away/annulled. God2 himself refers to those people saying they are ‘gods’.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lutheinai: abolished, annulled, dismissed, undone, transgressed,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">lutheinai: abolished, annulled, dismissed, undone, transgressed, broken, destroyed, done away with LITERALLY: If he called them 'gods', to whom the word of God came, and the Scripture cannot be broken,<span class="Italic">(35)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Jadi, kalo Tuhan sandiri subu sang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">Jadi, kalo Tuhan sandiri subu sang itu orang dong, bilang, dong tu, &lt;tuhan&gt;,</Message></Annotation><v n="36" />Jadi karmana sampe bosong bisa bilang Beta ada hojat tagal Beta bilang Beta jadi Tuhan pung Ana? Sonde maso di akal! Te Bapa di sorga yang tunju ame sang Beta, deng Dia yang utus sang Beta datang di ini dunya.<bt>So (consequently), how is it that you can say I am blaspheming because I said I am God2's Child? That doesn't make sense! Cuz (elaboration) Father in heaven is the one who designated Me, and He is the one who sent/commissioned Me to come to this world.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: how can you say I"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: how can you say I blaspheme, the one the Father dedicated and sent into the world, because I said, 'I am the Son of God'?</Message></Annotation><v n="37" />Bagini. Kalo Beta sonde kasi jalan Beta pung Bapa pung karjá, na, bosong sonde usa parcaya sang Beta.<bt>It's like this. If I do not carry out My Father's work, na, you don't need to believe in Me.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: If I am not doing"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: If I am not doing my Father's deeds, do not believe me.</Message></Annotation><v n="38" />Ma Beta ada kasi jalan Dia pung karjá tarús. Jadi biar bosong sonde mau parcaya sang Beta, ma paling sadiki, bosong musti tarima tanda heran yang Beta bekin. Deng bagitu, bosong ju bisa mangarti bilang, Beta pung Bapa ada ta'ika deng Beta. Deng Beta ju ada ta'ika deng Dia.&gt;&gt;<bt>But I do carry out His work continually. So (consequently) even though you don't want to believe in Me, nevertheless in the very least, you must accept the amazing signs that I do/have done. In that way you can also understand that My Father is bound/linked with Me. And I am also bound/linked with Him” [EXEG: “the works that I do” = ??; first group of UNS's got it no problem, but UNS's in consultant check didn't; NIV, Morris, Carson “miracles” (but not limited to).]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But if I do them,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But if I do them, even though you do not believe me, believe the deeds, that you may know and understand that the Father is in me, and I am in the Father.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="39" />Ais dong coba ulang ko mau tangkap sang Dia, ma Dia lolos.<bt>Then they tried to catch/arrest Him, but He got through safely.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: So they tried again to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: So they tried again to take him, but he escaped from them.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="40" />Ju Yesus pi ulang di kali Yarden pung sablá, di itu tampa partama yang dolu Yohanis sarani orang. Ais Dia tenga tahan di sana.<bt>Then Yesus went again to the other side of the Yarden river, to that first place where Yohanis had previously baptised people. Then2 He stayed there temporarily.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And he went again beyond"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And he went again beyond Jordan, to the place where John baptized at first, and he stayed there.</Message></Annotation><note reference="10:40" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yohanis 1:28</note><v n="41" />Banya orang datang cari sang Dia. Ju dong ba'omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Yohanis sonde bekin tanda heran apa-apa. Ma samua yang dia omong so'al ini Yesus ni, batúl, é!&gt;&gt;<bt>Many people came looking for Him. And they spoke (among themselves) saying, “Yohanis didn't do any amazing signs. But everything he said about this Yesus here is true, é!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Many people came to him."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Many people came to him. And they said, "John certainly did no miracles, but everything John said about this one was true!'</Message></Annotation><v n="42" />Ju banya orang parcaya sang Dia di sana.<bt>And many people believed in Him there.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And many believed in him"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And many believed in him there.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Lasarus pung mati<bt>The death of Lasarus (implies an internally complex event)</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="11" />
      <v n="1-2" />Ada satu orang, nama Lasarus. Dia tenga di kampong Betania, sama-sama deng dia pung kaka parampuan dua, Maria deng Marta. (Naa, ini Maria ni, yang po'a minya wangi di Tuhan Yesus pung kaki, ais lap pake dia pung rambu sandiri.) Satu kali, Lasarus saki barát.<bt>There was a person named Lasarus. He lived in the village of Betania, together with his two older sisters, Maria and Marta. (Naa, this Maria here, is the one who poured aromatic oil on the Lord Yesus' feet, and then wiped using her own hair.) One time, Lasarus became severely ill. [EXEG: (Morris) It seems that Martha was the elder of the two; (TRT) For some languages it is necessary to specify/say whether Mary and Martha were older or younger than Lazarus. We do not know for sure who was oldest, but some Bible scholars think that Martha was oldest and Lazarus was youngest, based on the order of their names in verses 5 and 19. In the Bible the names of brothers and sisters are often listed according to their ages. All three were adults,]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: 1 There was a sick"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: 1 There was a sick man, Lazarus from Bethany, from the town of Mary and her sister Martha. 2 (It was Mary who anointed the Lord with perfume, and wiped his feet with her hair, whose brother Lazarus was sick.)</Message></Annotation><note reference="11:1-2" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lukas 10:38-39; Yohanis 12:3</note><v n="3" />Ju dia pung kaka parampuan dong kirim pasán sang Yesus bilang, &lt;&lt;Bos pung tamán, andia Lasarus, ada saki barát.&gt;&gt;<bt>So his older sisters sent a message to Yesus saying, “Bos's friend, that is Lasarus, is severely ill.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: So his sisters sent word"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: So his sisters sent word to him, saying, "Look, Lord, the one you love is sick."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Waktu Yesus dengar itu pasán, ju Dia omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Ini panyaki sonde bekin dia mati. Tuhan Allah ada mau pake ini hal ko kasi tunju Dia pung hebat. Ko biar nanti orang dong ju angka tinggi-tinggi sang Beta, andia Tuhan pung Ana.&gt;&gt;<bt>When Yesus heard that message, He spoke saying, “This sickness will not make him die. God is going to use this matter to show His amazingness/incredibleness. so that people will *glorify (elevate way up high) Me, that is, God2's Child.” [EXEG: Carson: Gk. will not lead to death = not result ultimately in death. NLT: not end in death.] [EXEG: Gk: glory here]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: When Jesus heard that, he"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: When Jesus heard that, he said, "He will not die from this sickness. It is for the glory of God, that the Son of God might be glorified by it."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Naa, Yesus sayang sang Marta, Maria, deng dong dua pung adi Lasarus.<bt>Naa, Yesus loved Marta, Maria, and their younger brother Lasarus. [EXEG: see note on vs. 1]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Now Jesus loved Martha and"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Now Jesus loved Martha and her sister, and Lazarus.</Message></Annotation><v n="6" />Waktu Dia dapa dengar bilang, Lasarus ada saki, Dia masi tenga dua hari lai di kali Yarden pung sablá.<bt>When He heard that Lasarus was sick, He still stayed another two days on the other side of the Yarden river.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: So when he had heard"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: So when he had heard that he was sick, he still stayed two days in the place where he was.</Message></Annotation><v n="7" />Ais itu, Dia kasi tau sang Dia pung ana bua dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Mari ko kotong pi ulang lai di Lasarus pung tampa di propinsi Yudea.&gt;&gt;<bt>After that, He told His disciples saying, “Let's go again to Lasarus' place in the province of Yudea.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then after that he said"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then after that he said to his disciples, "Let us go into Judea again."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Ma Dia pung ana bua dong protes bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa Guru. Baru-baru ni, orang Yahudi pung bos-bos mau lempar bekin mati sang Bapa di sana. Ma sakarang Bapa mau kambali pi sana lai, ko?&gt;&gt;<bt>But His disciples protested saying, “Father Teacher. Just recently the bosses of the Yahudi people wanted to stone you to death there. But now You want to return there again, or (what)?”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: His disciples said to him,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: His disciples said to him, "Teacher, the Jews recently tried to stone you. Are you going back again?"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Ju Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Jang taku, é! Tiap hari, matahari basinar dari pagi sampe sore. Itu ada 12 jam, to? Kalo jalan di taráng, orang sonde ta'antok. Te taráng bacaya di ini dunya ko orang bisa lia.<bt>Yesus responded saying, “Don't be afraid, é! Every day, the sun shines from morning until late afternoon. That's 12 hours, right? If walking in the light, a person doesn't stumble. Cuz (elaboration) the light shines in this world so people can see. [EXEG: If we spiritualise too much in this verse to identify the light at two levels, then 9-10 don't hang together very well.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="HCE rethink"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">HCE rethink</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Jesus answered, &quot;Aren't there twelve"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Jesus answered, "Aren't there twelve hours in a day? If anyone walks in the daytime, he doesn't stumble, because he sees by this world's light.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Tuhan nanti jaga sang kotong, te"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">Tuhan nanti jaga sang kotong, te Dia sama ke taráng. [HCE, but Carson and Morris point out that it is Jesus who is the light of the world.]</Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Ma kalo orang jalan di galáp, dia ta'antok ulang-ulang, te dia sonde ada pung taráng.&gt;&gt;<bt>But if a person walks in the dark, he stumbles repeatedly, cuz (elaboration) he has no light.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="I am the light. So while"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">I am the light. So while I am still with you, you are safe.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But if anyone walks in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But if anyone walks in the night, he stumbles, because he has no light.</Message></Annotation><note reference="11:9-10" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Yesus pung maksud bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta ni, sama ke taráng. Jadi salama Beta masi ada sama-sama deng bosong, na, bosong aman sa.&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus meant saying, “I am like the light. So (consequently), as long as I am still together with you-pl, na, you are safe.”</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Yesus omong abis bagitu, ju Dia kasi tau bilang, &lt;&lt;Kotong pung tamán Lasarus su tidor. Ma nanti Beta kasi bangun sang dia.&gt;&gt;<bt>When Yesus finished speaking like that, He told (them) saying, “Our-inc friend Lasarus has gone to sleep. But later I will get/wake him up again.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: He said these things, and"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: He said these things, and after that he told them, "Our friend Lazarus has fallen asleep, but I am going to wake him up."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Ais Dia pung ana bua dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa. Kalo dia cuma tidor, dia pung arti, nanti dia jadi bae kambali, to?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then His disciples said, “Father/sir. If he is only sleeping, that means he will get well again, right?”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then his disciples said to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then his disciples said to him, "Lord, if he has fallen asleep, he will get well."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Dong omong bagitu, tagal dong pikir Yesus omong so'al tidor biasa. Padahal Dia ada omong so'al Lasarus pung mati.<bt>They spoke like that because they thought Yesus was talking about normal sleep. Whereas in fact, He was talking about Lasarus' death.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Jesus was talking about his"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Jesus was talking about his death, but they thought he meant natural sleep.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Padahal, Yesus ada omong so'al Lasarus"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">Padahal, Yesus ada omong so'al Lasarus pung mati. Ma dong pikir Dia omong so'al tidor biasa.</Message></Annotation><v n="14" />Ais Yesus kasi tau taráng-taráng bilang, &lt;&lt;Bagini. Lasarus su mati.<bt>Then Yesus explained clearly saying, “It's like this. Lasarus has died.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then Jesus said to them"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then Jesus said to them plainly, "Lazarus is dead.</Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Beta sanáng Beta sonde ada di sana waktu dia balóm mati, ko biar bosong jang susa. Te apa yang mau jadi sakarang tu, bekin bosong bisa parcaya sang Beta. Mari ko kotong pi sana su!&gt;&gt;<bt>I'm glad I was not there, before he died, so that you-pl would be troubled/in strife/upset. Cuz (elaboration) what is going to happen now, will make you able to believe in Me. Come on, let's go there now!” [NOTE: UNSs at a previous check, when asked “Why (opinion) do you think He was glad He was not there?” came up with speculative answers all over the place, including ones that were not acceptable. So the consultant at the time suggested this. It borders on overtranslation, but at least it narrows the possibilities. We are open to better solutions.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: I am glad for your"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: I am glad for your sakes that I was not there, so that you may believe. But we are going to him."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Ais ju Tomas, yang dong subu bilang, &lt;&lt;ana bagambar&gt;&gt;, kasi tau sang ana bua yang laen dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Mari su! Lebe bae kotong samua iko pi, ko biar kotong mati sama-sama deng Dia.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Tomas, who they called, “Twin (=child of reciprocal picture),” told the other disciples saying, “Let's go! It's better for all of us to go along, so that we-inc die together with Him.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then Thomas, the one called"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then Thomas, the one called 'Twin', said to his fellow disciples, "Let us also go so that we may die with him."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus pi Betania, ais hibur sang Marta [\s2]<bt>The Lord Yesus goes to Betania, and comforts Marta [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17-19" />Ais Yesus dong jalan pi kampong Betania.<bt>So/then Yesus (coll.) went/travelled to the village of Betania.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Naa, itu kampong pung jao cuma tiga kilo dari kota Yerusalem. Ju banya orang Yahudi datang dari sana ko mete deng hibur Marta deng Maria.<bt>Naa, [shift to background] that village was only 3 kilometers distance from the city of Yerusalem. And many Yahudi people came from there to stay awake (=sit with grieving family) and comfort Marta and Maria.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Waktu Yesus dong sampe di sana, ju dong baru tau bilang, orang su kubur sang Lasarus ampa hari.<bt>When Yesus (coll.) arrived there, they just found out that people had buried Lasarus four days ago.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: 17 Then when Jesus came,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: 17 Then when Jesus came, he found that he had been in the grave four days already. 18 Now Bethany was near Jerusalem, less than two miles away. 19 Many Jews came to Martha and Mary, to comfort them about their brother.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Ais waktu Marta dapa dengar bilang, Yesus su datang, ju dia kaluar ko pi katumu sang Yesus. Ma Maria tenga dalam ruma sa.<bt>So/then when marta heard that Yesus had come, she went out to go meet Yesus. But Maria just stayed in the house.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then Martha, as soon as"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then Martha, as soon as she heard that Jesus was coming, went and met him. But Mary sat in the house.</Message></Annotation><v n="21" />Ais Marta kasi tau sang Yesus bilang, &lt;&lt;Aduu, Bos, é! Kalo Bos ada di sini, pasti beta pung adi sonde mati.<bt>Then Marta told Yesus saying, “Aduu, Bos, é! If You were here, surely my younger sibling wouldn't have died.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then Martha said to Jesus,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then Martha said to Jesus, "Lord, if you had been here, my brother would not have died.</Message></Annotation><v n="22" />Ma beta ju yakin, Bos mau minta apa sang Tuhan Allah, na, Bos pasti dapa.&gt;&gt;<bt>But I am also confident/sure, whatever You request from God, na, You will certainly get it.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But I know that even"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But I know that even now, whatever you ask God, God will give it to you."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Ju Yesus kasi tau sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Ma'a! Nanti lu pung adi idop kambali.&gt;&gt;<bt>And Yesus told her saying, “Ma'a! Your younger sibling will live again.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Jesus said to her, &quot;Your"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Jesus said to her, "Your brother will rise again."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Marta mangaku bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta mangarti, nanti di hari kiamat, kalo Tuhan bekin samua orang mati jadi idop kambali, Dia ju kasi idop kambali sang beta pung adi.&gt;&gt;<bt>Mart acknowledged saying, “I understand, later at the end of the world, when God2 makes all dead people come back to life, He will also bring back to life my younger sibling.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Martha said to him, &quot;I"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Martha said to him, "I know that he will rise again in the resurrection at the last day."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Ju Yesus kasi tau bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta yang bekin orang mati jadi idop kambali. Beta ju yang kasi idop yang batúl. Jadi orang yang parcaya sang Beta nanti dapa itu idop, biar dia mati.<bt>Then Yesus told (her) saying, “I am the one who makes dead people come back to life. I am also the one who give real life. So (consequently) the person who believes in Me will get/obtain that life, even if he is dead/dies. [EXEG: Gk. abstract nouns ‘resurrection’ and ‘life’ are neutral in their argument focus. The context here is about what happens to other people, not Jesus. See Carson, TH: “It may be necessary in most languages to use verb phrases in place of nouns resurrection and life, for example, ‘I am the one who raises people from the dead and gives them life.’ GeCL translates ‘I am he who brings resurrection and life.’”] [NOTE to daughter translations: Be careful about ambiguous renderings. Avoid implication of 1) coming into belief after dying /biar dia su mati/, 2) a person who has ever/once believed (but later didn't) /yang parná parcaya sang Beta/]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Jesus said to her, &quot;I"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Jesus said to her, "I am the resurrection and the life. He who believes in me will live, even though he dies.</Message></Annotation><v n="26" />Ju orang yang dapa itu idop yang batúl, deng parcaya sang Beta, nanti idop tarús. Ma'a parcaya Beta pung omong, ko?&gt;&gt;<bt>And the person who gets that real life, and believes in Me, will live continually. Ma'a believes what I'm saying, right?”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And anyone who lives and"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And anyone who lives and believes in me will never die. Do you believe this?"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />Dia manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Ia, Bos! Beta parcaya bilang, Bos ni, andia Kristus, itu Orang yang Tuhan Allah su tunju memang dari dolu. Deng Bos ni, Tuhan pung Ana, yang Dia su janji mau kirim datang di ini dunya.&gt;&gt;<bt>She responded saying, “Iya, Bos! I believe that You are Kristus, that Person who God has designated from long ago. And You are God2's Child, whom He has promised to send into this world.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ALL CHANGE = ia -- iya"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">ALL CHANGE = ia -- iya</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: She said to him, &quot;Yes,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: She said to him, "Yes, Lord, I believe that you are the Christ, the Son of God, who was to come into the world."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus manangis [\s2]<bt>The Lord Yesus cries [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Marta omong abis bagitu, ju dia jalan pulang. Ais dia pange dia pung adi Maria, ko dong dua sandiri, ju kasi tau bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa Guru su datang. Dia ada mau katumu deng lu.&gt;&gt;<bt>When Marta finished speaking like that, she went home. Then she called her younger sister Maria, so the two of them were alone, and told (her) saying, “Father Teacher has come. He is wanting to meet with you.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lathraai: out of public view, privately,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">lathraai: out of public view, privately, without the knowledge of other people, secretly, but not "quietly." LITERALLY: When she had said that, she went back and called her sister Mary privately, and said, "The Teacher has come, an calls for you."<span class="Italic">(28)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="29-31" />Dengar bagitu, ju Maria bangun capát-capát ko pi cari sang Yesus. Orang Yahudi yang mete jaga deng Maria dalam ruma, ada lia dia bangun capát ko lari kaluar. Ais dong iko sang dia dari balakang. Te dong pikir bilang, dia mau pi manangis di kuburan.<bt>Hearing that, Maria got up quickly to go look for Yesus. the Yahudi people who were staying awake with Maria in the house, saw her get up quickly and rush out. So they followed her from behind. cuz (elaboration) they thought that she was going to go cry at the grave.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: 29 As soon as she"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: 29 As soon as she heard that, she got up quickly, and went to him. 30 Now, Jesus had not yet come into the town, but was in the place where Martha had met him. 31 The Jews who were in the house with Mary comforting her, when they saw her get up quickly and go out, followed her. They thought that she was going to the grave to cry there.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Naa, itu waktu, Yesus dong balóm maso dalam kampong. Dia masi ada di itu tampa yang Marta su katumu deng Dia.<bt>Naa, [shift] at that time, Yesus (coll.) had not yet entered the village. He was still at that place where Marta had met with Him.</bt><v n="32" />Waktu Maria sampe di itu tampa, ju dia lia sang Yesus. Ais dia tikam lutut di Yesus pung kaki. Dia kasi tau bilang, &lt;&lt;Aduu! Kalo Bos ada di sini, pasti beta pung adi sonde mati.&gt;&gt;<bt>When Maria arrived at that place, she saw Yesus. Then she knelt at Yesus' feet. She said, “Aduu [+grief, regret]! If Bos (=You) had been here, certainly my younger brother would not have died.” [NOTE to daughter trans: same wording as vs. 21]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then when Mary came where"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then when Mary came where Jesus was, and saw him, she fell down/knelt/prostrated herself at his feet. She said to him, "Lord, if you had been here, my brother would not have died."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="33" />Waktu Yesus lia dia ada manangis, deng itu orang Yahudi dong yang ada iko sang dia, ju ada makarereu, ais Dia mara dalam Dia pung hati deng rasa susa.<bt>When Yesus saw she was crying, and those Yahudi people who had followed her was also weeping in mourning, He was angry in His liver, and felt troubled/upset. [EXEG: NLT: he was moved with indignation and was deeply troubled. (Carson) ‘he was outraged in spirit, and troubled’ (see his extended discussion, also Morris, TH). NRSV: he was greatly disturbed in spirit and deeply moved. CEV: he was terribly upset. NIV: he was deeply moved in spirit and troubled.TB: maka sedihlah hati-Nya. Ia sangat terharu dan berkata. The commentators give the NIV and TB renderings low marks/little support (e.g. ‘deeply moved’ defaults to a positive reading to many English speakers, as does ‘terharu’ in Indo [although terharu and sedih certainly fit the context, that is not what the Gk text says]; ‘sad’ is not a gloss associated with this Gk word--there are several other words for that) --although they all acknowledge this word is vague and complex. Note the LXX uses this same Gk word to mean “to be enraged”. While jengkel might make more sense on its own, we couldn't use it, because 1) jengkel is always with reference to someone else, and b) the reading in context had UNSs saying that he was jengkel with Mary in vs.32--for which there is no support. More likely with the nosey people who had tagged along, but the higher level context provides many other possibilities too.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="UNS not know makarereu (mesolectal)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">UNS not know makarereu (mesolectal)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: When Jesus saw her weeping,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: When Jesus saw her weeping, and the Jews who had come with her weeping too, he was upset in his spirit and troubled.</Message></Annotation><v n="34" />Dia tanya bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong kubur sang dia di mana?&gt;&gt;<bt>He asked saying, “Where did you-pl bury him?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Dong manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Mari, Bos! Datang ko lia sandiri sa.&gt;&gt;<bt>They responded saying, “Come [invite], Bos! Come [motion] and see for yourself.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: He said, &quot;Where have you"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: He said, "Where have you laid him?" They said, "Lord, come and see."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="35" />Ju Yesus manangis.<bt>Then Yesus wept.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Jesus wept."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Jesus wept.</Message></Annotation><v n="36" />Ais, itu orang Yahudi dong ba'omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Lia sa. Dia sayang mati sang Lasarus!&gt;&gt;<bt>Then2 those Yahudi people spoke among themselves saying, “Look at that. He really loved Lasarus!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then the Jews said, &quot;Look"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then the Jews said, "Look how much he loved him!"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="37" />Ma ada saparu lai yang ba'omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Ini Orang ni, yang buka orang buta pung mata, ko dia bisa dapa lia. Akurang ko Dia sonde bisa tahan sang Lasarus ko dia jang mati?&gt;&gt;<bt>But there were some others who spoke among themselves saying, “This Person here is the one who opened a blind person's eyes so he could see. Why is it that He is not able to restrain/hold back Lasarus so he didn't die?”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But some of them said,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But some of them said, "This one opened the eyes of the blind. Couldn't he have kept this man from dying?"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Lasarus idop kambali<bt>Lasarus lives again</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="38" />Ais Yesus rasa hati barát lai. Ju Dia pi deka-deka di goa yang dong pake ko kubur sang Lasarus. Dong su tutu ame itu goa pake satu batu bésar.<bt>Then Yesus felt heavy livered (=upset, sad) again. And He went close to the cave which they used to bury Lasarus. They had closed that cave using a large stone.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="epekeito ep' autooi: leaning up against"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">epekeito ep' autooi: leaning up against the cave entrance, having been placed there by somebody. LITERALLY: Then again Jesus became upset within himself. He came to the grave, which was a cave, with a stone at the entrance.<span class="Italic">(38)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="39" />Ais Yesus suru orang di situ dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Kasi ondor ini batu, ko buka ini pintu goa doo!&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus ordered people there saying, “Remove/Retreat this stone, to open the door of this cave [+imperative]!”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ma Marta, andia orang mati pung kaka tu, protes bilang, &lt;&lt;Awe', Bos! Dia mati su ampa hari, ma! Pasti su baboo.&gt;&gt;<bt>But Marta, that is the dead person's older sibling, protested saying, “Awe' [+dismay], Bos! He's been dead for four days already [+objection]! Surely (he) smells (bad).”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Jesus said, &quot;Take away the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Jesus said, "Take away the stone." Martha, the dead man's sister, said to him, "Lord, he has been dead four days. There will be a bad smell!"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="Cook\CNT\cn01769b.tif" rtfFormat="width:6.5cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:right" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="40" />Ju Yesus kasi inga sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Inga tadi, to? Beta su kasi tau memang bilang, kalo Ma'a batúl-batúl parcaya sang Beta, nanti bisa lia Tuhan Allah pung hebat.&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus reminded her saying, “(You) remember earlier, right? I already told you that if Ma'a really believes in Me, (you) will be able to see God's amazingness/incredibleness.” [EXEG: in vs. 23-26 it is ‘believe in Me’]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Jesus said to her, &quot;Didn't"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Jesus said to her, "Didn't I tell you that if you would believe, you would see the glory of God?"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="41" />Ais ju ada barapa orang yang buka ame itu batu dari goa. Ais Yesus mangada pi langit, ju Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa! Beta minta tarima kasi, tagal Bapa dengar sang Beta.<bt>Then there were several people who opened up that stone from the cave. Then Yesus faced (up) toward the sky, and said, “Father! I give thanks, because Father listens to Me.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then they took away the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then they took away the stone. Jesus raised his eyes to heaven and said, "Father, I thank you that you hear me.</Message></Annotation><v n="42" />Beta su tau dari dolu bilang, Bapa salalu dengar sang Beta. Ma Beta omong bagitu sakarang, ko biar orang dong yang badiri di sini bisa tau bilang, Bapa yang utus sang Beta.&gt;&gt;<bt>I already know from before saying, Father always listens to Me. But I am saying that now, so that the people standing here can know that Father is the one who sent/commissioned Me.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: I knew that you always"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: I knew that you always hear me, but because of the people standing here I said that, that they may believe that you have sent me."</Message></Annotation><v n="43" />Waktu Dia omong abis bagitu, ju Dia batarea deng suara karás bilang, &lt;&lt;Lasarus! Kaluar su!&gt;&gt;<bt>When He had finished speaking like that, He shouted with a loud voice saying, “Lasarus! Come on out [+strong imperative]!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And when he had said"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And when he had said that, he shouted with a loud voice, "Lazarus, come out!"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="44" />Ju itu orang mati kaluar dari goa. Ada kaen orang mati yang bungkus ame dia pung tangan deng kaki. Ada kaen yang tutu dia pung muka ju. Yesus suru sang orang di situ dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Buka ame itu kaen dolo, ko biar dia jalan!&gt;&gt;<bt>And the dead person came out of the case. There was dead people's cloth which was wrapped around his hands and feet. And there was a cloth that covered his face. Yesus ordered people there saying, “Undo that cloth to let him walk!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: The dead one came out"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: The dead one came out wrapped hands and feet in grave cloths, and a cloth around his face. Jesus said, "Untie him and let him go!"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Dong ator siasat ko mau bunu sang Tuhan Yesus<bt>They plot to kill the Lord Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 26:1-5; Markus 14:1-2; Lukas 22:1-2)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="45" />Waktu dong lia apa yang Yesus bekin tu, banya orang Yahudi yang datang mete deng Maria, parcaya sang Yesus.<bt>When they saw what Yesus had done, many of the Yahudi people who came to stay awake (=sit with famliy of dead) with Maria, believed in Yesus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then many of the Jews"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then many of the Jews who had come to Mary, and had seen the things Jesus did, believed in him.</Message></Annotation><v n="46" />Ma ada saparu lai pi katumu deng orang partei Farisi dong, ko kasi tau sang dong, Yesus pung bekin tu.<bt>But there were some others who went to meet with people of the Farisi party, to tell them what Yesus had done.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But some of them went"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But some of them went to the Pharisees, and told them what Jesus had done.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="47" />Ais itu, ju kapala agama pung bos-bos dong, deng orang Farisi bakumpul ko dong barunding. Dong batanya bilang, &lt;&lt;Itu Orang tu, ada bekin tanda heran macam-macam! Jadi kotong musti bekin karmana lai?<bt>After that, the *chief priests (bosses of the priests), and the Farisi people gathered to confer/discuss a matter to seek a solution. They asked (each other) saying, “That Person has done many sorts of amazing signs! So (consequently) what else should we-inc be doing? [EXEG: Carson, Morris on “what have we accomplished?”]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then the chief priests and"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then the chief priests and Pharisees called a conference, and said, "What will we do [OR what have we accomplished]? Because this man is doing many miracles/signs!</Message></Annotation><v n="48" />Te kalo kotong kasi biar sang Dia, na, nanti samua orang baharap sang Dia sama ke Dia jadi dong pung raja. Deng bagitu, ju tantara pamarenta Roma nanti datang bekin ancor kotong pung Ruma Sambayang Pusat deng kotong pung bangsa.&gt;&gt;<bt>Cuz (elaboration) if we-inc just let Him be, na, then everyone will be hoping in Him as if He were their king. If that happens, then the soldiers of the Roma government will come and destroy/ruin/fall apart our Temple and our people/nation (not government).” [EXEG: not “believe in” in spiritual sense of salvation, but “put their hopes in” in the sense of a political deliverer and rallying point. Note following sentence about Romans.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="arousin: destroy, remove, take away, LITERALLY:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">arousin: destroy, remove, take away, LITERALLY: If we let him keep on doing this, everybody is going to believe in him! And then the Romans will come, and will take away both our holy place and our nation!."<span class="Italic">(48)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="49" />Itu taon, Kayafas yang jadi kapala agama dong pung bos bésar. Dia omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bodo, é! Bosong sonde tau apa-apa!<bt>That year, Kayafas is the one who was *high priest (big boss of priests). He spoke saying, “That's dumb, é! You-pl don't know anything!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Discuss Bodo, é! with team. Hee!"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">Discuss Bodo, é! with team. Hee! Important people talk a lot worse to their people here :)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: One of them, Caiaphas, the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: One of them, Caiaphas, the main priest that year, said to them, "You do not know anything!</Message></Annotation><v n="50" />Te ada lebe bae kasi bosong, kalo cuma ada satu orang sa yang mati kasi sang samua orang. Te kalo sonde, nanti tantara Roma dong kasi ancor buang bangsa Yahudi anteru!&gt;&gt;<bt>Cuz (elaboration) it's better for you, if there is only person who dies for everyone. Cuz (elaboration) if not, then the Roma army/soldiers will completely destroy/ruin/fall apart (our) entire Yahudi people/nation!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Don't you realize that it"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Don't you realize that it is better for you if one man dies for the people, instead of the whole nation being destroyed?"</Message></Annotation><v n="51" />Naa, Kayafas sonde omong iko dia pung mau sandiri sa. Te Tuhan ada pake dia pung mulu, tagal dia yang jadi kapala agama dong pung bos bésar itu taon. Andia ko Kayafas kasi tau memang bilang, nanti Yesus mati kasi sang samua orang Yahudi.<bt>Naa, [shift] Kayafas was not just talking according to his own will. Cuz (elaboration) God2 was using his mouth, because he is the one who was *high priest that year. That is why Kayafas foretold that Yesus would die for all Yahudi people.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: He did not say that"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: He did not say that by himself. Because he was the high priest that year, he prophesied that Jesus would die for the nation.</Message></Annotation><v n="52" />Padahal Dia bukan cuma mati kasi sang bangsa Yahudi sandiri sa, ma kasi sang Tuhan Allah pung ana samua yang ada tasiar di ini dunya. Dia nanti bekin sang dong samua jadi satu bangsa.<bt>Whereas in fact, He would not only die for the Yahudi people/nation alone, but for all of God's children who are scattered around this world. He would make them become one people/nation.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And not only for that"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And not only for that nation, but also to bring together into one people, God's children who are scattered all over.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="53" />Tagal Kayafas pung omong tu, andia ko, mulai itu waktu, orang Yahudi pung bos-bos dong ba'ator siasat ko mau bunu bekin mati sang Yesus.<bt>Because of what Kayafas said, that is why, beginning from that time, the bosses of the Yahudi people plotted together to kill Yesus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then from that day on,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then from that day on, they plotted to kill him.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="54" />Jadi Yesus sonde jalan taráng-taráng lai di orang Yahudi pung bos-bos dong pung teng-tenga. Dia deng Dia pung ana bua dong ondor diri pi satu kota, nama Efraim, yang deka-deka di tampa kosong. Ju dong tenga tahan di situ.<bt>So (consequently) Yesus did not go openly anymore among the bosses/leaders of the Yahudi people. He and His disciples retreated/withdrew to a city named Efraim, which was near the empty place. They stayed there temporarily.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: So Jesus no longer went"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: So Jesus no longer went around openly among the Jews, but went from there into the country near the desert, into a city called Ephraim, and stayed there with his disciples.</Message></Annotation><note reference="11:54" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Daftar Sensus 9:10</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="55" />Itu waktu, agama Yahudi pung hari bae Paska su deka-deka. Dia pung biasa, banya orang dari luar datang bakumpul di kota Yerusalem ko iko pesta Paska di situ. Dong sampe lebe dolo, ko bekin barisi diri iko agama pung atoran.<bt>At that time, the Yahudi religious festival Paska was very near. The norm/custom was for many people from outside to come and gather together in the city of Yerusalem to participate in the Paska feast there. They (would) arrive ahead of time, to clean/purify themselves according to religious regulations.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: The Jewish Passover was near,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: The Jewish Passover was near, and many went from the country to Jerusalem before the Passover, to purify themselves.</Message></Annotation><v n="56" />Banya orang yang datang di Yerusalem ada cari-cari sang Yesus di situ. Waktu dong ada badiri di Ruma Sambayang Pusat pung kintal, dong batanya bilang, &lt;&lt;Iko bosong, karmana? Bosong kira Yesus mau datang iko ini pesta agama, ko sonde?&gt;&gt;<bt>Many people who came to Yerusalem were looking (all over) for Yesus there. When they stood in the Temple yard, they asked each other saying, “According to you-pl, how is it? Do you think that Yesus is going to come participate in this religious feast, or not?”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: They looked for Jesus, and"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: They looked for Jesus, and asked each other as they were in the temple, "What do you think? That he won't come to the feast?"</Message></Annotation><v n="57" />Ma kapala agama pung bos-bos, deng orang Farisi dong su parenta bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo ada orang yang tau Yesus ada di mana, na, kasi tau sang botong dolo!&gt;&gt; Padahal dong ada maksud mau tangkap ame sang Dia.<bt>But the *chief priests (bosses of the priests), and the Farisi people had already ordered saying, “If there is anyone who knows where Yesus is, na, please tell us! [+imperative]!” Whereas in fact, their intention was to catch/arrest Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: The chief priests and Pharisees"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: The chief priests and Pharisees had ordered that if anyone knew where he was, he should tell, so he could be arrested.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Maria po'a minya wangi di Tuhan Yesus pung kaki<bt>Maria pours aromatic oil on the Lord Yesus' feet</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 26:6-13; Markus 14:3-9)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="12" />
      <v n="1" />Ais waktu masi tenga anam hari baru hari Paska, Yesus dong datang di kampong Betania. Lasarus dong tenga di situ. Lasarus tu, andia orang mati yang Yesus su kasi idop kambali.<bt>Then when there were still six days before the Paska day, Yesus (coll.) came to the village of Betania. Lasarus (coll.) lived there. That Lasarus is the dead person who Yesus had brought back to life.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then six days before the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then six days before the Passover, Jesus came to Bethany, where Lazarus was, whom Jesus raised from the dead.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="waktu masi anam hari baru hari"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">waktu masi anam hari baru hari Paska,</Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Ais dong masa ko Yesus makan malam deng dong. Marta yang layani meja. Lasarus ada dudu di meja sama-sama deng Yesus.<bt>So they cooked so Yesus could eat evening meal with them. Marta was the one who served table. Lasarus was sitting at the table together with Yesus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: There they made him a"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: There they made him a supper, and Martha served. And Lazarus was one of those who sat at the table with him.</Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Ais Maria ame satu botol minya wangi asli yang mahal. Ju dia po'a ame di Yesus pung kaki. Ais dia pake dia pung rambu ko lap Yesus pung kaki. Ju itu ruma anteru jadi baboo wangi.<bt>Then Maria took a bottle of pure aromatic oil whcih was expensive. And she poured it out on Yesus' feet. Then2 she used her hair to wipe Yesus' feet. And that entire house had a fragrant smell.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Why? love, gratitude, honour, ?? Carlton"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">Why? love, gratitude, honour, ?? Carlton “to honor him”; Carson “self-humbling devotion and love”; Morris “great humility as well as great devotion”</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then Mary took a pint"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then Mary took a pint of nard perfume, very expensive, and poured it on Jesus' feet, and wiped them with her hair. The house was filled with the fragrance of the perfume.</Message></Annotation><note reference="12:3" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Alkitab Bahasa Yunani bilang itu minya pung nama <span class="Italic">&lt;nardos&gt;</span>, yang dolu orang bekin dari akar wangi. Alkitab Bahasa Indonesia bilang &lt;narwastu&gt;. Alkitab Bahasa Yunani ju bilang itu botol pung bésar tu, satu <span class="Italic">&lt;litra&gt;</span>, andia 325 gram, ko kira-kira satenga liter.<bt>The Yunani language Bible says the name of that oil was <span class="Italic">&lt;nardos&gt;</span>, which they used to make from an aromatic root. The Indonesian language Bible calls it ‘narwastu’. The Yunani language Bible also says the size of that bottle was one <span class="Italic">&lt;litra&gt;</span>, that is 325 grams, or around half a liter.</bt></note><note reference="12:3" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lukas 7:37-38</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Ma Yesus pung ana bua satu, nama Yudas Iskariot, yang nanti jual buang sang Yesus, protes bilang,<bt>But one of Yesus'disciples, named Yudas Iskariot, who would later sell off (=betray) Yesus, protested saying,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then Judas Iscariot, one of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then Judas Iscariot, one of his disciples, who would later betray him, said,</Message></Annotation><v n="5" />&lt;&lt;Weh! Akurang ko dia sonde jual ini minya wangi sa? Te dia pung harga sama ke satu orang pung gaji satu taon. Lebe bae jual sa, ko dia pung doi kasi sang orang malarat dong!&gt;&gt;<bt>“Weh! Why didn't she just sell that aromatic oil? Cuz (elaboration) its price/value is the same as a person's wages for a year. It would be better to sell so its money (could be) given to the poor/unfortunate people!” [NOTE to daughter translations: Gk is passive in last clause (no subject identified). If need subject, use “Lebe bae lu/dia jual...” using Mary as referent.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: &quot;Why wasn't this perfume sold"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: "Why wasn't this perfume sold for three hundred denarii, and given to the poor?"</Message></Annotation><note reference="12:5" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Alkitab Bahasa Yunani bilang itu minya pung harga 300 <span class="Italic">&lt;denari&gt;</span>. Satu <span class="Italic">denari</span> tu, sama ke tukang pung gaji satu hari.<bt>The Yunani language Bible says the value of that oil was 300 <span class="Italic">&lt;denari&gt;</span>. One <span class="Italic">denari</span> was the same as a craftsman's wage for a day.</bt></note><v n="6" />Padahal Yudas omong bagitu bukan tagal dia sayang sang orang malarat dong. Ma tagal dia tu, pancuri. Dia jadi Yesus dong pung bendahara, ma dia maen se'ok doi dari kas.<bt>Whereas in fact, Yudas spoke like that, not because he loved poor people. But because he was a thief. He was the treasurer for Yesus (coll.), but he kept pilfering money from the till/cash(box)/kitty.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: He said this, not that"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: He said this, not that he cared for the poor, but because he was a thief. He carried the money bag, and would help himself to it.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Ma Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Kasi biar sang ini parampuan sa. Te dia su simpan ini minya wangi ni, ko bekin siap Beta pung mayat ko dong kubur sang Beta.<bt>But Yesus responded saying, “Let this woman alone/be. Cuz (elaboration) she has saved this aromatic oil, to prepare My corpse for them (non-referential) to bury Me.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then Jesus said, &quot;Leave her"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then Jesus said, "Leave her alone. She has kept this for the day of my burial.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Te dia su simpan lama ini"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">Te dia su simpan lama ini</Message></Annotation><v n="8" />Orang malarat salalu ada di bosong pung teng-tenga. Ma nanti Beta sonde ada sama-sama deng bosong tarús.&gt;&gt;<bt>Poor people are always in your midst. But later I will not be together with you-pl continually.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Because you always have the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Because you always have the poor with you, but you will not always have me with you.</Message></Annotation><note reference="12:8" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 15:11</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Kapala agama pung bos-bos cari jalan ko mau bunu sang Lasarus<bt>The chief priests look for a way to kill Lasarus</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Ais banya orang Yahudi dapa tau bilang, Yesus ada di kampong Betania. Dong datang ko mau lia sang Dia. Dong ju datang ko mau lia sang Lasarus. Te dong su dengar bilang, Yesus su kasi idop kambali sang Lasarus dari dia pung mati.<bt>Then many Yahudi people found out that Yesus was in the village of Betania. They came wanting to see Him. They also came wanting to see Lasarus. Cuz (elaboration) they had heard that Yesus had made Lasarus live again from his death.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then many Jewish people knew"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then many Jewish people knew that he was there, and they came not only to see Jesus, but to see Lazarus too, whom he had raised from the dead.</Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Ma kapala agama pung bos-bos dong barunding ko cari jalan mau bunu bekin mati sang Lasarus ju.<bt>But the *chief priests conferred/connived to find a way to kill Lasarus too.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But the head priests discussed"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But the head priests discussed how they could also kill Lazarus.</Message></Annotation><v n="11" />Te banya orang Yahudi su dengar so'al Lasarus pung carita, ais dong parcaya sang Yesus. Dong su sonde mau dengar sang orang Yahudi pung bos-bos lai.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) many Yahudi people had heard about Lasarus' story, so they believed in Yesus. They didn't want to listen to/obey the bosses/leaders of the Yahudi people anymore. [NOTE to daughter translations: watch out for ambiguity “dengar Lasarus pung carita” can be 1) story about Lazarus, or 2) story that Lazarus told. In KM using /so'al/ ‘about’ forces the first reading.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Since, because of him, many"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Since, because of him, many Jewish people left and believed in Jesus.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus maso pi kota Yerusalem sama ke orang bésar<bt>The Lord Yesus enters the city of Yerusalem like a big/important person</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 21:1-11; Markus 11:1-11; Lukas 19:28-40)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Dia pung beso, itu orang banya yang datang ko iko pesta Paska di kota Yerusalem tu, dapa dengar bilang, Yesus mau datang di situ ju.<bt>The next day, those many people/crowds who had come to participate in the Paska feast in the city of Yerusalem, heard/found out that Yesus was going to come there too.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: The next day the big"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: The next day the big crowd that had come to the feast heard that Jesus was coming to Jerusalem.</Message></Annotation><v n="13" />Ais dong pi potong daon palam ko pake sambut sang Yesus pung datang, sama ke Dia tu, orang bésar. Ju dong batarea rame-rame bilang,<bt>So they went and cut palam leaves/fronds to use to greet/welcome (formally, fanfare) Yesus' coming, like He was a big/important person. And they shouted festively saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;<span class="Italic">Hosana!</span> Kotong puji-puji sang Tuhan Allah!<bt>“<span class="Italic">Hosana!</span> We-inc praise God!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Te Tuhan kasi tunju Dia pung hati bae sang Isra'el pung Raja,<bt>Cuz (elaboration) God2 has shown His goodness/kindness/grace to the King of Isra'el,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">yang datang bawa Tuhan pung nama!&gt;&gt;<bt>who comes bearing God2's name!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="eulogeimenos: having been blessed, bestow divine"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">eulogeimenos: having been blessed, bestow divine favour, say good things about; not /makarizw/ LITERALLY: They took branches of palm trees and went out to meet him, and shouted, "Hosanna/Salvation! Blessed is the King of Israel who comes in the name of the Lord!"<span class="Italic">(13)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="12:13" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 118:26</note></p>
    <fig path="Cook\CNT\cn01782b.tif" rtfFormat="width:6.5cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:right" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Ais Yesus dapa satu binatang keledai ténak, ju Dia dudu di dia pung atas. Itu sama ke su tulis dalam Tuhan pung Tulisan Barisi bilang,<bt>Then Yesus found a juvenile keledai (donkey) animal, and He sat on top. That is the same as was written in the *Scriptures saying,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Jesus found a young donkey"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Jesus found a young donkey and sat on it, as it is written,</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="15" />&lt;&lt;Bosong orang kota Yerusalem, jang taku, ó!<bt>“You-pl people of the city of Yersusalem, don't be afraid, ó!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Bosong orang kota &lt;Sion&gt; ni, lia pi sana doo!<bt>You-pl people of the city of ‘Sion’ here, look yonder, do [=imperative]!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Bosong dari kota yang orang subu,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">Bosong dari kota yang orang subu, bilang, &lt;Sion&gt; tu, lia pi sana do!</Message></Annotation><note reference="12:15" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Kota Sion tu, andia kota Yerusalem pung nama laen.<bt>That city of Sion, is another name for the city of Yerusalem.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Te bosong pung Raja ada datang!<bt>Cuz (elaboration) your King is coming!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Dia datang di atas satu keledai ténak.&gt;&gt;<bt>He is coming on a juvenile donkey.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="poolon: from Homer down, it refers"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">poolon: from Homer down, it refers to a domestic animal that is old enough to use, but not yet an adult. "Baby" would not be big enough. LITERALLY: "Do not be afraid, daughter of Zion! Look! Your King is coming, sitting on a donkey's colt.<span class="Italic">(15)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="12:15" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Sakaria 9:9</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Itu waktu, Yesus pung ana bua dong sonde mangarti ini hal dong pung arti. Ma nanti, waktu Dia su idop kambali dari Dia pung mati, deng Tuhan Allah angka tinggi-tinggi sang Dia, baru dong inga hal-hal yang Tuhan pung Tulisan Barisi ada tulis so'al Dia. Dong ju inga ini orang banya dong pung bekin kasi sang Dia.<bt>At that time, Yesus' disciples did not understand the meaning of this thing/matter. But later, when He had come back to life from His death, and God *glorified Him (elevated Him very high), only then did they remember the things which the Scriptures had written about Him. They also remembered what these many people/crowds had done to/for Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: His disciples didn't understand these"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: His disciples didn't understand these things at first, but when Jesus was glorified, then they remembered that these things were written about him, and they had done these things to him.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Naa, waktu Yesus kasi idop kambali sang Lasarus dari dia pung mati, ais pange ame sang dia kaluar dari kuburan tu, ada banya orang sama-sama deng Yesus. Jadi sakarang, dong ada bacarita kiri-kanan so'al apa yang dolu dong su lia sandiri.<bt>Naa, [shift] when Yesus brought Lasarus back to life from his dead, and called him out from that grave, there were many people together with Yesus. So (conseuqently) now, they were telling/narrating to each other right-left (=busily all over the place) about what they had seen for themselves.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: The crowd who had been"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: The crowd who had been with him when he called Lazarus out of his grave and raised him from the dead, testified about what had happened.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Naa, itu orang banya yang ada"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">Naa, itu orang banya yang ada sama-sama deng Yesus waktu Dia kasi idop kambali sang Lasarus dari dia pung mati, ju pange ame sang dia kaluar dari kuburan tu, dong ada carita kiri-kanan so'al apa yang dong su lia sandiri.</Message></Annotation><v n="18" />Andia ko banya orang datang sambut sang Yesus deka-deka deng Yerusalem, tagal dong su dengar bilang, Dia su bekin itu tanda heran.<bt>That is why many people came to greet Yesus close to Yerusalem, because they had heard that He had done that amazing sign.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For that reason the crowd"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For that reason the crowd met him, because they heard that he had done a miracle/sign.</Message></Annotation><v n="19" />Ais orang Farisi dong ba'omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Cue! Lia doo! Samua orang di ini dunya ada batasibu ko mau iko sang Dia! Nanti dia pung ujung-ujung, kotong yang susa! Kalo bagitu, na, kotong mau bekin karmana lai?&gt;&gt;<bt>So/then the Farisi people spoke (with each other) saying, “Cue! [+disgust] Look there! Everyone in this world is acting like a busy-body to follow Him! The end result will be, we-inc are the ones in difficulty/strife/trouble! If it's like this, na, what else can we do?” [EXEG: (NIV): See, this is getting us nowhere; (NLT) We've lost!; (CEV) There is nothing that can be done!]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="oofeleite ouden: are doing no good"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">oofeleite ouden: are doing no good at all. Recrimination within the group: we as a whole, or those of you who were supposed to act? LITERALLY: Therefore the Pharisees said to each other, "Don't you see that you can't do anything? Look! The whole world is following him!"<span class="Italic">(19)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Ada barapa orang Yunani yang mau katumu deng Tuhan Yesus<bt>There are several Yunani people who want to meet with the Lord Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Ada barapa orang Yunani yang datang di kota Yerusalem sama-sama deng orang laen dong, ko mau iko pesta Paska di situ. Dong ju mau sémba sang Tuhan Allah di situ.<bt>There were several Yunani people who came to the city of Yerusalem together with the other people, wanting to participate in the Paska festival there. They also wanted to worship God there.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: There were some Greeks among"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: There were some Greeks among those who came to worship at the feast.</Message></Annotation><v n="21" />Ju dong datang katumu deng Filipus, yang asal dari kampong Betsaida di propinsi Galilea. Dong minta bilang, &lt;&lt;Bu! Botong ada mau katumu deng Yesus.&gt;&gt;<bt>And they came and met with Filipus, whose origins were from the village of Betsaida in the province of Galilea. They requested saying, “Older brother! We are wanting to meet with Yesus.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: They came to Philip, who"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: They came to Philip, who was from Bethsaida in Galilee, and asked him, "Sir, we want to see Jesus."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Ais Filipus pi kasi tau sang Anderias. Ju dong dua pi omong deng Yesus.<bt>So Filipus went and told Anderias. And the two of them went to speak with Yesus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Philip came and told Andrew,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Philip came and told Andrew, and Andrew and Philip tell Jesus.</Message></Annotation><v n="23-24" />Ais Yesus kasi tau sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta pung waktu su datang. Jadi Beta musti mati dolo, baru Tuhan Allah mau angka tinggi-tinggi sang Beta. Batúl tu! Kotong banding deng satu bibit. Kalo kotong tanam satu bibit padi, na, dia musti ancor dalam tana dolo, baru dia idop, ko dia kasi kaluar hasil bam-banya. Te kalo sonde bagitu, dia masi tatáp padi satu biji sa.<bt>then Yesus told them saying, “My time has come. So (consequently) I must die first, before God is going to *glorify (elevate very high) Me. That's right! We-inc could compare it with a seed (for planting). If/when we plant one seed (for planting) of rice/grain, na, it must be destroyed/decay/fall apart in the ground first, before it (can) live, so it can put out a lot of yield/produce/crop. Cuz (elaboration) if that's not the case, it just keeps staying/being just a grain seed (form-not intended for planting). [EXEG: Carson on “germination”, plus discussions with Crofts: Problem: agriculturally the seed doesn't die, it transforms to a different stage. KM people say that if the seed had “died”, then it couldn't sprout. Also few other cultures would describe what the seed does as “die”. So the challenge is to find something that both makes sense (the English doesn't) and carries the parallel with Christ's death.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Jesus said to them, &quot;The"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Jesus said to them, "The hour/time has come for the Son of Man to be glorified. 24 That's right! I tell you, Unless a kernel of wheat fall into the ground and die, it stays alone. But if it die, it makes a lot of wheat.</Message></Annotation><v n="25" />Orang yang sonde toe sang Tuhan pung mau, tagal dia talalu sayang ame dia pung idop di ini dunya, nanti itu idop ancor buang. Ma orang yang sadia sarakan buang dia pung idop di ini dunya, nanti dapa idop yang batúl yang sonde tau putus-putus.<bt>A person who doesn't care about God2's will (=the things of God2), because s/he excessively loves his life in this world, later that life will fall apart/be destroyed/come to ruin (completely). But a person who is prepared to (completely) give up/hand over his life in this world, later will get/obtain real life that never ends. [EXEG: (Carson on hate = fundamental preference, not hatred on some absolute scale. On “love his life” he says “to love one's life is a fundamental denial of God's sovereignty, of God's rights, and a brazen elevation of self to the apogee of one's perception, and therefore an idolatrous focus on self, which is the heart of all sin.” “shameless focus on self ”. Morris “The verb translated ‘lose’ often means ‘destroy’.”]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: The one who loves his"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: The one who loves his life will lose it, but the one who hates his life in this world will [keep/guard] it for eternal life.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Orang yang talalu sayang ame dia"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">Orang yang talalu sayang ame dia pung idop di ini dunya, nanti itu idop ilang buang. Ma orang yang sadia sarakan buang dia pung idop di ini dunya, nanti dapa idop yang batúl yang sonde tau putus-putus.</Message></Annotation><note reference="12:25" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 10:39, 16:25, Markus 8:35, Lukas 9:24, 17:33</note><v n="26" />Orang yang mau layani sang Beta, dia musti iko tarús sang Beta. Andia Beta ada di mana, na, Beta pung orang suru-suru ju ada di situ. Te kalo ada orang yang layani sang Beta, nanti Beta pung Bapa di sorga taro hormat sang dia.&gt;&gt;<bt>The person who wants to serve Me, he must follow Me continually. That is, wherever I am, na, My servant is also there. Cuz (elaboration) if there is a person who serves Me, My Father in heaven shows respect/honour to him.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: If anyone serves me, let"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: If anyone serves me, let him follow me [imperative]. And where I am, there my servant will be too. If anyone serve me, the Father will honor him.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus kasi tau memang so'al Dia pung mati<bt>The Lord Yesus foretells about His death</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />Yesus omong tamba bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta pung hati rasa susa. Ma, ais Beta mau bilang karmana lai? Beta musti minta bilang, &lt;Bapa! Kasi lapás sang Beta, ko biar Beta sonde usa mati sakarang,&gt; ko? Sonde! Beta sonde minta bagitu, tagal Dia utus sang Beta datang, ko Beta mati.<bt>Yesus spoke further saying, “My liver is troubled/stressed/in strife. But, then what else could/should I say? Should I request saying, ‘Father! Release/spare Me, so that I don't have to die now,’ or (what)? No! I do not request like that, because He sent/commissioned Me to come so I could/would die.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tetaraktai: is not the same as"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">tetaraktai: is not the same as embrimeesato, but is negative. LITERALLY: "Now my soul is troubled, and what am I going to say? 'Father, save me from this hour?' But for this reason I came to this hour.<span class="Italic">(27)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="28" />Jadi, yang Beta minta, bagini: &lt;Bapa. Biar Beta iko Bapa pung mau sa, ko biar samua orang angka tinggi-tinggi Bapa pung nama.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>So (consequently) what I request is like this: ‘Father. Just let/allow Me to follow/obey Father's will/desire, so that everyone can *glorify (elevate very high) Father's name/reputation.’”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ju ada satu suara dari langit bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta su angka tinggi-tinggi Beta pung nama. Deng Beta ju mau angka tinggi-tinggi ulang lai.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then there was a voice from the sky saying, “I have *glorified (elevate very high) My name/reputation. and I am going to *glorify (elevate very high) it again.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="&lt;&lt;Beta su kasi tunju Beta pung"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">&lt;&lt;Beta su kasi tunju Beta pung hebat. Deng Beta ju mau kasi tunju ulang lai.&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lexical cohesion between 2 parts of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">lexical cohesion between 2 parts of verse</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: 'Father, glorify your name.' Then"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: 'Father, glorify your name.' Then a voice came from heaven, saying, 'I have both glorified it, and I will glorify it again.'</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="29" />Ais, itu orang banya yang ada badiri di situ dong, dengar itu suara, ju bilang, &lt;&lt;He'ela! Ada guntur!&gt;&gt;<bt>Then, those many people who were standing there, heard that voice, and said, “He'ela! [+startled] There's thunder!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="he'ela ~ hi'ila = [+kaget]"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">he'ela ~ hi'ila = [+kaget]</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ada orang saparu lai yang omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Sonde! Itu Tuhan pung ana bua dari sorga satu ada ba'omong deng Dia.&gt;&gt;<bt>There were some people who spoke saying, “No! One of God2's *angels from heaven is speaking with Him.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Therefore the crowd that stood"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Therefore the crowd that stood near and heard it said that it thundered. Others said, "An angel spoke to him."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="30" />Ma Yesus kasi tau bilang, &lt;&lt;Itu suara tadi tu, buat bosong, bukan buat Beta.<bt>But Yesus told (them) saying, “That voice just now, was for you-pl, not for Me.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Jesus answered, &quot;This voice was"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Jesus answered, "This voice was not for my sake, but for yours.</Message></Annotation><v n="31" />Sakarang orang di ini dunya musti mangada sang Tuhan Allah, ko Dia putus dong pung parkara. Dia ju mau usir buang sang itu Tukang Bekin Jahat yang pegang parenta di ini dunya.<bt>Now people in this world must front up (to an authority) to God, for Him to decide their cases. He is also going to evict that Habitual Evildoer who holds rule/governs in this world.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Now is the judgment of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Now is the judgment of this world. Now the ruler of this world will be cast out.</Message></Annotation><v n="32" />Nanti kalo orang gantong sang Beta di atas kayu palang, Beta akan tarek samua orang ko dong parcaya sang Beta.&gt;&gt;<bt>Later if/when people hang Me on a *cross (crossed wood/pole), I will pull/draw inward all people so they believe in Me (purpose, irrealis).” [EXEG: NLT; While language sounds like it refers to ascention, vs.33 emphatically ties it with crucifixion; previous context links it to glorification/resurrection. Carson believes John is deliberately using it for multiple meanings.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="John 3:14 &quot;Hal bagitu ju musti"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">John 3:14 "Hal bagitu ju musti jadi kasi Beta, Manusia Tulen. Nanti dong mau kasi tagantong sang Beta di atas kayu," 8:28 "Nanti kalo bosong su gantong sang Beta, Manusia Tulen, di atas kayu palang, baru bosong mangarti, bilang, Beta ni, Kristus." LITERALLY: When I am lifted up from the earth, I will [draw/attract] everyone to myself." [lifted up on the cross, or in the resurrection, or both]<span class="Italic">(32)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="33" />(Dia omong bagitu, ko kasi tunju nanti Dia mati deng cara karmana.)<bt>(He spoke like that, to show what way He would later die.)</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: (He said that, showing the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: (He said that, showing the kind of death he would die.)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="34" />Ais orang di situ dong tanya bilang, &lt;&lt;Botong parná dengar dari Tuhan pung Atoran bilang, nanti Kristus idop tarús. Naa, Kristus deng Manusia Tulen tu, sama, ko? Jadi akurang ko Bapa bilang, &lt;Nanti dong mau gantong sang Manusia Tulen di atas kayu palang?&gt; Ko itu Manusia Tulen tu, sapa?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then people there asked saying, “We-exc have heard from God2's Regulations/Law that, later Kristus will live continually. Naa, Kristus and the Son of Man are the same, right? So (consequently) why do You say, ‘Later they will hang the Son of Man from a cross?’ So who is that Son of Man?” [EXEG: The references in this verse are confusing to say the least. This sounds like they equate Christ and the Son of Man, but don’t particularly id them to Him. We (CR) had to spell it out: “… You say you are the Son of Man, isn’t he the Christ? How can you say they are going to hang you up/kill you? B/c in God’s book it says the Christ will live forever. Who is this Son of Man you are talking about?” By this they do not seek simple identification, but demand to know what kind of Son of Man/Messiah Jesus has in mind, of whom it can be said that he will die. (Carson).]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Taking Christ to Heaven would not"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">Taking Christ to Heaven would not terminate his life. But killing him on a cross would keep him from living forever. LITERALLY: The crowd answered him, "We have heard from the Law that the Christ stays forever. How come you say, 'The Son of Man must be lifted up?' Who is this Son of Man?"<span class="Italic">(34)</span></Message><Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2011-05-28 00:56:38Z">The references in this verse are confusing to say the least. This sounds like they equate Christ and the Son of Man, but don’t particularly id them to Him. We had to spell it out: “… You say you are the Son of Man, isn’t he the Christ? How can you say they are going to hang you up/ kill you? B/c in God’s book it says the Christ will live forever. Who is this Son of Man you are talking about?” By this they do not seek simple identification, but demand to know what kind of Son of Man/Messiah Jesus has in mind, of whom it can be said that he will die. (Carson).</Message></Annotation><note reference="12:34" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 110:4, Yesaya 9:6, Yeskial 37:25, Daniel 7:14</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="35" />Ju Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Sonde lama lai, te Beta pung taráng su sonde bacaya di bosong lai. Jadi waktu Beta masi ada, bosong musti idop lurus, ko biar jahat jang tutu ame itu taráng yang ada di bosong pung hati. Te orang yang jalan di galáp, sonde tau dia mau pi mana.<bt>Then Yesus responded saying, “It won't be much longer (=soon) that My light doesn't shine on you-pl anymore. So (consequently), while I am still here/still is/exists, you must live straight (=morally pure), so that evil does not cover/shut out that light that is in your livers. Cuz (elaboration) a person who walks in the dark, does not know where he is going. [EXEG: Carson, NLT, HCE, Morris.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="use “light” in multiple senses ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">use “light” in multiple senses ; live in My light so that evil doesn't overcome you. de-metaphorise one part</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="katalabei: attack, sieze, overpower, take control"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">katalabei: attack, sieze, overpower, take control LITERALLY: Jesus said to them, "Yet a little while the light is with you. Walk while you have the light, that darkness may not overtake/overcome you. He who walks in the dark does not know where he is going.<span class="Italic">(35)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ju Yesus manyao, bilang, &lt;&lt;Dia tu,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">Ju Yesus manyao, bilang, &lt;&lt;Dia tu, Beta. Naa, Beta sama ke taráng (yang bacaya) kasi sang bosong. Sadiki lai itu taráng masi ada (sama-sama) deng bosong. Jadi, waktu taráng masi ada, bosong musti idop batúl/lurus, ko biar galáp jang kasi mati/redá/usir buang/tutu ame itu taráng yang ada di bosong pung hati. Te orang yang jalan di galáp, sonde tau dia mau pi mana.</Message></Annotation><v n="36" />Naa, waktu Beta pung taráng masi ada, bosong musti parcaya sang Beta, ko biar bosong jadi orang yang idop di taráng, ko tau bosong ada mau pi mana.&gt;&gt;<bt>Naa [shift], while My light is still here, you must believe in Me, so that you are people who live in the light, so you know where you are going to go.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Yesus omong abis bagitu, ju Dia ondor diri dari itu orang banya dong, ko biar Dia bisa sandiri sa.<bt>After Yesus finished speaking like that, then He retreated/withdrew from those many people/crowds, so that He could be alone.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ekrybee ap autoon: not hide and"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">ekrybee ap autoon: not hide and seek, but lying low or staying incognito. LITERALLY: While you have light, believe in the light, that you may be the children of light." Jesus said these things and went away, and hid himself from them.<span class="Italic">(36)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Orang Yahudi dong sonde parcaya sang Tuhan Yesus<bt>Yahudi people don't believe in the Lord Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="37" />Biar Yesus su bekin banya tanda heran di orang banya dong pung muka, ma dong sonde mau parcaya sang Dia.<bt>Even though Yesus had already done many amazing signs in front of those many people, nevertheless they didn't want to believe in Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But though he had done"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But though he had done so many miracles/signs in front of them, still they did not believe in him.</Message></Annotation><v n="38" />Itu sama ke Tuhan pung jubir, Yesaya, parná kasi tau memang bilang,<bt>That was like what God2's spokesperson Yesaya had once foretold saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Bos, é! Sonde ada orang yang parcaya botong pung omong!<bt>“Bos, é! There is nobody who believes what we-exc say!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Te biar Bos su kasi tunju Bos pung kuasa,<bt>Cuz (elaboration) even though You have already shown Your power/authority,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ma orang dong sonde lia apa-apa, na!&gt;&gt;<bt>nevertheless people don't see anything at all [+disgust]!” [DISCOURSE: changed RQ to statement; HCE]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: That the saying of Isaiah"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: That the saying of Isaiah the prophet might be fulfilled, who said, "Lord, who has believed our report, and to whom has the arm [strength] of the Lord been revealed?"</Message></Annotation><note reference="12:38" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 53:1</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="39" />Andia ko itu orang Yahudi saparu sonde bisa parcaya sang Tuhan sakarang, sama ke Yesaya tulis di laen tampa bilang,<bt>That is why some of those Yahudi people could not believe in God2 now, like Yesaya wrote in a different place saying,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Because of this they could"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Because of this they could not believe, for Isaiah said another time,</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="40" />&lt;&lt;Tuhan Allah su bekin dong pung hati buta,<bt>[DISCOURSE STYLE: unravel chiasmus] “God has made their livers blind,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ko biar dong sonde bisa dapa lia lai.<bt>so that they are not able to see anymore.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Dia kasi biar dong pung hati jadi karás,<bt>He has allowed their livers to become hard/stiff, (=1) hard hearted, 2) void of compassion),</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ko dong sonde usa mangarti batúl.<bt>so that they don't need to truly understand.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Kasi biar dong bagitu,<bt>Just let them be like that,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ko dong sonde usa bale cari sang Beta,<bt>so they don't need to turn and look for Me,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">deng Beta sonde usa bekin bae sang dong.&gt;&gt;<bt>and I don't need to heal them.” [STYLE: irony, cynical]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="4 terms in secondary meaning, blind,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">4 terms in secondary meaning, blind, turn &amp; look, heal,</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: &quot;He has blinded their eyes,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: "He has blinded their eyes, and hardened their heart, that they would not see with their eyes, or understand with their heart, and be converted, and I would heal them."</Message></Annotation><note reference="12:40" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 6:10</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="41" />Yesaya omong bagitu, tagal dia su lia ame Yesus pung hebat, ais dia carita memang so'al Yesus.<bt>Yesaya spoke like that, because he had already seen Yesus' greatness/incredibleness/amazingness, and so he foretold about Yesus. [EXEG: Gk: glory here] [EXEG: Carson on Jesus' glory as complement of ‘see’; NLT referring to]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="eiden: see, pay attention to, understand,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">eiden: see, pay attention to, understand, visit, experience LITERALLY: Isaiah said these things, when he saw his [Jesus'] glory, and spoke about him.<span class="Italic">(41)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="42" />Biar bagitu, ma banya orang parcaya sang Yesus. Bukan cuma orang biasa sa, te ada orang Yahudi pung bos-bos saparu ju yang parcaya sang Dia. Ma dong sonde mangaku Yesus di orang banya pung muka, tagal dong taku, nanti orang Farisi dong mau usir buang sang dong kaluar dari ruma sambayang.<bt>Even that being the case, nevertheless many people believed in Yesus. Not just common people, cuz there were also some bosses/leaders of the Yahudi people who also believed in Him. But they did not acknowledge Yesus in fron of many people/the crowds, because they were afraid, that the Farisi people would evict them out from the houses of worship.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Nevertheless, many believed in him,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Nevertheless, many believed in him, even among the chief rulers, but because of the Pharisees they did not confess it, lest they would be put out of the synagogue.</Message></Annotation><v n="43" />Itu bos-bos dong sonde toe kalo Tuhan mau puji sang dong, tagal dong lebe suka makan puji dari manusia.<bt>Those bosses/leaders did not care if God2 wanted to praise them, because they were more interested in receiving praise from humans.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dapa puji = (broader)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">dapa puji = (broader)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Because they loved the glory/praise"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Because they loved the glory/praise of people more than the glory/praise of God.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Te itu bos-bos dong lebe suka"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">Te itu bos-bos dong lebe suka tarima puji dari manusia, ma dong sonde toe kalo Tuhan mau puji sang dong.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus pung Kata-kata kasi tunju orang pung asli<bt>The Lord Yesus'Words/Message shows a person's nature/character (idiom: origins)</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="44" />Ais Yesus omong deng suara karás bilang, &lt;&lt;Orang yang parcaya sang Beta tu, dia sonde parcaya sang Beta sandiri sa, ma dia ju parcaya sang Orang yang utus sang Beta.<bt>Then Yesus spoke with a loud voice saying, “The person who believes in Me, he does not just believe in Me alone, but he also believes in the Person who sent/commissioned Me. [NOTE to daughter translations: our lgs vary whether God can be referred to as a ‘Person’ or not. If there is not a general ‘being’ word that works for God try ALT: parcaya sang Yang utus sang Beta // parcaya sang Dia yang utus sang Beta.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Jesus shouted, &quot;Whoever believes in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Jesus shouted, "Whoever believes in me, does not only believe in me, but in the one who sent me.</Message></Annotation><v n="45" />Te kalo orang ada lia sang Beta, na, dia ju lia sang Orang yang utus sang Beta.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) if a person sees/is looking at Me, na, s/he also sees the Person who sent/commissioned Me.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="@! CEV missed the aspect here"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">@! CEV missed the aspect here</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="thewrwn: see, understand, experience LITERALLY: And"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">thewrwn: see, understand, experience LITERALLY: And whoever sees me, sees the one who sent me.<span class="Italic">(45)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="46" />Beta datang ko jadi sama ke taráng di ini dunya. Ko biar samua orang yang parcaya sang Beta sonde idop di galáp.<bt>I came to be like a light to this world. So that everyone who believes in Me will not live in the dark/darkness.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: I have come as a"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: I have come as a light in the world, so that everyone who believes in me will not stay in darkness.</Message></Annotation><v n="47" />Kalo ada orang yang dengar Beta pung Kata-kata, ma sonde bekin iko, na, Beta sonde putus dia pung hukuman. Te Beta pung maksud datang di ini dunya, bukan mau putus orang dong pung hukuman, ma Beta mau kasi salamat sang orang dari dong pung sala-sala dong.<bt>If there is a person who hears/listens to My Words/Message, but doesn't obey/do according to (them), na, I don't decide his punishment. Cuz (elaboration) My intent/purpose for coming into this world, is not to decide people's punishment, but I want to *save people from their wrongs/sins.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="@! CEV too strong &quot;refuse to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">@! CEV too strong "refuse to obey my teachings"</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And if anyone hears my"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And if anyone hears my words and does not obey them, I do not judge him, because I did not come to judge the world, but to save the world.</Message></Annotation><v n="48" />Ma samua orang yang tola buang sang Beta, deng sonde mau tarima Beta pung Kata-kata, dia pung hakim ada. Te kalo hari kiamat datang, Kata-kata yang Beta parná omong dong, yang nanti putus orang macam bagitu pung hukuman.<bt>But everyone who rejects (lit: push away) Me, and doesn't want to accept My Words/Message, his judge exists/is there. Cuz (elaboration) if/when the end of the world comes, the Words/Message/s which I have spoken, are what will decide a person of that sort's punishment.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Whoever rejects me and does"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Whoever rejects me and does not receive my words, has one that judges him. the word which I have spoken will judge him on the last day.</Message></Annotation><v n="49" />Tagal Beta sonde parná omong deng bawa Beta pung nama sandiri. Ma Beta ada omong deng bawa Beta pung Bapa di sorga pung nama. Te Dia tu, yang utus sang Beta. Deng Dia yang parenta sang Beta ko Beta musti omong apa.<bt>Because I have never spoken bearing My own name. But I have spoken bearing My Father in heaven's name. Cuz (elaboration) He is the one who sent/commissioned Me. And He is the one who commanded Me (telling Me) what I must say.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Because I have not spoken"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Because I have not spoken by myself, but the Father who sent me has commanded me what to say and speak.</Message></Annotation><v n="50" />Beta ju tau bilang, Dia pung parenta tu bawa idop yang batúl yang sonde tau putus-putus. Andia ko Beta pung omong iko parsís deng apa yang Beta pung Bapa suru ko Beta omong.&gt;&gt;<bt>I also know that His commands bring real life that never ends. That is why what I say follows exactly what My Father orders Me to say.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="zooees aioonios: &quot;fo real kine&quot; emphasizes"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">zooees aioonios: "fo real kine" emphasizes the quality of life better than "to da max," which could also carry a meaning like "really living it up." LITERALLY: And I know that his commandment is eternal life. Therefore, what I speak is just as the Father told me.<span class="Italic">(50)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus cuci Dia pung ana bua dong pung kaki<bt>The Lord Yesus washes His disciples' feet</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="13" />
      <v n="1" />Waktu hari bae Paska balóm mulai, Yesus su tau bilang, Dia pung waktu su sampe, ko Dia musti kaluar kasi tenga ini dunya, deng kambali pi Dia pung Bapa di sorga. Ma Dia sayang mati sang Dia pung orang yang ada di ini dunya, sampe Dia sarakan Dia pung idop anteru-anteru kasi sang dong.<bt>When the Paska festival/holiday had not yet begun, Yesus already knew that His time had arrived, for Him to exit leaving behind this world, and return to His Father in heaven. But He really loved His people who were/are in this world, to the point that He turned over/gave up/surrendered His whole/entire life for them. [EXEG: “to the end” 1) temporally, 2) fully, totally, completely (See Carson, NLT)]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="@@ add Dia musti (mati??) kaluar"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">@@ add Dia musti (mati??) kaluar kasi tenga ini dunya, ?? UNS not explain</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="heorte: feast, festival metabainw: leave, go"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">heorte: feast, festival metabainw: leave, go out, depart<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>agapaw: love, cherish eis telos: to the end [of his life], completely<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>LITERALLY: Before the feast of the Passover, Jesus knew that the hour/time had come for him to go out of this world to the Father. Having loved his own people who were in the world, he loved them to the end.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Biar Dia sayang sang Dia pung"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">Biar Dia sayang sang Dia pung orang yang ada di ini dunya, (ma) Dia ju (musti) sayang mati sang dong sampe abis / deng samua-samua (?) / deng sarakan Dia pung idop anteru-anteru.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="2" />Itu waktu, setan dong pung bos su tusu-tusu sang Yudas, andia Simon Iskariot pung ana, ko dia jual buang sang Yesus. Ais Yudas su putus ko mau bekin bagitu, waktu Yesus dong ada dudu makan pesta Paska.<bt>At that time, the boss of the evil spirits had incited/pursuaded/goaded Yudas, that is Simon Iskariot's child, for him to sell off (=betray) Yesus. So/then Yudas had already decided to do that, when Yesus (coll.) were sitting eating that Paska fest.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="paradidwmi: hand over, give over, turn"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">paradidwmi: hand over, give over, turn over, deliver, entrust, betray LITERALLY: By supper time, the Devil had already put it into the heart of Judas, son of Simon Iscariot, to betray him.<span class="Italic">(2)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ais, waktu Yesus dong ada dudu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">Ais, waktu Yesus dong ada dudu makan pesta Paska tu, ju Yudas su putus ko mau bekin bagitu.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Yesus su tau bilang, Tuhan Allah yang utus sang Dia datang di ini dunya, deng sadiki lai Dia musti pulang kambali pi Tuhan. Deng Dia ju tau bilang, Dia pung Bapa di sorga su sarakan samua-samua di Dia pung tangan.<bt>Yesus already knew that God is the one who sent/commissioned Him to come into this world, and in a little while/soon He must go back (home) to God2. And He also knew that His Father in heaven had turned over/entrusted everything into His hand (=given Him responsibility).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="didwmi eis tas xeiras: give into"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">didwmi eis tas xeiras: give into his hands, put under his power, give him complete power LITERALLY: Jesus knew that the Father had given all things into his hands and that he came from God and was going to God,<span class="Italic">(3)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Ais Yesus bangun dari meja, ju buka Dia pung baju luar. Tarús Dia ame satu handok, ko ika di Dia pung pinggang.<bt>So/then Yesus got up from the table, and undid His outer shirt/clothes. Then He took a towel, to tie around His waist.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="handok"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">handok</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: So Jesus got up from"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: So Jesus got up from supper, he took off his outer robe, took a towel and put it around himself.</Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Ais Dia po'a aer pi dalam bokor kici satu. Ju Dia mulai cuci Dia pung ana bua dong pung kaki. Cuci abis satu, ju Dia lap kasi karíng pake itu handok yang Dia ada ika di Dia pung pinggang.<bt>Then He poured water into a small basin. And He began to wash His disciples'feet. After finishing washing one, He would wipe it dry using that towel He had tied around His waist. [NOTE to daughter translations: look at Cook cn01799B.tif and 1800B.tif to discuss “basin”.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bokor = basin"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">bokor = basin</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Q. ton nipteera: small wash basin"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">Q. ton nipteera: small wash basin holding a gallon or so. Herodotus speaks of a podanipteera, a foot basin. The definite article indicates that the basin was part of the regular furnishing of the room. LITERALLY: After that he poured water into a basin, and began to wash his disciples' feet, and to wipe them with the towel around his waist.<span class="Italic">(5)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="6" />Dia cuci dong satu-satu pung kaki. Pas sampe di Simon Petrus, ju Petrus tanya bilang, &lt;&lt;Bos ju mau cuci beta pung kaki, ko?&gt;&gt;<bt>He washed each of their feet. When He arrived at Simon Petrus, Petrus asked saying, “Are You (Boss) also going to wash my feet?”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then he came to Simon"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then he came to Simon Peter. He said to him, "Lord, are you going to wash my feet?"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Sakarang lu balóm tau so'al apa yang Beta ada bekin ni. Ma lama-lama baru lu mangarti.&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus responded saying, “Now you-sg do note yet know about what I am doing here. But eventually you will understand.” [NOTE: Gk uses 2 different words for understand here, reflected in KM.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="oidas: know, understand [knowledge as absolute"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">oidas: know, understand [knowledge as absolute and complete] ginwskw: know, understand, realize [knowledge gained by slow experience]<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>LITERALLY: Jesus answered him, "You do not understand what I am doing now, but you will understand these things later.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="Cook\CNT\cn01799b.tif" rtfFormat="width:6.5cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:right" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Ma Petrus protes bilang, &lt;&lt;Jang bagitu, Bos! Beta sonde kasi biar ko Bos cuci beta pung kaki.&gt;&gt;<bt>But Petrus protested saying, “Not like that, Bos! I won't allow You to wash my feet.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ju Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo Beta sonde cuci bekin barisi lu pung kaki, na, lu sonde ta'ika deng Beta.&gt;&gt;<bt>And Yesus responded saying, “If I do not wash making clean (fixed phrase) your feet, na, you are not bound/linked with Me.” [EXEG: see discussion in Carson] [NOTE to daughter trans: don't force the “wash you” if that carried undesirable baggage--use “wash your feet”.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Peter said to him, &quot;Never,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Peter said to him, "Never, at any time, will you wash my feet!" Jesus answered him, "If I do not wash you, you have no part with me."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Ju Simon Petrus manyao lai bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo bagitu, Bos jang cuma cuci beta pung kaki sa. Ma cuci beta pung tangan deng kapala ju!&gt;&gt;<bt>Simon Petrus responded saying, “If that's the case, Boss, don't just wash my feet. But wash my hands and head too!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Simon Peter said to him,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Simon Peter said to him, "Lord, not only my feet, but also my hands and my head."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Ais Yesus kasi tau sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Orang yang su mandi abis, cuma parlú cuci dia pung kaki sa. Te dia pung badan su barisi. Memang bosong pung hati su barisi, ma sonde samua yang barisi.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus told him saying, “A person who has finished bathing, only needs to wash his feet. Cuz (elaboration) his body is already clean. Yes, your-pl livers are clean/pure, but not all (of you) are clean/pure.” [EXEG: see Carson. Gk “all of you” is referring to number of people, not “entire body” TB is vague here.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="!@ TB"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">!@ TB</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Jesus said to him, &quot;The"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Jesus said to him, "The one who has bathed does not need anything except to wash his feet. His whole body is clean. And you are clean. But not all of you."</Message></Annotation><v n="11" />(Yesus omong bagitu, tagal Dia su tau sapa yang mau jual buang sang Dia. Andia ko Dia kasi tau bilang, &lt;&lt;Sonde samua yang barisi.&gt;&gt;)<bt>(Yesus spoke like that, because He already knew who it was who was going to sell Him off (betray). That's why He told (them) saying, “Not all (of you) are clean/pure.”)</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: (For he already knew who"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: (For he already knew who was going to betray him. That is why he said that "You are not all clean.")</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Waktu Yesus su cuci abis dong pung kaki, ju Dia pake kambali Dia pung baju, ko Dia pi dudu kambali di meja. Ais Dia tanya sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Karmana? Waktu Beta cuci bosong pung kaki, bosong mangarti apa yang Beta bekin, ko sonde?<bt>When Yesus had finished washing their feet, He put His shirt/clothes back on, to go sit at the table again. Then He asked them saying, “How is it? When I washed you-pl feet, did you understand what I was doing, or not?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then when he had washed"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then when he had washed their feet, and had put on his robe, and gone back to the table, he said to them, "Do you understand what I have done to you?".</Message></Annotation><v n="13" />Bosong suka subu sang Beta bilang, &lt;Bapa Guru&gt; deng &lt;Bos&gt; yang hak parenta sang bosong. Itu pantas, tagal Beta memang bagitu.<bt>You-pl like to refer to Me as ‘Father Teacher’ and ‘Bos/master/lord’ who has the say-so/ordering rights over you. That's appropriate, because that's what I really am.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: You call me 'Teacher' and"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: You call me 'Teacher' and 'Lord', and rightly so, because I am.</Message></Annotation><v n="14" />Ma kalo bosong pung Guru deng Bos ni, su cuci bosong pung kaki sama ke orang suru-suru satu, na, karmana deng bosong? Bosong ju musti layani satu deng satu; conto ke: bosong ju musti cuci satu deng satu pung kaki.<bt>But if your Teacher and Boss here, has washed your feet like a lowly servant, na, how about you? You-pl also must serve each other; for example: you must also wash each other's feet.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Therefore, if I, your Lord"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Therefore, if I, your Lord and teacher, washed your feet, you ought to wash each others' feet.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Bosong satu deng satu ju musti"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">Bosong satu deng satu ju musti bacuci bosong pung kaki.</Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Te Beta su jadi conto kasi bosong. Beta bekin karmana, na, bosong ju musti bekin iko bagitu.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) I have been an example for you. Whatever I do, na, you-pl must also follow/do according to that.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For I have given you"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For I have given you an example, that just as I did to you, you also should do.</Message></Annotation><note reference="13:12-15" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lukas 22:27</note><v n="16" />Batúl! Beta kasi tau sang bosong. Satu orang suru-suru sonde lebe hebat dari dia pung tuan. Deng satu utusan sonde lebe hebat dari orang yang utus sang dia.<bt>That's right! I'm telling you. A lowly servant is not greater than his master/owner. And an *apostle (commissioned one) is not greater than the person who sent/commissioned him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="megas: great, important, prominent, outstanding, superior"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">megas: great, important, prominent, outstanding, superior [of rank and dignity] LITERALLY: That's right! I tell you, a slave is not greater than his lord, nor is an apostle greater than the one who sent him.<span class="Italic">(16)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="13:16" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 10:24, Lukas 6:40, Yohanis 15:20</note><v n="17" />Tagal bosong su tau ini hal dong, bosong ontong kalo bosong bekin iko bagitu.<bt>Because you know these things, you are fortunate if you do accordingly.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="makarios: blessed, fortunate [NOTE: glossed as"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">makarios: blessed, fortunate [NOTE: glossed as "happy" in some sources, but the Gk doesn't carry the emotional side that the English does] LITERALLY: Since you know these things, you are fortunate/blessed if you do them.<span class="Italic">(17)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Beta sonde omong so'al bosong samua. Beta kanál batúl orang yang Beta su pili dong. Biar bagitu, ma itu musti jadi, sama ke apa yang su tatulis memang di Tuhan pung Tulisan Barisi bilang, &lt;Orang yang dudu makan sama-sama deng beta, su bale balakang ko jalan kasi tenga sang beta.&gt;<bt>I am not talking about all of you. I really know the people whom I have chosen. Even that being the case, nevertheless it must happen like what has been written beforehand in the *Scriptures saying, ‘The person who sits to eat together with me, has turned his back and abandoned me.’ (also implies rejection in KM.) [EXEG: “lifted his heel against me” = idiom; Carson says, “The most likely is that it means ‘has given me a great fall’ or ‘has taken cruel advantage of me’ or ‘has walked out on me’”; TH discussion on Middle Eastern custom really relates more to ‘sole’ than ‘heel’.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="batúl"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">batúl</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="oidas: know, understand [knowledge as absolute"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">oidas: know, understand [knowledge as absolute and complete] LITERALLY: I am not talking about all of you. I know those whom I have chosen. But to fulfill the Scripture, 'The one who ate bread with me has lifted his heel against me.'<span class="Italic">(18)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="13:18" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 41:10</note><v n="19" />Beta kasi tau memang sang bosong, ko kalo nanti orang su jalan kasi tenga sang Beta bagitu, na, bosong bisa parcaya bilang, Beta ni, andia Kristus.<bt>I'm telling this to you beforehand, so later when a person has abandoned Me like that, na, you can believe that I am Kristus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: I tell you this now,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: I tell you this now, before it happens, so that when it happens, you will believe that I am he.</Message></Annotation><v n="20" />Batúl! Beta ju kasi tau bilang, sapa yang buka hati ko tarima bae sang orang yang Beta utus, na, dia ju tarima sang Beta. Deng sapa yang tarima bae sang Beta, na, dia ju tarima sang Orang yang utus sang Beta.&gt;&gt;<bt>That's right! I'm also telling you that whoever opens his liver to receive/accept the people that I send/commission, na, s/he also receives Me. And whoever accepts Me, na, s/he also accepts the Person who sent/commissioned Me.” [NOTE to daughter translations: our lgs vary whether God can be referred to as a ‘Person’ or not. If there is not a general ‘being’ word that works for God, try ALT: tarima sang Yang utus sang Beta // tarima sang Dia yang utus sang Beta.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lambanein: accept. But for Pidgin, there"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">lambanein: accept. But for Pidgin, there are two kinds of acceptance. We had started out with "take him in," which implies that a more highly placed person allows a more low placed person to have a relationship with him. In this verse the social hierarchy goes the other way, with the lower placed person initiating a relationship with a more highly placed person. "Stick wit" is therefore more appropriate. LITERALLY: That's right! I tell you, he who receives/accepts anyone I send, receives me. He who receives me, receives the One who sent me."<span class="Italic">(20)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="13:20" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 10:40, Markus 9:37, Lukas 9:48, 10:16</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus kasi tau memang bilang, ada yang nanti jual buang sang Dia<bt>The Lord Yesus foretells that there is (someone) who will betray Him</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 26:20-25; Markus 14:17-21; Lukas 22:21-23)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Yesus omong abis bagitu, ju Dia pung hati mulai rasa tar enak. Ais Dia kasi tau bilang, &lt;&lt;Yang Beta omong ni, batúl. Satu dari bosong nanti jual buang sang Beta.&gt;&gt;<bt>When Yesus finished talking like that, His liver began to feel disturbed/unsettled/not nice. So He told (them) saying, “What I'm saying here is true. One of you will sell Me off (=betray).”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tarassw: stir up, disturb, unsettle, throw"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">tarassw: stir up, disturb, unsettle, throw into confusion, a state of mental and spiritual agitation LITERALLY: After Jesus said these things, he was troubled in his spirit, and declared, "This is certain what I am telling you, that one of you will betray me."<span class="Italic">(21)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Dengar bagitu, ju Dia pung ana bua dong balia satu deng satu, te dong bingung. Dong sonde tau sapa yang Dia maksud.<bt>Hearing that, His disciples looked around at each other, cuz (elaboration) they were confused. They didn't know who He meant.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="aporew: be at a loss, perplexity,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">aporew: be at a loss, perplexity, in doubt, uncertain, undecided, in bewilderment, to lose one's way LITERALLY: The disciples looked at each other, in bewilderment about who he meant.<span class="Italic">(22)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="23" />Di situ ju ada satu dari dong, yang Yesus sayang (andia beta, Yohanis, yang tulis ini buku).<bt>There, there was also one of them whom Yesus loved (that is me, Yohanis, who is writing this book).</bt><note reference="13:23" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Iko tradisi gareja deng orang yang pintar dong, &lt;ana bua yang Yesus sayang&gt; tu, andia Yohanis.<bt>According to church tradition and knowledgable people, ‘the disciple whom Yesus loved’ was Yohanis.</bt></note>Beta ada dudu di Yesus pung sablá.<bt>I was sitting beside Yesus. [NOTE: Local style/sociolinguistics a person can occasionaly use his full name to refer to himself, but not 3rd person pronoun.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: One of his disciples, whom"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: One of his disciples, whom Jesus loved, was reclining [sitting] next to Jesus.</Message></Annotation><v n="24" />Ju Simon Petrus kasi sein deng dia pung kapala, ko beta coba cari tau Yesus pung maksud tu, sapa.<bt>And Simon Petrus gave a sign with his head, so I would try to find out who Yesus meant.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Is there a way of saying"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">Is there a way of saying 'nod' meaning signal?</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: So Simon Peter nodded to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: So Simon Peter nodded to him to find out who it was that he meant.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Ais beta sorong beta pung badan lebe deka deng Yesus, ko tanya bilang, &lt;&lt;Orang yang Bapa maksud tu, sapa, é?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then I scooted my body closer to Yesus, to ask saying, “The person that You mean is who, é?”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="&lt;&lt;Orang yang Bos maksud tadi tu,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">&lt;&lt;Orang yang Bos maksud tadi tu, sapa, é?&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: So that one leaned close"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: So that one leaned close to Jesus and said, "Lord, who is it?"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="26" />Ju Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Bagini. Beta mau ame roti sapotong, ko calóp pi dalam mangko, ais Beta kasi pi orang yang Beta maksud.&gt;&gt; Dia calóp abis itu roti, ju Dia kasi sang Yudas, andia Simon Iskariot pung ana.<bt>And Yesus responded saying, “It's like this. I'm going to take a piece of bread, to dip into the bowl, then I will give it to the person I mean.” After dipping that bread, then He gave it to Yudas, that is Simon Iskariot's child.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sapotong = a piece ; sapo'ong"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">sapotong = a piece ; sapo'ong = a piece (small, insignificant) [from where? Aer Mata also says sadi'i]</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Jesus answered, &quot;It is the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Jesus answered, "It is the one for whom I will dip the piece of bread, and give it to him." So he dipped a piece of bread, and gave it to Judas, Simon Iscariot's son.</Message></Annotation><v n="27" />Tarima deng tarima itu roti, ju setan dong pung bos maso pi dalam Yudas. Ais Yesus kasi tau sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Capát su! Lu mau bekin apa, na, lu bekin su. Jang batunggu lai.&gt;&gt;<bt>Upon receiving that bread, the *boss of the evil spirits entered into Yudas. Then Yesus told him saying, “Hurry! What you are going to do, na, go ahead and do it. Don't wait any longer.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tarima deng tarima itu roti, ju"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">tarima deng tarima itu roti, ju = upon receiving the bread...</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And after the piece of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And after the piece of bread, then Satan entered into that one. Then Jesus said to him, "What you are doing, do quickly."</Message></Annotation><v n="28" />Ma satu orang ju dari dong yang ada dudu di situ sonde mangarti kanapa Yesus omong bagitu.<bt>But not one of the people sitting there understood why Yesus spoke like that. [NOTE: Subject fixed April 2014]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: None of the others sitting"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: None of the others sitting there knew why he said this to him.</Message></Annotation><v n="29" />Tagal Yudas jadi dong pung bendahara, ada yang pikir Yesus pung maksud tadi waktu Dia suru sang Yudas, &lt;&lt;Pi béli apa yang kotong parlú ko makan pesta Paska.&gt;&gt; Deng ada ju yang pikir Dia pung maksud, &lt;&lt;Pi kasi doi sadiki sang orang malarat dong.&gt;&gt;<bt>Because Yudas was their treasurer, there were those who thought Yesus had meant earlier when He had ordered Yudas, “Go buy waht we-inc need to eat the Paska feast.” And there were also those who thought that He meant, “Go give a little money to the poor people.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Some of them thought, because"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Some of them thought, because Judas had the money box, that Jesus was telling him, 'Buy what we need for the feast', or, 'Give something to the poor'.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="30" />Waktu Yudas tarima ame itu roti abis, ju dia jalan kaluar capát-capát. Waktu dia kaluar tu, hari su malam.<bt>After Yudas had accepted that bread, he went out quickly. When he went out, the day was already night. (normal way of saying this.)</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: So after he took the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: So after he took the bread, he went out quickly. It was night time.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Parenta yang baru<bt>A new command</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="31" />Waktu Yudas su kaluar, ju Yesus kasi tau bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta ni, Manusia Tulen. Sakarang dia pung waktu su sampe ko Tuhan Allah angka tinggi-tinggi sang Beta. Deng itu ju nanti bekin orang lia Tuhan Allah pung hebat.<bt>When Yudas had gone out, Yesus spoke saying, “I here am the *Son of Man (Authentic/Ideal Human). Now the time has arrived for God to *glorify (elevate way up high) Me. And that will also make/cause people to see God's greatness/amazingness.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then when he went out,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then when he went out, Jesus said, "Now the Son of Man is glorified, and God is glorified in him.</Message></Annotation><v n="32" />Tagal Beta ta'ika deng Tuhan, deng kasi tunju Dia pung hebat, andia ko Dia angka tinggi-tinggi sang Beta. Deng Dia sonde pake tunggu-tunggu lai.<bt>Because I am bound/linked with God2, and show His greatness/amazingness, that is why He will glorify Me. And He will not delay anymore.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Since God is glorified in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Since God is glorified in him, God also will glorify him in himself, and will glorify him right away.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="33" />Ana dong, é! Biar Beta sayang mati sang bosong, ma sadiki lai Beta su sonde ada sama-sama deng bosong lai. Bosong nanti cari sang Beta, ma sonde dapa. Beta kasi tau sang bosong ni, sama ke apa yang Beta su kasi tau sang orang Yahudi pung bos-bos dong bilang, &lt;Beta pi satu tampa yang bosong sonde bisa iko.&gt;<bt>Children/underlings, é! Even though I really/dearly love you, nevertheless soon I will not be together with you anymore. You will look for Me, but not find. I am telling you, just like what I have already told the bosses/leaders of the Yahudi people saying, ‘I am going to a place where you-pl cannot follow.’ [Cf. 7:34; 8:22-23.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="teknia: shows affection. LITERALLY: Little children,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">teknia: shows affection. LITERALLY: Little children, I am with you for only a little while longer. You will look for me, but just as I said to the Jews, that 'Where I go, you cannot come', so I say to you now.<span class="Italic">(33)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="13:33" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yohanis 7:34, 8:22-23</note><v n="34" />Beta kasi sang bosong satu parenta baru, bagini: <span class="Italic">bosong musti basayang satu deng satu, sama ke Beta sayang sang bosong.</span> Jadi bosong ju musti basayang satu deng satu.<bt>I am giving you-pl a new commandment, like this: <span class="Italic">you-pl must love each other, just like I love you.</span> So (consequently), you also must love each other.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: I give you a new"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: I give you a new commandment, that you should love each other, just as I have loved you, that you also should love each other.</Message></Annotation><note reference="13:34" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yohanis 15:12, 17, 1 Yohanis 3:23, 2 Yohanis 5</note><v n="35" />Kalo bosong basayang bagitu, na, samua orang bisa tau bilang, bosong ni, Beta pung ana bua dong.&gt;&gt;<bt>If you love each other like that, na, everyone can know that you-pl here are My disciples.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: By this everyone will know"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: By this everyone will know that you are my disciples, if you have love for each other.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus kasi tau memang bilang, Petrus mau manyangkal sang Dia<bt>The Lord Yesus foretells, that Petrus is going to deny (knowing) Him</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 26:31-35; Markus 14:27-31; Lukas 22:31-34)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="36" />Ais Simon Petrus tanya sang Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Ko Bos nanti mau pi mana?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Simon Petrus asked Him saying, “So where are You (Bos) going to go?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ju Yesus kasi tau bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta pi satu tampa yang lu balóm bisa iko pi sakarang. Ma tarahir lu pi situ ju.&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus told (him) saying, “I'm going to a place where you-sg can not yet follow now. But in the end you will also go there.” [NOTE: Gk here is different from vs.33.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Simon Peter said to him,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Simon Peter said to him, "Lord, where are you going?" Jesus answered him, "Where I am going, you cannot follow me now, but you will follow later."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="37" />Petrus tanya bilang, &lt;&lt;Bos, é! Akurang ko beta balóm bisa iko pi sakarang? Te beta su siap ko mati kasi sang Bos na!&gt;&gt;<bt>Peturs asked saying, “Bos, é! Why is it that I cannot yet follow now? Cuz (elaboration) I am ready to die for You (Bos) [+emphatic, obvious]!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Peter said to him, &quot;Lord,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Peter said to him, "Lord, why can't I follow you now? I will lay down my life for you."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="38" />Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Batúl, ko? Lu mau sarakan lu pung idop ko mati kasi sang Beta? Yang batúl, bagini: ayam balóm kokore'o, te lu su manyangkal sang Beta tiga kali.&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus responded saying, “Is that right/true? Are you going to/willing to give up/surrender your life to die for Me? The truth is like this: before chicken/rooster crows, you will have already denied (knowing) Me three times.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="manyangkal = sonde mau akui (UNS)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">manyangkal = sonde mau akui (UNS)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Jesus answered, &quot;Will you lay"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Jesus answered, "Will you lay down your life for me? That's right! I tell you, before the rooster crows, you will deny me three times."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Sonde ada jalan laen lai ko babae deng Bapa; cuma lewat Yesus sandiri sa<bt>There is no other way/path to be in a right relationship with Father; only by/via Yesus himself</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="14" />
      <v n="1" />Yesus omong tamba bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong jang pikiran. Parcaya sang Tuhan Allah. Deng parcaya sang Beta ju.<bt>Yesus spoke further saying, “You-pl should not worry/keep mulling things over with worry. Believe in God. And believe in Me too. [EXEG: Gk can be taken as indicative or imperative; see discussion in Carson.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(Bosong [su] parcaya sang Tuhan Allah."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">(Bosong [su] parcaya sang Tuhan Allah. Sakarang, bosong ju musti parcaya sang Beta - NLT &amp; Bultmann.)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: &quot;Do not let your hearts"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: "Do not let your hearts be troubled [worried and upset]. Believe in God, and/also believe in me. [Good News Version &amp; NIV] [or: You believe in God, and you believe in me.]</Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Di Beta pung Bapa pung tampa tenga, ada kamar bam-banya. Kalo tampa sonde cukup, na, tantu Beta su kasi tau memang sang bosong. Sakarang Beta mau pi siap tampa kasi bosong di sana.<bt>In/at My father's place of residence, there are many-many rooms. If there weren't enough places, na, surely I would already have told you-pl. Now I'm going to go prepare a place/s for you there (remote). [EXEG: Carson.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: In my Father's house there"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: In my Father's house there are many rooms. If not, I would have told you. I go to prepare a place for you.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Di Beta pung Bapa pung tampa"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">Di Beta pung Bapa pung tampa tenga, ada kamar bam-banya. Kalo tampa sonde cukup, na, Beta su kasi tau memang sang bosong sedu-sedu. Sakarang, Beta mau pi siap tampa kasi bosong di sana.</Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Kalo Beta su pi, deng su siap abis bosong pung tampa tu, nanti Beta datang kambali ko bosong iko sama-sama deng Beta. Deng bagitu, Beta ada di mana, na, bosong ju ada di situ.<bt>If/when I have gone, and have finished preparing your places, later I will come back again so you gollow together with Me. In that way, where(ever) I am, na, you-pl are also there.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And when I go and"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And when I go and prepare a place for you, I will come again, and take you to be with me, so that where I am, you also may be.</Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Te bosong su tau jalan yang pi itu tampa yang Beta mau pi tu.&gt;&gt;<bt>Cuz (elaboration) you already know the way which goes to that place where I am going.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Where I go, you know"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Where I go, you know the way."</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Te itu tampa yang Beta pi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">Te itu tampa yang Beta pi tu, bosong su tau dia pung jalan pi.&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Ma Tomas tanya sang Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Bos, é! Botong sonde tau Bos mau pi mana. Jadi karmana ko botong bisa tau dia pung jalan pi sana?&gt;&gt;<bt>But Tomas asked Him saying, “Bos, é! We-exc don't know where You are going. So (consequently) how could we be able to know the way there?”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Thomas said to him, &quot;Lord,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Thomas said to him, "Lord, we do not know where you are going. How can we know the way?"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="Cook\CNT\cn01735b.tif" rtfFormat="width:6.5cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:right" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Ju Yesus kasi tau bilang, &lt;&lt;Sonde ada jalan laen lai yang bawa orang pi di Bapa di sorga. Cuma lewat Beta sandiri sa. Te Beta ni, andia jalan pi Tuhan Allah. Beta ni, yang pegang apa yang batúl. Deng Beta ni, yang kasi orang idop yang batúl. Sonde ada jalan laen lai.<bt>Then Yesus told (him) saying, “There is no other way to bring people to Father in heaven. Only (exclusive) by/via Me alone. Cuz (elaboration) I here am the road/path/way to God. I here am the one who holds what is true/truth. And I here am the one who gives people real life. There is no other way. [NOTE: BIS leaves out ‘truth’ in this verse. Middle part adjusted Apr 2011 to remove weak simile. Last sentence is redundant, but added for emphasis/punch from UNS feedback.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Jesus said to him, &quot;I"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Jesus said to him, "I am the way, the truth, and the life. No one comes to the Father except by me.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ju Yesus kasi tau, bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">Ju Yesus kasi tau, bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo jalan yang bawa orang pi di Bapa di sorga, sonde ada orang laen lai. Cuma Beta sandiri sa. Te Beta ni, sama ke jalan. Beta ni, yang pegang apa yang batúl. Deng Beta ni, yang kasi orang idop yang batúl.</Message></Annotation><v n="7" />Andekata bosong kanál batúl sang Beta, na, bosong ju kanál sang Beta pung Bapa. Jadi mulai dari sakarang, bosong su kanál sang Dia, deng su lia sang Dia ju.&gt;&gt;<bt>If (hypothetical) you-pl really knew Me, na, you would also know My Father. So (consequently) beginning from now, you already know Him and have also seen Him.” [EXEG: see discussion in Carson.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: If you knew me, you"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: If you knew me, you would know my Father. And from now on, you know him and have seen him.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Filipus minta bilang, &lt;&lt;Bos, é! Tolong kasi tunju Bos pung Bapa sang botong doo! Te itu sa su cukup.&gt;&gt;<bt>Filipus requested saying, “Bos, é! Please show us Your (Bos') Father [+light imperative]! Cuz (elaboration) that is/would be enough.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="arkei: that satisfies us LITERALLY: Philip"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">arkei: that satisfies us LITERALLY: Philip said to him, "Lord, show us the Father, and that is enough for us."<span class="Italic">(8)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Ju Yesus kasi tau sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Ipu, é. Beta su sama-sama deng bosong bagini lama, ma bosong masi sonde kanál batúl sang Beta, ko? Te orang yang su lia sang Beta, itu sama ke dia ju su lia sang Beta pung Bapa. Ais, akurang ko tadi lu ada minta bilang, &lt;Kasi tunju Bapa sang botong&gt; lai?<bt>Yesus told him saying, “Ipu, é! [+familiar, affectionate for Filipus] I have already been together with you-pl for this long, but you still don't really know/recognise Me? Cuz/For (elaboration) the person who has seen Me, it's like s/he has also already seen My Father. So then, why is it that just now you-sg were requesting saying, ‘Show the Father to us’?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Jesus said to him, &quot;Have"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Jesus said to him, "Have I been with you so long, and yet you have not known me, Philip? He who has seen me has seen the Father. So why do you say, 'Show us the Father'?"</Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Karmana? Waktu Beta bilang Beta ta'ika deng Bapa, deng Bapa ju ta'ika deng Beta, na, lu parcaya sang Beta, ko sonde? Kata-kata yang Beta omong kasi bosong tu, sonde ba'akar di Beta sandiri, ma dong ba'akar di Beta pung Bapa. Deng Dia ada pake sang Beta ko bekin tarús Dia pung karjá.<bt>How about it? When I say I am bound/linked to Father, and Father is also bound/linked to Me, na, do you-sg believe (in) Me, or not? The Words/Message that I have spoken to you-pl, are not rooted/source in Me alone, but they are rooted/source in My Father. And He is using Me to keep carrying out His work.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Don't you believe that I"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Don't you believe that I am in the Father, and the Father in me? The words that I speak to you, I don't speak them by myself, but the Father who lives in me, he does his works.</Message></Annotation><v n="11" />Parcaya sang Beta waktu Beta bilang, Beta ada ta'ika bae-bae deng Beta pung Bapa, deng Dia ju ta'ika bae-bae deng Beta. Ma kalo bosong sonde bisa parcaya bagitu, na, parcaya sa sang Beta tagal bosong su lia itu hal yang Beta ada bekin dong.<bt>Believe Me when I say, I am bound/linked well to/with My Father, and He is also bound/linked well with Me. But if you-pl cannot believe like that, na, just believe in Me because you have seen those things that I ahve been doing. [NOTE to daughter translation: CHECK: is this interpreted as ‘miracles’?]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pisteúete: second time without object, but"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">pisteúete: second time without object, but the target language may require an object anyway LITERALLY: Believe me that I am in the Father and the Father in me, or if not, believe because of the works themselves.<span class="Italic">(11)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="12" />Beta pung omong tu, batúl! Te orang yang parcaya sang Beta, nanti dia ju bekin hal sama ke yang Beta bekin. Ma tagal Beta pi di Beta pung Bapa, apa yang itu orang bekin dong, nanti lebe hebat dari yang Beta bekin.<bt>What I am/have said is true! Cuz (elaboration) the person who believes in Me, later s/he will also do things like/same as I have done. But because I go to My Father, what it is that person does (pl), will be greater/more amazing that what I have done. [EXEG: see discussion in Carson --because after Jesus death, resurrection, and exaltation, the role of these acts in history and theology will be much clearer.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ho pisteúoon: generic, the one who"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">ho pisteúoon: generic, the one who believes pròs: the direction he is headed, go to<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>poreúomai: not just a quick visit, but plans to stay quite a while érga: deeds, in this context, miracles. Same in nature, but not the same actions done over<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>LITERALLY: That's right! And I tell you, he who believes in me, the works that I do, he will do also, and he will do greater works, because I go to my Father.</Message></Annotation><v n="13" />Bosong yang ta'ika deng Beta, ada pung hak ko bawa Beta pung nama. Jadi, kalo bosong sambayang ko minta apa sa, bawa Beta pung nama,<bt>You who are bound/linked with Me, have the right to bear My name. So (consequently), if/when you-pl are praying to request something/whatever, bringing/bearing My name,</bt><note reference="14:13" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Sambayang &lt;&lt;bawa Beta pung nama&gt;&gt; ada pung arti bilang, kotong sambayang iko Yesus pung mau. Kotong ada pung hak ko &lt;&lt;bawa Yesus pung nama&gt;&gt; kalo kotong jadi Dia pung orang, kalo kotong idop ta'ika tarús deng Dia, kalo kotong dengar-dengar sang Dia, deng kalo kotong parcaya bilang, Dia mati ko hapus buang kotong pung sala-sala. Jadi &lt;&lt;bawa Yesus pung nama&gt;&gt; tu, sonde sama deng cuma &lt;&lt;subu Yesus pung nama&gt;&gt; sa.<bt>Praying “bearing My name” means that we-inc pray according to Yesus' will. We have the right to “bear Yesus' name” if we are His person/people, if we live bound/linked with Him continnually, if we keep listening/obeying Him, and if we believe that He died to wipe away our sins. So (consequently), “bear Yesus' name” is not the same as merely “mentioning Yesus' name”.</bt></note>nanti Beta bekin kasi bosong. Deng bagitu, Beta ada angka tinggi-tinggi Beta pung Bapa, ko biar samua orang tau.<bt>I will do it for you. In that way, I am *glorifying (elevating way up high) My Father, so that everyone will know.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Whatever you ask in my"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Whatever you ask in my name, I will do it, so the Father will be glorified in the Son.</Message></Annotation><v n="14" />Beta kasi tau ulang lai: bosong sambayang ko minta apa sa, bawa Beta pung nama, nanti Beta akan bekin kasi bosong.&gt;&gt;<bt>I'll tell (you) again: you-pl pray to request something/whatever, bringing My name, I will do it for you.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Whatever you ask me in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Whatever you ask me in my name, I will do it."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus janji mau kirim datang Tuhan Allah pung Roh<bt>The Lord Yesus promises to send coming God's Spirit</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Yesus omong tamba bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo bosong sayang sang Beta, na, bosong bekin iko Beta pung parenta dong.<bt>Yesus spoke further saying, “If you-pl love Me, na, you will do according to/obey My commands.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="entolàs: commandments, words, what I have"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">entolàs: commandments, words, what I have told you to do LITERALLY: "If you love me, you will keep my commandments.<span class="Italic">(15)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="16-17" />Beta minta sang Beta pung Bapa, nanti, kalo Beta su sonde ada sama-sama deng bosong lai, na, Dia kasi sang bosong satu Pambina ko kasi tunju jalan sang bosong. Dia tu, Tuhan pung Roh, yang ajar sang bosong apa yang batúl. Orang saparu di ini dunya sonde mau tarima sang Dia, tagal dong sonde bisa lia sang Dia, deng sonde kanál sang Dia. Ma bosong kanál sang Dia tagal Dia ta'ika deng bosong. Dia nanti idop di bosong pung hati. Ais Dia ju nanti sama-sama deng bosong tarús.<bt>I have requested My Father, and later, when I am no longer together with you anymore, na, He will give you an Advisor/Mentor to show the way to you-pl. He is God2's Spirit, who teaches/will teach you what is true. Some people in this world don't want to accept/receive Him, because they can't see Him, and don't know/recognise Him. But you know/recognise Him because He is bound/linked to you. He will live in your livers. And He will also be together with you continually. [EXEG: Key Term: mentor, guide, comforter (too narrow), encourager (too narrow), advocate (too narrow, too much baggage), helper (too broad) see LN.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Pambina = supervisor, guide, mentor, (scouts"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">Pambina = supervisor, guide, mentor, (scouts guide/leader), pambimbing</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kagoò: and I, for my part"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">kagoò: and I, for my part erooteésoo: make a request, not ask a question<span class="Italic">(16) (16) </span>parakleiton: comforter, encourager, advocate, helper (too broad), mediator LITERALLY: I will pray to the Father, and he will give you another Comforter, that he may stay with you forever,<span class="Italic">(16) (16) </span>en hymíin: close relationship to you labéin: accept a person, implying that that person is taking over<span class="Italic">(16) (16) </span>LITERALLY: the Spirit of Truth, whom the world cannot receive, because they do not see him or know him. You know him, because he stays with you, and will be in you.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Deng bagitu, Beta sonde kasi tenga sang bosong sandiri, sama ke ana yang sonde ada pung mama-bapa. Ma inga, te Beta nanti datang kambali pi sang bosong.<bt>In that way, I am not abandoning/leaving you behind alone/by yourselves, like a child who has not mother-father. But remember, that I will come back again to you.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="orphanoús: orphans, nobody to care for"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">orphanoús: orphans, nobody to care for you (used of Socrates' pupils after his death, and also of the students of Jewish rabbis) LITERALLY: I will not leave you orphans. I will come to you.<span class="Italic">(18)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="19" />Sadiki lai, orang laen di ini dunya su sonde lia sang Beta lai. Ma bosong nanti lia sang Beta. Tagal Beta idop kambali, bosong ju dapa idop yang batúl.<bt>Soon/in a little while, other people in this world will not see Me anymore. But you-pl will later see Me. Because I will live again/come back to life, you will also get/obtain real life.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hyméis dè: but you all, in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">hyméis dè: but you all, in contrast with them theooréité: they were not going to see Jesus during the time he was dead, but they would see him again after he rose from the dead<span class="Italic">(19) (19) </span>hóti egoò: because I (emphatic) live (at that future time), that is what will make you live too LITERALLY: In a little while the world will not see me anymore. But you will see me, because I live, and you will live.<span class="Italic">(19)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="20" />Deng nanti, kalo Beta su idop kambali, bosong tau batúl bilang, Beta ada ta'ika deng Beta pung Bapa; bosong ada ta'ika deng Beta; ais Beta ada ta'ika deng bosong ju.<bt>And later, when I have already come back to life, you will really know that I am bound/linked to My Father; you-pl are bound/linked to Me; and I am bound/linked to you as well.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: In that day you will"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: In that day you will know that I am in my Father, and you are in me, and I am in you.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Orang yang tarima deng bekin iko Beta pung parenta dong, na, dia tu yang sayang sang Beta. Deng Beta pung Bapa ju sayang sang orang yang sayang sang Beta bagitu. Beta ju sayang sang dia, deng kasi tunju Beta pung diri sang dia.&gt;&gt;<bt>The person who accepts and does according to/obeys My commands, na, s/he is the one who loves Me. And My Father also loves the person who loves Me like that. I also love him, and show Myself to him.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="emphanw: reveal, disclose, show, make known,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">emphanw: reveal, disclose, show, make known, [special divine manifestation, more than showing him who I am, I will come to him, come to him personally] échoon: has my commandments, accepts my commandments -- the first step toward keeping them<span class="Italic">(21) (21) </span>LITERALLY: He who has my commandments and keeps them, he is the one who loves me. My Father will love the one who loves me, and I will love him, and make myself known to him.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Di situ ada satu orang, nama Yudas. Dia tu, bukan Yudas Iskariot. Waktu dia dengar Yesus pung omong, ju dia tanya bilang, &lt;&lt;Bos mau kasi tunju diri sang botong. Ma akurang ko Bos sonde mau kasi tunju diri sang orang laen di ini dunya dong?&gt;&gt;<bt>There, there was a person named Yudas. He was not Yudas iskariot. When he heard what Yesus was saying, he asked saying, “You (Bos) are going to show yourself to us-exc. But why is it that You (Bos) don't want to show yourself to other people in this world?”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kaì tí gégonen: what's up that"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">kaì tí gégonen: what's up that ... how can it be? not "why" emphanízein: Judas's problem is, if it's going to be so obvious to us, how can this happen without everybody else knowing about it?<span class="Italic">(22) (22) </span>LITERALLY: Judas (not Iscariot) said to him, "Lord, how can it be that you will make yourself known to us and not to the world?"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Bagini. Orang yang sayang sang Beta, dia nanti bekin iko Beta pung Kata-kata. Beta pung Bapa ju sayang sang dia. Ais Beta deng Beta pung Bapa idop satu hati deng dia.<bt>Yesus responded saying, “It's like this. The person who loves Me, s/he will do according to /obey My Words/Message. My Father (will) also loves him. So I, and My Father (will) live one livered (in harmony, one accord, same purpose) with him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="eán tis: generic, no matter who"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">eán tis: generic, no matter who moneen par autooi poieesometha: settle down permanently<span class="Italic">(23) (23) </span>LITERALLY: Jesus answered him, "Whoever loves me, he will keep my words, and my Father will love him, and we will come to him, and live with him.</Message></Annotation><v n="24" />Ma orang yang sonde sayang sang Beta, dia ju sonde bekin iko Beta pung Kata-kata. Naa, samua hal yang bosong dengar dari Beta ni, sonde ba'akar di Beta, ma ada ba'akar di Beta pung Bapa yang utus sang Beta.<bt>But the person who doesn't love Me, s/he also doesn't do according to /obey My Words/Message. Naa, [shift] everything that you-pl have heard from Me here, is not rooted/source in Me, but is rooted/source in My Father who sent/commissioned Me.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: The one who does not"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: The one who does not love me does not keep my word. The word which you hear is not mine, but the Father's who sent me.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Sakarang Beta masi sama-sama deng bosong. Andia ko Beta kasi tau memang ini hal dong.<bt>Noow I am still together with you-pl. That is why I am telling you beforehand (about) these matters.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: &quot;I have said these things"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: "I have said these things to you while I am with you.</Message></Annotation><v n="26" />Ma lama-lama, Beta pung Bapa mau kirim datang satu Pambina, andia Dia pung Roh Barisi. Itu Roh nanti ganti sang Beta di ini dunya. Dia pung tugas tu, andia: ajar samua hal sang bosong, deng kasi inga sang bosong samua hal yang Beta su parná kasi tau sang bosong.<bt>But eventually, My Father is going to send here an Advisor/Mentor, that is His *Clean/Holy/Pure Spirit. that Spirit will take My place in this world. His responsibilities/mission is this: teach all things to you-pl, and remind you everything that I have ever told/explained to you.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pánta: could be &quot;everything you need"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">pánta: could be "everything you need to know about what I have already taught you" LITERALLY: But the Comforter, who is the Holy Spirit, whom the Father will send in my name [to represent me, in my place], he will teach you everything, and remind you of everything I have told you.<span class="Italic">(26)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />Nanti, kalo Beta su pi, Beta bekin ko bosong bisa idop badame deng hati tanáng. Cuma Beta sa yang bisa kasi hati tanáng macam bagitu. Samua yang ada di ini dunya sonde bisa bekin bosong pung hati tanáng bagitu. Jadi jang kasi biar bosong bapikiran deng taku.<bt>Later, when I have gone, I will make it so you-pl can live in mutual good relations (peace #2), and calm livers (peace #3). I am the only one who can give you calm livers of that sort. Every (one/thing) in this world is not able to make your livers calm like that. So (consequently), don't let/allow yourselves to worry and be fearful.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="deiliátoo: afraid, cowardly, timid, dismayed, intimidated,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">deiliátoo: afraid, cowardly, timid, dismayed, intimidated, fearful LITERALLY: "I leave peace with you [plural]. I give you my peace. Not the kind of peace the world gives. Do not let your heart [singular] be troubled [worried and upset] or afraid.<span class="Italic">(27)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="28" />Bosong parná dengar Beta kasi tau sang bosong bilang, &lt;Beta kasi tenga sang bosong, ais nanti datang kambali.&gt; Sonde usa hati susa. Te kalo bosong sayang sang Beta, na, bosong pung hati sanáng, tagal Beta pi Beta pung Bapa. Naa, Beta pung Bapa tu, lebe hebat dari Beta.<bt>You-pl have heard Me tell/explain to you-pl saying, ‘I am leaving you-pl, and later will come back again.’ (You) don't need to be troubled in your livers/upset. Cuz (elaboration) if you-pl love Me, na, your livers will be happy, because I go/am going to My Father. Naa, [shift] My Father is greater/more amazing than Me.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: You have heard that I"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: You have heard that I said to you, 'I am going away and I will come again to you.' If you loved me, you would rejoice, because I am going to my Father, because my Father is greater than I.</Message></Annotation><v n="29" />Inga, te Beta su kasi tau memang sang bosong. Deng bagitu, kalo ini hal dong nanti jadi, na, bosong bisa parcaya sang Beta.<bt>Remember that I have already told you beforehand. In that way, when these things happen later, na, you can believe in Me.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And now I have told"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And now I have told you this before it happens, so that when it happens, you may believe.</Message></Annotation><v n="30" />Sadiki lai, Beta su sonde ba'omong deng bosong lai. Te setan dong pung bos ada datang. Dia pegang parenta di ini dunya, ma dia pung kuasa sonde kaná di Beta.<bt>Soon/in a little while, I will not speak with you anymore. Cuz (elaboration) the boss of the evil spirits is coming. He holds rule/government in this world, but his power/authority does not hit/effect Me. [EXEG: Gk is /gar/ ‘for’ which normally equates with KM /te/ and has a similar range of functions. Some translations use a stronger connector equivalent to /tagal/, but that is not appropriate here.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="@@ Te sends mixed signals. Check"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">@@ Te sends mixed signals. Check @@ Gk is /gar/ ‘for’ which normally equates with KM /te/ (al) Sadiki lai, Beta su sonde ba'omong deng bosong lai. Te setan dong pung bos ada datang. Biar dia parenta di ini dunya, ma dia pung kuasa sonde kaná di Beta. (but check how flows with next sentence below).<span class="Italic">(30)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: I will not speak with"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: I will not speak with you much longer, because the ruler of this world is coming. He has no effect on me.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Te setan dong pung bos, yang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">Te setan dong pung bos, yang parenta di ini dunya, ada datang. Ma dia pung kuasa sonde kaná di Beta.</Message></Annotation><v n="31" />Biar dia datang, ma Beta jalan tarús ko bekin iko Beta pung Bapa pung parenta. Itu kasi tunju sang orang di ini dunya bilang, Beta sayang mati sang Beta pung Bapa.<bt>Even though he comes, nevertheless I keep doing according to/obeying My Father's commands. That shows the people in this world that I dearly love My Father.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Naa. Mari ko kotong pi su!&gt;&gt;<bt>Naa [shift, conclusion]. Let's go now!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But so the world may"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But so the world may know that I love the Father, and as the Father commanded me, that is what I am doing. Get up! Let's leave!</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus sama ke anggor pung pohon<bt>The Lord Yesus is like a grape tree/vine</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="15" />
      <v n="1" />Yesus omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Dengar, é! Bosong ta'ika deng Beta. Beta sama ke anggor pung pohon satu. Ma Beta ni, pohon anggor yang batúl!<bt>Yesus spoke saying, “Listen, é! You-pl are bound/linked to Me. I am like a grape tree/vine. But I here, am the real/true grape vine!</bt><note reference="15:1" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Di Buku <span class="Italic">Janji Lama, </span>orang yang tulis dong suka banding bangsa Isra'el deng anggor pung pohon satu, ko, kabón anggor satu. (Lia <span class="Italic">Lagu Puji dong</span> 80:8-16; <span class="Italic">Yesaya</span> 5:1-7; <span class="Italic">Yermia</span> 2:21; <span class="Italic">Yeskial</span> 15:1-8, 19:10-14; <span class="Italic">Hosea</span> 10:1; deng tulisan laen lai ju.) Ma bangsa Isra'el dong serong dari Tuhan pung jalan yang batúl. Andia ko di sini Yesus subu diri bilang, Dia tu, andia &lt;pohon anggor yang batúl&gt;, te Dia sonde serong dari Tuhan pung mau.<bt>In the Book <span class="Italic">Old/Previous Promise, </span>the people who wrote often compared the people of Isra'el with a grapevine, or a grape orchard. (See <span class="Italic">Praise Songs</span> 80:8-16; <span class="Italic">Yesaya</span> 5:1-7; <span class="Italic">Yermia</span> 2:21; <span class="Italic">Yeskial</span> 15:1-8, 19:10-14; <span class="Italic">Hosea</span> 10:1; and other writings as well.) But the people of Isra'el strayed from God2's true path. That is why here Yesus refers to himself saying, that He is the ‘true/real grapevine’, cuz (elaboration) He does not stray from God2's will/desires.</bt></note>Deng Beta pung Bapa tu, sama ke tukang kabón.<bt>And My Father is like the gardener.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Israel is referred to as the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">Israel is referred to as the vine and the real vine (Jer. 2:21 and elsewhere) in the Old Testament, but they went astray. Jesus is the TRUE vine. ámpelos: grapes grow on a plant that is smaller than a tree. Some kinds are knee high, others higher than your head, but they need sticks to prop them up because the shoots can't handle the weight.<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>aleethineè: The nation of Israel was supposed to be "God's grape vine", like his favorite thing (Jeremiah 2:21), but the people didn't follow through. Jesus came and fulfilled the Jewish faith geoorgós: the person who takes care of the ground so it will grow a good crop<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>LITERALLY: "I am the true vine and my Father is the gardener.</Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Jadi orang yang cuma bilang dia ta'ika deng Beta, ma sonde bekin apa-apa, Beta pung Bapa buang sang dia, sama ke tukang kabón potong buang samua cabang yang sonde babua dong. Ma tiap orang yang ta'ika batúl deng Beta, Bapa kasi barisi kotoran dari dia pung hati, sama ke tukang kabón gunting kasi pende satu cabang ko dia pung bua batamba banya.<bt>So (consequently), a/the person who only/merely says s/he is bound/linked to Me, but doesn't do anything, My Father will get rid of him, just like a gardener cuts off &amp; gets rid of branches that don't bear fruit. But each person who is truly bound/linked to Me, Father cleans the dirt/filth/crud from his liver, just like a gardener prunes/scissors shortening a branch so it will bear more fruit.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: He takes off every branch"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: He takes off every branch in/on me that does not give fruit, and he cleans [prunes] every branch that gives fruit, so that it will give more fruit. kathaírei: prune a branch = cut off all the parts that are not going to produce fruit, so all the energy goes to the fruit. Cut off the stuff that isn't needed, get it properly prepared for the best production. They do it for coffee trees and avocados and fancy mangos<span class="Italic">(2)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="HK-LB\Hk00112c.tif" rtfFormat="width:6.5cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:right">Pohon anggor<bt>Grape vine</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Beta pung Kata-kata tu, su bisa bekin barisi bosong pung hati, sama ke tukang kabón bekin barisi dia pung pohon pung cabang dong.<bt>My Words/Message are already able to make a person's liver clean/pure/holy, just like a gardener cleans off the branches of his trees.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kasi barisi = focus on activity"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">kasi barisi = focus on activity ; bekin barisi = cause it to get into the state of CLEAN</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: &quot;You are clean already through"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: "You are clean already through the word which I have spoken to you.</Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Bosong musti ta'ika tarús deng Beta, sama ke Beta ta'ika deng bosong. Te cabang yang talapás buang dari dia pung pohon sonde bisa babua apa-apa. Bagitu ju deng bosong. Bosong sonde bisa bekin apa-apa yang bae, kalo bosong sonde ta'ika tarús deng Beta.<bt>You-pl must be bound/linked continually with Me, just like I am bound/linked to you. Cuz (elaboration) a branch that is separated off from its trunk/tree cannot bear any fruit whatsoever. It's the same way with you-pl. You are not able to do anything good at all, if you are not bound/linked continually with Me.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="méneei en téei ampélooi: break the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">méneei en téei ampélooi: break the branch off the main plant and it won't bear fruit. Leave it growing and it will en: in the New Testament for one person to be "en" another means that there is a very close relationship, like between good friends or people who are so close that each knows what the other is thinking. In Pidgin "stay tight wit" and "stick wit" are often used for this kind of relationship<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>LITERALLY: Remain in me, and I in you. Just as the branch cannot give fruit by itself unless it remains in the vine, neither can you unless you remain in me.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Beta ni, sama ke satu pohon anggor. Bosong tu, sama ke dia pung cabang. Jadi orang yang ta'ika tarús deng Beta, deng Beta ju ta'ika deng dia, dia tu sama ke satu cabang yang kasi kaluar banya bua. Tagal, kalo bosong sonde ta'ika tarús deng Beta, bosong sonde bisa bekin apa-apa yang bae.<bt>I here am like a grape tree/vine. You-pl are like its branches. So (consequently) a person who is bound/linked continually with Me, and I am also bound/linked continually with him, s/he is like a branch that gives out a lot of bruit. Because, if you are not bound/linked continually with Me, you are not able to do anything good.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: &quot;I am the vine, you"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: "I am the vine, you are the branches. He who remains in me, and I in him, he gives much fuit. Because without me you can do nothing.</Message></Annotation><v n="6" />Orang yang sonde ta'ika tarús deng Beta, dia tu sama ke satu cabang yang sonde ada pung guna. Cabang macam ke bagitu tu, biasa orang potong buang, ko kasi tenga dia jadi karíng. Ju orang kumpul ame itu cabang dong, ais lempar pi di api, ko bakar buang sang dong.<bt>A person who is not bound/linked continually with Me, s/he is like a branch that has no use. A branch of that sort, normally people would cut off and throw away, leaving it to dry out. then people would gather up those branches, and then throw them in the fire, to burn them up.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: If anyone does not remain"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: If anyone does not remain in me, he is thrown out like a branch, and withers, and they gather them, and throw them into a fire, and they burn.</Message></Annotation><v n="7" />Ma kalo bosong ta'ika tarús deng Beta, deng Beta pung Kata-kata ju tenga tarús dalam bosong pung hati, na, bosong bisa minta apa sa sang Tuhan Allah, ais nanti Dia bekin kasi bosong.<bt>But if you-pl are bound/linked continually with Me, and My Words/Message also lives/stays continually in your livers, na, whatever you request of God, He will do it for you.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="geneésetai hymíin: it will come to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">geneésetai hymíin: it will come to you (probably phrased in this impersonal way to avoid mentioning God's name, but everybody knew God was the person you were asking and God was the person who would do what you asked) LITERALLY: If you remain in me, and my words remain in you, you will ask whatever you want, and it will be done for you.<span class="Italic">(7)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Kalo bosong bekin hal bae bam-banya, sama ke satu cabang kasi kaluar bua bam-banya, itu angka tinggi-tinggi sang Tuhan Allah. Deng bagitu, bosong ju ada kasi tunju bilang, bosong tu, Beta pung ana bua dong.<bt>If you do many good things, like a branch puts out a lot of fruit, that *glorifies God. In that way, you are also showing that you are My *disciples.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="karpòn polýn: much fruit -- a"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">karpòn polýn: much fruit -- a word picture for lots of valuable results géneesthe: that you may be (parallel to "that you may bear fruit"). Quite a few manuscripts have geneésesthe "you will be", which is not parallel to "bear fruit" and has to be translated differently<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>LITERALLY: "By this my father will be glorified, that you produce much fruit, an you will become my disciples.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Sama ke Bapa ada sayang sang Beta, Beta ju ada sayang sang bosong bagitu. Bosong musti ta'ika tarús deng Beta, ko biar Beta bisa kasi tunju Beta pung sayang sang bosong.<bt>Just like Father loves Me, I also love you-pl like that. You must be bound/linked continually with Me, so that I can show My love to you.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: &quot;As the Father has loved"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: "As the Father has loved me, I also have loved you. Remain in my love.</Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Kalo bosong bekin iko Beta pung parenta dong, na, bosong ta'ika tarús deng Beta, ju Beta bisa kasi tunju Beta pung sayang sang bosong. Itu sama ke Beta bekin iko Beta pung Bapa pung parenta, ais Dia kasi tunju Dia pung sayang sang Beta tarús.<bt>If you do according to /obey My commands, na, you are bound/linked continually with Me, and I can show My love to you. That is like I do according to /obey My Father's commands, and He shows His love to Me continually.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="en: this is not for a"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">en: this is not for a relationship between people exactly. It's more like "not losing touch with God's love", a little more abstract entolas: plural, all of God's commands<span class="Italic">(10) (10) </span>LITERALLY: If you obey my commands, you will remain in my love, just like I have obeyed my Father's commands, and remain in his love.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Beta kasi tau ini hal dong sang bosong dari dolu, ko biar bosong pung hati bisa babunga, sama ke Beta pung hati babunga. Te Beta pung mau ko bosong pung hati babunga bam-banya!<bt>I have told/explained these things to you-pl from before, so the your livers can be happy/joyous (lit: flowered) just like My liver is flowered. Cuz (elaboration) My will/desire is for your-pl livers to have a lot of joy!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="leláleeka: I have been telling you"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">leláleeka: I have been telling you all along, right up to now hee charà hee emeé: the same kind of joy that I have<span class="Italic">(11) (11) </span>pleeroothéei: completely joyful, nothing lacking in your joy LITERALLY: "I have told you these things so that my joy may be in you, and that your joy may be complete/full.<span class="Italic">(11)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="12" />Beta pung parenta bagini: bosong musti basayang satu deng satu, sama ke Beta ju su sayang sang bosong.<bt>My command is like this: you-pl must love each other, just like I also have loved you. [Cf. 13:34-35]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: This is my command: love"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: This is my command: love each other just as I have loved you.</Message></Annotation><note reference="15:12" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yohanis 13:34, 15:17, 1 Yohanis 3:23, 2 Yohanis 5</note><v n="13" />Kalo satu orang sadia mati ko biar dia pung tamán bisa idop, dia sayang batúl sang dia pung tamán. Sonde ada sayang yang lebe hebat dari itu.<bt>If one person is prepared to die so that his friends can live, he really/truly loves his friends. There is no love which is greater/more amazing than that.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="teèn psycheèn autóu théei: allow oneself"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">teèn psycheèn autóu théei: allow oneself to be killed to benefit his friends. Some Pidgin speakers use "volunteer fo mahke", but most don't know the expression LITERALLY: No person has love greater than this: that someone lay down his life for his friends.<span class="Italic">(13)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="14" />Kalo bosong bekin iko Beta pung parenta tarús, bosong jadi Beta pung tamán dong.<bt>If you do according to /obey My commands continually (=keep doing), you are My friends.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: You are my friends if"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: You are my friends if you do the things I command you.</Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Beta sonde mau subu bosong, Beta pung &lt;orang suru-suru&gt; lai. Te satu orang suru-suru sonde mangarti batúl dia pung bos pung mau-mau. Ma Beta subu bosong, andia Beta pung &lt;tamán&gt;, tagal Beta su buka kasi taráng samua-samua yang Beta pung Bapa su kasi tau sang Beta.<bt>I don't want to refer to you as My ‘lowly servants’ anymore. Cuz (elaboration) a lowly servant does not truly understand his boss's wishes/desires/plans/values. But I refer to you, as My ‘friends’, because I have revealed plainly everything that My Father has told Me.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="doúlous: slaves, but Jesus never treated"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">doúlous: slaves, but Jesus never treated the disciples as if he owned them. But he did make it clear that they were to follow his instructions, so "servants" is probably okay LITERALLY: I do not call you 'slaves' any longer, because a slave does not know what his lord is doing. But I have called you 'friends', because I have made known to you everything my Father told me.<span class="Italic">(15)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="16" />Bosong sonde pili sang Beta. Ma Beta yang pili deng angka sang bosong ko kasi jalan ini tugas. Jadi bosong musti pi bekin banya hal yang bae yang batahan lama. Itu sama ke pohon anggor satu yang kasi kaluar bua yang bae tarús-tarús. Kalo bosong bekin bagitu, na, bosong bisa minta apa sa di Beta pung Bapa bawa Beta pung nama, ais Dia bekin kasi sang bosong.<bt>You-pl did not choose Me. But I am the one who chose and appointed/elevated you to carry out this work/responsibility/mission. So (consequently) you must go do many good things that endure/last/ keep/persevere. That is like a grape tree/vine which keeps putting out good fruit on and on. If you do like that, na, you can request whatever from My Father bearing My name, and He will do it for you.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: You have not chosen me,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: You have not chosen me, but I have chosen you, and appointed you to go and produce fruit, and that your fruit should last, so that whatever you will ask from the Father in my name, he may give it to you.</Message></Annotation><v n="17" />Jadi, yang Beta parenta sang bosong ni, bagini: bosong musti basayang satu deng satu.&gt;&gt;<bt>So (consequently) what I am commanding you here is like this: you must love each other.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: I command you these things:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: I command you these things: love each other."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Orang di ini dunya binci sang Tuhan Yesus pung orang dong<bt>People in this world hate the Lord Yesus' people</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Yesus omong tamba bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo orang di ini dunya binci sang bosong, na, inga te dong su binci sang Beta lebe dolo.<bt>Yesus spoke further saying, “If people in this world hate you-pl, na, remember that they hated Me first/before (you).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: If the world hates you,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: If the world hates you, you know that it hated me before you.</Message></Annotation><v n="19" />Kalo bosong ni, sama ke orang laen di ini dunya, pasti dong sayang sang bosong. Ma bosong sonde sama ke dong. Te Beta su pili ame sang bosong ko kasi pisa sang bosong dari dong. Andia ko dong binci sang bosong.<bt>If you are the same as other people in this world, surely they would love you. But you are not the same as them. Cuz (elaboration) I have already chosen/selected you to separate you from them. That is why they hate you.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: If you were from/of [belonged"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: If you were from/of [belonged to] the world, the world would love their own. But because you are not of [do not belong to] the world, but I have chosen you out of the world, therefore the world hates you.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Jang lupa yang Beta su kasi tau sang bosong bilang, &lt;Satu orang suru-suru sonde lebe hebat dari dia pung tuan.&gt; Jadi, kalo dong bekin sangsara sang Beta, pasti dong ju bekin sangsara sang bosong. Kalo dong dengar sang Beta pung Kata-kata, na, dong ju dengar sang bosong.<bt>Don't forget what I already told you saying, ‘A servant is not greater/more impressive than his master/owner.’ So (consequently), if/when they torment/cause suffering/misery to Me, surely they will also torment/cause suffering/misery to you-pl. If they listened to/obeyed My Words/Message, na, they should/would also listen to you. [NOTE to daughter translations: Compare wording in Jn. 13:16.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: &quot;Remember the word that I"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: "Remember the word that I spoke to you, the slave is not greater than his lord. If they persecute me, they will also persecute you. If they obey my word, they will obey yours too.</Message></Annotation><note reference="15:20" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 10:24, Lukas 6:40, Yohanis 13:16</note><v n="21" />Nanti dong bekin sangsara sang bosong, tagal bosong ta'ika deng Beta. Te dong ju sonde kanál sang Dia yang utus sang Beta.<bt>They will torment/cause suffering/misery to you, because you are bound/linked to Me. Cuz (elaboration) they also don't know/recognise Him who sent/commissioned Me. [NOTE: Gk ‘but’ here is contrary to expectation, not a contrast with what comes before, so Ma here would be awkward in Kupang. UNS's at Consultant check couldn't get the leap-frogging deixis of what the broader “do these thngs to you” referred to.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But they will do all"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But they will do all these things to you for my name's sake, because they do not know the one who sent me.</Message></Annotation><v n="22" />Kalo Beta sonde parná datang omong deng dong, ais kasi tunju jalan idop yang batúl sang dong, na, dong pikir tarús bilang, dong sonde ada pung sala apa-apa. Ma Beta su datang, deng su omong bagitu. Jadi sakarang, kalo dong ada bekin sala, na, dong su sonde ada pung alasan lai ko omong bilang, &lt;We! Botong ni sonde tau yang botong bekin tu, sala.&gt;<bt>If I had never come and spoken with them, and/then shown the true way of life to them, na, they would keep thinking that, they have no wrong/sin whatsoever. But I have come, and have spoken like that. So (consequently), if they are doing wrong/sin, na, they have no basis/excuse anymore to speak saying, ‘We! We-exc didn't know what we were doing was wrong/sin.’</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: If I had not come"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: If I had not come and spoken to them, they would not have sin. But now they have no cloak/cover/excuse for their sin.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Sakarang, dong su sonde ada pung"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">Sakarang, dong su sonde ada pung alasan lai ko bekin sala, ma ais dong omong, bilang, &lt;We! Botong sonde tau yang botong bekin ni, sala.&gt;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Orang yang binci sang Beta, dia ju binci sang Beta pung Bapa.<bt>The person who hates Me, he also hates My Father.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: He who hates me also"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: He who hates me also hates my Father.</Message></Annotation><v n="24" />Beta su bekin tanda heran macam-macam di dong pung muka, yang orang laen sonde parná bekin. Kalo Beta sonde bekin itu hal dong, dong ju sonde sala, kalo sonde mau tarima sang Beta. Padahal dong su lia ame itu tanda heran yang Beta su bekin dong. Biar bagitu, ma dong masi binci sang Beta deng Beta pung Bapa di sorga ju.<bt>I have done a variety of amazing signs in front of them, that other people have never done. If I hadn't done those things, they also wouldn't be wrong/at fault if they didn't want to accept Me. Whereas in fact, they have seen those amazing signs which I have done. Even that being the case, nevertheless they still hate Me and My Father in heaven. [EXEG: Carson, NLT, CEV. The sin is the rejection of Christ.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: If I had not done"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: If I had not done among them the deeds that no other man did, they would not have sin. But now they have both seen and hated both me and my Father.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Beta su bekin tanda heran macam-macam"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">Beta su bekin tanda heran macam-macam di dong pung muka, yang orang laen sonde parná bekin. Ma kalo Beta sonde bekin itu hal dong, dong ju sonde tau, yang dong pung bekin tu, sala ko sonde. Ma sakarang, dong su lia ame sang Beta deng Beta pung Bapa, ais dong binci sang Botong, tagal apa yang dong bekin tu, su jalás-jalás, sala.</Message></Annotation><v n="25" />Ma ini hal dong samua su jadi, ko bekin iko apa yang su tatulis dalam Tuhan pung Atoran bilang, &lt;Dong binci sang Beta. Padahal dong pung binci tu, sonde ada pung dasar apa-apa.&gt;<bt>But all these things happened, to to do according to/to fulfill what was written in God2's Regulations/Law saying, ‘They hate(d) Me. Whereas in fact their hate has no basis/foundation whatsoever.’</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But in order that the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But in order that the word which is written in their Law might be fulfilled, 'They hated me without a cause."</Message></Annotation><note reference="15:25" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 35:19, 69:5</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="26" />Ma nanti itu Pambina mau datang. Dia tu, Roh yang bekin bosong mangarti apa yang batúl. Dia datang dari Beta pung Bapa. Kalo Beta su pi Beta pung Bapa, nanti Beta kirim datang Dia pung Roh kasi sang bosong. Dia kasi tau sang bosong so'al Beta.<bt>But later that Advisor/Mentor is going to come. He is the Spirit who makes you-pl understand what is true. He comes from My Father. If/when I have gone to My Father, I will send coming His Spirit to you. He will tell/explain to you about Me.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: &quot;But when the Comforter comes,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: "But when the Comforter comes, whom I will send to you from the Father, the Spirit of Truth, who will come from the Father, he will testify of me.</Message></Annotation><v n="27" />Bosong ju nanti kasi tau orang so'al Beta, tagal bosong su ada sama-sama deng Beta dari mula-mula.<bt>You will also tell people about Me, because you have been together with Me from the beginning.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And you too will testify,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And you too will testify, because you have been with me from the beginning.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="16" />
      <v n="1" />Beta su kasi tau ini hal dong sang bosong, ko biar bosong sonde ondor diri dari Beta.<bt>I have told you these things, so that you will not retreat/withdraw from Me.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="!@ CEV grossly undertranslated"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">!@ CEV grossly undertranslated</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mee skandalistheete: this is broader than"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">mee skandalistheete: this is broader than "the integrity and durability of their faith" that some of the English versions seem to limit it to. It includes "not be turned away from trusting in me," but it's not limited to that. Arndt &amp; Gingrich gloss it in this passage as "let oneself be led into sin, fall away." When the word is used in Chapter 6 it refers to people who didn't really trust Jesus but wanted to listen to him, but they got bent out of shape when he said things that weren't already part of their world view. LITERALLY: "I have said these things to you so that you should not [fall away / give up your faith / go astray / be offended].<span class="Italic">(1)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Nanti orang Yahudi dong usir buang sang bosong dari dong pung ruma sambayang. Bukan cuma bagitu sa, te nanti ju ada jaman yang, kalo orang bunu bekin mati sang bosong, dong pikir dong ada bekin yang bae kasi sang Tuhan Allah.<bt>Later the Yahudi people will evict you from their houses of worship. Not only that, (but) later there will also be an age/long time period in which if/when people kill you, they will think they are doing something good for God.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: They will put you out"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: They will put you out of the synagogues. And the time is coming when anyone who kills you will think that he is doing God a favor.</Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Dong bekin bagitu kasi sang bosong, tagal dong sonde kanál batúl sang Beta. Dong ju sonde kanál sang Beta pung Bapa.<bt>They do that to you, because they don't really know/recognise Me. They also don't know My Father.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: They will do these things"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: They will do these things to you because they do not know the Father or me.</Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Ma Beta su kasi tau ini hal dong sang bosong, ko biar nanti, kalo ini hal dong su jadi, na, bosong bisa inga bilang, Beta su kasi tau memang sang bosong dari dolu. Tagal Beta masi ada sama-sama deng bosong, andia ko Beta sonde kasi tau lebe dolo.&gt;&gt;<bt>But I have told you these things, so that later, if/when these things happen, na, you can remember that, I already foretold (them) from beforehand/previous time. Because (now) I am still together with you, that is why I didn't tell you previously.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But I have told you"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But I have told you these things, so that when the time comes you may remember that I told you about them. I didn't tell you these things at the beginning, because I was with you.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan pung Roh pung karjá<bt>The work of God2's Spirit</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Yesus ajar tamba bilang, &lt;&lt;Sakarang Beta pulang pi Dia yang utus sang Beta datang di ini dunya. Ma sonde ada dari bosong yang tanya Beta bilang, &lt;Bos ada mau pi mana?&gt;<bt>Yesus taught further saying, “Now I am going home to Him who sent/commissioned Me to come to this world. But there aren't any of you-pl who ask Me saying, ‘Where are You (Bos) going?’</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But now I am going"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But now I am going to him who sent me. And none of you asks me, 'Where are you going?'</Message></Annotation><v n="6" />Tagal Beta su kasi tau ini hal sang bosong, andia ko bosong pung hati su jadi barát.<bt>Because I have told you these things, that is why your livers have become heavy.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lypee: how people feel at the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">lypee: how people feel at the funeral of someone they loved LITERALLY: But because I have told you these things, sadness has filled your hearts.<span class="Italic">(6)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="7" />Ma apa yang Beta kasi tau sang bosong tu, batúl. Kalo Beta pi, na, itu lebe bae kasi bosong. Te kalo Beta sonde pi, itu Pambina sonde datang kasi tunju jalan sang bosong. Ma kalo Beta pi, na, Beta kirim datang sang Dia kasi sang bosong.<bt>But what I have told/am telling you is true. If/when I go, na, that is better for you. Cuz (elaboration) if I don't go, that Advisor/Mentor will not come and show the way to you. But if I go, na, I will send Him coming to you. [EXEG: is “and show the way to you an addition?” A: part of meaning of parakletos; not adding any element that not explicit in context and discussion of HS in 14 &amp; 16. Felt by UNSs to be incomplete without it.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But I am telling you"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But I am telling you the truth. It is better for you that I go away. Because if I do not go away, the Comforter will not come to you. But if I go away, I will send him to you.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Nanti kalo Dia su datang, Dia kasi tunju sang orang di ini dunya bilang, dong pung hati deng dong pung bekin tu, sala. Dia buju sang dong ko iko jalan idop yang batúl. Deng Dia ju kasi inga sang dong bilang, nanti Tuhan mau putus dong pung parkara bilang, dong tu, batúl, ko sala.<bt>[EXEG for vs 8-11: see discussion in Carson] Later if/when He comes, He will show people in this world that, their livers and their deeds are wrong. He will persuade/coax/entice them to follow the true way of life. And He will also remind them that God2 is later going to decide their cases, whether they are right/true, or wrong/at fault.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: &quot;And when he comes, he"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: "And when he comes, he will convince/convict] the world about sin, and righteousness, and judgment.</Message></Annotation><v n="9" />Itu Pambina kasi tunju dong pung sala, tagal dong sonde parcaya sang Beta.<bt>That Advisor/Mentor shows their wrong/sin, because they do not believe in Me.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Of sin, because they do"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Of sin, because they do not believe in me.</Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Dia ju kasi tunju jalan idop yang batúl. Tagal Beta kambali pi Beta pung Bapa, nanti bosong su sonde lia sang Beta lai. Andia ko itu Pambina datang ko ganti sang Beta.<bt>He also shows the true way of life. Because I return to My Father, you will not see Me anymore. That is why that Advisor comes to replace Me. [DISCOURSE: context from vs. 7.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Of righteousness because I go"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Of righteousness because I go to my Father, and you won't see me any more.</Message></Annotation><v n="11" />Dia ju kasi tunju bilang, Tuhan mau putus orang pung parkara deng batúl, tagal Tuhan su putus parkara kasi setan dong pung bos, yang parenta di ini dunya.<bt>He also shows that God2 is going to decide people's cases correctly, because God2 has already decided the case of the boss of the evil spirits, who governs/rules in this world.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Of judgment, because the ruler"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Of judgment, because the ruler of this world is judged.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Ada banya hal yang Beta masi mau kasi tau sang bosong, ma bosong balóm bisa mangarti sakarang.<bt>There are many things which I still want to tell/explain to you, but you are note yet able to understand (them) now.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: I still have many things"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: I still have many things to tell you, but you cannot take them now.</Message></Annotation><v n="13" />Ma nanti kalo Roh yang kasi tunju hal-hal yang batúl su datang, na, Dia pimpin ko biar bosong bisa mangarti samua hal yang batúl. Dia sonde omong dari Dia pung diri sandiri sa, ma Dia kasi tau apa yang Dia dengar dari Beta pung Bapa. Dia ju mau kasi tau sang bosong, apa yang lama-lama nanti jadi.<bt>But later if/when the Spirit who shows the things that are true has come, na, He will lead/guide so that you are able to understand everthing that is true. He does not speak from His own self, but He tells/explains what He hears from My Father. He also is going to tell you what will eventually happen later.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But when the Spirit of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But when the Spirit of Truth comes, he will lead you into all the truth. He will not speak on his own, but whatever he hears, he will speak, and he will tell you what is coming.</Message></Annotation><v n="14" />Dia mau angka tinggi-tinggi sang Beta, tagal Dia mau buka samua hal yang batúl so'al Beta, deng kasi tunju sang bosong.<bt>He is going to *glorify (elevate very high) Me, because He is going to reveal everything that is true about Me, and show it to you-pl.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: He will glorify me, because"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: He will glorify me, because he will take of mine [my truth] and will show it to you.</Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Samua yang jadi Beta pung Bapa pung milik, ju jadi Beta pung milik. Andia ko Beta omong tadi bilang, Tuhan pung Roh nanti mau buka samua hal yang batúl so'al Beta, deng kasi tunju sang bosong.&gt;&gt;<bt>Every(thing/one) that is My Father's possession, is also My possession. That is why I said earlier that, God2's Spirit will reveal everything that is true about Me, and show it to you.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Everything the Father has is"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Everything the Father has is mine, therefore I said that he will take of mine [my truth], and will show it to you.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Bosong pung hati musti susa dolo, ais nanti baru kambali jadi sanáng<bt>Your-pl livers must be in difficulty first, and then later will return to happiness</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Yesus kasi tau tamba bilang, &lt;&lt;Sonde lama lai, bosong su sonde lia sang Beta. Ma sonde lama ju, bosong lia kambali sang Beta.&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus told (them) further saying, “Soon/not much longer, you will not see Me. But not long after that, you will see Me again.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: &quot;In a little while, you"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: "In a little while, you will not see me. And then in a little while, you will see me.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Ais itu, Dia pung ana bua saparu ba'omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bos pung maksud apa, ko bilang, &lt;Sonde lama lai, bosong su sonde lia sang Beta. Ma sonde lama ju, bosong lia kambali sang Beta.&gt; Deng, akurang ko Dia omong bilang, &lt;Tagal Beta mau pi Beta pung Bapa&gt;?&gt;&gt;<bt>After that, some of His disciples spoke (among themselves) saying, “What does Bos mean, by saying, ‘Soon/not much longer, you will not see Me. But not long after that, you will see Me again.’ And, why is it that He says, ‘Because I am going to My Father’?”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then some of the disciples"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then some of the disciples said to each other, "What is this that he says, 'In a little while, you will not see me. An then in a little while, you will see me.' And, 'Because I go to my Father'?</Message></Annotation><v n="18" />Ju dong batanya bilang, &lt;&lt;Dia pung maksud apa bilang, &lt;Sonde lama lai&gt;? Kotong sonde mangarti.&gt;&gt;<bt>And they asked (each other) saying, “What does He mean saying, ‘Soon/not much longer’? We-inc don't understand.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: So they said, &quot;What is"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: So they said, "What is this that he says, 'In a little while'? We do not know what he says."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Yesus su tau dong mau tanya sang Dia satu hal. Ju Dia omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Tadi Beta omong bilang, &lt;Sonde lama lai, bosong su sonde lia sang Beta. Ma sonde lama ju, bosong lia kambali sang Beta.&gt; Bosong ada batanya bagitu, to?<bt>Yesus already knew that they wanted to ask Him something. So He spoke saying, “Earlier I spoke saying, ‘Soon/not much longer, you will not see Me. But not long after that, you will see Me again.’ That is what you're asked (each other) about, right?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Jesus knew that they wanted"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Jesus knew that they wanted to ask him, and he said to them, "Concerning this do you ask among yourselves, that I said, 'In a little while you will not see me, and then in a little while you will see me?'"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Bae ju, kalo bosong mau cari tau bagitu. Beta ju ada mau kasi tau sang bosong bagini: bosong nanti manangis deng hati susa, ma orang laen di ini dunya dong hati sanáng. Biar bosong hati susa bagitu, ma nanti bosong pung hati kambali jadi sanáng.<bt>That's good if you are wanting to find out like that. I also want to tell you this: you will cry with troubled livers, but other people in this world will be happy livered. Even though your livers are troubled like that, nevertheless later your livers will return to being happy.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: It's true! I tell you,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: It's true! I tell you, you will cry and mourn, but the world will rejoice. You will be sorrowful, but your sorrow will be turned into gladness.</Message></Annotation><v n="21" />Itu sama ke satu parampuan yang rasa saki mau barana. Dia hati barát dolo, tagal dia pung susa su datang. Ma ais kalo dia su barana ame sang itu ana, dia pung susa ilang memang. Te dia pung hati jadi sanáng, tagal ada manusia baru yang su lahir di ini dunya.<bt>That is like a woman who feels pain about to give birth. Her liver is heavy/worried/sad/depressed first, because her difficulty/suffering has come. But then when she has already (finished) giving birth to that chcild, her suffering disappears/disapates immediately/instantly. Cuz (elaboration) her liver becomes happy, because there is a new human who has been born into this world.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: When a woman is in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: When a woman is in labor, she is sad, because her time [of suffering] has come. But when the child is born, she forgets her suffering, because she is happy that a person has been born into the world.</Message></Annotation><v n="22" />Bagitu ju deng bosong. Sakarang bosong manangis deng hati susa. Ma lama-lama Beta datang lia kambali sang bosong, ais bosong pung hati kambali jadi sanáng. Deng kalo itu hal su jadi, na, sonde ada satu orang ju yang bisa tahan bosong pung rasa sanáng.<bt>It's the same way with you-pl. Now you cry/weep with troubled livers. But eventually I will come back and see/visit/check up on you, and then your livers will return to happiness. And when that matter has happened, na, there is not one person who can hold back/restrain your feeling of happiness.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: So it is with you."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: So it is with you. Now you are sorrowful. But I will see you again, and your heart will rejoice, and nobody will take your joy away from you.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Deng kalo itu hal su jadi, na, bosong sonde batanya apa-apa sang Beta lai. Batúl! Beta kasi tau lai sang bosong bilang, kalo bosong minta apa sa dari Beta pung Bapa, bawa Beta pung nama, na, nanti Dia bekin bagitu kasi sang bosong.<bt>And when that matter has happened, na, you will not be asking Me anything else anymore. That's right! I'm telling you further that, if you request anything/whatever from My Father, bearing My name, na, He will do like that for you-pl.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="erooteésete: ask questions /tanya/ aiteéseete: ask"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">erooteésete: ask questions /tanya/ aiteéseete: ask somebody to do something (includes asking him to give you something) /minta/<span class="Italic">(23) (23) </span>en tóoi onómatí mou: on the grounds that you bear my name, are associated with me. Probably goes with "ask", rather than "give", because of parallels to "ask in my name" in these same chapters (14: 13-14, 16:16, 24, 26), because of the order of elements, and because "give in my name" is not found anywhere else in the New Testament, while "ask in my name" is common LITERALLY: And in that day you will not ask me anything. That's right! I tell you, whatever you ask the Father in my name, he will give it to you.<span class="Italic">(23)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="16:23" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Sambayang &lt;&lt;bawa Beta pung nama&gt;&gt; ada pung arti bilang, kotong sambayang iko Yesus pung mau. Kotong ada pung hak ko &lt;&lt;bawa Yesus pung nama&gt;&gt; kalo kotong jadi Dia pung orang, kalo kotong idop ta'ika tarús deng Dia, kalo kotong dengar-dengar sang Dia, deng kalo kotong parcaya bilang, Dia mati ko hapus buang kotong pung sala-sala. Jadi &lt;&lt;bawa Yesus pung nama&gt;&gt; tu, sonde sama deng cuma &lt;&lt;subu Yesus pung nama&gt;&gt; sa.<bt>Praying “bearing My name” means that we-inc pray according to Yesus' will. We have the right to “bear Yesus' name” if we are His person/people, if we live bound/linked with Him continnually, if we keep listening/obeying Him, and if we believe that He died to wipe away our sins. So (consequently), “bear Yesus' name” is not the same as merely “mentioning Yesus' name”.</bt></note><v n="24" />Sampe sakarang, bosong balóm minta apa-apa, bawa Beta pung nama. Jadi minta sa, ko bosong tarima. Deng bagitu, bosong pung hati bisa sanáng batúl.&gt;&gt;<bt>Until now, you have not yet requested anything, bearing My name. So (consequently) just request, so that you can receive. In that way your livers can be truly happy.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Until now you have not"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Until now you have not asked anything in my name. Ask and you will receive, that your joy may be full/complete.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus su kasi kala samua kuasa di ini dunya<bt>The Lord Yesus has defeated all powers/authorities in this world</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Yesus omong tamba bilang, &lt;&lt;Sampe sakarang ni, Beta biasa ajar sang bosong pake umpama dong. Ma nanti ada waktu ko Beta ajar deng sonde pake umpama lai. Te Beta mau omong taráng-taráng so'al Beta pung Bapa.<bt>Yesus spoke further saying, “Until now, I usually teach you using *illustrations/parables. But later there is a time for Me to teach without using illustrations/parables anymore. Cuz (elaboration) I am going to speak clearly/openly about My Father.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="paroimíais: symbols, figurative language. Probably includes"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">paroimíais: symbols, figurative language. Probably includes not just the stories or "parables", but also symbolic actions like washing the disciples' feet, and things that are not really stories like the "shepherd" symbolism and the "vine" symbolism parreesíaai: plainly, openly, so you will understand, clearly<span class="Italic">(25) (25) </span>LITERALLY: "I have told you these things in parables. But the time is coming when I will not talk to you in parables any longer, but I will tell you plainly about the Father.</Message></Annotation><v n="26" />Kalo itu waktu su datang, na, bosong sandiri yang sambayang ko minta langsung sang Beta pung Bapa, bawa Beta pung nama. Sonde usa Beta lai yang sambayang kasi sang bosong.<bt>When that time has come, na, you yourselves are the ones who will pray to request directly from My Father, bearing My name. It no longer needs to be Me anymore who prays for you. [EXEG: NLT, CEV]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: In that day, you will"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: In that day, you will ask in my name, and I'm not saying to you that I will pray to the Father for you,</Message></Annotation><v n="27" />Te Beta pung Bapa sayang sang bosong, tagal bosong ada sayang sang Beta. Deng bosong ju yakin bilang, Tuhan yang utus sang Beta.<bt>Cuz My Father loves you, because you love Me. And you are also assured/confident that God2 is the one who sent/commissioned Me.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="philéi, pephileékate: love, as good friends"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">philéi, pephileékate: love, as good friends love each other and try to help each other out pepisteúkate: some time ago you formed a conviction that I came from God, and you are still holding on to the same conviction<span class="Italic">(27) (27) </span>LITERALLY: because the Father himself loves [philew] you, because you have loved [philew] me, and have believed that I came from God.</Message></Annotation><v n="28" />Dolu Beta kasi tenga Beta pung Bapa, ko Beta tenga tahan di ini dunya. Ma sakarang Beta mau kasi tenga ini dunya, ko pi tenga kambali deng Dia.&gt;&gt;<bt>Previously I left My Father, so I could stay temporarily in this world. But now I am going to leave this world, so go back and live/stay with Him.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="exéelthon ... eleélytha: I came (an"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">exéelthon ... eleélytha: I came (an event) ... I came and have been here ever since then (a state) LITERALLY: I came out from the Father, and have come into the world. Now I leave the world, and go to the Father.<span class="Italic">(28)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="29" />Dengar bagitu, ju Yesus pung ana bua dong kasi tau bilang, &lt;&lt;Naaa! Sakarang Bos ada omong taráng-taráng, deng ajar sonde pake umpama dong lai!<bt>Hearing that, Yesus' disciples said, “Naaa! Now You (Bos) are speaking clearly/openly, and teaching without using illustrations/parables anymore!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="paroimían: just like Verse 25 LITERALLY:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">paroimían: just like Verse 25 LITERALLY: His disciples said to him, "Look! Now you are talking plainly, and are not speaking in parables.<span class="Italic">(29)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="30" />Botong su yakin, Bos tau samua hal. Orang sonde parlú tanya apa-apa sang Bos lai, tagal Bos su tau lebe dolo apa yang dong mau tanya, deng dia pung jawab karmana. Itu kasi tunju sang botong bilang, Bos datang langsung dari Tuhan Allah.&gt;&gt;<bt>We-exc are sure/confident that You (Bos) knows everything. Nobody needs to ask You anything anymore, because You already know beforehand what they are going to ask, and what the answer is/how to answer. That shows us that You came directly from God.” [EXEG: HCE (NLT &amp; CEV still confused, unclear).]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="chreían: need. In Verse 19 Jesus"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">chreían: need. In Verse 19 Jesus answered a question they wanted to ask him, and he knew what the question was before they asked it. In other words, they realized that Jesus already knew what they were thinking LITERALLY: Now we are sure that you know everything, and do not need anyone to ask you. By this we know that you came from God.<span class="Italic">(30)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="31" />Ju Yesus tanya sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Batúl, ko? Sakarang bosong parcaya sang Beta, ko?<bt>Yesus asked them saying, “Is that true? Now you believe in Me?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="árti: right now. The way Jesus"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">árti: right now. The way Jesus asks his question casts doubt on how strongly they actually trust him. He knows they're going to have real problems in a little while LITERALLY: Jesus answered them, "Now do you believe?<span class="Italic">(31)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="32" />Bagini. Sadiki lai, andia sabantar ni, bosong samua lari tasiram. Tiap orang lari kasi tenga Beta, ko pi sambunyi di dia pung tampa sandiri-sandiri. Biar bagitu, ma Beta sonde sandiri, tagal Beta pung Bapa ada sama-sama deng Beta.<bt>Like this. Soon, actually now, all of you will run scattering. Each person will run off abandoning Me, to go hide in his own (individual) place. Even that being the case, nevertheless I will not be alone, because My Father is together with Me.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="érchetai hoóra kaì eleélythen: in just"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">érchetai hoóra kaì eleélythen: in just a little while -- in fact, in a very short while, sooner than you think LITERALLY: Look! The time is coming, and is here now, when you will be scattered, everyone to his own place, and you will leave me alone. And yet, I am not alone, because the Father is with me.<span class="Italic">(32)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="33" />Beta su kasi tau ini hal dong sang bosong, ko biar bosong pung hati bisa tanáng, tagal bosong ta'ika deng Beta. Te orang di ini dunya nanti bekin susa deng sangsara sang bosong. Ma kasi kuat bosong pung hati, te Beta su kasi kala samua kuasa di ini dunya!&gt;&gt;<bt>I have told these things to you-pl, so that your livers may be calm, because you are bound/linked to Me. Cuz (elaboration) people in this world will cause suffering and strife you you. But be encouraged (strengthen your livers), cuz (elaboration) I have already caused defeat to all the powers/authorities in this world!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="!@ CEV doesn't quite capture it."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">!@ CEV doesn't quite capture it.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: I have told you these"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: I have told you these things so that in me you might have peace. In the world you will have trouble/tribulation. But be confident, I have had victory over the world.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus sambayang kasi sang Dia pung diri<bt>The Lord Yesus prays for Himself</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="17" />
      <v n="1-2" />Yesus omong abis bagitu, ju Dia mangada pi langit, ais sambayang bilang:<bt>[When] Yesus finished speaking like that, He faced the sky, and prayed, saying: [EXEG &amp; STRUCTURE: see Carson]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">&lt;&lt;Bapa Bo'i. Beta pung waktu su sampe ko Bapa angka tinggi-tinggi sang Beta. Beta ni, Bapa pung Ana. Bapa su kasi sang Beta hak ko ator samua orang di ini dunya. Bapa kasi itu hak, ko biar Beta kasi idop yang batúl yang sonde tau putus-putus sang samua orang yang Bapa su sarakan ko jadi Beta pung orang. Jadi sakarang, Beta minta ko Bapa angka tinggi-tinggi sang Beta, ko biar Beta bisa kasi tunju Bapa pung hebat.<bt>“Dear Father. My time has arrived for Father to *glorify Me. I am Father's Child. You (from ‘Father’ throughout) have given Me the right/authority to oversee/arrange/control/put in order everyone in this world. You gave that right, so that I give real life that never ends to everyone whom You have turned over/surrendered to be My people. So (consequently) now, I request that You *glorify (elevate way on high) Me, so that I can show Your greatness/amazingness/incredibleness. [EXEG: “the hour has come” Carson “the appointed time for Jesus' death/exaltation, for his glorification.” CEV “the time has come for you to bring glory to your Son,” Morris “Now with the cross in immediate prospect Jesus can speak of the hour as having come. This is that to which the whole ministry of Jesus has led up. ... To human view the cross was an instrument of shame. To Christ it was the means of true glory.”]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="&lt;&lt;Bapa. Dia pung waktu su datang/sampe."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">&lt;&lt;Bapa. Dia pung waktu su datang/sampe. Sakarang, angka tinggi-tinggi sang Beta, ko biar Beta bisa kasi tunju Bapa pung hebat. Te Beta ni, Bapa pung Ana. (2) Bapa su kasi sang Beta kuasa ko ator/hak parenta atas samua orang di ini dunya, ko biar Beta kasi idop yang sonde putus-putus sang samua orang yang Bapa su sarakan sang Beta Bapa Bo'i. Beta pung waktu su sampe. Beta ni, Bapa pung Ana. Bapa su kasi sang Beta hak ko ator samua orang di ini dunya. Bapa kasi itu hak, ko biar Beta kasi idop yang batúl yang sonde tau putus-putus sang samua orang yang Bapa su sarakan ko jadi Beta pung orang. Jadi sakarang, Beta minta ko Bapa angka tinggi-tinggi sang Beta, ko biar Beta bisa kasi tunju Bapa pung hebat.<span class="Italic">(1)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="HEADERS 1-5 prays for himself 6-19"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">HEADERS 1-5 prays for himself 6-19 prays for his disciples 20-26 prays for all believers (look at NIV)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Jesus said this, and looked"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Jesus said this, and looked up to heaven and said, "Father, the hour has come. Glorify your Son, that your Son may glorify you, exousia: *jurisdiction, authority to rule, control, power, supernatural power, right to judge.<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>LITERALLY: just as you have given him power over all [flesh/people/humans], that he should give eternal life to as many as you have given him.</Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Dia pung cara ko dapa itu idop yang batúl yang sonde tau putus-putus tu, bagini: orang musti kanál sang Bapa, andia Tuhan Allah yang batúl. Sonde ada laen lai. Dong ju musti kanál sang Beta, andia Yesus Kristus, yang Bapa su utus ko datang di ini dunya.<bt>The way to get/obtain that real life that never ends is like this: a person must know/recognise You, that is the true/real God. There is no other. They must also know/recognise Me, that is Yesus Kristus, whom You have sent/commissioned to come to this world. [EXEG: NLT; Apr 2011 changed ‘no other way’, to ‘no other’, Gk is ‘only true God’, not ‘only way’. OV was skewed focus.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: This is eternal life, that"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: This is eternal life, that they may know you, the only true God, and Jesus Christ, whom you have sent.</Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Beta su kasi tunju Bapa pung hebat di ini dunya. Beta su bekin abis itu tugas yang Bapa su kasi sang Beta.<bt>I have shown Your greatness/amazingness in this world. I have finished/completed that work/mission/responsibility that You gave to Me.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: I have glorified you on"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: I have glorified you on the earth. I have finished the work that you gave me to do.</Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Dolu, waktu Kotong balóm bekin ini dunya, Beta ada sama-sama deng Bapa. Itu waktu, Beta pung hebat ju sama ke Bapa pung hebat. Naa, sakarang Beta mau kambali pi Bapa. Jadi Beta minta ko Bapa angka tinggi-tinggi sang Beta, ko biar Beta hebat kambali sama ke dolu.&gt;&gt;<bt>Previously, when We-inc had not yet made this world (=before we made), I was together with You. At that time, My greatness/amazingness was also the same as Your greatness/amazingness. Naa, now I am going to return to You. So (consequently) I request You to *glorify Me, so that My greatness/amazingness returns to be the same as previously.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And now glorify me, Father,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And now glorify me, Father, with your own glory that I had with you before the world was.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Dolu, waktu Beta ada sama-sama deng"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">Dolu, waktu Beta ada sama-sama deng Bapa, mulai dari Kotong balóm bekin ini dunya tu, Beta pung hebat ju sama ke Bapa pung hebat. Naa, sakarang Beta kambali pi di Bapa. Jadi Beta minta Bapa angka tinggi-tinggi sang Beta, ko biar Beta hebat sama ke dolu.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus sambayang kasi sang Dia pung ana bua dong [\s2]<bt>The Lord Yesus prays for His *disciples [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Yesus sambayang tamba bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa su kasi orang di ini dunya ko jadi Beta pung orang dong. Beta su ajar sang dong, ko dong kanál sang Bapa. Dong jadi Bapa pung milik, ais Bapa sarakan sang dong ko jadi Beta pung milik ju. Ais dong bekin iko Bapa pung Kata-kata.<bt>Yesus prayed further saying, “You have given people in this world to be/become My people. I have taught them, so they know/recognise You. They are Your possession, and then You turned them over to become My possession as well. So they do according to/obey Your Words/Message. [EXEG: Broad view: disciples in general. Narrow view: those physically present with Jesus. Our wording nicely allows both readings of who these people might be--similar to the Greek. Our protocols say to preserve these multiple readings where possible. My reading of Carson, TH, TRT allows both readings. Morris is unclear, but seems to lean toward the narrower reading. Because of the details given through this and subsequent verses, I think we all end up with the same picture, so I'm not too worried about it.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: &quot;I have made you known"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: "I have made you known to the people you gave me out of the world. They belonged to you, and you gave them to me. They have obeyed your word.</Message></Annotation><v n="7" />Sakarang dong su mangarti bilang, samua hal yang Bapa su sarakan sang Beta tu, dia pung akar di Bapa.<bt>Now they already understand that everything that You have turned over to Me, its roots/source/origin is in You.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Now they know that everything"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Now they know that everything you have given me comes from you.</Message></Annotation><v n="8" />Te Beta su ajar sang dong, samua Kata-kata yang Bapa parná kasi tau sang Beta. Dong ju tarima itu Kata-kata dong. Dong ju tau bilang, Beta datang dari Bapa. Ais dong parcaya bilang, Bapa yang utus sang Beta datang di ini dunya.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) I have taught them, all the Words/Message which You have ever told Me. They also accepted/received those Words/Message. They also know that I came from You. So they believe that You are the one who sent/commissioned Me to come to this world. [NOTE: without comma in first sentence, the bracketing of /samua/ is ambiguous.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Because I have given them"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Because I have given them the words that you gave me, and they received them, and have known for sure that I came from you, and they have believed that you sent me.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Beta sambayang kasi sang dong. Beta sonde sambayang kasi sang samua orang yang ada di ini dunya. Ma Beta cuma sambayang kasi sang orang yang Bapa su sarakan sang Beta, te dong tu, Bapa pung milik.<bt>I pray for them. I do not pray for everyone who is in this world. But I only pray for the people You have turned over to Me, cuz (elaboration) those ones are Your possession.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: &quot;I pray for them. I"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: "I pray for them. I do not pray for the world, but for those that you have given me, for they are yours.</Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Te samua yang jadi Beta pung milik, ju su jadi Bapa pung. Deng samua yang jadi Bapa pung milik, ju su jadi Beta pung. Ais Beta pung orang dong tu, yang angka tinggi-tinggi sang Beta.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) every (thing/one) that is My possession, is also Yours. And every (thing/one) that is Your possession, is also Mine. So then My people are the ones who *glorify Me.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: All of mine are yours,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: All of mine are yours, and all of yours are mine. And I have been glorified [in/through] them.</Message></Annotation><v n="11" />Beta su sonde akan tenga tarús di ini dunya lai, tagal sonde lama lai Beta mau pulang kambali pi Beta pung Bapa. Ma ini orang dong musti tenga tarús di ini dunya. Naa, Bapa tu, barisi batúl. Jadi Beta minta ko Bapa jaga sang dong, pake Bapa pung kuasa yang Bapa su kasi sang Beta. Beta ju minta ko dong ta'ika jadi satu, sama ke Beta ta'ika jadi satu deng Bapa.<bt>I'm not going to keep staying/remaining/living in this world anymore, because soon/not much longer I am going to return home to My Father. But these people must continue to remain/stay in this world. Naa, [shift] You (Father) are really/truly clean/pure/holy. So (consequently), I request that You guard/watch over them, using your power/authority that You have given to Me. I also request that they are bound/linked becoming one/united, like I am bound/linked as one/united with You. [DISCOURSE: Gk is vocative ‘Holy Father’. Problem #1: Gk is a <span class="Italic">vocative </span>in the middle of a monologue. Our Timor area lgs can't do that. Vocatives generally only really start new paragraphs and only come in at discourse major shifts. Yet here 11b seems to link to or be set up by 11a. Problem #2: Gk is a <span class="Italic">modified </span>vocative, and the quality of “holy” seems to be part of what is relevant or even asserted. Timor lgs rarely modify vocatives. If they do, it is usually to indicate a contrast between a ‘(birth) father/mother’ from a ‘(classificatory) father/mother’. Or a highly restricted set of modifiers, such as ‘dear, beloved’ and little else. Problem #3: The easy solution for us would be to just ignore the vocative here and continue on without it. However, we are convinced the quality of ‘holy’ is actually part of what is being asserted as relevant here (Carson notes this form of address is only here and “was not arbritrarily chosen”), so the question is how to keep the quality without using a really forced vocative. Hence the apparently orphaned attributive clause. UNSs felt that the connector in the following sentence ‘So (consequently)’ links the quality of being holy as the reason for why the Father should protect them. This link is fairly close to how the TB renders it “Yes, Father who is holy, raise/care for [+imperative] them in Your name…”]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="go to a conference &quot;bawa GMIT"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">go to a conference "bawa GMIT pung nama" is more significant than "pake GMIT pung nama" ; Discuss with team opening “I'm not going to...” vs. “I don't want to...”; mention to the team UNS = “subu ketiga nama” in your authority Could drop this sentence altogether in this context.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: I am no longer in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: I am no longer in the world, but these are in the world, and I am coming to you. Holy Father, [keep/protect] them in your name which you have given me, that they may be one, just as we are.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Jadi, Beta minta ko Bapa jaga"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">Jadi, Beta minta ko Bapa jaga sang dong, pake Bapa pung kuasa yang Bapa su kasi sang Beta. Te dong bawa Bapa pung nama, sama ke Beta ju bawa Bapa pung nama. Beta ju minta ko dong ta'ika jadi satu, sama ke Beta ta'ika jadi satu deng Bapa.</Message></Annotation><v n="12" />Salama Beta ada di ini dunya sama-sama deng dong, Beta piara sang dong tagal dong su jadi Bapa pung milik. Beta jaga bae-bae sang dong ko biar dong ta'ika tarús deng Bapa. Sonde ada yang ilang. Cuma Yudas sa yang tapisa buang, iko apa yang Tuhan pung Tulisan Barisi su tulis memang dari dolu.<bt>As long as I am/was together with them, I cared for/raised them because they were already Your possession. I guarded/watched over them well/carefully so they they would be bound/linked with You continually. There aren't any who disappeared/were lost. Only just Yudas was separated off/cut off [i.e, from God and from group], according to what the Scriptures had already written beforehand from long ago. [EXEG: sense #4 of Gk “name” (affiliation, association).]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="perish @@ Can we use the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">perish @@ Can we use the tapisa buang dari Tuhan ??</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="apwleto: perish, destroyed, failed, lost, wasted"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">apwleto: perish, destroyed, failed, lost, wasted LITERALLY: While I was with them in the world, I kept them in your name which you have given me, and [protected/ guarded] them, and none of them is lost, except the one who was [destined] to be lost/perish (lit: son of destruction/ perishing), that the Scripture might be fulfilled.<span class="Italic">(12)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Cuma Yudas sa yang ancor,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">Cuma Yudas sa yang ancor,</Message></Annotation><note reference="17:12" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 41:9, Yohanis 13:18</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Sakarang Beta mau pulang kambali pi Bapa. Beta kasi tau ini hal dong waktu Beta masi ada di ini dunya. Deng bagitu, Beta pung orang dong pung hati bisa sanáng tarús, sama ke Beta pung hati ada sanáng.<bt>Now I'm going to come back home to You. I am telling/explaining these things while I am still in this world. In that way, My people's livers can continue to be happy, like my liver is happy.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: &quot;And now I come to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: "And now I come to you. I say these things in the world that they may have my joy fulfilled in themselves.</Message></Annotation><v n="14" />Beta su kasi tau Bapa pung Kata-kata sang dong. Orang laen di ini dunya binci sang Beta pung orang, tagal Beta pung orang sonde idop sama ke dong. Beta ju bagitu, te Beta sonde sama ke orang laen di ini dunya.<bt>I have already told Your Words/Message to them. Other people in this world hate My people, because My people don't live like them. I am also like that, cuz (elaboration) I am not the same as other people in this world.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: I have given them your"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: I have given them your word, and the world has hated them, because they are not of the world, even as I am not of the world.</Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Kalo Beta sambayang, Beta sonde minta ko Bapa cabu sang dong kaluar dari ini dunya. Sonde! Ma Beta minta ko Bapa jaga sang dong, ko dong jao dari yang jahat.<bt>If/when I pray, I do not request You to pull out/take out/pluck them out from this world. No! But I request You to guard/watch over them, so they are far/distanced from what is evil. [EXEG: 1) remove from world (like Jesus returning to Father), or 2) separate from people in the world (from vs.14); seems translations and commentaries favour #1] [NOTE to daughter translations: preserve ambiguity between “evil/evil one” if possible.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="teirew: guard or protect something in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">teirew: guard or protect something in order to keep it safe or free from harm LITERALLY: I do not pray that you take them out of the world, but that you keep them from the evil [/Evil One].<span class="Italic">(15)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ko dong jao dari yang jahat."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">ko dong jao dari yang jahat.</Message></Annotation><v n="16" />Dong sonde sama ke orang laen di ini dunya, sama ke Beta ju sonde sama ke orang laen di ini dunya.<bt>They are not the same as other people in this world, like I also am not like other people in this world.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: They are not from the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: They are not from the world, just as I am not from the world.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Pake apa yang batúl ko bekin dong pung hati barisi. Te Bapa pung Kata-kata dong, batúl.<bt>Use what is true to make their livers clean/pure/holy. Cuz (elaboration) Your Words/Message is true.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: &quot;Sanctify them through the truth."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: "Sanctify them through the truth. Your word is the truth.</Message></Annotation><v n="18" />Bapa yang utus sang Beta datang di ini dunya. Ais Beta ju utus sang dong bagitu, ko biar dong idop tasiar di orang dunya dong pung teng-tenga.<bt>You are the one who sent/commissioned Me to come to this world. So I also send/commission them like that, so that they will live scattered/dispersed in the midst of people of the world.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Just as you have sent"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Just as you have sent me into the world, even so I have also sent them into the world.</Message></Annotation><v n="19" />Beta jaga Beta pung diri ko barisi tarús kasi sang Bapa. Deng bagitu, Beta pung orang ju jaga dong pung diri ko barisi tarús kasi sang Bapa. Te Bapa pung Kata-kata yang batúl, yang bekin dong sarakan dong pung diri anteru-anteru sang Bapa.&gt;&gt;<bt>I guard Myself to stay clean/pure/holy for You. In that way, My people also guard/watch themselves to they stay clean/pure/holy for You. Cuz (elaboration) Your Words/Message that is true, is what makes them surrender/turn over/dedicate their entire selves/being to You.” [NOTE: NLT &amp; CEV seem to have missed the grammar and force of the last clause; HCE better.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="@! CEV NLT"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">@! CEV NLT</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hagiazw: dedicate to service, consecrate, make"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">hagiazw: dedicate to service, consecrate, make holy, sanctify, revere, honour as holy LITERALLY: For their sakes I [dedicate/sanctify] myself, that they also might be [dedicated/sanctified] through the truth.<span class="Italic">(19)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus sambayang kasi sang samua orang parcaya [\s2]<bt>The Lord Yesus prays for all believers [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Yesus sambayang tamba bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta sambayang bukan cuma kasi sang dong yang ada sakarang sa. Ma Beta ju sambayang kasi sang orang yang nanti parcaya sang Beta, tagal ini orang dong pung omong.<bt>Yesus prayed further saying, “I pray not only just for those who exist now. But I also pray for the people who will believe in Me, because of what these people (have to) say.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: &quot;I do not pray only"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: "I do not pray only for these, but for all those also who will believe in me through their word.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Bapa. Beta minta ko dong samua bisa ta'ika jadi satu, sama ke Kotong ju ta'ika jadi satu. Beta ju mau ko dong ta'ika jadi satu deng Kotong, ko biar orang laen di ini dunya bisa parcaya bilang, Bapa sandiri yang su utus sang Beta.<bt>Father, I request that all of them can be bound/linked as one/united, like We-inc are also bound/linked as one/united. I also want for them to be bound/linked as one/united with Us, so that other people in this world can believe that You yourself are the one who has sent/commissioned Me.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: That they all may be"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: That they all may be one, Father, just as you are in me, and I in you. That they also may be one in us, that the world may believe that you have sent me.</Message></Annotation><v n="22" />Bapa su kasi tunju Beta pung hebat sang orang dong. Ais Beta su angka tinggi-tinggi sang dong, sama ke Beta. Deng bagitu, dong ta'ika jadi satu, sama ke Kotong ju ta'ika jadi satu.<bt>You have already shown My greatness/amazingness/incredibleness to people. So then I have *glorified them, the same as Me. In that way, they are bound/linked as one/united, like We are also bound/linked as one/united.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: The glory which you gave"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: The glory which you gave me I have given them, that they may be one, just as we are one.</Message></Annotation><v n="23" />Beta ta'ika deng dong. Bapa ju ta'ika deng Beta. Dong musti ta'ika jadi satu bagitu, sampe dong idop satu hati deng batúl. Te kalo dong idop satu hati bagitu, orang laen di ini dunya nanti dapa tau bilang, Bapa yang sayang sang dong, sama ke Bapa sayang sang Beta. Deng bagitu dong ju tau bilang, Bapa yang utus sang Beta.<bt>I am bound/linked with them. You are also bound/linked with Me. They must be bound/linked as one/united like that, to the point that they truly live one livered (united, one accord, same purpose). Cuz (elaboration) if they live one livered like that, other people in this world will know/come to know that You are the one who loves them, like You love Me. In that way they will also know that You are the one who sent/commissioned Me. [DISCOURSE: order shifted for information load.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: I in them, and you"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: I in them, and you in me, that they may be made [perfect/complete] in one, and that the world may know that you have sent me, and have loved them, just as you have loved me.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Te kalo dong idop satu hati"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">Te kalo dong idop satu hati bagitu, orang laen di ini dunya nanti dapa tau, bilang, Bapa yang utus sang Beta. Dong ju tau, bilang, Bapa sayang sang dong, sama ke Bapa sayang sang Beta.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Bapa. Beta kapingin ko samua orang yang Bapa su sarakan sang Beta tu, ada sama-sama deng Beta. Te Beta mau ko dong bisa lia Bapa angka tinggi-tinggi sang Beta. Te Bapa su sayang memang sang Beta, waktu Kotong balóm bekin ini dunya.<bt>Father. I want/desire for everyone who You have handed over/surrendered to Me, be together with Me. Cuz (elaboration) I want for them to be able to see You *glorify Me. Cuz (elaboration) You have already loved Me beforehand, when We-inc had not yet made this world.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Father, I desire that those"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Father, I desire that those whom you have given me be with me where I am, that they may see my glory which you have given me. Because you loved me before the foundation [creation] of the world.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Bapa Bo'i pung hati lurus. Ma orang di ini dunya dong sonde kanál sang Bapa. Beta yang kanál sang Bapa. Deng Beta pung orang dong ju tau bilang, Bapa yang utus sang Beta datang di ini dunya.<bt>Dear Father has a straight/honest/righteous liver. But people in this world don't know/recognise You. I know/recognise You. And My people also know that You are the one who sent/commissioned Me to come to this world.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: O righteous Father, the world"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: O righteous Father, the world has not known you, but I have known you, and these have known that you have sent me.</Message></Annotation><v n="26" />Beta su kasi tau sang dong, Bapa tu, Sapa. Deng Beta nanti kasi tau tarús sang dong bagitu, tagal Beta mau ko dong bisa rasa batúl Bapa pung sayang. Te itu sayang yang dong rasa tu, sama ke Bapa pung sayang yang Bapa kasi sang Beta. Ko biar Beta ta'ika tarús deng dong.&gt;&gt;<bt>I have already told/explained to them Who You are. And I will keep telling them like that, because I want for them to be able to truly/really feel/experience Your love. Cuz (elaboration) that love that they experience, is the same as Your love which You gave to Me. So that I will be bound/linked continually to them.” [EXEG: Gk “name” in sense #3 (reputation) &amp; #5 (authority); NLT.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: I have declared to them"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: I have declared to them your name, and will declare it, that they may have the love in them which you have given me, and that I may be in them.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Dong tangkap ame sang Tuhan Yesus<bt>They (non-referential) catch/arrest the Lord Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 26:47-56; Markus 14:43-50; Lukas 22:47-53)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="18" />
      <v n="1" />Waktu Yesus su sambayang abis bagitu, ju Dia kaluar sama-sama deng Dia pung ana bua dong. Dong pi satu kabón di kali Kidron pung sablá. Ju dong maso di situ.<bt>When Yesus had finished praying like that, He went out together with His disciples. They went to a garden/orchard on the other side of the Kidron river/stream. And they went in there.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="keepos: &quot;garden&quot; in English sounds like"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">keepos: "garden" in English sounds like vegetables; orchard LITERALLY: When Jesus had said these words, he went out with his disciples over Kidron Brook where there was a garden, and he and his disciples went into it.<span class="Italic">(1)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="2-3" />Itu waktu, kapala agama Yahudi dong pung bos-bos, deng orang dari partei agama Farisi dong su sarakan tantara deng tukang jaga barapa orang kasi sang Yudas. Te dia mau jual buang sang Yesus. Naa, Yudas ju tau itu kabón, tagal Yesus su bakumpul banya kali di situ deng Dia pung ana bua dong. Ais Yudas dong pi itu kabón, bawa obor, lantera, deng sanjata tajam.<bt>At that time, the *chief priests (bosses of the Yahudi priests), and people from the Farisi religious party had handed over/turned over several soldiers and guards to Yudas. Cuz (elaboration) he was going to sell off (betray) Yesus. Naa [shift, explanatory] Yudas also knew that garden/orchard, because Yesus had gathered many times there with His disciples. So then Yudas (collective) went to that garden/orchard, taking torches, lamps/lanterns, and sharp weapons (category: swords, spears, etc. in contrast with firearms).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lantera = lantern"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">lantera = lantern</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And Judas also, who betrayed"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And Judas also, who betrayed him, knew the place, because Jesus often met there with his disciples. hupeireteis: servant, underling; but LN say particularly in John = "temple guards"<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>LITERALLY: So Judas went to the garden, taking some soldiers and policemen from the chief priests and Pharisees. They had torches, lanterns, and weapons.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Padahal Yesus su tau samua yang nanti jadi kasi sang Dia. Ais Dia maju pi sang dong, ju tanya bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong ada cari sapa?&gt;&gt;<bt>Whereas in fact, Yesus already knew everything that was going to happen to Him. So He moved forward to them, and asked saying, “Who are you-pl looking for?”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Jesus knew everything that was"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Jesus knew everything that was going to happen to him, so he went [forward/out] and said to them, "Who do you want?"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Ju dong manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Botong ada cari satu orang, nama Yesus, dari kampong Nasaret.&gt;&gt;<bt>And they responded saying, “We-exc are looking for a person, named Yesus, from the village of Nasaret.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ais Yesus kasi tau bilang, &lt;&lt;Andia Beta ni.&gt;&gt; Naa, itu waktu, Yudas, ada badiri sama-sama deng dong. Dia ni, yang jual buang sang Yesus.<bt>Then Yesus told (them) saying, “That's Me.” Naa [shift, background], at that time, Yudas was standing together with them. He (this one) was the one who solld off (betrayed) Yesus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: They answered him, &quot;Jesus from"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: They answered him, "Jesus from Nazareth." Jesus said to them, "I am he." And Judas, who betrayed him, stood with them.</Message></Annotation><v n="6" />Waktu Yesus omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Andia Beta,&gt;&gt; ju itu orang dong ondor dari Dia, ais jato di tana.<bt>When Yesus spoke saying, “That's Me,” those people moved back/retreated from Him, and fell to the ground.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: As soon as he had"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: As soon as he had said to them, "I am he," they moved back, and fell to the ground.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Ju Yesus tanya ulang sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong ada cari sapa?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus asked them again saying, “Who are you looking for?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ais dong manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Yesus, orang Nasaret.&gt;&gt;<bt>So they responded saying, “Yesus, the Nasaret person.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then he asked them again,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then he asked them again, "Who do you want?" And they said, "Jesus from Nazareth."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Ju Yesus omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta su kasi tau tadi bilang, Dia tu, andia Beta. Jadi, kalo bosong ada cari sang Beta, na, jang tangkap yang laen. Kasi biar ko dong pi sa.&gt;&gt;<bt>And Yesus spoke saying, “I already told (you) earlier saying, He is Me. So (consequently), if you are looking for Me, na, don't catch/arrest the others. Just let them go.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Jesus answered, &quot;I have told"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Jesus answered, "I have told you that I am he. So if you are looking for me, let these go."</Message></Annotation><v n="9" />(Dia omong bagitu ko bekin jadi apa yang Dia parná omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa. Samua orang yang Bapa su sarakan kasi sang Beta dong, sonde ada satu ju yang ilang.&gt;&gt;)<bt>(He spoke like that to make come into being/fulfill what He had once said saying, “Father. Everyone whom You (Father) have turned over to Me, there is not one who has been lost/disappeared.”) [NOTE to daughter translations: compare with 17:12.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: That the saying might be"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: That the saying might be fulfilled which he had spoken, "Father, I have not lost any of those you have given me."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Itu waktu, Simon Petrus ada bawa satu kalewang kudung. Ais dia cabu, ko mau potong orang. Tau-tau, te dia potong kasi putus satu orang pung talinga kanan. (Itu orang tu, nama Malkus. Dia tu, andia kapala agama Yahudi dong pung bos bésar pung orang suru-suru.)<bt>At that time, Simon Petrus was carrying/bearing a short sword. so he pulled it out, to cut people/someone. It turns out that he cut off a person's right ear. (That person was named Malkus. He was the Yahudi *high priest's servant.)</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="PHONOLOGY cabut if intransitive, otherwise cabu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">PHONOLOGY cabut if intransitive, otherwise cabu</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Simon Peter had a sword."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Simon Peter had a sword. He took it out, and hit the high priest's servant, and cut off his right ear. The servant's name was Malchus.</Message></Annotation><v n="11" />Ju Yesus suru sang Petrus bilang, &lt;&lt;Pe'u! Kasi maso lu pung kalewang dalam dia pung sarong. Te Beta pung Bapa su bilang Beta musti dapa sangsara macam bagini. Jadi biar sa! Itu sama ke Dia su kasi Beta satu galás yang dia pung isi pait. Biar ko Beta minum samua.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus ordered Petrus saying, “Pete! Put your sword back into it's sheath. Cuz (elaboration) My Father already said I must get suffering of this sort. So (consequently), just let it be! It's like He has given Me a glass filled with bitterness/bile. Let Me drink it all.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then Jesus said to Peter,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then Jesus said to Peter, "Put your sword back into its sheath. Shall I not drink the cup which my Father has given me? [Shouldn't I go through the suffering my Father has planned for me?]"</Message></Annotation><note reference="18:11" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 26:39, Markus 14:36, Lukas 22:42</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Dong antar Tuhan Yesus ko pi mangada sang kapala agama dong pung bos bésar<bt>They take/escort the Lord Yesus to front up to the *high priest</bt></p>
    <fig path="Cook\CNT\cn01814b.tif" rtfFormat="width:6.5cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:right" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Ais ju komandán, tantara dong, deng orang Yahudi dong pung tukang jaga dong, tangkap ame sang Yesus, ju ika sang Dia.<bt>Then the commander, the soldiers, and the Yahudi guards, caught/arrested Yesus, and tied/bound Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then the band, and the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then the band, and the captain, and the Jewish policemen took Jesus, and tied him up.</Message></Annotation><v n="13" />Tarús dong antar bawa sang Dia pi Anas dolo. Anas tu, andia Kayafas pung bapa mantu. Itu taon, Kayafas yang jadi kapala agama Yahudi dong pung bos bésar.<bt>Then2 they took/escorted/led Him first to Anas. That Anas was Kayafas' father in law. That year, Kayafas was the one who was the *high priest of the Yahudi religion.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And led him away first"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And led him away first to Annas. Now he was Caiaphas' father-in-law, who was high priest that same year.</Message></Annotation><v n="14" />Kayafas ni, yang parná kasi nasiat sang orang Yahudi pung bos-bos bilang, &lt;&lt;Ada lebe bae kasi bosong, kalo cuma ada satu orang yang mati kasi sang samua orang.&gt;&gt;<bt>This is the Kayafas who had once advised the bosses/leaders of the Yahudi people saying, “It's better for you-pl, if there is only one person who dies for everyone.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Now Caiaphas was the one"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Now Caiaphas was the one who gave advice to the Jews that it was better that one man should die for the people.</Message></Annotation><note reference="18:14" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yohanis 11:49-50</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Petrus manyangkal bilang, dia sonde kanál sang Tuhan Yesus<bt>Petrus denies saying, he doesn't know/recognise the Lord Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 26:69-70; Markus 14:66-68; Lukas 22:55-57)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Simon Petrus ada iko sang Yesus dari balakang, sama-sama deng Yesus pung ana bua satu lai, andia beta, Yohanis. Naa, agama Yahudi pung bos bésar ada kanál sang beta. Andia ko beta bisa maso pi dalam dia pung kintal, sama-sama deng Yesus.<bt>Simon Petrus was following Yesus from behind, together with one of Yesus' other disciples, that is me, Yohanis. Naa, the high priest of the Yahudi religion knew/recognised me. That is why I was able to enter into his yard, together with Yesus. [EXEG: Carson, Morris, HCE // Explicit to Implicit: “the High priest's palace courtyard”. Implied by his position that he would have had a fancy house or a house complex. Heavy information load.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Talking about oneself in the third"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">Talking about oneself in the third person doesn't fly in Pidgin. LITERALLY: Simon Peter followed Jesus, and another disciple. The high priest knew that disciple, so he went into the High priest's palace courtyard with Jesus.<span class="Italic">(15)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="16" />Ma Petrus badiri di luar, deka-deka deng pintu pagar. Ais beta kaluar, ju omong deng satu parampuan yang ada jaga di situ, ko biar beta bisa bawa sang Petrus maso pi dalam.<bt>But Petrus stood outside, near the fence door/gate. So I went out, and spoke to a woman who was guarding/watching there, so that I could bring Petrus inside.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pintu hek = UNS not know"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">pintu hek = UNS not know</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But Peter stood outside by"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But Peter stood outside by da gate. Then the other disciple, whom the high priest knew, went out and spoke to the [gatekeeper/girl that was in charge of the gate], and brought Peter in.</Message></Annotation><v n="17" />Ju itu parampuan tanya sang Petrus bilang, &lt;&lt;Weh! Lu ni, itu Orang pung ana bua satu, ko?&gt;&gt;<bt>And that woman asked Petrus saying, “Weh! You-sg here, are one of that Person's disciples, aren't you?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ma Petrus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Sonde!&gt;&gt;<bt>But Petrus responded saying, “No!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then the girl that was"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then the girl that was in charge of the gate said to Peter, "Aren't you one of this man's disciples?" He said, "I am not!"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Itu waktu, su dingin. Andia ko orang jaga deng orang suru-suru dong ada badiri panggang api. Ju Petrus pi, ko panggang api sama-sama deng dong.<bt>At that time it was cold. That is why the guard/watchers and the servants were standing warming (themselves) over the fire. So Petrus went to warm (himself) over the fire together with them.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: The servants and officers, who"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: The servants and officers, who had made a charcoal fire, stood there and warmed themselves, because it was cold. Peter stood with them and warmed himself.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Kapala agama dong pung bos bésar pareksa sang Tuhan Yesus<bt>The *high priest examines/interrogates the Lord Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 26:59-66; Markus 14:55-64; Lukas 22:66-71)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Itu waktu, ju agama Yahudi pung mantan bos bésar ada pareksa sang Yesus so'al Dia pung ajaran, deng so'al Dia pung ana bua dong.<bt>At that time, the former *high priest of the Yahudi religion was examining/interrogating Yesus about His teaching, and about His disciples. [NOTE: ‘former. added here at consultant's suggestion to reduce confusion with vs. 24.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then the high priest asked"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then the high priest asked Jesus about his disciples and what he taught them.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Ju Yesus kasi tau bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta omong taráng-taráng ko samua orang bisa dengar. Beta salalu ajar di tampa yang kotong pung orang Yahudi biasa bakumpul, andia di kotong pung ruma sambayang dong, deng dalam Ruma Sambayang Pusat. Beta sonde parná omong di balakang-balakang.<bt>And Yesus told (him) saying, “I spoke clearly/openly so everyone could hear. I always taught in places where we-inc Yahudi people normally gather, such as in our houses of worship, and in the Temple. I have never spoken behind-behind (idiom: in secret, trying to keep something hidden).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="omong di balakang-balakang = (idiom) in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">omong di balakang-balakang = (idiom) in secret</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Jesus answered him, &quot;I spoke"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Jesus answered him, "I spoke openly to the world. I always taught in the synagogues and in the temple, where all the Jews come together. I said nothing in secret.</Message></Annotation><v n="21" />Akurang ko lu ada tanya sang Beta? Tanya sa sang orang yang dengar Beta pung omong dong. Te pasti dong tau apa yang Beta su omong.&gt;&gt;<bt>Why do you-sg ask Me? Just ask the people who listened to Me speak/listened to what I had to say. Cuz (elaboration) surely they know what I have said.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Why do you ask me?"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Why do you ask me? Ask those who heard me what I said to them. Look, they know what I have said."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Waktu Yesus omong bagitu, satu orang jaga yang ada badiri di situ tampeleng sang Dia, ais omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Lu jang omong bagitu deng bos bésar!&gt;&gt;<bt>When He spoke like that, one of the guards who was standing there slapped (open-handed to the face) Yesus saying, “You-sg shouldn't talk like that to the big boss (short for high priest).”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: When he had said that,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: When he had said that, one of the policemen who stood there slapped Jesus with the palm of his hand, and said, "Do you speak to the high priest that way?"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Ju Yesus kasi tau sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo Beta su omong sala, na, kasi tunju itu sala yang mana. Ma kalo Beta omong yang batúl, na, akurang ko lu tampeleng sang Beta?&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus told him saying, “If I have spoken wrong/incorrectly, na, point out what that wrong/sin/fault is. But if I spoke what is true, na, why do you slap Me?”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Jesus answered him, &quot;If I"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Jesus answered him, "If I have spoken evil, testify about the evil. But if well, why do you hit me?"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Ais itu, ju Anas suru dong antar bawa sang Dia pi Kayafas, yang jadi agama Yahudi pung bos bésar. Waktu dong antar sang Dia tu, Dia masi ta'ika.<bt>After that, Anas ordered them to escort/lead Him to Kayafas, who was the *high priest of the Yahudi religion. While they were leading Him, He was still bound/tied.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then Annas sent him, tied"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then Annas sent him, tied up, to Caiaphas the high priest.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Petrus manyangkal ulang sang Tuhan Yesus lai<bt>Petrus again denies the Lord Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 26:71-75; Markus 14:69-72; Lukas 22:58-62)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Itu waktu, Simon Petrus masi badiri ko panggang api. Ju orang laen yang ada di situ dong tanya sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Lu ni, Dia pung ana bua satu, to?&gt;&gt;<bt>At that time, Simon Petrus was still standing to warm (himself) over the fire. And the other people who were there asked him saying, “You-sg here, are one of His disciples, right?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ma Petrus manyangkal bilang, &lt;&lt;Sonde!&gt;&gt;<bt>But Petrus denied (it) saying, “No!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Simon Peter stood and warmed"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Simon Peter stood and warmed himself. So they said to him, "Aren't you one of his disciples too?" He denied it and said, "I am not!"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="26" />Di situ ju ada agama Yahudi pung bos bésar pung orang suru-suru satu. Dia tu, ju kelu dari itu orang yang Petrus su potong putus dia pung talinga. Ais dia tanya bilang, &lt;&lt;Weh! Tadi lu ada di itu kabón, to? Te beta ada lia sang lu di situ!&gt;&gt;<bt>There, there was also one of the *high priest's of the Yahudi religion's servants. He was also a relative/family of that person whom Petrus had cut off his ear. So he asked saying, “Weh! Earlier you-sg were in that garden/orchard, right? Cuz (elaboration) I saw you there!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: One of the servants of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: One of the servants of the high priest, a relative of the one whose ear Peter had cut off, said, "Didn't I see you in the garden with him?"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />Ma Petrus manyangkal ulang lai, ju ayam kokore'o memang.<bt>But Petrus denied (it) again, and the chicken crowed immediately/straight away.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then Peter denied it again,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then Peter denied it again, and immediately a rooster crowed.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus mangada sang gubernor Pilatus<bt>The Lord Yesus fronts up to gubernor Pilatus</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 27:1-2, 11-14; Markus 15:1-5; Lukas 23:1-5)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Ais pagi-pagi, dong bawa ame sang Yesus dari Kayafas pi gubernor pung ruma jabatan di tantara Roma dong pung benteng.<bt>Then early in the morning, they took Yesus from Kayafas, going to the gubernor's official residence in the Roma soldier's fort.</bt><note reference="18:28" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Tantara Roma dong pung tampa tu, dong pange dalam bahasa Latin bilang, <span class="Italic">praetorium</span>.<bt>The Roma soldiers' place, they called in the Latin language saying, <span class="Italic">praetorium</span>.</bt></note>Orang Yahudi dong sandiri sonde maso pi dalam orang Roma dong pung tampa, te itu bekin dong kamomos, ko dong sonde bisa makan pesta Paska.<bt>The Yahudi people themselves did not enter into the place of the Roma people, cuz (elaboration) that would make them filthy/defiled, so they couldn't eat the Paska feast. [EXEG: see Carson on time frame.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then they led Jesus away"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then they led Jesus away from Caiaphas to the Roman governor's military headquarters. It was early. They themselves didn't go into the headquarters, so they wouldn't be [ritually defiled/contaminated], in order to be able to eat the Passover.</Message></Annotation><v n="29" />Ais gubernor Pilatus pi kaluar ko katumu deng itu orang Yahudi dong. Ju dia tanya bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong lempar sala apa sang ini Orang ni?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then gubernor Pilatus went out to meet with those Yahudi people. And he asked saying, “What are you-pl accusing this Person of?”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then Pilate went out to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then Pilate went out to them and asked, "What do you accuse this man of?"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="30" />Ju dong manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Bagini, pak. Kalo Dia ni, bukan orang jahat, pasti botong sonde datang ganggu sang pak. Apalai sarakan sang Dia pi pak pung tangan.&gt;&gt;<bt>And they responded saying, “It's like this, pak (sir-to officials). If he here were not an evil person/criminal, surely we-exc would not come bother/disturb pak. Let alone turn Him over to pak's hands.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: They answered him, &quot;If he"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: They answered him, "If he were not a [wrongdoer/ criminal], we would not have handed him over to you."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="31" />Ais gubernor kasi tau sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bagini. Biar bosong sa yang urus Dia pung parkara, iko bosong orang Yahudi pung atoran.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then the gubernor told them saying, “It's like this. Just let you-pll be the ones who handle/deal with/take care of His case/matter, according to your Yahudi regulations/law.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ju orang Yahudi pung bos-bos dong kasi tau bilang, &lt;&lt;Sonde bisa, pak. Botong orang Yahudi sonde ada pung hak lai ko putus hukuman mati. Itu cuma bosong pamarenta Roma sa yang ada pung hak bagitu.&gt;&gt;<bt>The bosses/leaders of the Yahudi people told (him) saying, “That can't be, pak. We-exc Yahudi people no longer have the right to decide the death penalty. It is only you-pl Roma government that has that right.” [NOTE: from UNS confusion at Amarasi check, fleshed out ‘anymore’ for historical accuracy as to why the Jews couldn't hand out the death penalty.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then Pilate said to them,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then Pilate said to them, "Take him, and judge him according to your law." Then the Jews said to him, "[It is not proper for us/We are not allowed] to put anyone to death."</Message></Annotation><v n="32" />(Waktu dong omong bagitu, apa yang Yesus parná omong dolu su jadi. Te Dia su kasi tau Dia pung orang dong bilang, nanti Dia mati iko pamarenta Roma pung cara, andia dong paku sang Dia di kayu palang.)<bt>(When/while they spoke like that, what Yesus had once said before, happened/came into being/fulfilled. Cuz (elaboration) He had already told His people that He would later die according to the Roma government's way/method, that is they would nail Him on a *cross.)</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: That the saying of Jesus"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: That the saying of Jesus might be fulfilled, which he said, indicating what kind of death he would die.</Message></Annotation><note reference="18:32" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yohanis 3:14, 12:32-33</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="33" />Ju gubernor maso kambali pi dalam tantara pung benteng. Ais dia pange ame sang Yesus, ju tanya bilang, &lt;&lt;Karmana? Lu ni, orang Yahudi dong pung raja, ko?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then the gubernor went back into the soldiers' fort. Then2 he summoned Yesus, and asked saying, “How is it? Are you-sg here the Yahudi people's king, or (what)?”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then Pilate came into the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then Pilate came into the military headquarters again and called Jesus, and said to him, "Are you the King of the Jews?"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="34" />Yesus tanya bale sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Pak sandiri yang tanya bagitu, ko, ada orang laen yang kasi tau sang pak so'al Beta?&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus asked him in return saying, “Are you (Pak) asking this yourself, or, are there other people who have told pak about Me?”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Jesus answered him, &quot;Are you"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Jesus answered him, "Are you saying this by yourself, or did someone else tell you that?"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="35" />Ju gubernor manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Hee! Beta ni, bukan orang Yahudi, to? Lu pung bangsa sandiri tu, yang su sarakan ame sang lu. Apalai kapala agama dong pung bos-bos. Ko lu ni, ada bekin apa? Coba lu kasi tau dolo!&gt;&gt;<bt>The gubernor responded saying, “Hee! I here am not a Yahudi person, right? Your-sg own race/people/ethnic groups are the ones who turned you over. Even the *chief prests. So what have you done? Come on and tell me [+imperative]!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Pilate answered, &quot;Do you think"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Pilate answered, "Do you think I'm a Jew? Your own nation and the chief priests have handed you over to me. What have you done?"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="36" />Ju Yesus kasi tau bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta bukan satu raja dari ini dunya. Te kalo Beta jadi raja macam bagitu, pasti Beta pung orang suru-suru dong marontak ko orang Yahudi sonde jadi tangkap ame sang Beta. Memang Beta jadi Raja. Ma sonde ada satu orang di ini dunya yang angka sang Beta bagitu.&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus told (him) saying, “I am not a king from this world. Cuz (elaboration) if I was a king of that sort, surely My servants would rebel/revolt/riot so the Yahudi people wouldn't have been able to catch/arrest Me. I really am a King. But there is nobody in this world who appointed Me like that.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Jesus answered, &quot;My kingdom is"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Jesus answered, "My kingdom is not from this world. If my kingdom were from this world, then my servants would fight, that I should not be handed over to the Jews. But my kingdom is not from here."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="37" />Ais gubernor tanya ulang bilang, &lt;&lt;Jadi lu ni, Raja, ko?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then the gubernor asked again saying, “So (consequently), are you a King, or (what)?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ju Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Pak sandiri yang bilang Beta jadi Raja. Yang batúl Beta lahir ko jadi Raja. Beta ju datang di ini dunya ko jadi Raja, ko biar Beta kasi tau so'al hal-hal yang batúl. Samua orang yang pegang kuat apa yang batúl, na, dong tu, dengar sang Beta.&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus responded saying, “Pak himself is the one who said I was a King. What is true is that I was born to be/become a King. I came to this world to become a King, so that I could tell/explain about things that are true. Everyone who holds firmly to true things/matters/issues, na, they listen to Me.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: So Pilate said to him,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: So Pilate said to him, "Are you a king then?" Jesus answered, "You say that I am a king. For that purpose I was born, and for that reason I came into the world, that I should give testimony of the truth. Everyone that is of the truth hears my voice."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="38a" />Ais gubernor tanya sang Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Yang batúl tu, apa?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then the gubernor asked Him saying, “What is true, is what?”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Pilate said to him, &quot;What"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Pilate said to him, "What is truth?"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Dong putus hukuman mati kasi sang Tuhan Yesus<bt>They decide the punishment of death for the Lord Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 27:15-31; Markus 15:6-20; Lukas 23:13-25)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="38b" />Waktu gubernor Pilatus omong abis bagitu, ju dia kaluar kambali pi orang Yahudi dong. Dia omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta su pareksa sang Dia, ma beta sonde dapa Dia pung sala apa-apa.<bt>When gubernor Pilatus finished speaking like that, he went back out to the Yahudi people. He spoke saying, “I have examined/interrogated Him, but I have not found/encountered any fault/wrong/sin with/in Him/of His.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And when he had said"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And when he had said that, he went out again to the Jews, and said to them, "I do not find any fault in him.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="39" />Ma bosong pung biasa, tiap taon di pesta Paska, beta musti kasi lapás satu orang bui sang bosong. Jadi ini taon, bosong mau ko beta kasi lapás orang Yahudi pung raja, ko karmana?&gt;&gt;<bt>But your-pl custom/norm, is that each year at the Paska feast, I must release one prisoner to you. So (consequently) this year, do you want me to release the king of the Yahudi people, or how is it?”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But you have a custom,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But you have a custom, that I should release one to you at the Passover. So do you want me to release to you the King of the Jews?"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="40" />Dong samua batarea rame-rame bilang, &lt;&lt;Jang kasi lapás ini Orang! Kasi lapás sang Barabas sa!&gt;&gt; Padahal Barabas tu, satu orang yang jahat mati pung.<bt>All of them shouted noisily saying, “Don't release this Person! Just release Barabas!” Whereas in fact, that Barabas was an incredibly evil person (overtones of violence).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="leisteis: BADG, LN ‘1) robber, bandit,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">leisteis: BADG, LN ‘1) robber, bandit, highwayman, 2) rebel, insurrectionist, revolutionary’ NRSV ‘bandit’, NLT ‘criminal’, CEV ‘terrorist’, TB ‘penyamun’ LITERALLY: Then they all shouted again, and said, "Not this man, but Barabbas." Now Barabbas was a violent criminal.<span class="Italic">(40)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="18:40" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">&lt;&lt;Orang yang jahat mati pung&gt;&gt; dalam bahasa Yunani ada pung dua arti, andia: 1) parampok yang curi barang pake cara paksa, deng 2) orang yang pake sanjata ko mau usir buang sang pamarenta Roma. <span class="Italic">Lukas</span> 23:19 bilang Barabas ni, parná bunu orang deng malawan pamarenta Roma ju.<bt>“An incredibly evil person” in the Yunani language word has two meanings, which are: 1) a robber who steal things by porce, and 2) a person who uses weapons to try to get rid of the Roma government. <span class="Italic">Lukas</span> 23:19 says that this Barabas had murdered people and opposed the Roma government too.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="19" />
      <v n="1" />Ais itu, ju gubernor Pilatus suru dia pung tantara ko pi firuk sang Yesus pake cambuk.<bt>After that, gubernor Pilatus ordered his soldiers to go whip Yesus using a whip (verb &amp; noun different lexemes).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="emastígoosen: had him flogged. The Roman"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">emastígoosen: had him flogged. The Roman army whips had a handle with several cords or strips of leather on the end. Each cord had jagged pieces of bone or metal in it. People often died from being whipped. Jewish law limited floggings to forty lashes, but the Romans didn't have any limit LITERALLY: Then Pilate took Jesus an had him [scourged/ whipped with thorns].<span class="Italic">(1)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="19:1" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Tantara Roma dong pake cambuk yang bekin dari tali kulit binatang barapa urat. Ais dong ika tulang tajam, ko tima tajam di tali pung ujung-ujung. Kalo firuk ulang-ulang pake itu cambuk, kulit dong takupas buang. Orang Yahudi pake batas firuk sampe 40 kali sa. Ma tantara Roma dong firuk deng sonde pake batas.<bt>The Roma soldiers used a whip that was made from the skin/leather rope several strips. Then they tied sharp bones or sharp lead on the ends of the rope/s. If whipped over and over using that whip, skins can peal.off throw away. The Yahudi people used a limit of whipping up to just 40 times. But the Roma soldiers whipped without a limit.</bt></note><v n="2-3" />Itu tantara dong ju ame pohon baduri pung takis ko mala'e bekin topi. Ais dong tendes itu topi baduri pi Yesus pung kapala, ko bekin maen-maen, sama ke dong mau angka raja baru pake topi jabatan. Ju dong kasi pake sang Yesus satu baju panjang warna ungu sama ke raja dong biasa pake. Tarús dong olok barmaen sang Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Idop orang Yahudi pung raja!&gt;&gt; Dong ju tampeleng barmaen sang Dia.<bt>Those soldiers also took the small branches of a thorn tree to weave into a hat. then they pressed that hat of thorns on Yesus head, to mock pretending like they were appointing/installing a new king with an official/govt position hat. Then they put on Yesus a long clothes purple in colour like kings normally wear. Then3 then mocked/scoffed at Him saying, “Live, king of the Yahudi people!” They also slapped Him around.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="akanthóon: the thorns were on branches,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">akanthóon: the thorns were on branches, probably bigger than kiawe thorns. There are at least a dozen species of thorn growing around Jerusalem (Zohary p. 153-157), and it could be any one LITERALLY: The soldiers braided a crown of thorns, and put it on his head, and put a purple robe on him.<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>LITERALLY: And were saying, "Hail! King of the Jews!" And they were slapping him.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Ais itu, ju gubernor kaluar satu kali lai, ko kasi tau sang orang banya dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bagini! Beta bawa kaluar sang Dia kasi bosong. Ma bosong musti mangarti, te beta su pareksa sang Dia, ma beta sonde dapa Dia pung sala apa-apa.&gt;&gt;<bt>After that, the gubeernor went out once again, to tell those many people/crowds saying, “It's like this! I am bringing Him out to you-pl. But you must understand, that I have examined/interrogated Him, but I do not find any wrong in/at/of Him.” [EXEG: NLT]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: So Pilate went forward again"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: So Pilate went forward again and said to them, "Look, I am bringing him forward to you, that you may know that I find no fault in him."</Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Waktu Yesus kaluar, Dia ada pake itu topi baduri, deng baju panjang warna ungu. Ais gubernor kasi tau sang itu orang banya bilang, &lt;&lt;Lia doo! Ini Dia, itu Orang su.&gt;&gt;<bt>When Yesus came out, He was wearing that hat of thorns, and the long purple clothes. Then the gubernor told those many people saying, “Have a look! He here is that Person.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then Jesus came forward, wearing"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then Jesus came forward, wearing the crown of thorns and the purple robe. And Pilate said to them, Look, the man!</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Waktu kapala agama dong pung bos-bos deng orang jaga dong lia sang Yesus, dong batarea rame-rame bilang, &lt;&lt;Bunu bekin mati sang Dia sa! Paku Dia di kayu palang!&gt;&gt;<bt>When the *chief priests and the guards saw Yesus, they shouted noisily saying, “Just kill Him! Nail Him on a cross!” [NOTE to daughter translations: if ‘guards’not clear, then say ‘*Temple guards’ (cf. NLT, CEV).]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ma gubernor kasi tau sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Biar bosong sa yang bawa Dia ko kasi mati sang Dia di kayu palang. Te beta sonde dapa Dia pung sala apa-apa yang pantas ko kasi hukum mati sang Dia.&gt;&gt;<bt>But the gubernor told them saying, “Let you-pl be the ones who take Him to kill Him on a cross. Cuz (elaboration) I haven't found any wrong of His worthy/appropriate to punish Him with death.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: So when the chief priests"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: So when the chief priests and officers saw him, they shouted, saying, "Crucify him! Crucify him!" Pilate said to them, "You take him, and crucify him, because I don't find any fault with him!"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Orang Yahudi dong manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Botong ada pung Atoran yang turun dari Tuhan. Iko itu Atoran, ini orang musti mati, tagal dia angka diri jadi Tuhan Allah pung Ana.&gt;&gt;<bt>The Yahudi people responded saying, “We-exc have regulations/law that came down from God2. According to that Regulation.Law, this person must die, because he has elevated himself to be God's Child.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: The Jews answered him, &quot;We"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: The Jews answered him, "We have a law, and by our law he ought to die, because he made himself the Son of God."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Waktu gubernor dengar dong pung omong, ju dia tamba taku.<bt>When the gubernor heard what they were saying, he became more afraid.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: So when Pilate heard what"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: So when Pilate heard what they said, he was more afraid.</Message></Annotation><v n="9" />Ais dia maso kambali pi dalam tantara dong pung benteng, ju tanya sang Yesus bilang, &lt;&lt;Lu ni, orang mana?&gt;&gt; Ma Yesus sonde manyao sang dia.<bt>So he went back into the soldiers' fort, and asked Yesus saying, “You here, are a person from where?” But Yesus didn't resonde to him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="póthen: what part of the country?"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">póthen: what part of the country? LITERALLY: He went into the judgment hall again, and said to Jesus, "Where do you come from?" But Jesus did not answer him.<span class="Italic">(9)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Ju gubernor masparak sang Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Aiih? Akurang ko lu sonde ba'omong deng beta? Lu pasti su tau, to? Beta ni, yang ada pung kuasa ko kasi mati sang lu, ko, kasi lapás sang lu.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then the gubernor spoke.angrily to Him saying, “Aiih? [+frustration] Why is it that you-sg won't talk with me. Surely you already know, right? I here am the one who has the power/authority to kill you, or, release you.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ou laléis: Pilate is surprised that"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">ou laléis: Pilate is surprised that Jesus is not defending himself. How is it that you do not answer me? Why will you not speak to me? LITERALLY: Then Pilate said to him, "Why will you not speak to me? Don't you know that I have power to crucify you, and power to release you?"<span class="Italic">(10)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Ju Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Bagini, pak. Kalo pak ada pung kuasa bagitu, na, itu tagal pak dapa itu kuasa dari Tuhan Allah di sorga. Te cuma Dia sa yang kasi loos sang pak ko bekin apa sa kasi sang Beta. Ma orang yang sarakan sang Beta kasi pi sang pak, dong tu yang pikol sala lebe barát.&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus responded saying, “It's like this, pak. If pak had that power/authority, na, that is because pak got/obtained that authority from God in heaven. Cuz (elaboration) only He is the one who gives permission for pak to do whatever to Me. But the people who turned Me over to pak, they are the ones who carry a much heavier wrong/sin.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ho paradoús mé soi: the one"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">ho paradoús mé soi: the one who turned me over to you -- probably not Judas, but could be Caiaphas the head priest, or it could be a reference to the Jewish leaders all together. Pilate is just doing his job, but has ducked a serious moral issue; Caiaphas has been plotting to get rid of Jesus for a long time LITERALLY: Jesus answered, "You could have no power at all against me unless it were given you [from above / from God]. So the one who turned me over to you has sinned more."<span class="Italic">(11)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Mulai dari dong omong bagitu, gubernor ada cari-cari jalan ko kasi lapás sang Yesus. Ma orang Yahudi dong batarea rame-rame bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo pak kasi lapás sang ini Orang ni, su jalás pak bukan raja bésar keser pung tamán. Te orang yang angka diri jadi raja ada malawan sang keser.&gt;&gt;<bt>Beginning from them speaking like that, the gubernor kept looking for a way to free Yesus. But the Yahudi people kept shouting noisily saying, “If pak releases this Person, it is clear that pak is not the big king Keser's friend. cuz (elaboration) a person who elevates himself as king is opposing Keser.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ezeétei: was looking for a legal"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">ezeétei: was looking for a legal way (not just that he tried to get him out the door but the unfriendly crowd wouldn't let him) LITERALLY: From that time Pilate tried to release him. But the Jews cried out, saying, "If you let this man go, you are not [King] Caesar's friend. Whoever makes himself a king [talks against/opposes] Caesar.<span class="Italic">(12)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Jadi waktu gubernor dengar dong pung omong bagitu, ju dia kasi kaluar sang Yesus. Ais dia dudu di hakim pung korsi, di satu tampa yang dong kasi nama bilang, &lt;&lt;Tana Lapang dari Batu Plat&gt;&gt;. (Dalam bahasa Aram dia pung nama bilang, <span class="Italic">Gabata</span>.)<bt>So (consequently), when the gubernor heard them talking like that, he brought Yesus out. Then he sat in the judge's seat, in a place they named, “(Muster) Field of Flat Stones”. (In the Aram language its name is <span class="Italic">Gabata</span>.) [NOTE: Carson says: “An area paved with stones, originally about 3000 square feet in size, has been discovered in a building identified as the Fortress of Antonia,”]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="korsi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">korsi</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Lithóstrooton: an open area paved either"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">Lithóstrooton: an open area paved either with small stones like a mosaic, or with large flat stone blocks. The First Jewish Temple had a pavement of large stones that was called the same thing LITERALLY: Therefore when Pilate heard that, he brought Jesus out, and sat down in the judgment seat, in a place that is called "the Pavement", but in the Hebrew, "Gabbatha."<span class="Italic">(13)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Itu hari tu, Hari Sadia Pesta Paska. Kira-kira tenga hari, ju gubernor kasi tau sang orang Yahudi dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Lia su! Dia ni, bosong pung raja!&gt;&gt;<bt>That day was the Day of Preparing for the Paska Feast. Around noon/mid-day, the gubernor told the Yahudi people saying, “Have a look! He here is your-pl king!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="íde: drawing attention to something LITERALLY:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">íde: drawing attention to something LITERALLY: It was the preparation day for the Passover. About the sixth hour he said to the Jews, "Look at your king!"<span class="Italic">(14)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Ma dong batarea ukur kuat bilang, &lt;&lt;Bawa Dia kaluar dari sini! Bekin mati sang Dia sa! Paku sang Dia di kayu palang!&gt;&gt;<bt>But they shouted with all their strength saying, “Bring/Take Him out from here! Just kill Him! Nail Him on a cross!”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ju gubernor tusu-tusu sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Jadi karmana? Bosong pung maksud, beta musti bunu bekin mati bosong pung raja ni, ko?&gt;&gt;<bt>The gubernor goaded/stirred them up saying, “So (consequently), how about it? Do you mean I must kill your king here, or (what)?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ais kapala agama Yahudi dong pung bos-bos manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Botong pung raja cuma satu sa, andia keser! Sonde ada yang laen lai!&gt;&gt;<bt>Then the *chief priests responded saying, “We-exc only have one king, that is Keser! There is no other!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But they shouted, &quot;Away with"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But they shouted, "Away with him! Away with him! Crucify him!" Pilate said to them, "Should I crucify your king?" The chief priests answered, "We have no king but Caesar!"</Message></Annotation><v n="16a" />Ais ju gubernor sarakan sang Yesus pi di tantara dong, ko dong pi paku bekin mati sang Dia di kayu palang.<bt>So then the gubernor turned Yesus over to the soldiers, for them to go nail Him to death on a cross.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Dong paku tagantong Tuhan Yesus di kayu palang<bt>They nail hanging the Lord Yesus on a cross</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 27:32-44; Markus 15:21-32; Lukas 23:26-43)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16b" />Ais, itu tantara dong tarima ame sang Yesus.<bt>Then, those soldiers accepted/received Yesus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Some versions put the title after"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">Some versions put the title after Verse 17, but the natural break is here LITERALLY: Then he [Pilate] turned him [Jesus] over to them to be crucified. And they took charge of Jesus.<span class="Italic">(16)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="17" />Ju Dia pikol ame Dia pung kayu palang kaluar dari kota. Dong pi satu tampa yang dong subu bilang, &lt;&lt;Tampa Tulang Kapala&gt;&gt;. (Dalam dong pung bahasa Aram, itu tampa pung nama, <span class="Italic">Golgota</span>.)<bt>And He shoulder carried His cross out from the city. They went to a place they called, “Skull Place”. (In their Aram language, the name of that place is, <span class="Italic">Golgota</span>.)</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bastázoon: usually the condemned person carried"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">bastázoon: usually the condemned person carried the crossbeam he was going to be nailed to, not the whole cross, which was 6" X 6" or thicker. Mark indicates that Jesus was so weak from the whipping that he had to be helped LITERALLY: He carried his cross and went out to a place called "The Place of the Skull."<span class="Italic">(17)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Sampe di situ, ju dong paku sang Yesus di satu kayu palang. Dong bekin bagitu kasi dua orang laen ju. Dong paku tagantong yang satu di Yesus pung sablá kanan, deng satu lai di Dia pung sablá kiri, deng Yesus di dong pung teng-tenga.<bt>Arriving there, they nailed Yesus to a cross. They also did that to two other people. They nailed ahning one on Yesus' right side, and the other on His left side, with Yesus in their middle/in between them.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Where they crucified him, and"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Where they crucified him, and two others with him, one on each side, and Jesus in the middle.</Message></Annotation><v n="19" />Ju gubernor suru dia pung tantara dong ko tulis satu papan, ais paku di Yesus pung atas kapala. Di itu papan dong tulis bilang,<bt>The gubernor ordered his soldiers to write on a board, then nail it above Yesus' head. On that board they wrote saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line Centered" usfm="qc">
      <span class="Italic">&lt;&lt;Ini ni, Yesus, orang Nasaret. Dia tu, orang Yahudi dong pung Raja&gt;&gt;</span>
      <bt>
        <span class="Italic">“This here, is Yesus, a Nasaret person. He is the King of the Yahudi people”</span>
      </bt>
      <Annotation class="General" selectedText="títlon: the notice board with the">
        <Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">títlon: the notice board with the name of the condemned person, or his crime, or both, a technical term LITERALLY: Pilate wrote a notice and put it on the cross. The writing said, "Jesus of Nazareth, the King of the Jews."<span class="Italic">(19)</span></Message>
      </Annotation>
    </p>
    <fig path="HK-LB\LB00327C.tif" rtfFormat="width:6.5cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:right" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Dong tulis itu papan, pake tiga bahasa. Andia: bahasa Aram, bahasa Yunani, deng bahasa Latin. Banya orang Yahudi baca itu papan, tagal Yesus pung tampa mati tu, deka deng kota Yerusalem.<bt>They worte on that board using three languages. That is: the Aram language, the Yunani language, and the Latin language. Many Yahudi people read that board, because the place of Yesus' death was close to the city of Yerusalem. [EXEG: Carson, etc.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="enggýs: relatively close, like a few"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">enggýs: relatively close, like a few hundred yards outside the old city walls LITERALLY: Then many Jews read that notice, because the place where Jesus was crucified was near the city, and it was written in Hebrew, Greek, and Latin.<span class="Italic">(20)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="21" />Ma kapala agama Yahudi dong pung bos-bos kabaratan. Ais dong pi kasi tau sang gubernor bilang, &lt;&lt;Pak! Jang tulis &lt;orang Yahudi dong pung Raja&gt;! Ada lebe bae tulis bilang, &lt;Ini orang bilang dia tu, orang Yahudi pung raja.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>But the *chief priests of the Yahudi religion objected. So they went and told the gubernor saying, “Pak! Don't write ‘King of the Yahudi people’! It would be better to write saying, ‘This person says he is king of the Yahudi people.’”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then the Jewish chief priests"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then the Jewish chief priests said to Pilate, "Do not write, "the King of the Jews", but that he said, "I am the King of the Jews".</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Ma gubernor manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta yang suru dong tulis bagitu. Jadi kasi tenga pi sa!&gt;&gt;<bt>But the gubernor responded saying, “I am the one who told them to write like that. So (consequently), just let it be!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Pilate answered, &quot;What I have"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Pilate answered, "What I have written, I have written."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Waktu tantara dong su paku tagantong sang Yesus di kayu palang, ju dong babagi Dia pung pakean ko taro di ampa tampa. Satu bagian kasi satu tantara. Ju dong ame Dia pung baju luar yang ada tanún anteru dari atas pi bawa, yang sonde pake jaitan.<bt>When the soldiers had nailed hanging Yesus on the cross, they divided His clothes and put (them) in four places. One part for each soldier. And they took His outer clothes which was woven whole from top to bottom, that had no sewing/stitching.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tumpuk ; jaitan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">tumpuk ; jaitan</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="téssara: four places; one pile for"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">téssara: four places; one pile for each of the four soldiers on the squad. The robe was too special to rip up, so they gambled for that chitóona: This was like a knee-length T-shirt of nice handwoven material. It was worn inside the heavier outer robe and next to the skin, but it wasn't underwear; it was more like the inside of a layering<span class="Italic">(23) (23) </span>LITERALLY: Then when the soldiers had crucified Jesus, they took his clothes, and divided them into four, one for each soldier. They also took his robe, which was woven from the top down, and did not have a seam.</Message></Annotation><v n="24" />Ais dong ba'omong bilang, &lt;&lt;We! Kotong jang robe buang Dia pung baju ni. Lebe bae, kotong hela lot sa, ko cari tau sapa yang dapa.&gt;&gt; Itu bekin jadi, apa yang su tulis dalam Tuhan pung Tulisan Barisi bilang,<bt>Then they spoke (with each other) saying, “Weh! We-inc shouldn't tear up this (piece of) His clothes. It would be better if we draw lots, to find out who gets it.” That made happen what had been written in the Scriptures saying,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tarek lot preferred by some UNS's"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">tarek lot preferred by some UNS's</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Dong babagi kasi beta pung pakean,<bt>“They divided up my clothes,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ju dong hela lot ko dapa beta pung baju.&gt;&gt;<bt>and they drew lots to get my shirt/clothes.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ais, itu tantara dong bekin bagitu.<bt>Then those soldiers did that. [TEXT: versification on this last sentence varies. AGNT, TB, CEV, Carlton, have it in vs.24. NRSV and NLT have it is vs.25. I can't find any discussion on why the difference.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: So they said to each"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: So they said to each other, "Let's not tear it, but cast lots for it to see who will get it." This happened that the Scripture might be fulfilled, which said, "They divided my clothing among themselves, and cast lots for my robe." So that is what the soldiers did.</Message></Annotation><note reference="19:24" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 22:19</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus suru Yohanis ko jaga Dia pung mama<bt>The Lord Yesus orders Yohanis to guard/look after His mama</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Di situ ju ada badiri parampuan barapa orang. Dong tu, andia: Yesus pung mama, Yesus pung tanta, Klopas pung bini Maria, deng Maria dari kampong Magdala.<bt>There, there were also several women standing. They were: Yesus' mama, Yesus' aunt, Klopas' wife Maria, and Maria from the village of Magdala. [EXEG: see Carson, NRSV, NLT, CEV. 2nd name in list is MZ, not FZ.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="María: there are several ways to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">María: there are several ways to read this, giving two, three, or four women. But it's not too likely that Mary the mother of Jesus had a sister named Mary. Better: (1) Jesus's mother, (2) Jesus's aunt, (3) Mary Clopas's wife, and (4) Mary from Magdala LITERALLY: Now Jesus mother and his mother's sister, Mary the wife of Clopas, and Mary Magdalene were standing by Jesus' cross.<span class="Italic">(25)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="26" />Yesus lia Dia pung mama ada badiri di situ, sama-sama deng itu ana bua yang Dia sayang, andia beta, Yohanis. Ais Dia kasi tau sang Dia pung mama bilang, &lt;&lt;Mama. Dia ni, mama pung ana.&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus saw His mother was standing there, together with that disciple whom He loved, that is me, Yohanis. Then He told His mama saying, “Mama. He here, is your child.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: So when Jesus saw his"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: So when Jesus saw his mother, and the disciple whom he loved standing there, he said to his mother, "[Woman/Mother] Here is your son!"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />Ju Dia kasi tau sang beta bilang, &lt;&lt;Bagini. Sakarang, anggap dia lu pung mama su!&gt;&gt; Ais mulai dari itu waktu, Yesus pung mama ada tenga deng beta.<bt>And He told me saying, “It's like this. Now, consider her your-sg mother [+mild imperative, urging]!” So beginning from that time, Yesus' mama lived with me.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="élaben: take her to live in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">élaben: take her to live in his own home LITERALLY: Then he said to the disciple, "Look, your mother!" And from that hour that disciple took her into his own home.<span class="Italic">(27)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus pung mati<bt>The Lord Yesus' death</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 27:45-56; Markus 15:33-41; Lukas 23:44-49)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Ais itu, ju Yesus su tau bilang, Dia su bekin abis Dia pung tugas samua. Itu bekin jadi, samua yang Tuhan pung Tulisan Barisi su tulis memang dari dolu. Ju Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta su aus ni.&gt;&gt;<bt>After that, Yesus knew that He had finished/completed all of His work/responsibilities/mission. That made happen/fulfilled everything the Scriptures had written beforehand from long ago. And He said, “I'm thirsty (here/now).”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: After that Jesus knew that"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: After that Jesus knew that everything was done that the Scripture might be fulfilled. Then he said, "I'm thirsty."</Message></Annotation><note reference="19:28" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 69:22, 22:16</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="29" />Naa, di situ ada anggor asam dalam satu kumbang kici. Ais tantara dong ame lumut ko calóp pi dalam itu anggor, ju taro di kayu sapotong<bt>Naa [shift], there, there was sour wine in a small (clay) jug. So then the soldiers took moss and dipped it into that wine, and put it on the end/tip of a stick/piece of wood,</bt><note reference="19:29" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Bahasa Yunani bilang dong natok itu lumut di kayu <span class="Italic">hussopos</span> pung ujung. <span class="Italic">Hussopos</span> tu, satu kayu wangi yang orang Yahudi biasa pake dalam barapa acara adat. Dia pung panjang kira-kira 20-40cm. Baca so'al <span class="Italic">hussopos</span> di <span class="Italic">Kaluar dari Masir</span> 12:22; <span class="Italic">Kapala Agama dong pung Atoran</span> 14:4, 6, 49-52; <span class="Italic">Daftar Sensus</span> 19:2-6; (banding deng <span class="Italic">Ibrani</span> 9:19); <span class="Italic">Lagu Puji dong</span> 51:7.<bt>The Yunani language says they poked that moss on the tip of a <span class="Italic">hussopos</span> stick. <span class="Italic">Hussopos</span> is an aromatic wood that the Yahudi people normally use in several adat ceremonies. It's length is around 20-40cm. Read about <span class="Italic">hussopos</span> in <span class="Italic">Exit from Masir</span> 12:22; <span class="Italic">Priests Regulations</span> 14:4, 6, 49-52; <span class="Italic">Census List </span>19:2-6; (compare with <span class="Italic">Hebrews</span> 9:19); <span class="Italic">Praise Songs</span> 51:7.</bt></note>pung ujung, ju sorong pi Dia pung bibir.<bt>and stretched it up to His lips. [NOTE to daughter translations: it's really a sea sponge. Some lgs have a word for it that everybody knows. Use it. Picture of hyssop HK00114C.tif.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="óxous: wine that had gone vinegary,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">óxous: wine that had gone vinegary, and was sold cheap. Day laborers and soldiers would buy it and sometimes cut it with water because it was refreshing, like soda without the fizz. The soldiers were trying to help Jesus out by giving him a drink, not to make his torture worse mestòn: soaking up as much wine as the sponge would hold<span class="Italic">(29) (29) </span>hyssoópooi: a branch of an orégano plant that was probably growing nearby [IVP Dictionary says "In the OT ‘hyssop’ was used in the Passover rites (Ex. 12:22) for the purification of lepers (Lv. 14:4, 6), for plague (Lv. 14:49-52) and at the red heifer sacrifice (Nu. 19:2-6; cf. Heb. 9:19). The purifying qualities of ‘hyssop’ are referred to in Ps. 51:7. This plant is generally considered to be the Syrian marjoram (Origanum syriacum) which is a fragrant grey-leaved wiry-stemmed perennial herb, 20-30 cm high, with white flowers in small heads, growing in dry rocky places. In the NT the ‘hyssop’ employed at the crucifixion (Jn. 19:29, where NEB [incorrectly] reads hyssO, ‘on a javelin’) was probably a reed or stick, but the reed-like cereal durra (Sorghum vulgare) has been considered the most likely suggestion."] perithéntes: either tying it around the end, or pushing the stick into the sponge<span class="Italic">(29) (29) </span>LITERALLY: Now there was sitting there a [bowl/dish/jar/jug] full of cheap wine. They filled a sponge with wine, and put it on a branch of hyssop, and raised it to his lips.</Message></Annotation><v n="30" />Waktu Yesus su isap itu anggor, ju Dia omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Samua su abis.&gt;&gt; Tarús Dia tondo Dia pung kapala, ju Dia putus napas memang.<bt>When Yesus had sucked that wine, He spoke saying, “Everything is done/finished/complete/accomplished.” Then He bowed His head, and He breathed His last (right then).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="!@ CEV &quot;drink&quot; problematic; if sponge/moss,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">!@ CEV "drink" problematic; if sponge/moss, should be sip</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: So when Jesus had taken"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: So when Jesus had taken the wine, he said, "It is finished." And he bowed his head, and give up his spirit.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tantara tusu ame sang Tuhan Yesus di kayu palang [\s2]<bt>A soldier pierces the Lord Yesus on the cross [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="31" />Itu hari kaná deng hari Jumat. Iko atoran agama, orang Yahudi musti basiap di itu hari, ko dia pung beso sambut dong pung hari sambayang. Andia ko dong sonde mau orang pung mayat tagantong tarús di kayu palang pas di hari sambayang. Te itu hari sambayang tu, hari bae. Jadi orang Yahudi pung bos-bos minta gubernor ko dia suru orang puku bekin pata orang di kayu palang dong pung tulang kaki. Deng bagitu, dong bisa mati capát, ko biar orang bisa kasi turun dong pung mayat sedu-sedu.<bt>That day fell on Friday. According to religious regulations, Yahudi people must prepare on that day, for the next day greets their day of worship. That is why they don't want people's corpses to keep hanging on crosses on their day of worship. Cuz (elaboration) that day of worship is a special/good day. so (consequently) the bosses/leaders of the Yahudi people requested the gubernor to order people to hit/beat breaking the leg bones of the people on the crosses. In that way, they could die quickly, so that people could bring down their corpses earlier/sooner.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hamar (puku) batu = sledge hammer"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">hamar (puku) batu = sledge hammer</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="megálee: a specially important holy day,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">megálee: a specially important holy day, with Passover coming on the Rest Day that year, kind of like when Christmas falls on a Sunday so you have regular church plus special celebrations kateagóosin: break their leg bones, probably with a sledge hammer, to make them die faster. Some people hung there two or three days before they died when they were crucified, and having bodies hanging on crosses on the Rest Day would have violated Jewish law<span class="Italic">(31) (31) </span>LITERALLY: Therefore, since it was the preparation day [Friday], the Jews felt that the bodies should not stay on the cross on the Sabbath, because that Sabbath was a high day. So they asked Pilate to have their legs broken, that they might be taken away.</Message></Annotation><v n="32" />Ais tantara dong pi sana, ju puku bekin pata satu orang pung tulang kaki. Ais itu, ju dong bekin pata orang yang satu lai pung kaki. Dong dua tu, andia, itu orang yang dong paku tagantong sama-sama deng Yesus.<bt>So the soldiers went there, and hit breaking one of the people's leg bones. After that, they also broke the other person's legs. The two of them were those people they had nailed hanging together with Yesus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then the soldiers came and"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then the soldiers came and broke the first one's legs, and the other one that was crucified with him.</Message></Annotation><v n="33" />Ma waktu dong sampe di Yesus, dong lia Dia su mati batúl. Andia ko dong sonde puku bekin pata Dia pung tulang kaki dong.<bt>But when they arrived at Yesus, they saw He was already truly dead. That's why they did not hit breaking His leg bones.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But when they came to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But when they came to Jesus, and saw that he was already dead, they did not break his legs.</Message></Annotation><v n="34" />Ma tantara satu ame dia pung tombak, ju tusu maso di Yesus pung rebis. Tarús ada dara kaluar, deng ada aer ju kaluar.<bt>But one soldier took his spear, and pierced it into Yesus' side/ribs. Then3 there was blood came out, and there was also water/liquid came out. [NOTE to daughter translations: TB “lambung” (stomach) seems to have no support from Gk text, lexicons, other translations, or commentaries.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="TB"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">TB</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But one of the soldiers"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But one of the soldiers pierced his side with a spear, and blood and water came out.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="35" />(Naa, satu orang yang jadi saksi mata tu, andia beta. Beta ada lia samua, deng beta tulis yang batúl di sini. Te beta tau apa yang beta carita tu, batúl, ko biar bosong bisa parcaya sang beta pung omong.)<bt>(Naa, one person who was an eye witness there was me. I saw everything, and I write what is true here. Cuz (elaboration) I know what I am telling is true, so that you-pl can believe/trust what I am saying.)</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And one that saw it"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And one that saw it has given record, and his record is true. He knows that what he says is true, so that you may believe.</Message></Annotation><v n="36" />Ini hal dong samua jadi, tagal Tuhan pung Tulisan Barisi ada tulis bilang, &lt;&lt;Dia pung tulang dong, sonde ada satu ju yang pata.&gt;&gt;<bt>All these things happened, because the Scriptures write saying, “His bones, there was not even one that was broken.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: These things were done that"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: These things were done that the Scripture might be fulfilled, "None of his bones will be broken."</Message></Annotation><note reference="19:36" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 12:46, Daftar Sensus 9:12, Lagu Puji dong 34:21</note><v n="37" />Di itu Tulisan Barisi, ju ada tampa laen yang tulis bilang, &lt;&lt;Nanti dong lia sang itu orang yang dong su tusu ame.&gt;&gt;<bt>In those Scriptures, there is another place that writes saying, “They will look at that person whom they have pierced.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And again, another Scripture says,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And again, another Scripture says, "They shall look at the one they pierced."</Message></Annotation><note reference="19:37" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Sakaria 12:10, Dunya Model Baru 1:7</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Dong kubur sang Tuhan Yesus<bt>They bury the Lord Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 27:57-61; Markus 15:42-47; Lukas 23:50-56)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="38" />Ada satu orang, nama Yusuf, dari kampong Arimatea. Dia ju jadi Yesus pung ana bua. Ma dia iko sang Yesus deng sambunyi-sambunyi, tagal dia taku sang orang Yahudi pung bos-bos. Dia pi gubernor Pilatus, ju minta ko gubernor kasi isin sang dia, ko bawa ame Yesus pung mayat. Gubernor tarima bae. Ais Yusuf pi kasi turun Yesus pung mayat, ju bawa pi.<bt>There was a person named Yusuf, from the village of Arimatea. He was also Yesus' disciple. But he followed Yesus secretly, because he was afraid of the bosses/leaders of the Yahudi people. He went to gubernor Pilatus, and requested that the gubernor give him permission to take away Yesus' corpse. The gubernor accepted. so Yusuf went and took down Yesus' corpse, and took it away.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="éeren: Joseph was a nobleman, so"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">éeren: Joseph was a nobleman, so he probably had his servants get the body down off the cross and carry it to the tomb, maybe on a kind of stretcher. There was no casket LITERALLY: Now, Joseph of Arimathea was a secret disciple of Jesus, for fear of the Jews. He asked Pilate if he could take away Jesus' body, and Pilate gave him permission. So he came and took Jesus' body.<span class="Italic">(38)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="39" />Nikodemus ju pi sama-sama deng Yusuf. Dia tu, yang dolu ada pi katumu sang Yesus malam-malam. Dia béli rampe bam-banya, kira-kira 33 kilo, ko taro di Yesus pung mayat.<bt>Nikodemus also went together with Yusuf. He was the one who had previously gone to meet Yesus (secretly) at night. He bought a lot of burial.spices, around 33 kilos, to put on Yesus' corpse. [NOTE to daughter translations: TB ‘rempah-rempah’ is spices for food, not for corpses. :) // The weight called ‘kati’ in the TB is not known to educated eastern Indonesians.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="malam-malam ; according to E &amp;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">malam-malam ; according to E &amp; S a 'kati' is 617 gram (it is a transliteration of an archaic English term 'catty'--which I have never heard of) ; @@TB use in seminar??</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="smýrnees kaì alóees: it doesn't mention"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">smýrnees kaì alóees: it doesn't mention "spices", and neither of these was anything you would put on food. Aloes are the same plant that we use for burn medicine here, and they were using them for keeping the body from smelling bad LITERALLY: And Nicodemus also came. He was the one who earlier had come to Jesus at night. He brought a mixture of myrrh and aloes, about a hundred pounds by weight.<span class="Italic">(39)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="19:39" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Bahasa Yunani tulis bilang, <span class="Italic">&lt;100 litras&gt;</span>, andia 32,7 kilo. Dong pung rampe tu, bahasa Yunani tulis bilang dong campor <span class="Italic">smurna</span> (andia gatá dari satu kayu wangi) deng <span class="Italic">aloe</span> (andia gatá dari satu pohon wangi yang mirip lida buaya). Baca so'al Nikodemus ni, di <span class="Italic">Yohanis </span>3:1-21.<bt>The Yunani language says, <span class="Italic">&lt;100 litras&gt;</span>,that is 32.7 kilos. Their burial.spices, the Yunani language says they mixed <span class="Italic">smurna</span> (that is the sap from an aromatic tree) and <span class="Italic">aloe</span> (that is the sap from an aromatic plant similar to crocodile tongue). Read about this Nikodemus is Yohanis 3:1-21.</bt></note><v n="40" />Ju dong feo ame Yesus pung mayat pake kaen alus. Tiap kali dong feo, dong taro rampe dolo. Dong bekin bagitu, iko orang Yahudi pung adat kubur orang mati.<bt>Then they wound around Yesus' corpse using fine cloth. Each time they folded/wrapped, they placed burial.spices first. They did that according to the Yahudi people's adat for burying dead people. [EXEG: Morris says “They put the spices between the folds.”]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="feo"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">feo</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="othoníois: pieces of linen cloth. Linen"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">othoníois: pieces of linen cloth. Linen is woven from the fiber taken from flax stalks by beating out the soft stuff aroomátoon: spices, but in this case not used for food. The Greek word means "nice smelling things"<span class="Italic">(40) (40) </span>LITERALLY: Then they took Jesus body, and wound it up in linen clothes with spices, as the Jewish burial custom is.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ju dong bungkus ame Yesus pung"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">Ju dong bungkus ame Yesus pung mayat pake kaen alus yang dong campor deng itu rampe, iko orang Yahudi dong pung adat kubur orang mati.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="41" />Naa, sonde jao dari itu tampa yang Yesus mati tu, ada satu táman. Di itu táman, orang baru pahat abis satu kuburan. Dong balóm parná kasi maso mayat di situ.<bt>Naa [shift], not far from that place where Yesus died, there was a garden/park. In that park, people had just finished chiselling a grave. They had not yet put a corpse in there.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="taman CIE with tamán"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">taman CIE with tamán</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kéepos: not a vegetable garden, but"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">kéepos: not a vegetable garden, but more like a small private park LITERALLY: Now in the place where he was crucified there was a garden, and in the garden a new tomb, where no one was ever laid yet.<span class="Italic">(41)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="42" />Itu waktu, orang Yahudi pung hari basiap ko sambut dong pung hari sambayang su mau amper abis. Andia ko dong simpan Yesus pung mayat dalam itu kuburan, te itu tampa tu, sonde jao.<bt>At that time, the Yahudi people's day for preparing to greet their day of worship was almost ended. That's why they stored/put away Yesus' corpse in that grave, cuz (elaboration) that place wasn't far.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: They laid Jesus there, because"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: They laid Jesus there, because of the Jews' preparation day, because the tomb was nearby.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus idop kambali!<bt>The Lord Yesus lives again!</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 28:1-8; Markus 16:1-8; Lukas 24:1-12)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="20" />
      <v n="1" />Hari Minggu, andia minggu baru pung hari partama, Maria dari kampong Magdala pi papagi buta di Yesus pung kuburan. Sampe di sana, dia lia batu bésar yang dong pake tutu itu kuburan tu, su taguling dari dia pung tampa.<bt>Sunday, that is the first day of a/the new week, Maria from the village of Magdala went very early in the morning (around first glimpse of light) to Yesus' grave. Arriving there, she saw the big stone that they had used to close/cover that grave, was already rolled from its place.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="papagi buta"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">papagi buta</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: The first day of the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: The first day of the week Mary [the Magdalene/ from Magdala] came to the grave early, when it was still dark, and saw the stone removed from the grave [opening].</Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Ju dia lari kambali pi Simon Petrus, deng beta, andia Yesus pung ana bua yang Dia sayang tu, tarús dia kasi tau bilang, &lt;&lt;Dong su curi bawa kotong pung Bos dari Dia pung kuburan! Botong sonde tau dong ada taro sang Dia di mana!&gt;&gt;<bt>Then she ran back to Simon Petrus, and me, that is Yesus' disciple whom He loved, and told (them) saying, “They have stolen taken our-inc Bos from His grave! We-exc don't know where they put/placed Him!” [EXEG: Carson, Morris.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then she ran, and came"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then she ran, and came to Simon Peter, and to the other disciple whom Jesus loved, and said to them, "They have taken the Lord away from the grave, and we don't know where they have put him."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="Cook\CNT\cn01852b.tif" rtfFormat="width:6.5cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:right" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Ju beta deng Petrus lari pi itu kuburan.<bt>Then I and Petrus ran to that grave.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: So Peter went out, and"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: So Peter went out, and the other disciple, and went to the grave.</Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Botong lari sama-sama, ma beta lebe capát. Ais beta sampe di itu kuburan lebe dolo.<bt>We-exc ran together, but I was faster. So I arrived at the grave sooner/first.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: So they ran together, and"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: So they ran together, and the other disciple outran Peter, and came to the grave first.</Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Ma beta sonde maso pi dalam. Beta cuma maloi maso sa. Di situ, beta lia itu kaen alus yang dong pake ko feo ame di Yesus pung mayat.<bt>But I didn't go inside. I only scrutinised inside. [NOTE: /maloi/ implies squinting, craning, or bending to scrutinise, so the team and UNS's felt that making 'bending' explicit here would be overtranslating.] There, I saw that fine cloth which they had used to wrap/wind up Yesus' corpse.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: He bent down, and saw"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: He bent down, and saw the linen cloths lying there, but he did not go in.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ju beta maloi pi dalam. Di"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">Ju beta maloi pi dalam. Di situ, beta lia itu kaen alus yang dong pake ko feo ame di Yesus pung mayat. Ma beta sonde maso pi dalam.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Ma waktu Petrus sampe di sana, ju dia maso tarús sampe di dalam. Dia ju lia itu kaen alus yang ada di situ.<bt>But when Petrus arrived there, he went straight inside. He also saw that fine cloth that was there.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then Peter came afterward, and"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then Peter came afterward, and went into the grave, and saw the linen cloths lying there.</Message></Annotation><v n="7" />Dia ju lia lencu satu, yang dong pake ko tutu Yesus pung kapala. Ma itu lencu tu, ada talipa, deng tapisa dari itu kaen alus.<bt>He also saw a handkerchief/square cloth (lencu), which they had used to cover Yesus' head. But that handkerchief was separated from that fine cloth.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lencu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">lencu</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: The cloth that was around"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: The cloth that was around his head was not lying with the linen cloths, but was rolled up by itself.</Message></Annotation><v n="8" />Ais beta, yang tadi sampe di kuburan lebe dolo, ju iko maso pi dalam. Waktu beta lia itu samua, ju beta parcaya sang Yesus pung omong dolu bilang, nanti Dia mau idop kambali dari Dia pung mati.<bt>Then I, who earlier had arrived at the grave first, also went inside. When I saw all that, I also believed what Yesus had said previously that, later He was going to live again from His death.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then the other disciple, who"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then the other disciple, who had come first to the grave, also went in, and he saw, and believed.</Message></Annotation><v n="9" />Te itu waktu, botong yang jadi Dia pung ana bua balóm mangarti Tuhan pung Tulisan Barisi yang su tulis memang bilang, Kristus musti idop kambali dari Dia pung mati.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) at that time, we-exc who were His disciples did not yet understand the Scriptures which had written beforehand saying, Kristus must live again from His death.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Because they still did not"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Because they still did not understand the Scripture, that he must rise again from the dead.</Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Ais itu, ju botong dua pulang.<bt>After that, the two of us-exc went home.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then the disciples went back"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then the disciples went back home.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus kasi tunju Dia pung diri sang Maria dari kampong Magdala [\s2]<bt>The Lord Yesus shows Himself to Maria from the village of Magdala [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 28:9-10; Markus 16:9-11)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Ma Maria masi badiri di luar itu kuburan. Dia manangis tarús. Waktu dia masi manangis, ju dia maloi maso pi dalam itu kuburan.<bt>But Maria still stood outside that grave. She kept crying. While she was still crying, she scrutinised into that grave. [NOTE: Again, /maloi/ implies squinting, craning, or bending to scrutinise, so the team and UNS's felt that making 'bending' explicit here would be overtranslating.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But Mary stood outside the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But Mary stood outside the grave crying. As she wept, she bent down and looked into the grave.</Message></Annotation><v n="12" />Dia ada lia Tuhan pung ana bua dari sorga dua orang. Dong ada pake pakean puti. Dong dua ada dudu di tampa yang kamaren dolu orang simpan Yesus pung mayat. Satu ada dudu di kapala pung tampa. Yang satu lai ada dudu di kaki pung tampa.<bt>She saw two of God2's *angels. They were wearing white clothes. The two of them were sitting in the place where day-before-yesterday people had placed/stored Yesus' corpse. One was sitting at the place of the head. The other was sitting at the place of the feet.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: She saw two angels in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: She saw two angels in white sitting there by where Jesus had lain, one at the head and the other at the feet.</Message></Annotation><v n="13" />Dong tanya sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Akurang ko susi manangis?&gt;&gt;<bt>They asked her saying, “Why is older sister crying?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ju dia manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta manangis, tagal dong su angka bawa beta pung Bos pung mayat. Ma beta sonde tau dong ada taro sang Dia pi mana.&gt;&gt;<bt>And she responded saying, “I am crying, because they have lifted taking my Bos's corpse. But I don't know where they have put/placed Him.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: They said to her, &quot;Lady,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: They said to her, "Lady, why are you crying?" She said to them, "Because they have taken away my Lord, and I do not know where they have put him."</Message></Annotation><v n="14" />Dia omong abis bagitu, ju dia bale ko lia pi luar. Dia lia ada satu orang badiri di situ, ma dia sonde tau itu Orang tu, andia Yesus.<bt>When she finished speaking like that, she turned to look outside. She saw there was a person standing there, but she didn't know that Person was Yesus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ma dia sonde tau, (kalo) itu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">ma dia sonde tau, (kalo) itu tu, Yesus. Ambiguous 1) that 2) whether or not</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: When she had said that,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: When she had said that, she turned around, and saw Jesus standing there, but did not know that it was Jesus.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Ju Yesus tanya sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Akurang ko susi manangis? Te susi ada cari sang sapa?&gt;&gt;<bt>And Yesus asked her saying, “Why is older sister crying? Cuz (elaboration) who are you (older sister) looking for?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Naa, Maria sangka itu orang tu, tukang kabón sa. Ju dia buju-buju bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa. Kalo bapa su angka bawa Dia pung mayat, na, kasi tau dolo bapa ada simpan di mana. Biar ko beta bawa sang Dia pi tampa laen ko kubur bae-bae. Tolong doo!&gt;&gt;<bt>Naa [shift, background, speaker comment], Maria thought/assumed that person was just a gardener. So she coaxed/pursuaded/urged saying, “Father. If you have lifted taking His corpse, na, tell my where you have put/stored Him. [+mild imperative] Let me take Him to a different place to bury (Him) well/properly. Please!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Jesus said to her, &quot;Woman,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Jesus said to her, "Woman, why are you crying? Who are you looking for?" She thought he was the gardener, and said to him, "Sir, if you have taken him away, tell me where you have put him, and I will take him away."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Ais Yesus pange sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Maria.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus called her saying, “Maria.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ju dia bale mangada sang Yesus bilang, <span class="Italic">&lt;&lt;Raboni!&gt;&gt;</span> (Dalam bahasa Aram, dia pung arti bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta pung Guru!&gt;&gt;)<bt>And she turned to face (bodily) Yesus saying, <span class="Italic">&lt;&lt;Raboni!&gt;&gt;</span> (In the Aram language, it means, “My Teacher!” [EXEG: Contrast with 1:38 Rabbi ‘teacher’ vs. Rabboni ‘my teacher’ (LN). It came up because we were challenged on glossing the two. The were the same in an earlier draft.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Jesus said to her, &quot;Mary.&quot;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Jesus said to her, "Mary." She turned and said, "Rabboni," which means in Aramaic, "Teacher."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Yesus kasi tau sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Jang sonto sang Beta dolo, te Beta balóm nae pi Beta pung Bapa di sorga. Ma susi pi dolo, ko kasi tau Beta pung sodara dong bilang, &lt;Beta mau nae pi Beta pung Bapa. Dia ju, andia bosong pung Bapa. Dia tu, Beta pung Tuhan Allah. Jadi Dia tu, bosong pung Tuhan Allah ju.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus told her saying, “Don't touch Me (now), cuz (elaboration) I have not yet ascended to My Father in heaven. But older sister go now, to tell My siblings saying, ‘I am going to ascend to My Father. He is also you-pl Father. He is My God. So (consequently) He is also your God.’”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Jesus said to her, &quot;Do"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Jesus said to her, "Do not touch me, because I have not yet ascended to my Father. But go to my brothers and say to them "I ascend to my Father, who is your Father, and to my God, who is your God."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Ais itu, ju Maria dari Magdala pi carita kasi Yesus pung ana bua dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta su katumu deng kotong pung Bos, Yesus!&gt;&gt; Ju dia kasi tau Yesus pung pasán sang dong.<bt>After that, Maria from Magdala went to tell/narrate to Yesus disciples saying, “I have met with our-inc Bos, Yesus!” And she told Yesus' message/instructions to them.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Mary the Magdalene went and"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Mary the Magdalene went and told his disciples that she had seen the Lord, and that he had said these things to her.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus kasi tunju Dia pung diri sang Dia pung ana bua dong [\s2]<bt>The Lord Yesus shows himself to His disciples [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 28:16-20; Markus 16:14-18; Lukas 24:36-49)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Itu hari jato kaná di hari Minggu, andia minggu baru pung hari partama. Matahari baru tanggalám. Ju Yesus pung ana bua dong ada bakumpul. Dong konci mati pintu ruma dong, tagal dong taku sang orang Yahudi pung bos-bos. Takuju sa, Yesus datang badiri di dong pung teng-tenga bilang, &lt;&lt;Saloom!&gt;&gt;<bt>That day fell on Sunday, that is the first day of a/the new week. The sun had just gone down. And Yesus' disciples were gathered. They had locked up tight the doors of the house, because they were afraid of the Yahudi peoples bosses/leaders. Suddenly, Yesus came and stood in their midst saying, “Saloom!” [EXEG: ‘suddenly’ from context, following NLT, CEV.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then the same day, the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then the same day, the first day of the week, it was evening. The disciples were together and the doors were closed there, because they were afraid of the Jews. Jesus came and stood in their midst, and said to them, "Peace be to you."</Message></Annotation><v n="20" />Waktu Yesus togor sang dong bagitu, ju Dia kasi tunju itu luka dong yang ada di Dia pung tangan deng Dia pung rebis. Dia pung ana bua dong talalu sanáng waktu dong lia sang dong pung Bos.<bt>When Yesus greeted them like that, He showed those wounds which were in His hands and His side/ribs. His disciples were too happy/overjoyed when they saw their Bos. [NOTE to daughter translations: Dhao and other lgs here distinguish lexically between ‘fresh wounds’ and ‘old wounds’. Gk in vs. 27 say “put your hand ‘into’ my side”, that leans it toward a fresh wound that does not have skin healed over.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And when he had said"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And when he had said that, he showed them his hands and side. Then the disciples were glad, when they saw the Lord.</Message></Annotation><v n="21" />Ais Yesus kasi tau sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Biar ko bosong aman deng tanáng. Inga, Beta pung Bapa su utus sang Beta karmana, na, Beta ju utus sang bosong bagitu.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus told them saying, “May you-pl be safe and calm. Remember, how My Father sent/commissioned Me, na, I also send/commission you-pl like that.” [EXEG: see extensive discussion in Carson. He concludes in the context of John's gospel it is primarily about “unqualified obedience to and dependence upon their Lord”; “Peace” in sense #1 (context of fear and locked doors, not of broken relationships).]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then Jesus said to them"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then Jesus said to them again, "Peace be to you. As my Father has sent me, that's how I send you."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Dia omong ais bagitu, tarús Dia deka-deka sang dong, ju fuu Dia pung napas pi di dong satu-satu. Ais Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta kasi Tuhan pung Roh yang Barisi sang bosong. Tarima ame sang Dia.<bt>After He finished speaking like that, He came nearer/close to them, and blew His breath on each of them. Then He said, “I give God2's Clean/Holy/Pure Spirit to you. Receive Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And when he had said"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And when he had said that, he breathed on them, and said to them, "Receive the Holy Spirit.</Message></Annotation><v n="23" />Jadi, kalo bosong lupa buang orang pung sala, na, itu sala su ilang buang, te Tuhan ju su hapus buang itu sala dong. Ma kalo bosong sonde mau lupa buang orang pung sala, na, Tuhan ju sonde hapus buang itu sala.&gt;&gt;<bt>So (consequently), if/when you completely forget (=deliberate forgiveness1) a person's wrong/sin/fault, na, that wrong is gone (disappeared completely, cuz (elaboration) God2 has already wiped away (forgiveness2) those wrongs. But if you do not want to completely forget a person's wrong, na, God2 also doesn't wipe away that wrong.” [NOTE: Carson and others note that the Holy Spirit in vs. 22 is tightly linked to the issue of forgiveness in 23. At the encouragement of a consultant, we added the connector ‘so (consequently)’ at the beginning of 23 to force the link. Amarasi, May 2014.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: If you forgive anyone's sins,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: If you forgive anyone's sins, they are forgiven. And if you do not forgive anyone's sins, they are not forgiven."</Message></Annotation><note reference="20:23" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 16:19, 18:18</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus deng Tomas [\s2]<bt>The Lord Yesus and Tomas [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Ada satu dari Yesus pung ana bua dua blas orang. Dia pung nama, Tomas, yang dong ju subu bilang, &lt;ana bagambar&gt;. Waktu Yesus datang kasi tunju Dia pung diri sang dong, Tomas sonde ada sama-sama deng ana bua yang laen dong.<bt>There was one of Yesus' twelve disciples. His name was Tomas, who they also referred to as ‘twin’. When Yesus came and showed himself to them, Tomas was not together with the other disciples.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NOTE to daughter translations: check this"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">NOTE to daughter translations: check this passage against draft in GRN "Good News"</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But Thomas, called Twin, one"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But Thomas, called Twin, one of the twelve, was not with them when Jesus came.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ma satu dari Yesus pung ana"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">Ma satu dari Yesus pung ana bua dua blas orang, sonde ada sama-sama deng yang laen dong waktu Yesus datang kasi tunju Dia pung diri sang dong. Dia pung nama, Tomas, yang dong ju subu, bilang, &lt;ana bagambar&gt;.</Message></Annotation><v n="25" />Andia ko waktu dia pung tamán dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Botong su katumu sang kotong pung Bos,&gt;&gt; ju dia manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Bagini. Beta musti lia deng raba dolo itu luka dari paku pung bakás di Dia pung tangan. Deng beta musti calóp beta pung jari maso di itu luka di Dia pung rebis. Te kalo beta balóm bekin bagitu, na, beta balóm mau parcaya bilang, Dia su idop kambali.&gt;&gt;<bt>That's why when his friends/companions said, “We-exc have met our-inc Bos,” he responded saying, “It's like this. I must first see and touch those wounds from the nails (+leftover = scars) in His hands. And I must dip my finger into that wound in His side. Cuz (elaboration) if I have not yet done that, na, I'm not yet wanting to believe that He has come back to life.” [EXEG: OV undertranslated “Unless I see the mark of the nails in his hands [and put my finger in the mark of the nails]...” so restored with “see and touch”. We take Gk repetition of “mark of the nails” as slowing down the rate of new info. We take Gk: put my finger ... put my hand ... as a parallelism, not implying inserting a whole hand into the spear wound. RL reality handles this nicely with “touch (implying finger/hand) ... dip finger (which would be what one would gingerly do if actually probing a spear wound—as implied by the Gk)”.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: So the other disciples said"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: So the other disciples said to him, "We have seen the Lord." But he said to them, "Unless I see the print of the nails in his hands, and put my hand into his side, I will not believe."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="26" />Dia pung satu minggu lai, ju Yesus pung ana bua dong ada sama-sama deng Tomas dalam satu ruma. Biar pintu dong su takonci, ma Yesus maso badiri di dong pung teng-tenga. Dia togor sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Saloom!&gt;&gt;<bt>One week later, Yesus' disciples were together with Tomas in one house. Even though the doors were locked, nevertheless Yesus entered standing in their midst. He greeted them saying, “Saloom!” [EXEG: NRSV, CEV, Carson.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Again after eight days his"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Again after eight days his disciples were inside and Thomas was with them. Then the doors were shut, and Jesus came and stood in their midst, and said, "Peace be to you."</Message></Annotation><v n="27" />Tarús Dia omong sang Tomas bilang, &lt;&lt;Sorong lu pung jari di sini, ko pareksa Beta pung tangan dolo. Ais mari raba ini luka di Beta pung rebis. Naa, parcaya su, bilang Beta su idop kambali! Buang lu pung rasa sonde parcaya tu.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then He spoke to Tomas saying, “Stretch/scoot your-sg finger here, to examine My hands now. Then come (invitation) touch this wound in My side. Naa [shift, conclusion, peak], believe that I have come back to life [+imperative]! Get rid of that feeling/perception of not believing of yours.” [EXEG: NLT, Carson.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then he said to Thomas,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then he said to Thomas, "Stretch out your finger and look at my hands, and stretch out your hand and put it into my side. Do not doubt, but believe."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Tomas manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Awii, Bapa, é! Sakarang beta parcaya batúl! Bapa ni, andia beta pung Bos yang hak parenta sang beta, deng beta pung Tuhan Allah ju!&gt;&gt;<bt>Tomas responded saying, “Awii, Father, é! [+amazement] Now I really believe! You (Father) here, are my Bos who has the say-so/ordering rights over me, and also my God!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Thomas said to him, &quot;My"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Thomas said to him, "My Lord and my God!"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="29" />Ju Yesus kasi tau sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Tomas! Lu parcaya Beta su idop kambali, tagal lu su lia sang Beta deng lu pung mata kapala sandiri. Ma yang lebe ontong lai, andia orang yang sonde lia sang Beta, ma dong parcaya.&gt;&gt;<bt>And Yesus told him saying, “Tomas! You believe that I have come back to life, because you have seen Me with your own eyeballs. But even more fortunate are the people who have not/do not see Me, but they believe.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Jesus said to him, &quot;Thomas,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Jesus said to him, "Thomas, because you have seen me, you have believed. [Blessed/happy] are those who have not seen me, and yet have believed."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Ini buku pung maksud<bt>The purpose of this book</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="30" />Yesus ju bekin banya tanda heran yang laen, yang beta sonde tulis dalam ini buku. Dia pung ana bua dong lia itu tanda heran dong deng mata kapala sandiri.<bt>Yesus also did many other amazing signs, that I have not written in this book. His disciples saw those amazing signs with their own eyeballs.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Jesus did many other signs"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Jesus did many other signs in his disciples' presence which are not written in this book.</Message></Annotation><v n="31" />Ma hal yang beta su tulis dalam ini buku ni, beta tulis ko biar bosong parcaya bilang,<bt>But the things/matters/events/issues I have written in this book here, I wrote so that you-pl would/could believe that,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Yesus tu, andia Kristus yang Tuhan Allah su janji memang ko mau kirim datang.<bt>Yesus is Kristus whom God had promised beforehand to send coming.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Yesus ju, andia Tuhan Allah pung Ana.<bt>Yesus is also God's Child.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Deng waktu bosong parcaya sang Dia, bosong dapa idop yang batúl yang sonde tau putus-putus, tagal bosong jadi Dia pung orang dong.<bt>And when you-pl believe in Him, you get/obtain real life that never ends, because you have become His people.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But these are written, that"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But these are written, that you might believe that Jesus is the Christ, the Son of God, and that as you believe you might have life through his name.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus kasi tunju Dia pung diri sang Dia pung ana bua tuju orang<bt>The Lord Yesus shows himself to seven of His disciples</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="21" />
      <v n="1" />Lewat barapa hari ju, Yesus kasi tunju Dia pung diri ulang lai di dano Tiberias pung pinggir. Dia pung carita bagini:<bt>After several days, Yesus showed himself again at the edge of lake Tiberias. The story is like this:</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="metà táuta: a few days later"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">metà táuta: a few days later than the events at the end of Chapter 20 ephanéroosen heautòn: showed himself (1:31, 2:11, 3:21, 7:4, 9:3, 17:6)<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>pálin: not the last time, but an additional time LITERALLY: After these things, Jesus showed himself again to his disciples by Lake Tiberias. This is how he showed himself.<span class="Italic">(1)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Itu waktu, Yesus pung ana bua tuju orang ada bakumpul. Dong tu, andia:<bt>At that time seven of Yesus' disciples were gathered. They were:</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Simon Petrus,<bt>Simon Petrus,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Tomas, yang dong subu bilang, &lt;ana bagambar&gt;,<bt>Tomas, whom they refer to as ‘twin’,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="UNS said = artist/painter"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">UNS said = artist/painter</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Natanel, dari kampong Kana di propinsi Galilea,<bt>Natanel, from the village of Kana in the province of Galilea,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Sabadeus pung ana dua orang,<bt>Sabadeus' two children/offspring,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">deng Yesus pung ana bua laen dua orang.<bt>and two of Yesus' other disciples.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Kanà: Cana, a very small village,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">Kanà: Cana, a very small village, not a big town LITERALLY: These were together: Simon Peter, Thomas called The Twin, Nathaniel of Cana in Galilee, the sons of Zebedee, and two other disciples of his.<span class="Italic">(2)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Simon Petrus kasi tau dia pung tamán dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta mau pi buang pukat.&gt;&gt;<bt>Simon Petrus told his friends/companions saying, “I'm going to throw out the dragnet.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ju dong manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Hoo! Botong ju iko.&gt;&gt; Ais dong pi dano pung pinggir. Tarús dong nae parahu ko pi cari ikan. Ma itu malam dong sonde dapa tangkap apa-apa.<bt>And they responded saying, “Hoo! [+agreement, affirmation] We-exc'll go too.” So they went to the edge of the lake. Then they got in a boat to look for fish. But that night they didn't catch anything.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="halieúein: fish with nets, not hooks"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">halieúein: fish with nets, not hooks syn soí: not as freeloaders, but to help with the work<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>LITERALLY: Simon Peter said to them, "I'm going fishing." They said to him, "We're going with you too." They went out, and got into a boat, and that night they didn't catch anything.</Message></Annotation><note reference="21:3" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lukas 5:5</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Dia pung beso pagi, ju Yesus ada badiri di dano pung pinggir. Ma Dia pung ana bua dong sonde tau Dia tu, Yesus.<bt>The next morning, Yesus was standing at the edge of the lake. But His disciples didn't know that He was Yesus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Early in the morning, Jesus"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Early in the morning, Jesus was standing on the beach. But the disciples did not know that it was Jesus.</Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Ju Dia eki ko tanya sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bu dong, é! Su dapa ikan, ko?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then He called out/shouted/yelled (message) to ask them saying, “Older brothers, é! Have (you) got fish, or (not)?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Dong manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Kosong, Bu! Botong sonde dapa sadiki ju.&gt;&gt;<bt>They responded saying, “Empty, Older Brother! We didn't even get a little.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then Jesus said to them,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then Jesus said to them, "[Children / Friends], don't you have any fish?" They answered him, "No."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Ju Dia kasi tau sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Coba buang itu pukat di parahu pung sablá. Nanti bosong dapa.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then He told them saying, “Have a try at throwing the dragnet on the other side of the boat. Then you'll get (some).” [EXEG: “right side” to “other side” (explicit to implicit-naturalness in context).]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Tarús dong bekin iko. Ju dong dapa ikan. Ma itu ikan talalu banya, sampe dong sonde bisa hela itu pukat kambali pi dalam parahu.<bt>Then they did that. And they got fish. But those fish were too many, too the point that they couldn't pull that dragnet back into the boat.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="díktyon: probably a circular net with"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">díktyon: probably a circular net with weights around the outside, but the word could cover other kinds. Big enough that when it really got filled up, seven men couldn't haul it on board heureésete: you will find, you will catch<span class="Italic">(6) (6) </span>LITERALLY: He said to them, "Throw the net on the right side of the boat, and you will find some. So they threw it, and then they were not able to draw it up because of the large haul of fish.</Message></Annotation><note reference="21:6" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lukas 5:6</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Naa, beta ju ada di situ. Beta ni, ana bua yang Yesus sayang. Ais beta kasi tau sang Petrus bilang, &lt;&lt;Awii! Dia tu, kotong pung Bos!&gt;&gt;<bt>Naa [shift], I was also there. I am the disciple that Yesus loved. So then I told Petrus saying, “Awii! [+amazment, awe] He is our-inc Bos!”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Dengar beta pung omong, ju Simon Petrus pake kambali dia pung baju, ais buang diri pi dalam dano ko mau baranáng pi darat.<bt>Hearing what I said, Simon Petrus put his shirt/clothes back on, and threw himself into the lake to swim to shore/land. [DISCOURSE: put back on implies he had taken off, so “naked” is explicit to implicit. CHECKed w/UNS.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="diezoósato: put a belt or a"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">diezoósato: put a belt or a rope around himself, or tuck in what he was already wearing gymnós: naked or lightly clothed. He was probably stripped down to their kind of malo, and put a shirt kind of like a thick knee-length T-shirt over it with a belt around it. Or else he was already wearing the T-shirt because it was kind of cold and foggy just before dawn, and tucked it into his belt so he could swim better<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>LITERALLY: So that disciple whom Jesus loved said to Peter, "It is the Lord." Now, when Simon Peter heard that it was the Lord, he put his fishing coat around him (because he was naked), and threw himself into the lake.</Message></Annotation><v n="8" />Te itu parahu kira-kira cuma 100 meter dari darat. Ais dia pung tamán dong dayong parahu kambali pi darat, deng ada hela bawa itu pukat yang ponu deng ikan dari parahu pung balakang.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) that boat was around only 100 meters from shore/land. So/then his friends paddled the boat back to shore, and they were pulling/dragging along that dragnet which was full of fish from behind the boat.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="éelthon: came by boat, brought the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">éelthon: came by boat, brought the boat on in to the beach, probably with oars (they didn't use paddles in that part of the world) LITERALLY: And the other disciples came in the boat, [pulling/ dragging] the net full of fish, because they were not far from land, but only about a hundred yards away.<span class="Italic">(8)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Waktu dong sampe di darat, ju dong lia ada api bara yang manyala di situ. Di api pung atas, ada ikan. Deng ada roti ju.<bt>When they arrived on land/shore, they saw there was a fire of coals burning there. On top of/above the fire, there were fish. And there was also bread.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="api bara = burning coals ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">api bara = burning coals ; arang - charcoal</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: As soon as they had"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: As soon as they had come to land, they saw a fire of coals there, and fish on it, and bread.</Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Yesus kasi tau sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bawa datang ikan sadiki dari yang bosong baru tangkap ame tadi.&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus told them saying, “Bring some/a few fish from what you-pl just caught.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Jesus said to them, &quot;Bring"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Jesus said to them, "Bring some of the fish you have just caught."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="Cook\CNT\cn01877b.tif" rtfFormat="width:6.5cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:right" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Ais ju Simon Petrus nae kambali pi dalam parahu, ko dia hela itu pukat pi darat. Itu pukat ponu deng ikan bésar. Dia pung banya, 153 ekor. Biar ikan banya bagitu, ma itu pukat sonde tarobe.<bt>Then Simon Petrus got back in the boat, to pull/drag net into shore. The dragnet was full of large fish. their amount was 153 tails [counter]. Even though there were so many fish, nevertheless that dragnet didn't tear.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Simon Peter went aboard, and"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Simon Peter went aboard, and dragged the net ashore. It was full of big fish, 153 in all, but even with so many the net did not break.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Ais Yesus pange sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Mari ko makan doo!&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus called/summoned them saying, “Come on, and eat!” [EXEG: Gk is 2p here.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Dong su tau bilang, Dia tu, dong pung Bos. Andia ko dong sonde barani tanya bilang, &lt;&lt;Bu ni, sapa?&gt;&gt;<bt>They already knew that He was their Bos. That is why none of them dared to ask saying, “Who are You (older brother)?”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Jesus said to them, &quot;Come"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Jesus said to them, "Come and eat." None of his disciples dared ask him, "Who are you?" Because they knew that it was the Lord.</Message></Annotation><v n="13" />Tarús Yesus ame roti deng ikan, ju pi kasi sang dong.<bt>Then Yesus took the bread and fish, and went to give (it) to them.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: So Jesus went over, and"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: So Jesus went over, and took bread, and gave it to them, and fish too.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Itu, andia, kali katiga Yesus kasi tunju Dia pung diri sang Dia pung ana bua dong, waktu Dia su idop kambali dari Dia pung mati.<bt>That was the third time Yesus showed Himself to His disciples, when He had come back to life from His death.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: This was now the third"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: This was now the third time that Jesus showed himself to his disciples after he had risen from the dead.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus ba'omong deng Petrus<bt>The Lord Yesus speaks with Petrus</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Waktu dong su makan abis, Yesus tanya sang Simon Petrus bilang, &lt;&lt;We, Simon, Yohanis pung ana. Karmana? Lu sayang sang Beta lebe dari ini tamán dong sayang sang Beta, ko?&gt;&gt;<bt>[EXEG: see Carson (on whole passage).] When they had finished eating, Yesus asked Simon Petrus saying, “Eh, Simon, Yohanis' child. How about it? Do you-sg love Me more than these friends/companions love Me, or (what)?” [EXEG: CEV]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Dia manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Batúl! Bos su tau beta sayang sang Bos.&gt;&gt;<bt>He responded saying, “True! You (Bos) already know I love You.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ju Yesus pasán sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo bagitu, na, foo bae-bae Beta pung domba ana ko dong dapa makan.&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus instructed him saying, “If that's the case, na, herd well My lambs (sheep offspring) so they get food.” [EXEG: agapáais ... philéis: probably not a strong distinction in words for “love”, even though it is possible to read quite a bit into the passage. (See also Carson: on Exegetical Fallacies).]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="légei: not just saying something, but"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">légei: not just saying something, but posing a serious question that Peter has to respond to. "aks"? "try tell"? pléon: more than the others love me (not "more than you love the others" or "more than you love anything else")<span class="Italic">(15) (15) </span>agapáais ... philéis: probably not a strong distinction in words for "love", even though it is possible to read quite a bit into the passage [See also Carson: on Exegetical Fallacies] bóske: not "put out food for them" or "put food in their mouths" but "take them where the food is and take care of them"<span class="Italic">(15) (15) </span>LITERALLY: So when they had eaten, Jesus said to Simon Peter, "Simon, son of John, do you love [agapaw] me more than these? He said to him, "Yes, Lord, you know that I love you [philew] [/you know that I am your friend]. He said to him, "Feed [boskw] my lambs."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Ju Yesus tanya ulang sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Simon, Yohanis pung ana. Karmana? Lu sayang sang Beta, ko?&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus asked him again saying, “Simon, Yohanis' child. How about it? Do you-sg love Me, or (what)?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Dia manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Batúl! Bos su tau beta sayang sang Bos.&gt;&gt;<bt>He responded saying, “True! You (Bos) already know I love You.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ju Yesus pasán sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo bagitu, piara bae-bae Beta pung domba dong.&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus instructed him saying, “If that's the case, care for/raise well My sheep.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="poímaine: do what a sheep herder"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">poímaine: do what a sheep herder does LITERALLY: He said to him a second time, "Simon, son of John, do you love [agapaw] me?" He said to him, "Yes, Lord. You know that I love [philew] you." He said to him, "Take care of [poimanw] my sheep."<span class="Italic">(16)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Ais ju Yesus tanya ulang lai sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Simon, Yohanis pung ana. Karmana? Lu ni, Beta pung tamán, ko?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus asked him again saying, “Simon, Yohanis' child. How about it? Are you-sg My friend, or (what)?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ju Petrus hati susa memang, tagal Yesus su tanya tiga kali bilang, &lt;&lt;Lu sayang sang Beta, ko?&gt;&gt; Ais dia manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Bos yang tau samua hal. Jadi Bos su tau bilang, beta ni, Bos pung tamán.&gt;&gt;<bt>And Petrus' liver was really troubled, because Yesus had already asked three time saying, “Do you love Me, or (what)?” So he responded saying, “You (Bos) know everything. So (consequently) You already know that I am Your friend.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Tarús Yesus pasán sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo bagitu, na, foo bae-bae Beta pung domba ko dong dapa makan.<bt>Then 3 Yesus instructed him saying, “If that's the case, na, herd well My sheep so they get food.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="elypeéthee: grieved, like his best friend"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">elypeéthee: grieved, like his best friend had let him down LITERALLY: He said to him a third time, "Simon, son of John, do you love [philew] me?" Peter was grieved because he said to him a third time, "Do you love me?" And he said to him, "Lord, you know all things. You know that I love [philew] you." Jesus said to him, "Feed [boskw] my sheep.<span class="Italic">(17)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="18" />Lu su tangkap Beta pung maksud, ko? Beta ju mau kasi tau bagini: dolu waktu lu masi muda, na, lu biasa pake baju, deng pake ika pinggang, ais lu jalan pi mana sa, iko lu pung suka. Ma nanti kalo lu su tua, lu sorong lu pung tangan ko orang laen ika sang itu tangan dong, pake lu pung ika pinggang sandiri. Ais ju dong hela bawa sang lu pi satu tampa yang lu sonde mau pi.&gt;&gt;<bt>Have you caught My meaning/purpose? I also want to tell/explain like this: previously when you-sg were still young, na, you normally put on clothes, and wore a belt/waist tie, then you went off wherever, according to your desire. But later when you are already old, you will stretch out your hand/s so other people tie/bind them, using your own belt/waist tie. Then they will pull/drag you to a place where you don't want to go.” [EXEG: Carson “stretch out your hands was understood in the ancient world: it widely referred to crucifixion”. Morris “there is evidence that the stretching forth of the hands was held in the early church to refer to crucifixion.”]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="zoósei: same word as earlier in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">zoósei: same word as earlier in the verse for putting a belt over your robe; but now it is being used of tying him up as a prisoner for execution LITERALLY: That's right. And I tell you, "When you were young, you dressed yourself and went anywhere you wanted. But when you are old, you will stretch out your hands, and another will put on your belt and take you where you do not want to go.<span class="Italic">(18)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="19" />(Yesus omong bagitu ko kasi tau sang Petrus so'al apa yang nanti jadi di dia pung diri. Te nanti Petrus pung mati tu, kasi tunju Tuhan Allah pung hebat.)<bt>(Yesus spoke like that to tell Petrus about what would later happen to him. Cuz (elaboration) later Petrus' death showed God's greatness/amazingness/incredibleness.) [BACKGROUND: Carson “Peter had glorified God by his martyrdom, probably in Rome, under the emperor Nero. Extra-biblical sources for the event are not strong. Clement of Rome (c. AD 96) mentions Peter's martyrdom but does not reveal what form it took (1 Clement 5:4). Writing about AD 212, Tertullian affirms that it was when Peter was bound to the cross that he was girded by someone else ... Later accounts of Peter asking to be crucified upside down, because he felt unworthy to be crucified as his Lord was, are too remote and too infected with legendary accretions to be reliable.” Carlton (TRT) Suggested FOOTNOTE: According to tradition, about 30 years later (around A.D. 64-65) Peter was crucified upside down. He felt unworthy to be crucified in the same position that Jesus was crucified.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Research ftn on crucifed upside-down."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">Research ftn on crucifed upside-down.</Message></Annotation><note reference="21:19" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Kira-kira taon 96M, ada satu pamimpin gareja, nama Klement dari kota Roma, yang tulis bilang, orang dong bunu bekin mati sang Petrus. Kira-kira taon 212M, ada satu pamimpin gareja laen, nama Tertulian, yang tulis bilang, dong paku tagantong sang Petrus di kayu palang. Deng ada ju satu tradisi laen dalam gareja yang bilang, waktu dong mau paku tagantong sang Petrus di kayu palang kira-kira taon 64-65M, Petrus minta ko dong gantong sang dia deng kapala di bawa. Itu tagal dia rasa dia sonde pantas mati deng dia pung kapala di atas, sama ke Yesus.<bt>Around the year 96M (A.D.), there was a church leader, named Klement from the city of Roma, who wrote saying, people had killed Petrus. Around the year 212M, there was another church leader, named Tertulian, who wrote saying, they nailed hanging Petrus on a cross. And there is also another tradition in the church that says, when they were about to nail hanging Petrus on a cross around the years 64-65M, Petrus asked them to hang him with his head down. That was because he did not feel he was worthy to die with his head above/up, like Yesus.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ais itu, ju Yesus kasi tau sang Petrus bilang, &lt;&lt;Mari ko jadi Beta pung orang su!&gt;&gt;<bt>After that, Yesus told Petrus saying, “Come and be My person!” [EXEG: Carson, HCE]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: He [Jesus] said this, signifying"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: He [Jesus] said this, signifying by what death he [Peter] would glorify God. After he had said that, he said, "Follow me."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Ana bua yang Tuhan Yesus sayang<bt>The disciple whom the Lord Yesus loved</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Itu waktu, Petrus bale ko lia pi balakang. Ju dia lia beta ada iko dari dong dua pung balakang. Beta ni, andia ana bua yang Yesus sayang. Beta ju yang dudu di Yesus pung sablá waktu botong dudu makan pesta Paska. Beta ni, yang tanya sang Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Bos, é! Sapa yang nanti jual buang sang Bos?&gt;&gt;<bt>At that time, Petrus turned to look back. And he saw me following behind them. I here, am the disciple whom Yesus loved. I am also the one who sat beside Yesus while we-exc were sitting eating the Paska feast. I am the one who asked Him saying, “Bos, é! Who is it that will sell of (betray) You?”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then Peter turned around and"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then Peter turned around and saw the disciple whom Jesus loved following, who had also leaned against Jesus at supper, and had said, "Lord, who is going to betray you?"</Message></Annotation><note reference="21:20" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yohanis 13:25</note><v n="21" />Waktu Petrus dapa lia sang beta, ju dia tanya sang Yesus bilang, &lt;&lt;Bos su omong so'al beta tadi. Ma karmana deng dia?&gt;&gt;<bt>When Petrus saw/happened to see me, he asked Yesus saying, “Bos (=you) have spoken about me earlier. But what about him?”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: When Peter saw him he"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: When Peter saw him he asked Jesus, "Lord, what will this man do?"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Yesus kasi tau sang Petrus bilang, &lt;&lt;Itu bukan lu pung urusan. Andekata Beta pung mau ko dia cuma tunggu di sini sampe Beta datang kambali, dia pung masala apa? Yang pantíng tu, lu musti inga apa yang Beta pasán sang lu tadi tu, andia: mari ko jadi Beta pung orang su.&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus told Petrus saying, “That is not your business. If perchance (hypothetical) it is My will for him to just wait here until I come back, what's the problem? The important this is you must remember what I instructed you earlier, that is, come and be My person.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Jesus said to him, &quot;If"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Jesus said to him, "If I wish that he stay here until I come, what is that to you? Follow me."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Tagal Yesus omong bagitu, Dia pung ana bua yang laen mulai ba'omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Yohanis tu, sonde akan mati.&gt;&gt; Padahal Yesus sonde omong bagitu. Yang Dia bilang tu, andia: &lt;&lt;Itu bukan lu pung urusan. Andekata Beta pung mau ko dia cuma tunggu di sini sampe Beta datang kambali, dia pung masala apa?&gt;&gt;<bt>Because Yesus spoke like that, His other disciples began to speak (among themselves) saying, “That Yohanis is not going to die.” Whereas in fact, Yesus did not say that. What He said was this: “If it is My will for him to just wait here until I come back, what's the problem? Cuz (elaboration) that is not your business.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="jump to conclusions = BI kesimpulan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z">jump to conclusions = BI kesimpulan dingin</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then this saying went around"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then this saying went around among the disciples, that that disciple would not die. But Jesus did not say to him, "He will not die," but "If I desire that he stay here until I come, what is that to you?"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yohanis tutu dia pung tulisan<bt>Yohanis closes/ends his writing</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Itu ana bua yang Yesus omong tu, andia beta, Yohanis. Beta yang carita ini hal dong samua kasi sang bosong. Beta yang lia deng beta pung mata kapala sandiri. Ais beta yang tulis samua. Ju kotong su tau bilang, apa yang beta kasi tau sang bosong tu, batúl.<bt>That disciple whom Yesus was talking about, that was me, Yohanis. I am the one who has told/narrated all these things to you-pl. I am the one who saw (them) with my own eyeballs. so I am the one who wrote everything. And we-inc already know that what I have told you is true.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: This is the disciple who"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: This is the disciple who testifies of these things, and wrote these things. And we know that his testimony is true.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Deng masi ada banya hal laen yang Yesus bekin. Kalo orang coba tulis ame samua-samua, mulai dari Yesus kasi jalan Dia pung karjá sampe abis, na, beta kira satu dunya anteru ju sonde bisa mua itu buku dong samua.<bt>And there are still many other things that Yesus did. If a person tried to write everything, beginning from Yesus starting to carry out His work until the end/completed, na, I think/imagine that a whole world would not be able to carry/hold all those books.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Bagitu sa,<bt>That's it,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Yohanis<bt>Yohanis</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And there are also many"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:47:29Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And there are also many other things which Jesus did. If every one were written down, I suppose that even the world could not hold all the books that would be written.</Message></Annotation></p>
  </book>
</bible>